NAME: Belkadan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: swamps, rainforests, lakes, multiple small seas
INTERESTING: many tall dalloralla trees; ruled by Rakata ~ 30,000 BBY; at some point, Belkadan gov't replaced with Sith-loyal puppet gov't; location of ExGal-4 outpost by 25 ABY; overrun and terraformed by YV

NAME: Zeta Zero Nine
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: cold wasteland, thick surface ice covering a vast body of water
INTERESTING: hidden Imperial base here built underwater under thick surface ice; electromagnetic storms cut off communication and disrupted most instruments, though Imperials managed to overcome this via use of a disrupter box; Imperial base commanded by Moff Jesco Comark during GCW, was involved in Operation Death-Hunter, to create the Death-Hunter Cyborg before being destroyed by Rebels

NAME: Salfrem system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Barely Tolerable: Alien Henchmen of the Empire (SW.com)/

NAME: PL-40112-CE-021105
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Barely Tolerable: Alien Henchmen of the Empire (SW.com)/
INTERESTING: homeworld of Bertroff Hissa (Human-Sephi hybrid Imperial Grand Moff); surveyors awoke ancient horde of Rozzum (inter-dimensional monsters) and allied with near-human natives to vanquish them but only two survived: Hissa and ranking Imperial officer from Naboo (Quarsh Panaka)

NAME: Chrelythiumn system
NOTES: Mortis monolith appeared somewhere deep in the system sometime during CW and broadcasted ancient Jedi distress signal

NAME: Mortis monolith
INTERESTING: massive octahedral monolith containing a vergence in the Force that functioned as a portal to the realm of Mortis; 5km long (deep & wide) where The Ones (originally Celestials) lived

NAME: Nharqis'I
INTERESTING: black, starless cloud in an area of space known as "the death place" when translated from an old smugglers' dialect; said to be home of mythical Nharqis'Al (hideous leviathan)

NAME: Te Hasa
INTERESTING: population 10 K; connected to Malanose by relatively poorly-known hyperlane; bioengineered predators; storehouse for old Gree technology they had forgotten how to use, but were trying to relearn using the Great Library of Manuals; many Gree made pilgrimages here to study tech knowledge

NAME: Malanose
INTERESTING: Malanose once covered with Gree cities producing new tech; primary Crafter and Researcher castes were located here; eventually remaining structures were raided for all but largest of remaining artifacts, including Totth'k Lotos

NAME: Revyia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungle, open woods, meadows, rivers, lakes
INTERESTING: Tyia Force tradition brought here by missionary in 30 BBY; located halfway between Pits of Plooma and Galactic Rim; sole city: Revyia Station

INTERESTING: considered inhospitable; no native life forms; site of YV's first foothold, and they set their yammosk (War Coordinator) under frozen surface; Anakin Solo devised plan to use shieldship to reflect energy back at planet, stealing yammosk's energy through evaporation; ice planet's liquid core froze and shattered, killing yammosk and all YV here

NAME: Helska 5
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Rychel
INTERESTING: invaded by YV early in the war, shortly after Battle of Artorias; members of New Jedi Order including Luke, Le-Ung, and new recruit Finn Galfridian helped evacuate at cost of Le'Ung's life and many troops and civilians

NAME: Zipthar system
INTERESTING: origin point of Zipthar hexa-crystals (rare, valuable, shimmering, round crystals formed in a prism-like lattice thatreflected light in unusual ways)

NAME: Gree system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Gree
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: not easily inhabitable, and no one had taken time or trouble to build planet up

NAME: Licha In
INTERESTING: first Gree world to suffer degeneration of Gree society, reculting in a repuation its inhabitants were for wild and backwards; nexus for Hypergate transportation mechanism

NAME: Hettitite
INTERESTING: homeworld of Sernpidalians until world was threatened by a supernova; natives left for Sernpidal, eventually known as Sernpidalians

NAME: Ord Janon system
INTERESTING: Ordnance / Regional Depot outpost for Republic during Pius Dea Era; CIS forces had to withdraw from here during CW; attacked by YV between 25 - 26 ABY, still held by 27 ABY

NAME: Xo
NOTES: rocky, jungles, mountains, rainforests
INTERESTING: bathed in red light; inhabitants practiced ritual sacrifice; home to spiked, carnivorous plants, reptilian species; planet had Pre-Republic human civilization ruins; early human inhabitants probably eliminated by Zanibar

NAME: Serianan system
INTERESTING: system contained four major bodies, of which only Serias (the only one classified as a planet) was habitable; the other three were too small and distant from their sun to support life

NAME: Serias
INTERESTING: Korren Starchaser (NR Scout service captain) theorized the existence of a sentient humanoid species based on information collected in the nearby Serianan Belt; he elected to retreat after making only a cursory inspection of the planet, planning to analyze the info already gathered before making first contact

NAME: Serianan Belt
INTERESTING: an enormous asteroid belt that took up easily half the system; many larger asteroids had stable orbits and some even had their own moonlets; may have been result of planetary collisions; NR scouts discovered runes carved into some asteroids; an immense cavern nicknamed The Gulch was large enough to pilot a scout ship inside and contained more runes and small statuary

NAME: Ardis system
NOTES: Coords not on WP
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic space station during the Galactic War; the reconstituted Sith Empire attacked it unsuccessfully

NAME: Ardis Outpost
NOTES: Coords not on WP
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic space station during the Galactic War; the reconstituted Sith Empire attacked it unsuccessfully

NAME: Perann Nebula
INTERESTING: radiated scarlet glow due to energy of twelve stellar clusters, collectively known as Nihil Retreat

NAME: Rhand
INTERESTING: once inhabited by species that disappeared before members of Knell of Muspilli, Kanzer Exiles, and Warriors of Shadow arrived; after thousands of years these merged to become Sorcerers of Rhand, who lived in ruins of progenitor species; homeworld of Cronal / Blackhole

NAME: Eckless
INTERESTING: primitive world rich in ores, minerals; once subjugated by Hahz Fallone, who attacked with a fleet supplied by Jorga Sune; eventually natives rebelled and drove Fallone and his men offworld, but not before they raided the planet's treasury

NAME: Xerton Nine
INTERESTING: at some point after Endor, an individual from here held the title of Grand Magnus; Andrephan Stormcaller (former NR military colonel) released a scandoc around that time mentioning that a mercenary using proper forged documentation, especially one produced by an ID processor, could impersonate anyone from an Imperial customs inspector to the Grand Magnus from Xerton Nine

NAME: Qonto system
INTERESTING: Qonto: though not generally known for their perception, some exceptional Qonto (such as Lina Adonais) had senses considerably sharper than an average Human

NAME: Lew'el system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map; The Legends of Luke Skywalker/

NAME: Lew'el
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map; The Legends of Luke Skywalker/
INTERESTING: settled long ago by humans who mostly lived by and were totally dependent on the sea; razorback whales provided blubber fuel, bone for construction; triple-speared marlin provided leather, tools; clams & kiln oysters provided pearls and decorative shells; fish & seafood provided sustenance; Luke Skywalker learned to spearfish here; mostly forgotten by powerbrokers of galaxy

NAME: Orinackra
INTERESTING: infamous prison planet; Crix Madine (Imperial General who attempted to defect to Alliance after Yavin) was kept here during Dark Trooper crisis for leaking valuable info to the Rebels and was rescued by Kyle Katarn; easily compared to Kessel and Oovo IV; its maze-like valleys had numerous dead-ends, making it a perfect site for an Imperial detention center

NAME: Rimcee Station
INTERESTING: Imperial Military base used by Moff Disra (during bid against Pellaeon's peace proposal) to imprison Colonel Meizh Vermel as political prisoner

NAME: Lokondo
INTERESTING: site of Imperial base where dangerous prisoners were kept; testing site of experimental cloaking device

NAME: Kindlabethia
INTERESTING: a routing clerk quietly offered select parties from Kindlabethia to Nar Shaddaa, a hint to the Corellian Queen's upcoming cruise

NAME: Taspir III
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: industrial, volcanoes, craggy mountains, lava lakes & rivers
INTERESTING: polluted wasteland with a constant downpour of acid rain; during the time of the Disciples of Ragnos, a chain of Imperial Remnant fortresses and manufacturing plants were largely responsible for the pollution; Rosh Penin held here after having fallen to the dark side; Kyle Katarn and Jaden Korr launched a rescue mission; defended by hazard troopers, jumptroopers, Sith Cultists

NAME: Dolis 3
INTERESTING: locked in perpetual winter due to distance from star; Moff Derran Takkar planned to disrupt Luke & Mara's wedding from here

NAME: Aracara
NOTES: remote swampy planet with Rebel starfighter base in abandoned Aracara Testing Facility

NAME: The Edge of the Galaxy
INTERESTING: home to new and exotic resort that included Rodon Value Pod, the Solar Power Plant, and the Space Observatory, as well as an asteroid installation; Star Tours facilitated travel here through their Family Adventure Package

NAME: Anorelga system
INTERESTING: origin point of Anorelgan slip-socker (item sold on Kuari Princess luxury liner during GCW); fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Bastion
INTERESTING: originally settled by Humans who opposed non-human membership in OR; ironically, colony later heavily relied on Muuns for financial support; in CIS during CW; meeting place for Moff Council; site of state archives, civil administration, and Bastion Military Control; location hidden until Bastion Accords

NAME: Bastion Customs Station
INTERESTING: waypoint of all travel to and from Bastion; Muunilinst used its leverage to refuse to surrender one of its Golan battlestations to guard Bastion, so this station served alone

NAME: Unknown Gas Giant (Sartinaynian system)
NOTES: Numerous moons
INTERESTING: numerous rings orbited this gas giant; beldon-like creatures inhabited the clouds

NAME: Anthan Prime
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: planet had many moons

NAME: Anthan Spire
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: vacation resort for extremely wealthy

NAME: Anthan Prime Orbital Dockyards
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: at least one Venator and 4 Arquitens here a few months after Battle of Yavin

NAME: Anthan 1
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: orbited so close to Anthan Prime that it lay within the Thanteen Substrata (upper layers of planet's atmosphere); site of Plasma Devils (Alliance Starfighter corps) base

NAME: Anthan 12
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: considered one of the "mid-moons"

NAME: Anthan 13
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: considered one of the "mid-moons"; had crystalline cave

NAME: Anthan 14
NOTES: not listed in Albarrio sector WP page; supposedly in same sector as Mygeeto
INTERESTING: considered one of the "mid-moons"; massive dome, an Imperial bunker and TIE Fighter wreckage here

NAME: Obtrexta system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Bescane
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: overpopulated (10.2 B); run by Galentro Heavy Works; natural environment destroyed; Imperial fortress world by 4 ABY; fell under Pentastar Alignment by 4 ABY, Imperial Remnant by 12 ABY

NAME: Bnar VII
INTERESTING: Tir'uh (Noehon slaver) had a career that saw her operate within an area from Bnar VII to Kessel

NAME: Asation
INTERESTING: major port world of Gree, home to Crafter caste; Rokak'k Baran (spaceship providing main method of travel in Gree Enclave) started its circuit here; moist, high-pressure world; most Gree born here tended to be shorter than those born on Gree itself; Dread Masters released a creature known as the Terror From Beyond here during Galactic War; during GCW Imperials ostensibly ruled Gree Enclave from here but in practice took hands-off approach (sole Carrack cruiser orbited Asation to give impression of Imperial presence

NAME: Cilare
INTERESTING: Tayand (crime lord) lived here

NAME: Tulatharri Junction
INTERESTING: Hurst Romodi (Republic Colonel) decorated for military actions here during CW

NAME: Nharl
INTERESTING: star system contained Equanus and 4 other planets

NAME: Equanus
NOTES: EA: Superlaser test site "Squanus" a typo for Equanus

NAME: Artorias
INTERESTING: sunny world with planetary comm center; many buildings built from white stone; ruled by King Caled Galfridian since time of GCW; opposed to Empire; Galfridian fought with Rebels at Hoth; upon rumors of Imperial expansion in Outer Rim, King Galfridian returned home and oversaw construction of deep sea shelter to protect populace; many refugees settled here after GCW; one of first planets attacked by YV; ecosystem altered, inhabitants evacuated, enslaved or killed; resistance force led by King Caledto disrupt Vongforming

NAME: Criton's Point
INTERESTING: Library of Xer built here 26,000 BBY; quarantined by Pentastar Alignment and Commerce Master Commissioner of Velcar Free Commerce Zone, despite many historians interested in getting access to library; population 1,000

NAME: Dubrillion system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dubrillion system star
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dubrillion
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: massive high-rise cities, vast oceans, lush green continents
INTERESTING: dual planet with Destrillion; in heart of CIS space during CW; Lando took over after fall of Empire, served as administrator; world hosted many luxury suites; conquered by YV; later Fel Empire world

NAME: Destrillion
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: dual planet with Dubrillion; appeared brown and dirty from space; turbulent atmosphere; contained energy field with tibanna gas platform; Wedge sent here to investigate Imperial research facility in 3 ABY, but found only TIE Hunters and Imperial convoy; facility later discovered on Dubrillion; in 25 ABY Lando built several ore processing plants in upper atmosphere; conquered by YV

NAME: Lando's Folly
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Lando used this asteroid belt, near Dubrillion/Destrillion, to train pilots; dominated by Belt-Runner I station

NAME: Belt-Runner I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: this station dominated the Lando's Folly asteroid belt; 284 meters long; centerpiece of specialized training starfighter obstacle course; repulsors and shields protected pilots from dying in crashes; destroyed by YV

NAME: Ahakista
INTERESTING: overlooked world; Empire established Pyramid One (secret outpost hosting the Hub computer complex, built to coordinate Imperial Navy) here befote Yavin; Daystar casino built here

NAME: Belladoon
INTERESTING: By 5 ABY, it was one of 3 worlds held by the Empire, along with Korrus and Zhadalene

NAME: Lonatro
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mixed terraformed, game preserves, botanical gardens, farm fields, moderate surface water
INTERESTING: population 3 M; primary ag world of Gree; dominated by farms and food production facilities during height of Gree civilization, but after decline 90% given over to game preserves, botanical gardens; remaining land used for food production

NAME: Plesstil
INTERESTING: homeworld of Terkuss (Human male conscripted into Empire, threatened with destruction of Plesstil)

NAME: Veragi system
INTERESTING: shared name with Ghost Ship of Veragi (spaceship that haunted Outer Rim hyperlanes for decades)

NAME: Arbiflux
NOTES: At least 4 moons
INTERESTING: Chelli Aphra and her mother moved to Arbiflux after leaving her father; Lona Aphra was killed here in raider attacks orchestrated by the Empire, which were meant to drive the inhabitants to seek Imperial support

NAME: Oru
INTERESTING: home to human warriors known as Oruans; the First Order stripped it of its resources, turning the climate toxic; a group of Oruans almost succeeded in driving off the First Order but had to flee to Horizon Base instead

NAME: Trassitan
INTERESTING: office of Republic's Judiciary located here (nearest such facility to Gree enclave); a merchant filed a report to said office of a sighting of Dooku aboard the Rokak'k Baran (massive transport ship, main method of travel within Gree enclave)

NAME: Plooma system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Plooma
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: subject world of Rakata during Infinite Empire

NAME: Pits of Plooma
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: deep space formation; Han passed by while delivering 100 kilos of rock ivory to Grambo the Worrt sometime prior to Yavin

NAME: Kogan system
INTERESTING: Dr. Bromial led an Obroan Institute archaeological expedition to Kogan 6 aboard Penga Rift (starliner converted to research use) after Black Fleet crisis

NAME: Vonak
INTERESTING: Cilare: martial, assured of own battle prowess, exterminated by YV; same battle fleet then attacked Artorias in Myto sector

KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: dusty surface, damp ravines, subterranean ag farms watered by aquifers
INTERESTING: orbited only 115 K km from star; population 8 M; damp ravines were occupied by slow, tough tentacled creatures considered both flora and fauna; Sernpidalians: white-haired, pale-skinned, red-eyed, deeply religious, revering goddess Tosi-karu among others; most killed in YV cataclysm

NAME: unknown larger moon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dobido
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: 20 km in diameter; covered in large cities; YV used dovin basal to pull it into Sernpidal, destroying both

NAME: Rayamal
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Altora
INTERESTING: warm climate in southern regions; grasslands home to altagaks (predatory reptilians described as "high speed death on four legs"; ranchers posted bounties on altagak hides in an effort to protect their herd animals; altagaks menioned in holobrochure for Tagge Holographic Museum of Chandrila

NAME: Laerdocia system
INTERESTING: Laerdocian: species that spoke Basic with unusual accent; a Laerdocian served on Booster Terrik's Errant Venture as technician in 19 ABY

NAME: Amaxine Station system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: The High Republic (comic), The Rise of Kylo Ren (comic)/

NAME: Amaxine Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: The High Republic (comic), The Rise of Kylo Ren (comic)/
INTERESTING: orbited dying star; ancient station with central sphere encircled by a number of rings; built by Amaxine warriors; abandoned after it was infested by the Drengir; later sealed here by the Sith; later acquired by Snoke, who resided here; Ben Solo met him here after destroying Luke's Jedi Temple, believing Luke had died; according to legend these warriors refused to make peace with Republic and left galaxy and encountered Drengir who drove them extinct

NAME: Lokud 7
INTERESTING: Vader tracked Rebel spies carrying Imperial intelligence to this world

NAME: Lah'mu system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where In the Galaxy Are the Worlds of Rogue One (SW.com)/

NAME: Lah'mu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where In the Galaxy Are the Worlds of Rogue One (SW.com)/

NAME: Seline
INTERESTING: during Galactic War, Republic & Empire battrled for control of two Gree hypergates; in 29 BBY Obi-Wan & Anakin guided injureed and dying organic ship Jabitha here to a deserted starport here, known only to Jedi

NAME: Tantiss Station
NOTES: no coords or system listed in WP
INTERESTING: HoloNet node; destroyed by YV in 28 ABY

NAME: Birgis system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Birgis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: several cities here, spread across planet (at least 5 on northern hemisphere; spaceport serving both military and civilian vessels; member state of NR in 25 ABY; YV planned to terraform planet, take population as slaves

NAME: Antmuel VI
INTERESTING: site of Ch'hosk Cave Drawings discovered by Doctor Angrail Ryht (human male archaeologist)

NAME: Aeos Prime
INTERESTING: native Aeosians allowed the Rebel Alliance to establish a base here that was abandoned by the time of the New Republic; later the First Order destroyed the base to prevent the Resistance from making use of it; the space station Colossus sought refuge here; after an initial misunderstanding, the Aeosian queen permitted the mobile station to stay; later, the Aeosians helped the Colossus escape a First Order attack, although they suffered retribution from the First Order fleet

NAME: Zeffo
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: cliffs, ice caves, mountains, seas, oceans, grasslands
INTERESTING: wind-swept world featuring ruins and crypts protected by the Tomb Guardians (ancient automatons); home to creatures such as Phillak and Scazz; home to pioneers and archaeologists during Republic era, but their community was destroyed by the burgeoning Empire, which pillaged the ancient sites; various people sought valuable info on Zeffo, including Emperor Palpatine and former Jedi Padawan Cal Kestis

NAME: Puloorn
INTERESTING: site of ancient, ruined Sith temple inhabited by cultists and twisted Dark Side creatures; Chancellor Palpatine dispatched agents to investigate rumored existence

NAME: Lobaoc
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: lakes, marshes, shallowly flooded crop fields
INTERESTING: dianogas found in lakes and marshes here; between 67 and 19 BBY, Jedi High Council sent a Mon Cal Jedi to investigate and bring her back for training but had to send additional Jedi after him upon realizing he had fallen to the Dark Side on a previous mission; Koab was village of several thousand with makeshift spaceport

NAME: Sartoy
INTERESTING: site of Alliance weapons plant during GCW

NAME: Tiragga
INTERESTING: planet was orbited by at least 2 moons, second of which held Rebel Alliance outpost during GCW; at some point, base personnel became infected with Direllin Plague (fatal disease that could only be cured with administration of Shiarha Root, rare plant from Kirtania)

NAME: Bogano
INTERESTING: largely unexplored by Imperial era; home to a great vault built by the ancient Zeffo civilization; important to the Zeffo due to the presence of the Binog, a large creature important to their culture;

NAME: Jentares
INTERESTING: orbited white dwarf star; home to reclusive Jedi Master Siolo Ur Manka; he was ambushed and killed by Darth Maul on Sidious's orders

NAME: Foxar system
NOTES: missing "searching (for) natural"?
INTERESTING: site of Bureau of Scouting and Exploration Services' HQ; during NR times, the starship NRSS Founder left Outer Region Foxar Scout Base with a crew of 3 scouts (Deeve, Jarsa, and Effcee) to survey 8 planets in different star systems, searching for valuable natural resources; ship was slated to return to Outer Region Foxar Scout Base once mission was over

NAME: Ramook system
region/grid square/just beyond far end of CHiloon Rift

NAME: Ramook
region/grid square/just beyond far end of CHiloon Rift
INTERESTING: agriworld; in 45 ABY, Jedi Knight Ben Skywalker investigated here while searching for signs of Ship (Sith Meditation Sphere controlled by former Lost Tribe of the Sith member Vestara Khai)

NAME: Sarnus
INTERESTING: Lando established a refinery here to mine plentiful asteroids in Chiloon Rift

NAME: Bubble of the Lost
DESC: center of Chiloon Rift (inversed black hole)
INTERESTING: monolith on Base Prime bent space-time (5 years inside Bubble was about one year outside); ships sometimes went missing here for hours, days or centuries

NAME: Base Prime
INTERESTING: construct erected by Qreph brothers on a monolith of unknown origin inside Bubble of the Lost

NAME: Valnoos
INTERESTING: world in Chiloon Rift; in 45 ABY, home to several casinos attended by miners in Rift, including the Blue Star casino (site of assassination attempt on Luke and Han by Craitheus and Marvid Qreph)

NAME: Chiloon Rift
INTERESTING: contained one of the largest and most bountiful asteroid fields in galaxy; navigation difficult; pirates plentiful

NAME: Brink Station
INTERESTING: Red Ronto (cantina) located here

NAME: Gorta
INTERESTING: desolate

NAME: Gorsh
INTERESTING: 100,000 LY from Core; population 100 K; discovered by Genetech Laboratories explorers (rights granted by Empire); orbital pharmaceutical lab built quickly; climate warm and muggy, mostly carbon dioxide atmopshere (breath mask suggested); tallest island was about 260m above sea level; storms wracked the coasts and volcanic eruptions were frequent; Orgons; intelligent clam-like plants

NAME: Yntrann
INTERESTING: after Alliance Special Forces Scandium Team was disbanded, former member Rith Tar'ak (Ebranite female) was transferred here, where she commanded a small but highly decorated desert warfare task force as part of one of the early SpecForce wilderness regiments; when leadership didn't appeal to her, she aventually requested transfer to another branch of the Alliance

NAME: Pitrillistia
INTERESTING: remote; Pitrillistians: bipedal, peaceful, seven feet tall, hunchbacked, insectoid, had purple, two-piece shells; spoke mostly musical language produced by small wings

NAME: Seltaya Major
INTERESTING: riddled with cave systems; Safonne Pendon (pirate captain) maintained fleet here that targeted NR ships

NAME: N'oka Brath
NOTES: Qella system page doesn't mention asteroid belt

NAME: Maltha Obex
INTERESTING: 5 days from N'zoth, 8 days from Coruscant with standard hyperdrive; thick atmosphere lent planet hazy, gray appearance; one moons was stuck in irregular collision course orbit with other moon; Qella built Teljkon Vagabond as means of escape and eventual restoration of species; by 140 BBY, moons had collided, sending numerous asteroids into Brath Qella and kicking off a deep ice age; when planet was first discovered by Third General Survey in 145 BBY it was deemed unworthy of exploration; Vagabond's energy beams were used to begin thawing world from ice age

NAME: Qella system asteroid belt
INTERESTING: orbited close to Brath Qella

NAME: Breta Yaga
INTERESTING: several flatsculp art pieces from Breta Yaga were stored in the Mount Tantiss complex on Wayland

NAME: The Hammer's system
INTERESTING: system contained several notoriously stable asteroid belts

NAME: HM7-R
INTERESTING: refitted FireStar-class orbital defense station

NAME: Murninkam
INTERESTING: carnivores roamed the Kaijin swamp here

NAME: Gulma
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: swamps (prior to Imperial Era); barren wastes (after Imperial Era)
NOTES: "until" ?
INTERESTING: Empire subjugated peoples of Gulma, shipping the Gulmarid off as experimental fodder for Mir Tork and Leonis Murth; world was stripped of its resources and left to rot as a barren, uninhabitable wasteland; NR freed many Gulmarid from the Azgoghk but they soon found the planet could no longer support them; a survivor, Slique Brighteyes, hired Boba Fett to destroy the Azgoghk in 10 ABY

NAME: Ethav Major system
INTERESTING: Drolen Antig (Nalroni smuggler) was spotted here without his ship or crew at some point following Endor; Airen Cracken noted that a group of operatives was preparing to locate and detain him

NAME: Soullex
INTERESTING: garrisoned as headquarters of Fleet Admiral Gaen Drommel after Battle of Tantive V

NAME: Peppel
INTERESTING: Fett took Slave IV here, where he captured Kardue'sai'Malloc

NAME: Sormahil system
INTERESTING: origin point of Sormahil fire gems

NAME: Kaisa
INTERESTING: Buro: sentient insects considered ethereally beautiful; a human-crewed geological survey team negligently destroyed a forest on Kaisa, leading to the accidental extinction of the Buro species

NAME: Eol Sha
INTERESTING: temperate climate but geologically unstable; groundquakes, avalanches common; settled by miners during Galactic Republic era; single moon was in unstable descending orbit; plane rediscoverd in 9 ABY; remaining natives resettled to Dantooine in 11 ABY; Eol Sha likely destroyed when Kyp Durron used the Sun Crusher to destroy Cauldron Nebula

NAME: Cauldron N.
grid square/sector/Eol Sha was just outside nebuls
INTERESTING: surrounded 7 supergiant blue stars; Kyp Durron used Sun Crusher superweapon to destroy system's stars

NAME: Hakara
INTERESTING: Hakarans were tiny insectoids with swarming behavior; after Seperatists established scouting base here, Hakarans sent a distress signal to the Republic but their language was unknown; Anakin and Ahsoka dispatched to find the source

NAME: Pervick system
INTERESTING: home to Pervickian dung camel

NAME: Babali
INTERESTING: Obroan Institute research base here was headed by Kroddok Stopa until his death on Brath Qella

NAME: Ventooine system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ventooine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: ruled by satrabs until Han and Chrysalla (local Tieress); exported sansanna spice, crystals, Shadeshine (mineral)

NAME: Hanod
INTERESTING: at some point by 38 ABY, military bunkers on Hanod were identified by letters from ancient Common Sith writing system

NAME: Oricon
INTERESTING: moon just outside the Seat of the (Sith) Empire; an insignificant world once home to Darth Vitus before its location was lost to the wider galaxy; the Dread Masters built the Dread Fortress using thousands of slaves with the Emperor's blessing

NAME: Basteel
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: subterranean urban, little vegetation, frigid, mountainous, snowy, bleak, temperate
INTERESTING: almost no flat ground; underground capital: Eladro City; Slique Brighteyes hid from Admiral Mir Tork and Doctor Leonis Murth here

NAME: Trascor
INTERESTING: Shatras: reptilian bipeds

NAME: Proxima Dibal
INTERESTING: song serpents and dinkos were native to planet's deserts

NAME: Bosph
INTERESTING: Bosphs: short, horned, no-necked, four-limbed, insectoid-eyed isolationist beings who tattooed star maps on their skin; bombed by Empire due to the Bosphs' Force-sensitivity; Bosphs went into denial about bombardment even though their planet was almost completely destroyed

NAME: Otunia
INTERESTING: Imperial sector capital of Bosph sector; home of Kabul family; had mineral-rich soil, perfect for mining

NAME: Harrandarr
INTERESTING: Buzchubs: stocky beings covered in blue fur; homeworld of Und'l (Buzchub who worked for Imperial sympathizers on Roldalna in 4 ABY)

NAME: Jandolhoon system
INTERESTING: location of Daxis Outpost, used by NR Bureau of Scouting and Exploration Services as staging ground for expeditions into the further reaches of the Galactic Rim

NAME: Hintivan II
INTERESTING: Empire used slaves as lumberjacks here

NAME: Titan (unidentified star system)
INTERESTING: remote system; contained Titan Base (Rebel starfighter base); Alliance kept location secret, even from Rebel agents

NAME: Kyoloria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Kyolorian snake-god deity

NAME: Hordon Cal
INTERESTING: both planet and its small moon were destroyed by Centerpoint Station during Starbuster Plot

NAME: Thanta Zilbra
INTERESTING: first discovered in 8 ABY by Thanta Zilbra (smuggler who discovered native Zilbra fungi posessed therapeutic life-saving properties, established an outpost with a population grown to 13,000 by 18 ABY); planet and its moons wiped out when Centerpoint Station destroyed the system's star during the Starbuster Plot; planet's surface appeared barren, but underground lakes and rivers grew fungi

NAME: Jontan Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: destroyed by Centerpoint Station during Starbuster Plot

NAME: Flandar
INTERESTING: destroyed by Centerpoint Station during Starbuster Plot

NAME: Neelgaimon
INTERESTING: notorious for its hazardous sandmines (planet's main industry, developed and maintained by slave and droid labor); Han visited here once; still an Imperial world by 12 ABY

NAME: Werma Lesser
INTERESTING: homeworld of Kedpin Shoklop

NAME: Cerilia system
INTERESTING: shared name with Cerilian Trade Agreement

NAME: Tralfin
INTERESTING: tropical resort world; Imperial Moff Crin Harson murdered here shortly after Yavin; a group of Rebel agents who had been acquainted with Harson were implicated in the murder but eventually cleared; popular vacation site for Alliance personnel because they could be anonymous here; Empire did not deem it necessary to station troops or weapons here

NAME: Ruuria system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ruuria
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: noted for its pink rivers, along the banks of which chroma-wings would eat, fly, and mate; aligned with Sith Empire during Jedi Civil War; Sith Empire established a puppet government in 3681 BBY; loyalist world during CW; briefly surrendered to Imperial Remnant when Thrawn "returned from the dead" in 19 ABY; featured manufacturing centers and universities; conquered by YV but left alone

NAME: Stic
INTERESTING: subject to severe climate changes, leading to Xi'Dec evolving into hundreds of different forms to survive, with each form becoming a new sex of Xi"Dec; during GCW the planet was going through an unusually hot period in its climatological cycle; despite this, a steady stream of tourists traveled here to observe the wide variety of Xi'Dec forms; government changed rapidly

NAME: Bendone
INTERESTING: Howler Tree People: spoke strange and difficult language in ultrasonic voices, which could give non-Howlers headaches; Leia considered entertaining Howler Tree People diplomats was crucial to survival of NR, despite difficulty of communication

NAME: Xappyh sector space station
INTERESTING: during Galactic War between Republic and Sith Empire, a space station was captured hereby pirates who promptly began selling off its contents

NAME: Kwapi system
NOTES: no mention of Kwapi system / Kwapi pirates in corresponding WP pages
INTERESTING: shared name with Kwapi pirates, who once threatened Trianii Space before being beaten back by the efforts of the Trianii Rangers

NAME: Monic
INTERESTING: Trianii colony planet

NAME: Trian system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Trian
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: governed by Yu'nar triumvirates; population 100 - 500 M (c. 25 ABY)

NAME: Pypin
INTERESTING: one of the Trianii colony worlds within the disputed border of the Corporate Sector

NAME: Ekibo
INTERESTING: Trianii colony world, famous for its farms and herdbeasts; Atuarre and Keeheen (Trianii Rangers) responsible for overthrowing a herdbeast-rustling ring here

NAME: Mavva system
INTERESTING: members of Kobok species lived here; site of Mavvan Conflict sometime between 19 and 15 BBY

NAME: Glite-Ven
INTERESTING: Glite-Ven hostilities occurred here by 2 ABY

NAME: Lo'Uran
INTERESTING: remote world marginally controlled by Empire, which deemed it too far-removed to warrant a full garrison; its governor was Blithane

NAME: H'relac system
INTERESTING: natives of this system fought to maintain their freedom when an alliance of corporations tried to take control of the system, around the time of the Battle of Yavin

NAME: Oshetti IV
INTERESTING: inhabitants used dried swamp hemp (contained bioluminescent bacteria) to create illuminescence (a type of glowing fabric)

NAME: Wenderal system
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance Intelligence Service discovered EV-series supervisor droid fiasco (due to the installation of the MDF motivator) thanks to some cells there

NAME: Boztrok
INTERESTING: dominated by gangsters; bounty hunter Zo'Tannath frequented the planet; Greezim Trentacal (Karazak Slave Master) started his career in the betting pits here; there was a Shrine of Kooroo here

NAME: Cadomai system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Cadomai
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, tundra plains, mountains, canyons, subterranean caverns, resorts
INTERESTING: frigid world; intolerable winters; tundra plains were home to Snivvians, renowned for their art; Snivvians made their homes in cavern systems during subfreezing winters; bloody history despite Snivvians' artistic sensibilities; historically a Republic planet; Imperial Coalition for Progress took notice of Cadomai, wanting to ensure Cadomai's famous transnovels held to tenets of New Order

NAME: Salient's red dwarf
NOTES: "Salient system" on Wook has planets in wrong order
INTERESTING: orbited by three planets and at least one moon

NAME: Salient I
INTERESTING: a rebel encampment was located here in the early Imperial era; entire system was considered autonomous

NAME: Salient II
INTERESTING: in 18 BBY the planet and the rest of its system resisted a perceived intrustion by the Empire in a hard-fought, prolonged campaign; the planet's government was bombed into submission, despite several guerilla forces forestalling the imposition of an occupying force

NAME: Epiphany
INTERESTING: Second Battle of Epiphany took place during the Imperial era and the early years of TIE pilot Soran Keize's service; he later reflected that the battle taught him the importance of protecting those close to him in order to protect the lives of even more

NAME: Epiphany Moon
INTERESTING: location of Zerpen Industries headquarters

NAME: Mytus system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Mytus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Mytus system WP page shows Mytus VIII even though it was a hoax

NAME: Mytus V
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: barren world inhospitable to humanoid life; assigned to Pakka during Han's scheme to determine Rekkon's assassin

NAME: Mytus VI
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: barren world inhospitable to humanoid life; assigned to Torm Dadeferron during Han's scheme to determine Rekkon's assassin

NAME: Mytus Asteroid Belt
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: thick concentration of asteroids halfway between its star and Mytus VII; Han altered the course of one of the asteroids to act as cover for the Falcon during the liberation of Stars' End

NAME: Mytus VII
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: region was heavily avoided, even by the Ocsin spacers because it was the site of the Corporate Sector Authority's Stars' End penal facility

NAME: Artiod Minor
INTERESTING: cool, swampy world discovered by Zygerrian slavers trying to escape Republic justice, who overran the planet, returned over centuries to fill their slave pens with Artiodacs, train them for sale; home of prengalli (water creatures who Artiodacs raised in schools on aqua-farms); also home to Shuimi, whose feathers juvenile Artiodacs would collect to make mate-attracting crowns

NAME: Morellia
INTERESTING: homeworld of Barosa Warren (Morellian lawman and scout who headed the Galactic Outdoor Survival School, born c. 158 BBY, believed to be the last Morellian in existence by 2 ABY); part of Morellian Commonwealth, which included several other systems; Morellians: long-lived near-Humans

NAME: Brochiib
INTERESTING: Trianii colony planet; Atuarre and Keeheen (Trianii Rangers) stopped thionarx dealers here

NAME: Fibuli
INTERESTING: planet in Trianii Space annexed by CSA; once the site of a major Trianii colony before 3 years of fighting turned it into a wasted neutral land; served as location of peace talks between Trianii and CSA; one of planet's major cities was Knanan

NAME: Perin
INTERESTING: Trianii colony planet

NAME: Hull's Star
INTERESTING: contained no planets; was a jumping-off point for the Stars' End prison on a planetoid in the Mytus system

NAME: Farana system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Farana
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: foggy terrestrial world; never governed by Republic or Empire; by 3705 BBY it was situated at endpoint of Morellian Trail hyperlane; Ocsin: near-Human merchants and explorers who dominated the Farana region and established extensive ties between it and the rest of the galaxy via trade and migration; c. 25 ABY, population of the system was 1 - 10 B

NAME: Thandon Cluster/Thandon Nebula
NOTES: Also a nebula

NAME: Bonadan system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Bonadan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kamar
INTERESTING: home of howlrunners; in 3668 BBY, Akaavi Spar (female Zabrak) born here; at same time, a space battle took place above the planet, leaving several shipwrecks to slowly be pulled towards surface; Han and Chewie once visited the Kamarians, fascinating them with the holodocumentary Varn, World of Water and kickstarting the Cult of Varn before upsetting Kamarians and having to flee

NAME: Teptixii
INTERESTING: blue-green world; Imperial forces under Captain Voss Parck fought against elements of warlord Nuso Esva's navy near here in 0 ABY

NAME: Guiteica
INTERESTING: Historically, Kaleesh warlords took roggwarts (large, 2-legged predatory beasts) from here as trophies; harsh planet with rich reserves of ores and minerals; 16 primary continents each governed by separate military force (together made up planetary defense force); earlier conflict led to eternal enmity of Republic and Jedi, and later Alliance (though also Empire)

NAME: Huk
INTERESTING: beginning many years prior to CW, Yam'rii in constant state of war with Kaleesh people of nearby Kalee, resultingin devastation of much of planet's surface; Yam'rii called on Republic for help, who were able to prevent Qymaen jai Sheelal (later known as Grievous) from claiming total victory; CIS planted a bomb aboard his shuttle, maiming him and framed Republic, swaying him to CIS cause

NAME: Tovarskl
INTERESTING: during Huk War, Grievous led his forces as far as Tovarskl before Jedi arrived to halt the conflict; after being rebuilt as a cyborg, Grievous returned to finish what he started, annihilating the Yam'rii population and killing Jedi Masters Puroth and Nystammall on the fire-grass plains, taking their lightsabers as trophies; site of an Imperial Remnant territory battle amongst Moffs in 44 ABY

NAME: Oben
INTERESTING: after the Huk war, Yam'rii desecrated Kaleesh burial grounds here, prompting Grievous to lead the kolkpravis again; the InterGalactic Banking Clan sabotaged Grievous's shuttle, nearly killing him and killing most of his elite warriors; the sole surviving Izvoshra led the slaughter od the Yam'rii on Oben; Thrawn was tasked with pacification of galaxy's fringe and was forced to raze Oben

NAME: Vexta Belt
INTERESTING: Delephran corporation's transports attacked by pirates in the belt until they mobilized its militia to wipe out the attackers

NAME: Baramorra
NOTES: WP article for Baramorra system fails to mention planet
INTERESTING: Imperial Remnant planet governed by the "Boss" (Admiral Llon Banjeer's nephew, funded by Grappa the Hutt) who hired bounty hunters to keep populace in line; had elders killed when they objected; the Boss was executed as traitor by Kir Kanos when ties to Grappa were exposed

NAME: Delephr
INTERESTING: origin point of Delephran social group (& Delephran corporation?); fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Sojourn
INTERESTING: also known as "the Hunters' Moon"; fortress home and personal retreat of Plagueis; ancient fort here founded as retreat by InterGalactic Banking Clan generations before CW; rendered desolate by bombing orchestrated by Sidious in attempt to kill Plagueis

NAME: Zin Taal
INTERESTING: First Sun Mobile Regiment (mercenary group) established command base here; NR Special Forces strike team intended to capture base but mission was eventually complicated

NAME: Dactruria system
INTERESTING: renowned actor Anorad Estuan was a Dactrurian

NAME: Gandrossi VI
INTERESTING: under authority of Imperial Governor Desh

NAME: Brodo Asogi
INTERESTING: also known as the Green Planet; near Kalee & Huk; Senator Grebleips funded extragalactic expedition shortly before CW;

NAME: Valc system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Valc VII
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Imperial fortress world by 4 ABY; governed by Moff Crowall at time of Yuuzhan Vong invasion

NAME: Cantras Gola
INTERESTING: corporate world controlled by PowerOn Conglomerate; decided to leaved Pentastar Alignment and join NR during Thrawn Crisis; children of Ambassador (taken by slavers to Gabredor III) threatened by Pentastar, rescued by Red Moons mercenary team, and Cantras Gola joined NR

NAME: G'haris
INTERESTING: origin point of rare saass worm (creature whose silk was used to fashion cloth)

NAME: Bettok
INTERESTING: TIE Pilot Creb born here in 20 BBY

NAME: Bextar
INTERESTING: one of four gas giants in the system; site of several Amber Sun Mining Corporate gas mines; Amber Sun imported Entymal slaves as miners

NAME: Varvrona system
INTERESTING: fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Jaemus
INTERESTING: had Galentro Heavy Works shipyards comparable in size to Sluis Van's; CIS member during CW; site of Death-Hunter Cyborg assassin project; Imperial fortress world by 4 ABY

NAME: Karavis system
INTERESTING: remote; KDY assembly line here used to construct prototype Dragon-class Heavy Cruiser Galaxy Dragon

NAME: Quanton
INTERESTING: Airen Cracken captured by ISB here, subjected to Bavo Six (truth serum)

NAME: Fegorosk IV
INTERESTING: known for swuvehorn (musical instrument) clubs, an attraction well-known enough to include in scenic replicators in the Arcade Omicron cantina on Bescane

NAME: Muunilinst
INTERESTING: major Muun colony

NAME: Trinciuum
INTERESTING: orbited by single moon

NAME: Muunilinst
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, plains, forests, hills, tall jagged mountains, volcanoes, shallow oceans
INTERESTING: nicknamed Moneylend; population 5 B; CIS member; Republic captured world during Battle of Muunilinst during CW; home to division of InterGalactic Banking Clan; skies said to be most beautiful in galaxy; volcanically active; shallow oceans contained many "smokers" (volcanic vents) spewing rich, pure precious metals from liquid iron core

NAME: Havath Prime
INTERESTING: had rings; was most easily spotted planet in system when viewed from other systems

NAME: Havath Minor
INTERESTING: smaller han Havath Prime

NAME: Gabredor III
INTERESTING: Karazak Slavers Cooperative had transfer center / camp here, which was destroyed by the Red Moons, who rescued kidnapped children and other slaves

NAME: Angor system
INTERESTING: Kyp's Dozen battled smugglers here shortly before YV war

NAME: Praya
INTERESTING: ocean world; by 4.3 ABY, home to luxurious Sea Castle Resort Hotel; Star Tours facilitated transit here through Deluxe Undersea Package

NAME: Bisellia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Lobster Bisellian (meal); fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Endoraan
INTERESTING: remained under control of Grand Moff Ardus Kaine and Pentastar Alignment after Endor; later part of Imperial Remnant

NAME: Venestria
INTERESTING: origin point of Venestrian poetry; father of future Stormtrooper Isila Drutch served with Republic in a confrontation here; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY

NAME: Korrus
INTERESTING: by 5 ABY it was one of 3 worlds held by the Empire, including Belladoon and Zhadalene

NAME: Kwevron
INTERESTING: lightly populated; almost all citizens farmers; Imperial Prefect oversaw starport during GCW; Rebel recruiter Cala Worner escaped with assistance of some bystanders, who she recruited; capital: Mal Ethon City

NAME: Kwevron
INTERESTING: lightly populated; almost all citizens farmers; Imperial Prefect oversaw starport during GCW; Rebel recruiter Cala Worner escaped with assistance of some bystanders, who she recruited; capital: Mal Ethon City

NAME: Shramar
INTERESTING: controlled by Imperial Remnant during YV war; YV seeded planet with lambents and Muur with intention of harvesting them at later date; site of Battle of Shramar

NAME: Fodro
INTERESTING: serves as endpoint of Dahvil-Fodro Hyperspace Promenade (popular interstellar racing route); later fell within borders of Pentastar Alignment

NAME: Karka system
INTERESTING: origin point of karkan ribenes (meal)

NAME: Gwori
INTERESTING: home to Gwori Revolutionary Industries; site of one of CIS's biggest shipyards; inflitrated by Republic forces on mission to destroy shipyards; one of first deployments of Y-wing; shipyards siezed by Empire to exclusively produce ISDs

NAME: Ord Sedra
INTERESTING: colonized sometime before Pius Dea Era; Imperial Remnant world; liberated from YV by Kyle Katarn, Jan Ors, and Imperial Remnant troops; later Katarn returned, finding clues that Sith survived in the Cloak of the Sith

NAME: Cezith system
INTERESTING: home to Cezith water-lily; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY (remained part of Remnant by 40 ABY)

NAME: Marmoth
INTERESTING: explored btwenn 1000 and 25 BBY; population 1 M - 10 M; one of ports of call for Kuari Princess (luxury liner)

NAME: Ushmin
INTERESTING: small world on borders of Imperial Remnant

NAME: Entralla system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Entralla
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: diversity of religions and rich history blended with myths until New Order rose; most notable holiday: Lunar Night, when Parade of Ghosts was held; subjugated by Pentastar Alignment after trying to regain independence post-Endor; independent resistance group called Red Moons arose under disillusioned NRI officer; headquarters of Guild of Interstellar Merchants

NAME: Capza
INTERESTING: home to Commerce Master Commissioner Gregor Raquoran

NAME: Tertiary Kesmere
INTERESTING: home of winged hornagaunts; shared name with Kesmere & Kesmere Minor systems; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Shusugaunt
INTERESTING: Shusugaunt: warlike, enslaved Anx millennia before 0 BBY; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY

NAME: Alurion
INTERESTING: population less than 1 M; Alurion captured in conquest of YV's invasion of Raioballo sector early in war; cut off from Republic assistance, Alurion sat behind enemy lines until end of war

NAME: Kesmere Minor system
INTERESTING: shared name with Kesmere & Tertiary Kesmere systems; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Dantooine
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: small settlements, savannas, mountains, hills, steppes, rivers, grasslands, plains, lakes, oceans
INTERESTING: removed from most galactic traffic; no industrial settlements or advanced tech by GCW; temporary Rebel base here abandoned before Yavin; several continents; home of blba tree; Rakata world; later Jedi enclave

NAME: Purnell
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: Parakus not mentioned on Purnell WP entry

NAME: Parakus
INTERESTING: 1 of 6 moons of Purnell; small moon where CIS kept garrison

NAME: Ferionic N.
INTERESTING: nebula contained within Area Ferionic 7-IK of Dantooine system

NAME: "Dantooine's Second Star"
INTERESTING: under control of small, little-known band of thugs called Velocity Mercenaries; once Empire moved in the mercenaries began launching continuous attacks against them, hoping to drive out the Empire

NAME: Kesmere system
INTERESTING: shared name with Kesmere Minor & Tertiary Kesmere systems; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 18 - 35 ABY

NAME: Neka
INTERESTING: during Jedi Civil War, Neka was subject to a Sith blockade, then Sith virus-bombed the world, killing all intelligent life; only a few fortunate individuals were able to evade the blockade, including SHuma the Hutt

NAME: Sinsang
INTERESTING: one among thousands of worlds in the sector represented by Horox Ryyder (impartial Anx senator) until his retirement in 22 BBY; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY

NAME: Anx Minor
INTERESTING: presumably colonized by Anx from Gravlex Med; massacre here during GCW; situated in Pentastar Alignment territory from 4 ABY to 12 ABY, remained within borders until 17 ABY, when Pellaeon and Ackbar faced off in a confrontation at Anx Minor

NAME: Gravlex Med
INTERESTING: Gravlex Launchworks based here, with shipyards in orbit; protected by Republic & saw no action during CW; during reign of Empire, became so polluted as to become uninhabitable; Anx were nearly driven extinct, and all survivors were driven offworld

NAME: Verig
INTERESTING: Rebel tactician Beryl Chiffonage traveled here and was inspired by the native nomadic hunters' use of bolas to develop a similar tactic against AT-ATs

NAME: RZ7-6113-23
INTERESTING: small class-6 planetoid, devoid of life but site of large military storehouse built during early Empire; outdated hardware retired from Imperial amy sent here; Ennix Devian (Imperial warlord) planned to attack Imperial Remnant with old war materiel; NR Navy Captain described area surrounding the system as having no nearby planets capable of supporting life, and there being no trade routes in Chopani Sector

NAME: Morturia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Morturian energy disk (weapon)

NAME: Grumwall
INTERESTING: site of massacre carried out by 204th Imperial Fighter "Shadow" Wing during Battle of Grumwall; Jan Dodonna (Alliance general) later wrote a report on the battle

NAME: Ord Trasi system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ord Trasi
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: major shipbuilding world and also manufactured weapons and comm gear; rich in natural resources (metals, minerals, ores, crystals); completely encircled by space platforms, defended by defense platforms; mining and smelting on moons

NAME: Ord Trasi Salvage Yards
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: decommissioned Republic warships dumped here; Bogga salvaged Enforcer One here

NAME: Vantillia
INTERESTING: shared name with Vantillian catamaran (type of starship Lando deemed an acceptable gift for Han and Leia in 5 ABY after recapturing Cloud City)

NAME: Vernid system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map, Alphabet Squadron/Alphabet Squadron p. 393 (Outer Rim system, squalid, barbarous) p. 534 (one of the farthest planets from Galactic Core) p. 535 (Red Moon festival, celebrating 2nd satellite)

NAME: Vernid
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map, Alphabet Squadron/Alphabet Squadron p. 393 (Outer Rim system, squalid, barbarous) p. 534 (one of the farthest planets from Galactic Core) p. 535 (Red Moon festival, celebrating 2nd satellite)
INTERESTING: pounded by heavy rains; had one spaceport; one of several worlds where the 204th Imperial Fighter "Shadow" Wing's Major Soran Keize attempted to live under an alias after Operation: Cinder; described as barbaric and rural; drinking mijura was a cultural tradition here, as was a "Red Moon Festival", celebrating 2nd satellite

NAME: Mek'tradi
INTERESTING: "pearl spires climbing into orbit"; housed Rebel cell during the Imperial Era; 204th Imperial Fighter "Shadow" Wing bombarded planet from orbit to draw out the rebel cell and destroy them; Yrica Quell (Imperial pilot who later defected) was horrified about what she had done, but followed orders

NAME: Malicar 3
INTERESTING: in 11 ABY Dr. Leonis Murth and Admiral Mir Tork fled here from NR aboard Imperial extermination ship Azgoghk; after Fett killed them, planet served as home for nonhumans freed from Empire

NAME: Ibanjji
INTERESTING: home to packs of varns (predators); site of Imperial motivational camp to harden recruits

NAME: Amaltanna
INTERESTING: discovered by 4000 BBY; most of Kanz sector was independent of any major sector-spanning gov't; in 3970 BBY Myrialites formed Argazdan Redoubt and began to annex nearby worlds; Amaltannan resistance formed here, and Myrialites were outraged and reacted by enslaving Lorrdian supporters; in 3670 Jedi led task force to liberate sector; during CW, Baron Edi Wedd took up residence in Impregnable fortress; natives resisted but were defeated; Jedi General Bultar Swan destroyed his life-support system and left him to die on the lifeless world

NAME: Ayceezee
INTERESTING: inhabited world with rolling walkways, Ayceezee Public College; Voort SaBinring retired here as mathematics professor until re-recruited by Garok Loran in 44 ABY

NAME: Bimmiel
INTERESTING: discovered by Imperial survey team led by man named Bimmiel; elliptical orbit; as planet neared sun, ice caps started to melt, increasing moisture and plant growth; natives who lived here used crude wooden spears, tools; advance YV scouts landed here in 25 BBY

NAME: Bimmiel asteroid field
INTERESTING: during Galactic War, Republic tried to establish minefield here but were stopped by Sith Empire forces

NAME: The Home
INTERESTING: large iron asteroid; name was teanslation of what mynock-like sapients called it; iblued with dark side energy from mynocks, which eventually created fairly advanced civilization before going extinct; millennia later a mine was established, but abandoned after strange happenings due to Dark Side energy; mine administrator later returned as Sith Lord Darth Vectivus and built mansion here; unknown centuries later Lumiya moved in; finally destroyed by members of One Sith

NAME: Omega 379
INTERESTING: largest asteroid in system; Dician ordered crew to wait for retrieval here after they destroyed Alema Rar's base

NAME: 3?. Atterra Belt
NOTES: not listed on Wook page for Atterra System

NAME: Sipsk system
INTERESTING: Sipsk'ud: avian-like, with large cluster of 7 eyes; at least one wore a sealed spacesuit while in human-friendly atmopshere; many converted to Vianism during Old Republic era; could be found wandering streets of Nar Shaddaa at end of CW

NAME: Noremac
INTERESTING: Jedi Watchman Mari-Elan Nore killed by slavers here after end of Kanz Disorders in 3670 BBY

NAME: Jerne
INTERESTING: human colonists here exhausted natural resources; during GCW, home to Imperial base; Leia and Luke once searched for the Eternity Crystal here

NAME: Argazda
INTERESTING: around time of Mandalorian Wars, local Provisional Governor Myrial, Myrialite followers rebelled against Republic, established Argazdan Redoubt, starting Kanz Disorders; in CIS space during CW; surrendered to YV

NAME: Nord system
INTERESTING: home system of Iceman (bounty hunter who operated in Minos Cluster

NAME: Ereesus
INTERESTING: Ereesi heavily involved in slave trading, slave markets; their slave raids throughout sector prompted Argazdans to join Republic in 4200 BBY; Tott Doneeta and family rescued from slave markets here by Master Arca; in 3970 BBY, Argazdan Redoubt forces devastated Ereesus, exterminating all life; during CW Ereesus Planetary Security Forces and Republic's Torrent Company fought CIS here

NAME: Lorrd
INTERESTING: great repository of academic knowledge; Lorrd City had great university; Argazdans enslaved Lorrdians and forbade them from speaking with each other, leading to development of nonverbal language of subtle gestures, expressions and postures known as kinetic communication

NAME: Lorrd II
INTERESTING: largest moon of Lorrd; Argazdan Redoubt established slave colony here during Kanz Disorders, and was raided by group of Revanchist Jedi during later stages of Mandalorian Wars; freed slaves and looted Lorrdian gemstones (used in lightsabers)

NAME: Alpinn
INTERESTING: its surface was covered in a layer of minerals that made it appear bright white from space; Lyra Erso conducted an archaeological expedition here to search for Kyber crystals here but was unable to find any true specimens; she felt the planet deserved Legacy status and told Orson Krennic she hoped the Empire would be gentle with the world

NAME: Kol Atorn
INTERESTING: settled by Mandalorian emigrants and exiles; homeworld of individual who became Mandalore the Hammerborn

NAME: Kol Huro system
INTERESTING: system conquered by YV

NAME: Kol Huro I

INTERESTING: harvested for natural resources; local tyrant Mustag Olus was influenced by Sidious to develop and manufacture starships and weapons here, but was defeated by Jedi in 44 BBY
