INTERESTING: harvested for natural resources; local tyrant Mustag Olus was influenced by Sidious to develop and manufacture starships and weapons here, but was defeated by Jedi in 44 BBY

NAME: Kol Huro VII
INTERESTING: harvested for natural resources; local tyrant Mustag Olus was influenced by Sidious to develop and manufacture starships and weapons here, but was defeated by Jedi in 44 BBY

NAME: Trif
INTERESTING: legendary city called the "World Below" was exposed after a series of massive groundquakes opened fissures exposing city during Galactic War between Republic and Sith Empire; under Imperial Control as of Black Fleet Crisis

NAME: Zhadalene
INTERESTING: by 5 ABY it was one of the 3 Outer Rim worlds held by the Empire, including Korrus and Belladoon

NAME: Tholian system
INTERESTING: shared name with Tholians (social group appearing in the play Jedi!, authored by Palleus Chuff by 19 BBY

NAME: Arcanum
INTERESTING: space station commissioned by Sith Emperor as storehouse for dangerous Sith artifacts; in 3638 BBY rogue Sith Lord Tagriss raided facility, stole Darkstaff and Seeds of Rage on behalf of Dread Masters

NAME: Gaalt system
INTERESTING: Gaalt Sky Rowing team hailed from here

NAME: Zorb
INTERESTING: self-described "Rubenesque beauty" placed a personal ad seeking a generous male from either Cryon or Zorb

NAME: Cryon
INTERESTING: self-described "Rubenesque beauty" placed a personal ad seeking a generous male from either Cryon or Zorb

NAME: Valfin system
INTERESTING: The Valfin Labor Camps Insurgence took place here during NR era

NAME: Lusaanda system
INTERESTING: Destiny Days was a fictional account written by Skreen (technical director of Manifold Mollusk Matrix and Matrimony Association) based on historical events occurring on Lusaanda after his death

NAME: Simento-Threk
INTERESTING: homeworld of mOKDAR 15's species

NAME: Kauron
INTERESTING: served as hideout for Cavrilhu Pirates

NAME: Kauron Asteroid Field
INTERESTING: one of hese asteroids held the base of the Cavrilhu Pirates, which was taken out by Luke in 19 ABY

NAME: Regalia Sub-space Station-12
INTERESTING: manned by eminent director mOKDAR 15, who kept copious amounts of video journals with intent of broadcasting them over subspace transceiver medium

NAME: Misnor
INTERESTING: had liquid water, unlike many frozen ice worlds; home of Chiilaks (2.2m, 6-limbed, excellent hunters, long-furred marine mammals, average lifespan 50 years)

NAME: Meserian
INTERESTING: used as hiding place by Jedi Master Djinn Altis and his group shortly after formation of Galactic Empire

NAME: Vannan system
INTERESTING: origin point of Vannan Crystals

NAME: Kabieroun
INTERESTING: Imperial forces enslaved native Kabieroun

NAME: Di'wor
INTERESTING: tourists were attracted to Di'wor to view the singfruit groves' pollination season; Star Tours operated here; Mara Jade tracked the Cavrilhu Pirates here before losing their trail

NAME: Skaross system
INTERESTING: site of battle during the Cold War

NAME: Miglar 2
INTERESTING: Ma'w'shiye lost facial horns in a speeder bike accident here

NAME: Tangrene system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Tangrene
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: crags, mountains, canyons, almost no vegetation or water
INTERESTING: Tangrene: peaceful nomads enslaved by Empire, wiped out by local Moff to avoid any risk of insurrection; Tangrene became one of the Empire's most heavily defended fortress worlds; site of NR feint (correctly predicted by Thrawn) as Ackbar intended to strike Bilbringi Shipyards; conquered by YV in 27 ABY

NAME: Rentalles
INTERESTING: Dagra Van (Crakka the Hutt's beastmaster) captured a hunanetre on the wastes of Rentalles; site of Imperial base; alliance planned to attack base until they learned it had been deserted and sent a team to investigate

NAME: Demesel
INTERESTING: Outer Rim trading hub settled by consortium of Galactic Core businesses; lost importance during GCW, becoming a backwater and HQ of Glasfir Ring, which took over local underworld, eliminating Hutt competition; population: 720,000

NAME: Nebula Fourso
INTERESTING: Horticultural educator Kaat Thrick-Thrick hailed from Nebula Fourso and lived and conducted her work inside a housing structure known as a hubcap with her three families

NAME: Daranc system
INTERESTING: shared name with Daranc Run hyperlane

NAME: Thalassian system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Thalassia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: location of Thalassian slavers' base; population 1M to 10M

NAME: Langhesa
INTERESTING: Langhesi: could mold and shape life-forms and specialized in producing unique pets for the Republic's wealthy; conquered in 129 BBY by Tsinimals, leading to a mass migration of Langhesi offworld

NAME: Tuulab
INTERESTING: Tuulab was 2nd planet of system; 721 humans settled here in expedition; population grew (6000 inhabitants); no gov't formed; neither Empire nor NR established a presence here

NAME: Jaresh
INTERESTING: key member of Republic during High Republic era; received a sky-island at Republic Fair on Valo, which held a representation of its bustling markets; homeworld of Grimshaw (Kyuzo)

NAME: Jaresh
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungle, trees hundreds of meters tall
INTERESTING: remote; Ree Shala (Twi'lek smuggler) purchased moon as a smuggling base (population: 20)

NAME: Ligna system
INTERESTING: origin point of Lignan (mineral)

NAME: Jandoon system
INTERESTING: Brizzit colony here that died out centuries before Yavin; it was rumored that the spirits of the dead roamed the system, which tended to keep away visitors

NAME: Sesid
INTERESTING: Draedan: swimming humanoid amphibians with aggressive reputation; run by Governor Arvel Trace during GCW; popular tourist destination

NAME: H'ken
INTERESTING: 20km wide navigational nightmare used by NR Sector Fleet for training purposes; planet of H'ken orbited within the belt, which made the planet difficult to access

NAME: H'ken Belt
INTERESTING: located within H'ken asteroid belt, a 20km wide navigational nightmare that made the planet difficult to access

NAME: Galaan system
INTERESTING: source of Corva sector's name; Corva system (eponymous of its sector) mentioned in AoR Beta adventure; Galaan/Galaanus system mentioned in BF2, Rebel Files; Corva system was probably original name

NAME: Galaan
INTERESTING: north pole home to Corva sector's primary NR comm base and NRI base, which was discovered and destroyed by Kaarenth Dissension aftet THrawn campaign

NAME: Yellow Moon
INTERESTING: inspiration for name of Rebels' Operation Yellow Moon

NAME: Corva
NOTES: "The incident at Corva" may refer to a planet by this name in the Galaanus system, or a planet in the Corva sector's Galaanus system
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic established colony here which was wiped out when clodhoppers that arrived in a grain shipment ate all the planet's vegetation as well as 87% of the colonists

NAME: Betha II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren, arid buttes, crevasses, desert canyons, cave systems
INTERESTING: once was more moist world, colonized by Republic and became thriving port world but abandoned when planet dried up significantly; resettled by smugglers about 20 BBY; surface often swept by dust or sandstorms; smugglers expanded and connected cave systems; NR Intelligence discovered it to be headquarters of Ennix Devian's Restored Empire

NAME: Spawn Nebula
INTERESTING: 30-minute hyperjump from Betha II; Kaarenth Dissension maintained fleet here

NAME: Kaarenth Dissension Repair Sta.
INTERESTING: repair station and much of Dissension fleet destroyed here

NAME: Delari Prime
INTERESTING: once teemed with life; thousands of years prior to rise of Empire, several-km asteroid slammed into world, pushing it closer towards the system's binary stars; weather patterns massively distorted, oceans evaporated within weeks, forming thousands upon thousands of rivers crisscrossing planet, pressure discrepancies kicked up fierce winds, furthering erosion; hardier plant life colonized more temperate poles; Imperial relay station was abandoned after Endor, became home of NR archaeologist Dr. Oron

NAME: Jurio
INTERESTING: under control of Sith Empire by time of Great Galactic War; granted Imperial governance before 3666 BBY

NAME: Bizikia system
INTERESTING: home to Bizikian hornets

NAME: Haaridin system
NOTES: Haaridin system WP page lacks coords and link to Haaridin page

NAME: Rya
INTERESTING: inhabited by Humans; homeworld of Cinto Alaras (engineer)

NAME: Korlings
INTERESTING: home to a noble family; rumored homeworld of Faarl the Conqueror (notorious pirate, warlord and slaver born in 12 BBY who conquered several low-tech planets in Wild Space before 20th birthday)

NAME: Yyrta
INTERESTING: orbited by at least 4 planets including Kirtania

NAME: Kirtania
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: arctic, deserts, tropical jungles, woodlands, mountains, plains
INTERESTING: Araquia: spider-like; numbered thousands; planet colonized by several groups of Human and alien settlers who disturbed the natural environment; misunderstanding led to the groups labeling the Araquia a threat; hunted and exterminated until only 1,500 remained; understanding reached and Araquia became overlords and protectors of the forests; divided into 3 competing economic states

NAME: Carosi
INTERESTING: expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY, resulting in the destruction of its five innermost planets

NAME: Carosi I
INTERESTING: destroyed when Carosi (star) expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY

NAME: Carosi II
INTERESTING: destroyed when Carosi (star) expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY

NAME: Carosi III
INTERESTING: destroyed when Carosi (star) expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY

NAME: Carosi IV
INTERESTING: destroyed when Carosi (star) expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY; native Carosites fled to Carosi XII beforehand

NAME: Carosi V
INTERESTING: considered a prime candidate for colonization; destroyed when Carosi (star) expanded into a red giant in 200 BBY

NAME: Carosi VI
INTERESTING: considered suitable for terraforming until Carosi's expansion burned away any life-sustaining potential

NAME: Carosi VII
NOTES: Carosus system WP page sidebar doesn't list all moons?
INTERESTING: following Carosi's expansion, became a hot, swampy planet deemed suitable for colonization at a later date

NAME: Carosi VIII
INTERESTING: represented at a celebration for the worlds of the Outer Rim on Serenno during Republic era; during celebration, Jedi Initiate Dooku and the young Lady Jenza of House Serenno ate lalaren blooms from here; hot jungle planet deemed suitable for future Carosite colonization efforts

NAME: Carosi X
INTERESTING: became fifth planet in system after expansion of Carosi

NAME: Carosi XI
INTERESTING: became sixth planet in system after expansion of Carosi

NAME: Carosi XII
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: glaciers, mountains, plains, crystalline caves, sea
INTERESTING: terraformed prior to star's expansion; colonized by Carosites in 200 BBY as their homeworld of Carosi IV was being destroyed; center of healing and tourism; one of few worlds to openly support Rebel Alliance; served as safe haven for free-traders and Alliance/NR agents; Avuae Sea was only large body of water, unfrozen due to high mineral content; Rebel base during GCW; later NR outpost built

NAME: Shi'kar Straits
INTERESTING: formed after Shi'kar homeworld was obliterated by a comet; by time of CW, Straits were a haven fro smugglers, pirates and scavengers; large asteroids prevented Republic from patrolling the area; Obi-Wan, Anakin, Ahsoka visited while trying to track down the Zygerrian Slavers Guild

NAME: Otranto
INTERESTING: base of Church of the First Frequency; Church ordered to be closed by Torbin (Imperial Grand Inquisitor

NAME: Seikosha
INTERESTING: 4th planet in Breoga system; Cryospac Repulsorlift Corporation (produced Model 90 Ranger landspeeder) based here; planet remained neutral during GCW; hot, violent thunderstorms and downpours were common; Janelle Serap (crimelord) had a fortress in the jungle outside Cairn (city)

NAME: Chromovon
INTERESTING: contained Imperial prison

NAME: Rindia
INTERESTING: Rindians: small stature, pointed ears, eight digits per hand, melodious speech

NAME: Q'nithia
INTERESTING: had a moon with an atmosphere, which supported a colony of q'nithian mimbranes (small creatures that lived deep within faults and rocky fissures and were trainable as living recording devices)

NAME: Praadost II
INTERESTING: located in CIS space during CW; aligned with Rebels shortly before Kwymar Suppressions; Beilert Valance involved in subjugation by Empire; many civilians died in battle

NAME: Jendar
INTERESTING: site of campaign between forces of Rebel Alliance and Galactic Empire for control of the planet

NAME: Direllia
INTERESTING: origin point of Direllian plague

NAME: Protazk
INTERESTING: characterized as a "dirt-ball world" "crawling with Rebel scum" by Gortz; one of many worlds subjugated by Empire during Kwymar Suppressions; assaulted by Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit led by Colonel Zel Johans

NAME: Listehol system
INTERESTING: notable spice-smuggling system

NAME: Listehol system
INTERESTING: notable spice-smuggling system

NAME: Port Tooga
NOTES: WP article is a stub (Listehol system has more info)
INTERESTING: located close to system's star, where solar winds, stellar ejections and radiation overwhelmed Imperial sensors; owned by Shoola the Hutt; major transshipment point for spices, all kinds of illicit goods along Hydian Way; shortly after Yavin, Rebel frigate Shadow Raptor visited here to take posession of a group of droids, which had been reprogrammed by the Empire, leading to a droid revolt

NAME: Listehol
INTERESTING: homeworld of Baron Yasto Attsmun (tyrant, captain of Undisputed Victor on Cantonica) located in CIS space during CW, later full under Imperial control

NAME: Teagan
INTERESTING: Devon: owners of the Teagan Tech Consortium (droid manufacturer)

NAME: Rakrir
INTERESTING: Rakririans: could move extremely quickly, had 10 limbs, 2 eyes on stalks, highly refined and meticulous, rarely left homeworld because they found the rest of the galaxy too unsophisticated; homeworld of Mogoyu (second place in decaped-plus category of Mobquet Presents: Fastest Land Beings races); homeworld of Sabodor (set up a boutique petstore on Etti IV)

NAME: Tantive IV
INTERESTING: home to Tantive Gallery of Progressive Art (sister project to Alderaan's Aldera Museum of Modern Expression (at some point during Republic's decline there was a cultural exchange of art and artists between the two worlds); in honor of diplomats from Tantive IV who visited Alderaan, the Star of Alderaan was renamed Tantive IV; later resided in Imperial Remnant territory ruled by Gaen Drommel

NAME: Tantive V
INTERESTING: location of Battle of Tantive V, won by NR after Battle of Endor; Gaen Drommel retreated to Soullex after the battle; known to have shipyards capable of producing ISDs

NAME: Doniphon
INTERESTING: invaded by Empire in 17 BBY during Kwymar Suppressions of Rebel activity in the sector; Imperial platoon succeeded in rooting out dissidents, though Beilert Valance (Stormtrooper commander) was grievously wounded

NAME: Werncin 3
NOTES: on Listehol Run but not listed on Listehol Run sidebar
INTERESTING: slaving world; location of Jinorota City

NAME: Telos IV
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban; forests, canyons, grasslands, hills, mountains, beaches, polar regions
INTERESTING: during Imperial campaign at Salient, an Imperial battle group was stationed at Telos; during Telosian Restoration Project (spearheaded by Ithorians) to restore the ecosystems devastated in Jedi Civil War, Citadel Station (massive space station) housed the planet's populace and government; by 44 BBY, tourist traffic to see planet's natural wonders accounted tor a significant portion of economy

NAME: Citadel Station
INTERESTING: immense orbital space station serving as Republic's Ithorian-led effort to restore natural ecosystems of Telos IV after their devastation by a Sith Fleet during the Jedi Civil War; had massive grid of residential, entertainment and dock modules; Czerka Corporation eventually integrated itself into the project for its own enrichment; station still orbited by 53 BBY

NAME: Jelucan
INTERESTING: cold world that sided with CIS during CW; annexed by Empire; population divided between First Wavers (Human remote valley dwellers who first arrived around 511 BBY) and 2nd wave of Human, alien settlers (lived in urban centers such as Valentia); urbanites tended to be wealthier and the two populations distrusted each other; origin point of Jelucani fogstone (mineral used for carving statues)

NAME: Vendara
INTERESTING: Vendarans: near-humans resulting from an ancient colonization attempt); home to predatory mollusks called skeeg, which attracted poachers

NAME: Kestos Minor
INTERESTING: represented by Ivor Drake (Human female) in Galactic Senate, then Imperial Senate until rounded up in mass arrest of senators critical of Palpatine; planet was targeted by Empire during Kwymar Suppressions; Modigal Glave (Imperial commando) sustained facial damage during Imperial assault

NAME: Artus system
INTERESTING: during Cold War, Darth Jadus's dreadnaught was stationed here in orbit of gas giant Artus Five

NAME: Artus Prime
INTERESTING: primarily served as mining colony, known for its Artusian crystals, which could also be used in construction of lightsabers; not considered major destination hub in sector; population relatively low; Artus Prime Mining Facility captured by Empire Reborn movement in 12 ABY; Kyle Katarn aided a NR fleet in recapturing facility and planet; Katarn confronted Desann here but was easily beaten

NAME: Artus Five
INTERESTING: lifeless gas giant where Darth Jadus faked his death during the Cold War; he hid his secret dreadnought here, which was soon infiltrated by Cipher Nine; Jadus then revealed his plans to take control of the Empire

NAME: Seelos
INTERESTING: once considered a prospective mining world; by age of Empire all attempts at settlement or exploitation were abandoned, in part due to massive, deadly joopa worms that burrowed under the surface of the salt flats; largely uninhabited, though there were isolated settlements of outlaws at the feet of some mountains; Rex, Wolffe and Gregor lived here for a time after CW on an old AT-TE walker

NAME: Picutorion
INTERESTING: among locations identified in an ISB report in 3 ABY that generated targets for Viper droid surveys hunting for Rebels; rebelled against Empire during Kwymar Suppressions; Beilert Valance involved in Imperial assault on the world, which forced Rebels to evacuate; Commodore Beven was stationed here and in charge of TIEs used in attack; ground forces commanded by High Colonel Theol Drost

NAME: Soco-Jarel system
INTERESTING: shared name with Soco-Jarel Spaceport on Socorro

NAME: Peragus II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: terrestrial (ancient); half destroyed (hundred of years before 3959 BBY)
INTERESTING: major source of low-grade engine fuel, but nearly completely destroyed hundreds of years before 3959 BBY by earlyattempts of miners to siphon fuel; mining accident blew a massive hole in planet, forming an asteroid field around the world

NAME: Peragus asteroid field
INTERESTING: formation of fuel-rich asteroids created after first attempt to mine fuel from Peragus II resulted in a massive explosion, blowing a huge hole in the planet's crust; Peragus Mining Facility established by 3951 BBY but destroyed when a firefight between the Ebon Hawk and the Harbinger (Hammerhead-class cruiser) ignited the fuel in the asteroid field; no further mining projects attempted

NAME: Peragus Mining Facility
INTERESTING: mining facility established in the asteroid field created when an attempt at mining fuel from Peragus II blew a massive hole in its crust; destroyed when a firefight between the Ebon Hawk and the Harbinger (Hammerhead-class cruiser) ignited the fuel in the asteroid field; no further mining projects attempted

NAME: Notonia system
INTERESTING: home of Notonian mudworms

NAME: Mirial
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: small rebellious militia group from planets in system was imprisoned across different prisons to separate them, with limited success; Mirial joined galactic community sometime prior to 3951; joined Sith Empire during Jedi Civil War but returned to Republic after Malak's death; later triumphed in a war against a neighboring planet thanks to Arwen Cohl (merc); joined CIS, hen controlled by Empire

NAME: Serpine
INTERESTING: known for its gambling palaces; ruled by an "emperor-governor"

NAME: Sagma
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Sagma in 18 BBY, in which Wullf Yularen (Imperial Admiral) and Bannidge Holt (Imperial Captain) defeated the Sikurdian pirates here

NAME: Aldivy
INTERESTING: originally discovered c. 3000 BBY; backwater agriworld located in space previously controlled by Revan's Sith Empire; after New Sith Wars, Aldivy joined Republic aligned with CIS during CW; later granted membership in Empire in exchange for loyalty; Apwar Trigit (agent of Zsinj's empire) destroyed the city of New Oldtown; as of 137 ABY, controlled by Krayt's Empire

NAME: Lubang Major system
INTERESTING: conjectural world; Wedge's assertion that Lubang Minor was nameless suggests its name may be unofficial or hastily named based on another nearby world

NAME: Lubang Major
INTERESTING: conjectural world; Wedge's assertion that Lubang Minor was nameless suggests its name may be unofficial or hastily named based on another nearby world

NAME: Lubang Minor
INTERESTING: tropical world widely considered nameless; during CW a battle stranded BL-1707 (Clone Trooper known as Able); after Yavin, Rebels attempted to establish a listening post here during a mission by Luke, Wedge, Zev Senesca and Arhul Narra; after recruiting Able, they were attacked and driven offworld by Imperial forces

NAME: Camus IV
INTERESTING: sometime prior to Hoth, Han and Chewie vacationed on Camus IV, but Han became seasick while floating among the waves

NAME: Thila
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: major Rebel base here (Thila Command, underground base in mountains); had relatively massive mountains whose peaks could be seen from orbit; Voren Na'al interviewed Luke here shortly after Yavin; c. 8 months ABY, Imperial forces under Kale Roshuir investigated possible Rebel activity here and discovered the abandoned base; Roshuir survived a booby trap explosion set off by his Stormtroopers

NAME: Ferro
INTERESTING: Ferroans: colonized Zonama Sekot in 89 BBY, had pale blue skin, most frmales had white hair but some had black, known for independence and reclusive manner

NAME: Sathiemon
INTERESTING: while pursuing a bounty, Boba Fett attacked and presumed dead by an Imperial hit squad here during Imperial era; Sahiemon's natives used numerous holes and burrows here

NAME: Javarica system
INTERESTING: origin point of Javarican espresso

NAME: Rokaria system
INTERESTING: home of Rokarian dirt-fishes

NAME: Sikurd
INTERESTING: Sikurdians: short, rotund bipeds with prehensile, tentacle-like arms and purple-and-orange skin; when CW ended in 19 BBY, Sikurdian pirates entered an alliance with Tervig and Zygerrian slavers establishing illegal trade routes along Listehol Run and Shaltin Tunnels and raiding the newly reorganized Corporate Sector; origin point of Sikurdian battle-axes

NAME: Gathus
INTERESTING: inhabitants (some of whom were Twi'leks) were so skilled at wiring up security and defense systems that they were commonly hired as security specialists; the local smashball team played against a team from Lafra

NAME: N'ildwab
INTERESTING: inhabitants lived simple lives; Nobam Nol terrorized them, claiming to be a Sith and fooling them with wired gloves that mimicked Force powers; the locals hired Boba Fett to kill Nol, which he did

NAME: Buamlon Central
INTERESTING: dangerous world; claim staked by Barosa Warren (scout serving with Republic Survey Corps)

NAME: Haffrin
INTERESTING: a shrine of Kooroo was built here millennia before GCW using native stone

NAME: Melldia
INTERESTING: in 3950 BBY, Sith Lord Darth Nyriss claimed to be "the destroyer of Melldia"

NAME: Critoki
INTERESTING: Critokians: 2m sentient yellow & black arachnids who used large claws to hunt prey and sometimes found work as bounty hunters; biological makeup featured a complex nervous system and 6 apertures through which they could communicate and breathe, and used hoots and whistles to communicate

NAME: Antared III
INTERESTING: hideout site of Yesgar's pirates during reign of Empire; population: less than 1 M

NAME: Tiss'sharl
INTERESTING: region of space surrounding Tiss'sharl explored between 3000 and 1000 BBY; most of planet was temperate, but Tiss'sharl hailed from the humid, dangerous jungle continents; ruled by Tiss'sharl League (consortium of highest-profit business leaders of previous five years); Tiss'sharl sold diatium power cells to Jedi Council and later Tagge blaster cartridges to Empire; semi-loyal to Empire

NAME: Thela system
INTERESTING: Pride of Thela was named after this system

NAME: Lur
INTERESTING: Lurrians: dangerous wildlife forced them to keep tight family groups; Lur's harsh environment limited technological development so Lurrians mastered flora and fauna, breeding and cloning purposely designed creatures that helped them build cities within glaciers; world was racked by severe storms and high winds; genetic mastery led to Imperial quarantine and made them target of slavers

NAME: Dra III
INTERESTING: high-gravity world with frequent groundquakes, hurricanes and severe storms; home of powerful fauna popular with sport hunters; nashtahs were often used as guard beasts offworld; main export was Kell Mark II heavy assault rifle (powerful but outdated weapon)

NAME: Draethos
INTERESTING: isolated world; Draethos: xenophobic, didn't allow any offworlders, ruled by military dictatorship; located in Sith Space during GCW; raturned to isolation after Malak's death

NAME: Lafra
INTERESTING: Lafrarians: gray-skinned humanoids who lost ability to fly via evolution, built homes in high inaccessible locations such as treetops and high mountainsides; amost citizens owned flying mode of transportation; ground or water travel was rare; planet's smashball team played against Gathus's team; incident involving an improperly maintained CSPL-12 projectile launcher resulted in death of Imperial General Azarin here

NAME: Glakka
INTERESTING: Jabba the Hutt and Ephant Mon once had a gun-running operation here; the two tried to steal an Imperial weapons cache but were ambushed by an Imperial squad, barely surviving the attack; they almost died in the subzero temperatures at night

NAME: Anarak IV
INTERESTING: discovered during Mandalorian Wars; conquered by Mando Neo-Crusaders; fell to Sith Empire during Jedi Civil War; remained independent during Ruusan Reformation, when the tetrarchy claimed total control; remained neutral during CW; a chef from Anarak IV was serving the republic on Drongar, where several Black Sun members commented that if this chef cooked for the tetrarchy of his homeworld he would probably be boiled alive

NAME: Kormoran
INTERESTING: site of Imperial attack, during which TIEs were sent in to clear the road of 90,000 refugees; after the attack, a TIE pilot defected to the Rebellion and became an X-wing pilot

NAME: Naplousea system
NOTES: WP article lacks coords

NAME: Pegg
INTERESTING: Yesgar's pirates spotted in the main spaceports here during GCW; Merrk's Weapons shop was located in main spaceport

NAME: Gigor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: snow-covered mountains, caves, valleys, hot springs
INTERESTING: Gigorans divided into home-clans of around 50 members in 3 to 5 family groups, led by most skillful hunter; Galactic scouts discovered, then ignored Gigor long before Imperial era, when a smuggler group built a secret base, later selling Gigorans as slaves; eventually many Gigorans rounded up by Zygerrian slavers; homeworld of Senna (Kessel mine slave)

NAME: Korriz
INTERESTING: part of Sith Empire before its collapse in 5000 BBY; site of workshop owned by Sith Lord Tritos Nal; agents of the Patron (Sith Lord) traveled here and stole Garu's Warblade (Sith sword Tritos Nal made for Sith Lord Garu); became part of reconstituted Sith Empire by time of Cold War, when a Sith Empire cargo ship was diverted by pirates after departing here

NAME: Athiss
INTERESTING: Sith sanctuary world orbiting binary stars between two other uninhabited worlds ; held sanctuary of Vodal Kressh (renowned Sith alchemist); hot climate with mostly desert terrain, though fields and forests grew atop the sands in some places; small, unexplored ruins dotted the planet but were never properly studied; later site of mysterious cult devoted to Vodal Kressh

NAME: Ziost
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: thickly forested (prior to 27700 BBY) rocky, frozen mountains, glaciers, tundra, polar ice caps, brackish oceans
INTERESTING: quarantined during Republic era; site of ancient Sith ritual altar brought to Grand Republic Medical Facility on Coruscant by 19 BBY; originally thickly forested with fertile climate until arrival of Sith; an ice age leveled most woodlands; many Sith relocated here from Korriban using Rakatan vessels c. 27700 BBY; eventually became Sith buffer world, then forgotten

NAME: Svolten system
INTERESTING: origin point of Svolten rhyolite, a substance that permanently sharpened the edge of a Sith sword, mentioned in the Book fo Sith by Sorzus Syn

NAME: Bhargebba Six
INTERESTING: all life forms on Bhargebba Six began rapidly dying out; individual affiliated with reconstituted Sith Empire visited to obtain biological samples before they were lost forever; Lord Tibris allowed this before carrying out a final extermination of life here

NAME: Ch'hodos
INTERESTING: orbited a red sun; lesser world of Sith Empire; served as central base of Shar Dakhan by 5000 BBY; rally ground for Naga Sadow's forces during preparations to attack Republic; more than 1000 years later, radiation from its star increased, leading to mutations in local desert wildlife

NAME: Savek system
INTERESTING: Sith followers here used amplified lightsabers, which were powerful but highly unstable

NAME: Nfolgai
NOTES: WP article lacks mention of Descri Wris hyperlane
INTERESTING: Sorzus Syn encountered a Mrlssi slave here, burdened with stones and nearly unrecognizable under its soot-slicked feathers; during conflict with Eternal Empire, Hutts were shipping contents of several ammunition storehouses offworld to a safe location

NAME: Begeren
INTERESTING: originally part of Sith Empire, which constructed enormous monuments to notable Sith on the planet's surface, costing lives of an estimated 100 K slaves; claimed by Republic after Empire's defeat in Great Hyperspace War; Republic allowed construction of a gemstone quarry to the detriment of the Sith statues, which fell into ruin; seized by revived Sith Empire in 3678 BBY; site of GCW battle

NAME: Krayiss Two
INTERESTING: considered one of five sacred Sith worlds that formed the heart of the Sith Empire; home to massive library-temple buried and largely forgotten before 14000 BBY, with only its large obelisk remaining aboveground; Vara Nreem (Jedi Knight) traveled here to learn temple's secrets, but deemed unworthy by Sith spirits and killed and made to suffer for eternity

NAME: Kharzet III
INTERESTING: uncharted as of 3 ABY; lush forests home to a variety of plant life and a unique species that was named the long-necked gundark due to its temperament (rather than any physiological similarities); Leia and C-3PO scouted the world as a possible home for a Rebel base after Hoth, but fled after being attacked by long-necked gundarks

NAME: "Mudball"
grid square/sector/half a parsec from Kharzet III
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: muddy barren plains, mud lakes, mountains
INTERESTING: half a parsec from Kharzet III, this unidentified world housed an Imperial base and communications beacon; believing i to be devoid of any Imperial presence, Luke scouted it as a potential Rebel base location, but was ultimately driven offworld by Imperial forces under command of Major Kuhru

NAME: Iliabath
INTERESTING: an insurrection took place here some years before the Second GCW

NAME: Pal Goral
INTERESTING: poor world; native Palarians often recruited to work on Duroon in Corporate Sector, but promised jobs were near-slavery, Palarians forced to mine Duroon's vast resources alongside other indentured species and in turn started a guerilla war against CSA

NAME: Fislan
INTERESTING: Cene Gilvent (Ocsinin near-Human swordsbeing) nearly killed a Rebel recruit under the command of Bren Derlin, who was then convinced of the threat Gilvent posed

NAME: Vyndal
INTERESTING: at some point, a Jedi piloting an Eta 2 interceptor crashed here and was killed; around 4 BBY, Yeleb (Human male) found the Jedi's lightsaber and took it as his own, posing as a Jedi; natives made Yeleb protector of their village; a skirmish later took place between the natives, Yeleb, Kanan Jarrus, the Empire and The Grand Inquisitor

NAME: Vyndal Sta.
INTERESTING: Paramiah Shrove (COMPNOR agent) confiscated spacer's strongbox containing book later known as Smuggler's Guide, later scanned by a DD-13 medical droid here, which came back negative for foreign contaminants; marked down to be returned to owner by Hedge Deviln (Chief Imperial Inspector, who was focused on confiscating spice rather than objectionable literature

NAME: Unidentified overgrown mudball system
INTERESTING: half-a-parsec from Kharzet III

NAME: Joodrudda
INTERESTING: barren, nearly uninhabited world just outside Corporate Sector borders; only point of interest was a sprawling palace constructed hundreds of years before Yavin by a clan of eccentric Hutts

NAME: Beta Olikark
region/grid square/at tip of a galactic arm opposite from Rayter sector

NAME: Xanlanner
INTERESTING: located near the Uziel system

NAME: Corus system
INTERESTING: haven for pirates, smugglers

NAME: Zygerria
INTERESTING: successful slavers' world for thousands of years until Jedi cracked down on slaving operations and its glory faded; flourished again upon collaboration with CIS during CW and during Imperial era; Zygerrians built fortresses and cities atop mesas using slave labor; attracted tourists from as far as Alderaan to see podraces and fortresses of Zygerrian Slave Empire's height

NAME: Zygerria Four
INTERESTING: home of many slave traders during Cold War; underwent orbital bombardment with purpose of driving off slavers; once the slavers left their fortresses, scavengers searched the strongholds for valuable objects left behind

NAME: Kip
INTERESTING: damp mud-ball riddled with caves; source of ulikuo gemstones; in 22 BBY, shortly before CW, Zorba Desilijic Tiure imprisoned here in Girigard (capital) city's Subsurface Correctional Facility; after Endor, Ysanne Isard arranged for pirates to take over and free Zorba

NAME: Baltimn
INTERESTING: Ephaan Kenzon established School of Hidden Wisdom here (only dueling academy to survive CW and rise of Palpatine); pleasant environment but remote location made the world inaccessible for many tourists

NAME: Sevari system
INTERESTING: shared name with Sevari Cabal (colony ship that carried the ancestors of Sevari, humanoid inhabitants of Sevarcos II)

NAME: Sluudren
INTERESTING: Sludir: reptilians with 2 arms, 6 legs, thick armored carapace, had a caste-based feudal system (ruled by warrior caste) until enslaved by Empire

NAME: Irudiru
INTERESTING: Irudiru had at least one city, Kai Pompos; in the final years of the Galactic Civil War, Golas Aram, an architect who had designed prisons for the Empire lived on Irudiru, along with Kanjiklub and Splugorra the Hutt; Han Solo was captured by Aram here

NAME: Sarlucif
INTERESTING: site of a secret outlaw tech base constructed from quickly assembled hangar domes and habitation bubbles, run by Klaus Vandangante and his daughter Jessa; landing field was a large, flat expanse of fusion-formed soil; base had a number of turbolaser emplacements; evacuated in 2 BBY after a Corporate Sector Authority incursion

NAME: Vaynai
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: vast shallow ocean, chain of tropical island mesas, mountains, cliffs
INTERESTING: 110-meter harvester-processor ships harvested teeming sea life, seaweed to make "Slick" -- medicinal substance that induced euphoric delirium; world's only starport constructed on one of its island mesas; corrupt aristocrats built towers atop islands such as Streysel, defended with anti-aircraft weaponry; less fortunate dwelt underground in artificially-created caverns; booming tourism trade

NAME: Malachor
INTERESTING: considered taboo by Mandalorians; known to only have 3 planets, but filled with mass shadows (more than 3 planets' worth, though Malachor V's gravity was particularly strong

NAME: Malachor II
INTERESTING: Sith Empire member; Barden Golah (Imperial Reclamation Service Captain) led an excavation here

NAME: Malachor III
INTERESTING: Sith Empire member even before Mandalorian Wars; burial ground of Terrak Morrhage (Human male Sith Lord, died centuries before Cold War), whose spirit was reawakened by Jedi expedition; Morrhage played with their emotions, drove them insane but they subsequently escaped and reported the planet as "barren" to Jedi Council; Darth Thanaton traveled here to attend to some business

NAME: Malachor IV
INTERESTING: rocky, hellish wasteland shrouded in mystery; site of Great Scourge of Malachor thousands of years before rise of Empire (ancient battle between Sith and Jedi, in which a superweapon petrified all the participants, who remained for thousands of years afterward; smugglers found or forged Sith relics they claimed they found here; site of battle between Ezra, Kanan, Ahsoka, Maul, Inquisitors, Vader

NAME: Malachor V
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fertile (pre-3951 BBY); caverns, crevasses, gorges, jagged rock spires, poison gas vents, sheer cliffs (post-3951 BBY)
INTERESTING: fertile, hospitable prior to final battle of Mandalorian Wars in 3951 BBY; cataclysm caused by the Mass Shadow Generator shattered the planet, resulting in a cracked-open world with unstable gravity, wracked by constant lightning storms and inhabited by monstrous storm beasts; by 3640 BBY surveys showed small pockets of surviving biological life in the remains; sometimes used as a curse word

NAME: Nathema
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fertile agricultural fields (pre-4999 BBY); barren plains (4999 BBY - 3630 BBY); forests (post-3630 BBY), oceans
INTERESTING: fertile agriworld; in 5103 BBY, Dramath (Sith Lord) depoaed by illegitimate son Tenebrae, receiving rulership, title of Lord Vitiate from reigning Dark Lord of the Sith Marka Ragnos; Vitiate's Ritual of Nathema granted him immortality while killing every living thing on the planet and stripping Force from the world; after death of Vitiate's spirit, planet was miraculously revitalized, renewing its forests

NAME: Rekkiad
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ice, snow, glaciers, mountains, frozen wastelands
INTERESTING: before Great Hyperspace War, Dramath the Second (Sith Lord) came here after his half-brother Tenebrae conquered his homeworld of Medriaas; emissary of Vitiate's found, broke into his tomb, taking his remains for Vitiate; Jedi Knights Revan and Malak later hid Mandalore's mask in Dramath's sarcophagus following the Mandalorian Wars, later found by Canderous Ordo and an amnesiac Revan

NAME: Sigil
INTERESTING: Terrak Morrhage (Sith) trained here; source of expensive and dangerous sigil lightsaber crystals; aligned with Sith Empire during Jedi Civil War

NAME: Drahgor III
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: yellow fog, mountain spires, cave networks
INTERESTING: c. 34 ABY, the Gozzo Flix returned to his homeworld to obtain fuel for the Colossus; he and Kazuda Xiono discovered that his cousin Flanx and the rest of his flock had disturbed the legendary Karnex dragons that

NAME: Troiken
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, forests, mountains, plains, rainforests, tundra
INTERESTING: home to raw spice mining operations controlled by Pyke Syndicate; tidally locked, so only a narrow band was inhabitable by humanoids, taken up by mountains and dense forests; Xextos lived in tree villages; c. 17000 BBY, Arkanian scientists visited and promised to take a group of Xexto volunteers to settle a new world, but genetically experimented on them to create the Quermians

NAME: Th'irus
NOTES: info from Th'iruckai could be added to Th'irus WP page
INTERESTING: hot desert world with virtually no surface water; Th'iruckai; short, reptilian bipeds, organized into tribes with a Teruk (king) as leader; warlike with bronze-age tech, vast knowledge of poisons; tribes fought bloody battles over advanced technology brought in by offworlders; a group of smugglers eventually learned about an ancient tribal misunderstanding and tried to mediate a ceasefire

NAME: Kadavo
INTERESTING: cold, ugly, barren world wih thick smoggy atmopshere under control of Zygerrian Slave Empire, which used it to process slaves; had multiple volcanoes, but they were mostly dormant; smoggy atmosphere appeared purplish from space; an abducted Togruta colony, as well as Obi-Wan and Rex were sent here until they could escape with Republic help

NAME: Valtha Divide
INTERESTING: distant space location where a living Teezl (nonsentient, bluish, luminous, swirling creature that could serve as a natural hyperspace communications amplifier) was found and captured by the Empire; Mils Giel (Imperial Admiral) later used the Helmsman (Praetor Mark II-class battlecruiser) to transport it to Coruscant

NAME: Natinati
INTERESTING: one of its main cities was Poborandurannum, where Jabba once rented a secret chamber; population: less than 1 M by 25 ABY

NAME: Loce
INTERESTING: Locans: hulking, muscular, near-Human species with blue skin covered in black spots

NAME: Parthovian Cluster
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Faarlsun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Jun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Zossi Belt
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Weken
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: poisonous atmosphere

NAME: Pochi
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: low mountain ranges, endless dry grassland plains, caves, coastlines with small forests
INTERESTING: Tulvarees: semi-intelligent, tribe-based hunter avians; site of Fortress Baarlos (massive tower constructed 10000 years before GCW by a forgotten group); Faarl (Human pirate, warlord of several planets by age 20) established base here in Fortress Baarlos and provided Tulvarees with food, medicines, commodities in exchange for their service as soldiers; mountains home to grazing herbivores

NAME: Koss
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Calipp
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Braccio system
INTERESTING: shared name with Braccio campaign (conflict insigated by alien warlord Nuso Esva by 8 ABY)

NAME: Pashvi
INTERESTING: nutritional plants and dangerous predatory avians could be found at tops of thousands of rock pillars; native Pashvi were both drawn to and afraid of the pillars; Pashvi created works of art sought-after in the Corporate Sector; Dubrak Qennto had visited a few times by 27 BBY in connection of art trade in Corporate Sector; by 27 BBY, the Pashvi had fallen prey to a Vagaari raid

NAME: Morcanth
INTERESTING: in region disputed by separate starfaring species

NAME: Nirauan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Nirauan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: hills, lakes, jungles, forests, cliffs, canyons, caves
INTERESTING: 2nd of 3 inner planets in system; former Rakata colony; site of ancient fortress known as the High Tower or Hand of Thrawn (built of same black, energy-absorbing stone as the ancient citadel on Hijarna; capital world of the Empire of the Hand; site of a Chiss and Human garrison, including a Thrawn clone awaiting activation; Luke and Mara seriously damaged the base in 19 BBY

NAME: Betal
INTERESTING: origin point of Poraskors (group who reportedly wove neural-web reflex threads by hand

NAME: Kynachi
INTERESTING: in 32 BBY the world was seized by the Trade Federation and Umbrag (Skakoan Overseer) took over the KynachTech factory; TF imposed a frequency jammer and isolated it from the rest of the galaxy; rest of the galaxy assumed the planet had voluntarily isolated itself; planet's captive inhabitants were liberated from KynachTech factory prison in 21 BBY by Republic's Breakout Squad unit

NAME: Endex
INTERESTING: Entymals: sentient hive insectoids (1 fertile queen, many infertile females, rare male drones) with great strength, gliding membranes, piloting skills; during OR pilots trained in canyons for centuries, leaving a lot of wreckage behind; Entymals enslaved under Empire, Pentastar Alignment, and Imperial Remnant

NAME: Ryloon
INTERESTING: site of sseveral Imperial orbital factories where captured prisoners (Entymals?) sent to work; remained part of Imperial Remnant following NR peace agreement

NAME: Churruma
INTERESTING: large deposits of precious metals mined by Empire; Stormtroopers garrisoned here; shaman leader Chrech Estha urged natives to fight Empire and was sent to Kessel; a group of individuals rescued and brought back Estha and his symbolic carved stick, convincing remaining natives to rebel and end Imperial presence

NAME: Marquarra
INTERESTING: Ubiqtorate had weapons cache here; allied with Imperial Remnant

NAME: Kuratooine
INTERESTING: though home to several Galactic Alliance Army bases and a Galactic Alliance embassy, it was not officially part of the GA and maintained its own government and system of laws; Turman Durra and Myri Antilles traveled to the capital of Kura City, disguised as honeymooners, while other members of Wraith Squadron traveled in pairs or threes to set up temporary new HQ for an operation

NAME: Marcelan Prime
INTERESTING: Tempest Force (Imperial legion) saw action here

NAME: Khonji Seven
INTERESTING: site of Imperial testing base; in 1 BBY, ISD Vector sent to transport a virus to the base but never arrived due to outbreak that turned the crew into mindless creatures

NAME: Bid'jerma
INTERESTING: site of Imperial Detention Block; Alliance Special Forces established Outpost Cinder on ridge overlooking the facility in order to recover imprisoned Rebels

NAME: Comra
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: in Outer Rim's "Dead Zone", near Wild Space; headquarters of Drixo the Hutt; later, site of comm relay belonging to Talon Karrde, considered by NR to be closest inhabited world to Chiss Ascendancy or EMpire of the Hand

NAME: Yaga
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Yaga Minor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Darth Desolous and forces lured here and destroyed during Inter-Sith Wars period; Republic member world Outbound Flight launched from; Yagai: insectoids with hive-caste society enslaved during Imperial era; known as important trade world, for starshipbuilding facilities and as site of Ubiqtorate base

NAME: Ompersan
INTERESTING: site of Imperial Navy fleet records center; In Imperial Remnant space

NAME: Prefsbelt IV
INTERESTING: "Prefid's Belt" was constellation visible from Fedje that included Prefsbelt system's star; discovered by Republic citizens fleeing Pius Dea cult in 11,600s BBY; later Renunciate stronghold; secret for millennia, then officially classified Republic Naval Academy at Castle Pradeux; later became Imperial Naval Academy (one of three primary, rivalling Anaxes)

NAME: Borosk
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: fortified as strongpoint against NR in final years of GCW; relatively small world with orbiting ion minefields, planetary shields, turbolasers and ion cannons; near Yaga Minor

NAME: Asteroid Belt / Ring
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Yorgraxx
INTERESTING: 1000+ BBY, Quorlac Fornayh (near-human Sith Lord) traveled here and enslaved natives to build his fortress, then exterminated them; during GCW, Imperial ship crashed here, reawakening Sith spirit; Palpatine sent his Hand Jallar Golin to investigate; Rebel ship in orbit was attacked above planet by Imperials and crashed; survivors of both crashes united to defeat Fornayh's spirit, and Golin arrived and encountered them

NAME: Carlac
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: snowy plains, mountains, forests, pink blossoming trees
INTERESTING: town inhabited by Ming Po culture until enslaved and razed by Death Watch during CW; pink blossom trees sometimes dwarfed humans; Republic later fought to destroy Death Watch camps here

NAME: Ywllandr
INTERESTING: used as chokepoint by CIS during late CW; Plo Koon led Republic Navy strike force against Separatists here during Outer Rim Sieges aboard Courageous

NAME: Reerez
INTERESTING: closely orbited star Malola

NAME: Pergoomi
INTERESTING: closely orbited star Malola

NAME: Mygeeto
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, thick ice, jagged mountains, ice canyons, ice wadi, crevasses, tunnels, cliffs, crystallized glaciation; huge crystal spurs; ice shelves; underground lakes
INTERESTING: locked in ice age; no volcanic activity and cooled internal core; many precious metals, crystals found in crust; few cities, which drew power from synthesized crystals in capacitor towers; InterGalactic Banking Clan enslaved native Lurmen; became sister world of Muunilinst

NAME: Zuborte Ma
INTERESTING: easily navigable asteroid field between Mygeeto and Itzeho; part of Battle of Mygeeto took place here

NAME: Scipio
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, frozen peaks, cliffs, canyons, towering columns, graceful arches, ice, snow
NOTES: confusion about location rseolved with placement in Outer Rim
INTERESTING: Muuns exploited Scipio's geothermal energy; no naturalr esources of note, so Muuns colonized Muunilinst; subjugated under Empire

NAME: Aris
INTERESTING: sector capital; home to Wok-Wok (monkey-like scavanger); no native intelligent life but was colonized; primary language was Bocce; home of Resistance member Byrco Hansid

NAME: Aris
INTERESTING: sector capital; home to Wok-Wok (monkey-like scavanger); no native intelligent life but was colonized; primary language was Bocce; home of Resistance member Byrco Hansid

NAME: Ancathia
INTERESTING: home of Ancathian fungus-flowers

NAME: Morishim
INTERESTING: after Endor, planet was integrated in Pentastar Alignment and later Imperial Remnant; location of secret Imperial comm center in a cave of the High Tatmana peak; after Imperials left, used by the Old Recluse (Imperial Spy) to gather info and indoctrinate population; liberated by NR in 17 ABY; taken by YV; home of wk'ou melon

NAME: Quintus
INTERESTING: profitable spice-smuggling market

NAME: Haverling
INTERESTING: near Morishim; joined NR and provided new shipyards to support NR navy

NAME: Bar Neth
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: formerly desert; terraformed with bountiful farmlands; ochre cliffs, bluffs, canyons
INTERESTING: orbited 5 suns; by 4.3 ABY, world had been terraformed into a "Natural Wonderland"; considered pleasant place to live and appealing to tourists; Star Tours organized trips here under Frontier Vacation Package; climate remained hot and had dust storms; popular attractions included Carl Hodgesville Dude Ranch, camping, safaris, zero-g golf course

NAME: Scipio
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, frozen peaks, cliffs, canyons, towering columns, graceful arches, ice, snow
NOTES: confusion about location rseolved with placement in Outer Rim
INTERESTING: Muuns exploited Scipio's geothermal energy; no naturalr esources of note, so Muuns colonized Muunilinst; subjugated under Empire

NAME: Dibrook Station
INTERESTING: New Republic station; YV established a base here and placed a Yammosk under surface; Heart of Artorias landed here to search for refugees taken by YV following Battle of Dibrook in 25 ABY

NAME: Anemcoro
INTERESTING: terraformed / colonized by Ho'Din from Moltok; after rise of Empire, Anemcoro suffered a war with fighting between two races from neighboring planets; supposedly accidental Imperial turbolaser attack destroyed many cities, caused vast firestorm which desolated the terra-scaped surface; few Ho'Din escaped; later annexed as part of Oversector Outer; eventually part of Pentastar Alignment, then Imperial Remnant

NAME: Sinjan
INTERESTING: site of Rebel base compromised by Imperial espionage droid

NAME: Reynon
INTERESTING: amount of Reynonian dissenters sympathized with Rebel Alliance and lived on Rebel safeworld of Isis; Harovan Toth (Rebel agent) from here and sent his own daughter Samona to live on Isis

NAME: Moskk system
NOTES: appears to be on Entralla Route, but not listed on WP
INTERESTING: had at least two planets (double world?) and two moons; Republic task force used this system as staging area for an attack on Gwori's shipyards, several sectors away

NAME: Oasis? (unidentified volcanic moon)
INTERESTING: Oasis mining colony (hidden inside Maelstrom Nebula) was thriving settlement where Oxite was mined; Riders of the Maelstrom (pirates) and Rebel Alliance had bases here

NAME: Maelstrom Nebula
PARENT: Outer Rim/unknown//Albarrio / Aris, Relgim/Oasis? (unidentified volcanic moon)
INTERESTING: huge green cloud of charged space dust, raw energy; altered navigation coords and fuddled nav computers; starships on the Relgim run had to exit the cloud and navigate at sublight speeds, creating opportunities for pirates such as the Riders of the Maelstrom

NAME: Minashee
INTERESTING: homeworld of Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas, whose father worked as fisherman

NAME: Biitu
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: farm fields, forests, grasslands, strip mines (under Empire)
INTERESTING: low-tech agriworld; Jedi General Traavis led clone forces here during CW; Mungo Baobab discovered valuable fuel source here; Empire dispatched Great Heep to capture Mungo, take control of world and turn it into a wasteland; later became part of Pentastar Alignment, then Imperial Remnant

NAME: Monhudle
INTERESTING: during Outer Rim sieges, Jedi General Traavis led clone forces against CIS here

NAME: Altunna
NOTES: position in Cassander Subsector not listed on WP page

NAME: Vykos

NAME: Rhuvia

NAME: Sestooine
INTERESTING: Imperial world first colonized in Kymoodon Era

NAME: Ord Biniir

NAME: Moltok
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: orbited close to star but ash in atmosphere created a shield that kept out some sunlight, making temperatures tolerable; part of galactic society from at least 5000 BBY; almost faced ecological disaster in 300 BBY when Ho'Din began clearing large swaths of land for new industry, uncovering a plague that was solved with an herbal remedy

NAME: Kalki N.
INTERESTING: treacherous; according to Paige Tico's journal, pirates had built bases in nebula for centuries, from which they organized raids on nearby systems; an old abandoned frigate frigate drifted out of the nebula in 3643 BBY, and an individual boarded and recovered navigational data and some cargo

INTERESTING: treacherous; according to Paige Tico's journal, pirates had built bases in nebula for centuries, from which they organized raids on nearby systems; an old abandoned frigate frigate drifted out of the nebula in 3643 BBY, and an individual boarded and recovered navigational data and some cargo

NAME: Isiring
INTERESTING: capital of Tendrannan subsector; ore-rich mining world; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 12 - 13 ABY

NAME: Mantooine
INTERESTING: colonized during Kymoodon era; Mantooine constantly at war with nearby Fest; natives were xenophobic yet sympathetic to Rebel Alliance; soon before GCW the Mantooine Liberators (local resistance group) successfully captured Imperial base but Imperials immediately retaliated; eventually Mantooine and Fest found common cause against Empire

NAME: Imperial orbital base
INTERESTING: destroyed by Rebels during Operation Cobolt

NAME: Gibbela
INTERESTING: Dazouri: shapeshifters; Imperial officer sent to scout Gibbela for colonization/conquest, encountered Dazouri farmer who shapeshifted into a large ferocious creature and wiped out the Imperial scouts, later repurposing their leftover equipment and weapons as farming tools

NAME: Spefik
INTERESTING: Rebel base here destroyed by Imperial forces in Battle of Spefik ~ 0.5 ABY

NAME: Desolation Sta. Belt
INTERESTING: home to Desolation Station Imperial construction facility

NAME: Desolation St.
INTERESTING: Imperial construction facility used o build Death Star I components; destroyed in mission led by X2 (Rebel operative)

NAME: unknown gas giant
INTERESTING: skimmed close to system's star

NAME: Despayre (Horuz)
INTERESTING: Empire completed Death Star I's construction in orbit using slave labor in surface prison colony, then destroyed planet with three 33 percent shots; system later captured by YV

NAME: Haroon
INTERESTING: likely destroyed when Despayre was obliterated by Death Star I

NAME: Nam'ta
INTERESTING: bands of red, ornage and white clouds; inhabited during Galactic War between Republic and reseurgent Sith Empire; governed locally; later part of Pentastar Alignment

NAME: Zeffliffl
INTERESTING: Zeffliffl: resembled lumps of dark green or blue-black seaweed, evolved in southern hemisphere continent's salt water seas; established contact with wider galaxy prior to 14 ABY

NAME: Hethar
INTERESTING: colonists used local gornts (omnivorous creatures) as staple of diet; Empire annexed shortly before Yavin and instituted gorn breeding and processing program for meat supplies for Imperial navy

NAME: Atrivis
INTERESTING: may refer to same world as Atrivis 7; Rebel pilot shot down here and was pursued by Imperial Storm commandos before stealing a ship and escaping

NAME: Generis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, grasslands, jungle, rivers, rapids, rugged terrain
INTERESTING: high gravity; population ~2000; natural beauty attracted offworld travelers seeking wilderness; no major cities; later captured by Thrawn, recaptured by NR, then largely destroyed by YV

NAME: Generis orbital base
INTERESTING: base for leadership of Atrivis Resistance Group, occupying long-abandoned space station; Treaty of Generis signed here

NAME: Atrivis 7
INTERESTING: domestic conflicts called range wars fought here; homeworld of Sheeka Tull, who became resistance fighter with guerilla group Desert Wind on Ord Cestus during CW

NAME: Gree Baaker
INTERESTING: Imperial labor camp; some prisoners from here ended up on Death Star

NAME: Iridium
INTERESTING: home to infamous Pirates of Iridium, who used Iridium "power gems" to disable ships' shields, raiding Atrivis spacelines for a year; Jedi and Republic Judicials routed pirates over Vuchelle in 22 BBY

NAME: Shar'Ack
INTERESTING: Shaliz'Na: humanoid avians, produced many artisans, preferred to use locally-produced chemically-propelled slugthrowers in combat; by GCW, Empire controlled all liquor produced on and imported to Shar'Ack; Empire enslaved Shaliz'Na, so many became addicted to alcohol

NAME: Vuchelle
INTERESTING: appeared orange-colored from orbit; site of attempted negotiations between Jedi-led Republic task force and Pirates of Iridium; fell within Pentastar Alignment borders between 4 - 12 ABY, Imperial Remnant between 12 - 13 ABY

NAME: Devon Four
INTERESTING: several years before CW, government (members of a religious sect) refused to pay Republic taxes and subsequently the Republic embargoed them, which prevented even medicine from being delivered during a plague outbreak; smugglers led by Sheeka Tull (whose sister lived on Devon Four) later broke the embargo to save the populace

NAME: Fest
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban; frozen plains, snowy hills, icy valleys, steep-ridged mountains
INTERESTING: densely populated, few wilderness areas; climbing tournament held here during Cold War; CIS set up research center here during CW; during GCW Fest was ravaged by both civil war and war against Mantooine; conflict prevented them from warning Mantooine about Imperial reprisal, which in turn later led them to combine forces with Mantooine to form Atrivis Resistance Group

NAME: Fedje
INTERESTING: home to many exotic creatures, including folded ear boosqueak (arboreal creature); refugees fled from Fedje to Prefid's Belt during Pius Dea Era; an Imperial intelligence agent saboteur made use of the typical expansive hand gestures of Fedje's Betreasley region to impersonate an exotic pet salesman from Fedje

NAME: Ajara
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where in the Galaxy Are the Worlds of The Rise of Skywalker (FanthaTracks.com)/
INTERESTING: situated in partially explored region of space off the Celanon Spur; strong magnetic field shielded Ajan Kloss from cosmic radiation; gas giant reflected sunlight onto moon's surface, allowing many plants to gain some sustenance even at night

NAME: Ajan Kloss
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where in the Galaxy Are the Worlds of The Rise of Skywalker (FanthaTracks.com)/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, jungles, cliffs, valleys, grottos, caves, oceans
INTERESTING: charted by Alderaanian scouts who hid existence from Imperial Senate because it was short-listed as possible home for a secret Rebel base, though not used until time of Resistance; Luke and Leia traines here after Endor; mission to Exegol launched from here

NAME: Ketaris
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: University of Ketaris based here; major trade center; planet colonized in unsuccessful bid to establish trading rival to Ord Mantell; joined CIS during CW; became Imperial fortress world after Endor; joined NR in 8 ABY; attacked by Thrawn in 9 ABY but stayed under NR control, one of the only NR worlds in New Territories; eventually joined Imperial Remnant, was site of one of GCW's last battles

NAME: Akuria II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Scum & Villainy: Case Files, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: site of Imperial base prior to destrucion of Death Star I; Imperials hunted Akurians without realizing they were intelligent; Imperials defeated by Rebel force led by Colonel Odan; Rebels considered a base here but chose Yavin 4 instead

NAME: Harrod's Planet
INTERESTING: housed base of Imperial Oplovis Sector Fleet during GCW; after Rebel attack in Yuvern system, Sector Fleet withdrew to Harrod's Planet and spent six months in covering range of its base until being deployed by Atrivis system by 2 ABY

NAME: Yuvern
INTERESTING: Yuvernians: snake-like, two-headed

NAME: Sronk
INTERESTING: during Thrawn campaign, defenses were beaten by 7 Imperial Dreandaught-class heavy cruisers; Sronk advised caution to NR Senate when Thrawn appeared to return in 19 ABY

NAME: Vosteltig Shipyards
INTERESTING: Empire maintained shipyards; Ten Dorne (Sluissi engineer who deserted from Rebels years before) stationed here

NAME: Oplovis
INTERESTING: homeworld of Gaen Drommel (Imperial admiral, later Imperial warlord); origin point of Oplovis linens (fine textile); Oplovian love poems by Simu Zanthe were a part of classic literature

NAME: Gondagali
INTERESTING: first planet attacked with MS-19 shield buster during NR era

NAME: Gandolo IV
INTERESTING: shortly before 1 BBY, several dozen fugitive Wookiee slaves including Chewbacca attempted to establish safe colony here but Bossk, paid in advance by Imperial sector governor, attemped to recapture them; Solo returned to find Wookiees captured and landed the Falcon on Bossk's ship, allowing them to escape in the chaos

NAME: Chabosh
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Chabosh where Sith Lord Tulak Hord and Khem Val led the Sith Empire to victory over Jedi forces by performing a ritual allowing him to draw on the strength of his enemies; Captain Harsh aboard ISD Cauldron wiped out a small rebel base here during GCW

NAME: Hazzard
INTERESTING: homeworld of Boo Rawl

NAME: Tellik Four Sta.
INTERESTING: Site of Inferno Squad mission to recover Bokk Naarg, a defecting partisan.

NAME: Horn Station
NOTES: Horn Station System could be added to list of systems in Lahara sector
INTERESTING: backwater world neglected by Republic until Jedi nicknamed "Pinky" liberated planet from Shoto Eyefire (Defel crimelord, blastfighter); unidentified Horn Station species: hulking, green-skinned reptilians

NAME: Agamar
INTERESTING: Dooku ordered CIS general Kalani to retreat from Onderon to Agamar garrison base following defeat on Onderon; during GCW, Spectres confronted Kalani on Agamar and eventually teamed up to defeat Empire

NAME: Oorn Tchis
INTERESTING: human-inhabited; exported colorful fabrics and rare ore used in guidance system design; joined CIS in 22 BBY; eventually became part of Empire

NAME: Chrellis
INTERESTING: after foundation of Rebel Alliance in 2 BBY, Alliance High Command's first base was established on Chrellis planetoid but when Empire reallocated sector fleets, the Chrellis base ended up uncomfortably close to Imperial Navy activity and the rebels moved their base to Brigia in Tion Cluster

NAME: unnamed asteroid
INTERESTING: in notorious incident, a team of G2 repair droids stole a fueling freighter and established their own community on Chrellis system's asteroid

NAME: Kebolar
INTERESTING: Republic set up farms here for colonists they needed to remove from Qiilura

NAME: Gaddria
INTERESTING: origin point of Gaddrian ambassador (leader of Imperial Senate faction sympathetic to Rebel Alliance

NAME: Cowl Crucible
INTERESTING: ships often suffered unexpected hyperspace reversions when passing too close to the crucible, becoming stranded; just before Lahara sector seceded, 4 Subpro C-73 Trackers (backed by a Corellian freighter) strafed the Space Rescue Corp patrol cutter Iron Tether as it passed near the Lahara sector border on a patrol, forcing the cutter to take refuge in the Crucible, exposing the crew to dangerous radiation

NAME: Pas'sic
INTERESTING: world was involved in Vrassh slaughter, but as of 19 ABY neither Pas'sic gov't nor NR had compensated survivors, despite requirements of Pas'sic law

NAME: Argo-6
INTERESTING: a family of sentients lived here who maintained miniature farms within their mouths, which their molecular dentist discovered during a routine visit

NAME: M2934738
INTERESTING: sparse star system on hyperlane between Liinade III and NR; site of Battle of M2934738 in 9 ABY

NAME: Shaum Hii
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: population: 100 - 500 M (25 ABY); Kian'thar: rode bentails, herded derlacs for meat; discovered 300 BBY; in 297 BBY natives began developing strong Black Sun ties; in CIS space during CW; had diret representation in NR; conquered by YV

NAME: Bakisian Drift
INTERESTING: notoriously perilous nebulosity that prevented exploration of Tragan Cluster until ~300 BBY, until group of Shistavanen scouts charted the sector; convoy owned by Twin Suns Transport Services lost a GR-75 here, which attracted scavengers when word got out

NAME: Maxet system
INTERESTING: shared name with Maxet Intitute of Technology

NAME: Ord Traga
INTERESTING: possibly location of Imperial base

NAME: Tinuvia system
INTERESTING: location of Tinuvian tar pits

NAME: Abar-12
NOTES: non-canon but Abar system listed in EA appendix
INTERESTING: Oeklass went to Cylinder 14 in Vemu on Abar-12 after stealing a boat on Mistar-5

NAME: Corvis Minor
INTERESTING: system had unremarkable history; most Imperial libraries had a blaster hidden in a box disguised as a datacard set titled The Complete History of Corvis Minor

NAME: Corvis Minor III
INTERESTING: produced some exotic xenobiological luxury products within and outside Ciutric Hegemony

NAME: Corvis Minor IV
INTERESTING: produced some exotic xenobiological luxury products within and outside Ciutric Hegemony; guarded by Victory-Class Star Destroyer Aspiration

NAME: Corvis Minor V
INTERESTING: gray-orange gas giant near asteroid belt

NAME: Liinade IIII
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, light industrial, agricultural fields, valleys, snow
INTERESTING: agriworld; development began near end of Galactic Republic and continued under Empire; light industry produced comlinks, caf synthesizers; fell to NR in 9 ABY during Battle of Liinade III; capital of Valleyport was comm and transport nexus and contained spaceport

NAME: Liok
INTERESTING: archaeologists discovered Shadow Traproom here (considered one of the greatest discoveries of post-Ruusan Reformation era

NAME: Ciutric IV
INTERESTING: located at hub of trade routes; subject to frequent, brief periods of torrential downpour; had small shipyard; capital: Daplona (by 980 BBY); Darth Bane lived here for several years with his apprentice Darth Zannah

NAME: Binquaros
NOTES: missspelled once in WP article
INTERESTING: following CW, many CIS forces retreated to Binquaros; became Separatist stronghold; besieged by Imperial forces led by General Hurst Romodi; siege eventually broken by merc, pirate reinforcements (Battle of Binquaros); Separatists fled to Unknown Regions

NAME: New Holgha
INTERESTING: known for Five Holy Cities (had tall buildings, based around a large marketplace); easily conquered by Yuuzhan Vong after NR relocated defense force to Pedd 4, not believing Mandalorian intelligence on an upcoming attack to be trustworthy

NAME: Aar
INTERESTING: reptilian sentients often employed as enforcers by Hutts

NAME: Vrosynri 8
INTERESTING: minor world in Ciutric Hegemony

NAME: Nijune
INTERESTING: origin point of Nijune Treasure Fleet

NAME: Ramoa
INTERESTING: Ramoans: bulky, green-skinned, with pig-like snouts and tusks; homeworld of Bazel Warv (Ramoan Jedi Knight); wrecked by YV; an effort was made to relocate the Ramoans after the war

NAME: Portminia system
INTERESTING: shared name with Portminian (starship)

NAME: Esooma
INTERESTING: Esoomians: considered among best hired muscle in galaxy; quarantined by Empire until around 7 ABY, after which Esoomians could leave and find work;

NAME: Thaylia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Thaylian bog-slime (possibly a type of slime or algae, used as an insult)

NAME: Jargridia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Jargridian Brandy (beverage)

NAME: Asher III
INTERESTING: Rebels maintained cell on Asher III; when Delt Nerris (pilot sympathetic to Alliance) hicjacked CorSec starship Nova Whisper, it was turned over to Rebels and used as medical transport; shortly before Hoth, Empire eliminated Rebel cell and Lernik De'Yago (Rodian arms dealer) stole Nova Whisper and used it to escape

NAME: New Agamar
INTERESTING: high-gravity; at least one native was enlisted in Republic military by late CW

NAME: Sprizen
INTERESTING: by 3705 BBY, system was at endpoint of Sprizen End Run hyperlane, which connected it to Vinsoth system; almost 3000 years later, the majority of that route had become part of Salin Corridor; at some point before 3681 BBY, Sprizen system participated in Celanon-Sprizen Negotiation (dispute mediated by Jedi Consulars), which was settled in favor of Celanon traders; dispute reopened after trade boundaries shifted due to Great Galactic War

NAME: Salin
INTERESTING: part of Kwa holdings during Pre-Republic era; with rise of Rakata, Salin was annexed and Kwa were decimated and driven back to Dathomir

NAME: Abafar
INTERESTING: lightly populated; a massive desert here was called The Void; light here was strangely twisted by the properties of the regolith so there were no shadows; CIS set up mining installation in settlement of Pons Ora; during Imperial Era, Jabba had a drilling platform here to mine rhydonium; sister world Adrafar followed four months behind in same orbit

NAME: Adrafar
INTERESTING: followed in same orbit as Abafar, but four months behind

NAME: Aefao
INTERESTING: remote (on other side of galaxy from Nar Shaddaa); discovered between 5000 & 1000 BBY by Republic; part of Sith Space until New Sith Wars; quickly seceded curing CW; joined Empire, Thrawn, Imperial Remnant

NAME: Vinsoth
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, grassy plains, mountains, polar ice caps
INTERESTING: 7 continents; Chevin had tough skin that could adapt to varied environments; in 3,000,000 BBY an asteroid hit Vinsoth, destroying most life, but remaining survivors evolved into Chevin (nomadic pastoralists who kept Chev as slaves in small farming and manufacturing villages

NAME: Keeper's World
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, jungles, plains, mountains, rivers, coastlines, caves, varied (mostly temperate) terrain
INTERESTING: inhabited by The Keeper, a massive computer/artificial intelligence tasked by its makers with restoring the planet; the Keeper's makers were pacifists who had fled an ancient pan-galactic war but were expected to return someday; The Keeper could cause or remove sudden groundquakes or lava geysers with the aim or scaring off outsiders

NAME: Priole Danna system
INTERESTING: origin point of Priole Danna Festival (celebration of music, parades, dramatic reenactments helf annually on Lamuir IV)

NAME: Isen
INTERESTING: highly radioactive, still-forming; system in birth throes with endless sea of rock

NAME: Isen
INTERESTING: young still-forming gas giant

NAME: Isen IV
INTERESTING: airless, rocky moonlet; location of Void Demons' pirate base; population: 500

NAME: Ethrani system
INTERESTING: home of Ethrani orobouros (creature)

NAME: Veil Nebula
INTERESTING: inhabited by giant neebay; no hyperroutes ran through it; Harko Station located within

NAME: Valahari
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, rivers, canyons, dense tree groupings
INTERESTING: famed for building some of the best ships in the galaxy; claimed neutrality in CW but gave advanced ships to CIS that gave them an edge; blockade by Republic after refusing to take Republic's side

NAME: Altyr V
INTERESTING: CIS-allied during CW; Clone commander Deviss and his forces destroyed a CIS ion cannon here and retook world; as Empire destabilized after Endor, NR was able to establish base here; in 10 ABY Dark Empire began assault on world while Kyle Katarn and Mara Jade were present; Katarn destroyed two asteroid weapons and learned of an Imperial presence on Dromund Kaas

NAME: Ootoola
INTERESTING: theocratic monarchy led world before 33 BBY, but a rebellion arose then that deemed the king impure, overthrew and killed king and his wife; Purists took control, naming the Revolutionary Purist Council the ruling class, but the Princess Foolookoola escaped to Dur Sabon; Vilmarh Grahrk destroyed revolutionaries in capital building, and princess reestablished royal house and took the throne

NAME: Dur Sabon
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: vast oceans, cities on stone platforms jutting out of water on columns
INTERESTING: Princess Foolookoola lived here after fleeing her home planet of Ootoola

NAME: Edusa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: considered to be in Ciutric Hegemony; in CIS space during CW; target of Kavil's Corsairs; conquered by YV

NAME: Camden
INTERESTING: Snakes' Den starport located here; the alien informant known as "Eyes" operated out of the Jade Simian (restaurant & bar) inside the spaceport

NAME: Vandyne
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: considered to be in Ciutric Hegemony; in CIS space during CW; target of Kavil's Corsairs; conquered by YV

NAME: Nichen
INTERESTING: the Kettemoor jumped here after its encounter with the Teljkon Vagabond

NAME: Galloa II
INTERESTING: Wind Dancers: nonhuman, noted for gracefulness

NAME: Hexus system
INTERESTING: CW battle occurred here; at least one planet, possibly gas giant here

NAME: Clysm system
INTERESTING: shared name with Clysm Fleet (commanded by CIS General Calli Trilm)

NAME: Rivvidu
INTERESTING: Boba Fett once chased a female Iotran mark here and afterwards acquired his Silver Speeder; planet's Imperial governor employed a Kubaz spy

NAME: Samarine system
grid square/sector/7 kiloparsecs from Damualer Triac
INTERESTING: located 7 kiloparsecs from Damualer Triac

NAME: Axxila
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: described as an inside-out Coruscant and a "jail where the inmates are in control"; notable spice-smuggling system; homeworld of Admiral Firmus Piett; part of Ciutric Hegemony; when Hegemony joined CIS, many Axxilans (known as Free Axxilans) relocated to Halmad; home to a Kavil's Corsairs base

NAME: Nez Peron
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: agriworld of farming collectives; homeworld of powerful D'Asta family; controlled by Sith Empire during Cold War; in Seperatist space during CW; capital of D'Astan sector during GCW; people of Nez Peron endured starvation under Empire; years after Endor, Baron Ragez D'Asta seceded from Crimson Empire; returned to Imperial Remnant under condition of Pellaeon considering truce with NR

NAME: Thesme
INTERESTING: lackluster capital of Thesme sector; before CW, Thesme was represented in Galactic Senate by Silya Shessaun (ally of Padme), who was often called upon to return home to mediate territorial disputes in the sector; during GCW, a bounty was posted here for Marko Tyne (Zygerrian slaver); shortly after Endor, Leia visited here to pay her respects to former senator Shessaun, who was dying

NAME: Feriae
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Korfin
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Feriae Junction
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Gordian Reach listed as hyperlane; shouldn't it be Junction-Tierell Loop (of Gordian Reach?)
INTERESTING: tradeworld; located in CIS space during CW; tourism flourished briefly during a boom in demand for COrusca gems from Yavin 4; a Hutt-controlled company was located here and maintained an account for transferring funds from the shipping magnate Brevis Taug to the Thanda (Zygerrian) clan; C-3PO saved luke from being killed by Beilert Vlance here; after Endor, integrated in Zsinj's Empire

NAME: Moraices
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ios
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Serenno
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, rainforests, misty rivers, mountains, savannas, desert wastes, oceans
INTERESTING: known for aristocracy, resistance to authority; captured by Sith Forces under Malgus c. 3661 BBY; in 52 BBY, caught in dispute with Celanon over placement of hyperwave transcievers that would disrupt existing hyperroutes, exposing Serennian ships to greater tariffs; Dooku tested bounty hunters here in Moralo Eval's Box; even after CW, shadowy interests here backed Seperatist holdouts

NAME: Cinnatar
INTERESTING: ruled by a Republic governor

NAME: Sorrus
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: sprawling urban; mountain ranges, large deserts
INTERESTING: three capitals, one of which was Yinn La Hi (located near Arra Desert); Sorrusians: xenophobic; Jenna Zan Arbor once had a scientific lab here

NAME: Hynah
INTERESTING: thriving industrial world; vast cosmopolitan population drawn from many species across the galaxy

NAME: Endymion
