INTERESTING: c. 3660 BBY it was involved in Great Galactic War; according to Darth Malgus's personal journal, Sith troops were moved from here, but no more is known since the next part of the journal was cut out; also site of a skirmish

NAME: Tyshapahl
INTERESTING: site of some peaceful demonstrations during early days of Rebel Alliance; regional Moff of sector sent ships to disperse crowds, but they refused and the Imperial commander ordered his ships to hover above the crowds and incinerate them with their engines; family of Tedris Bjalin was among the dead

NAME: Teevan
INTERESTING: homeworld of Tru Veld

NAME: Pho Ph'eah system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: relied on its heavy natural geothermal energy to provide heat to native lifeforms; Pho Ph'eahians: four-armed, naturally adept with technology, developed nuclear fusion and limited spaceflight on their own; once held by Rakatan Infinite Empire; turned into a hub of technological development in years after contact with the Republic (between 5000 and 3000 BBY); fell within CIS space during CW

NAME: Pho Ph'eah system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: relied on its heavy natural geothermal energy to provide heat to native lifeforms; Pho Ph'eahians: four-armed, naturally adept with technology, developed nuclear fusion and limited spaceflight on their own; once held by Rakatan Infinite Empire; turned into a hub of technological development in years after contact with the Republic (between 5000 and 3000 BBY); fell within CIS space during CW

NAME: Pho Ph'eah
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: relied on its heavy natural geothermal energy to provide heat to native lifeforms; Pho Ph'eahians: four-armed, naturally adept with technology, developed nuclear fusion and limited spaceflight on their own; once held by Rakatan Infinite Empire; turned into a hub of technological development in years after contact with the Republic (between 5000 and 3000 BBY); fell within CIS space during CW

NAME: Athus Klee
INTERESTING: Dexter Jettster traveled here during reign of Empire and discovered an ore hub operated by Crimson Dawn (criminal syndicate), whose workers had been cybernetically altered by Dr. Evazan; Jettster rescued a Rodian worker and reported it to Imperial Senate's Council of Labor Abuses; there was a spaceport city with a Spacer's District

NAME: Durollia
INTERESTING: during GCW, Yesgar's pirates were spotted in the main spaceports of Durollia

NAME: M'Bardi
INTERESTING: waterworld; site of M"Bardi Prison during CW; population: at least 300 (prisoners)

NAME: Gaftikar
INTERESTING: sometime before the Galactic War, the Brig Stompers (mercenaries) wiped out planet's entire defense force during a coup; during CW, Omega Squad was stationed here for some time; site of battle of Gaftikar; Omega Squad speculated Republic was attacking to help Shenio Mining; Human inhabitants hired reptilian Marits to build cities but afterwards exiled them to the forests in (unfounded) fear they would rise up against Humans; population: 500 M

NAME: Tandun III
INTERESTING: youthful planet occupying a young star system; originally surveyed c. 12,293 BBY on an expedition from Ord Mantell; lush and beautiful; ruins of ancient population centers believed constructed by Rakata; Republic Group brought the Insignia of Unity here, later forgotten in a warehouse for 60 years; Vongforming severely disrupted atmopshere; later erupted and destroyed in 43 ABY

NAME: Toprawa system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Toprawa system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Toprawa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: homeworld of Sila Kott (Rebel pilot, died at Endor), in whose name a flight school was established here; remote; Ansharii Caverns were site of a battle between Jedi and Exar Kun's Sith Empire; during Cold War, a failed experiment destroyed a lab complex here; in CIS space during CW; known for its community of Antarian Rangers; homeworld of Tyria Sarkin Tainer; DS superlaser developed here

NAME: Shenio system
INTERESTING: shared name with Shenio Mining (company)

NAME: Simpla
NOTES: EA lists as O-5; Gordian Reach map shows P-5

NAME: Simpla-12
NOTES: EA lists as O-5; Gordian Reach map shows P-5; WP article strangely written
INTERESTING: neglected, underdeveloped planet; strip-mined; criminal-infested; Jenna Zan Arbor had a lab here where she performed her twisted experiments on Jedi; home of Cholly, Weez, Tup (thieves); home of Ona Nobis (bounty hunter); capital: Sim-First (buildings had poor foundations and sank into mud, not much police presence, population dense)

NAME: Kho Nai
INTERESTING: Khotta: had ability to alter their perspective of the world around them

NAME: Feswe Prime
INTERESTING: barren system; unstable red giant given to periodic flares, stellar eruptions; after Alliance scouts blazed a stable but dangerous route from Feswe corridor to Hynah, Luke used the Force to lead the Alliance Fleet past Feswe Prime, and Admiral Griff's task force was destroyed when they came out of hyperspace into the Executor's shields, allowing the Rebels to escape

NAME: Feswe Minor system
INTERESTING: lifeless system on route between Feswe corridor and Feriae Junction, a stopping point for Rebel ships running the blockade of Yavin that was cut off during Rebels' attempt to evacuate Yavin 4

NAME: Feswe Corridor
NOTES: on Feriae System WP page, listed as a belt in that system, but in Feswe Corridor page, listed as own system (EA confirms)
INTERESTING: uninhabited star system full of closely-packed asteroids that made navigation difficult; named after Feswe (Rebel scout who blazed a hyperlane from Ladarra to Feswe Corridor; system used by Rebels to smuggle supplies from Feriae Junction to Yavin 4, avoiding Imperial blockade of Gordian Reach; Executor later damaged by Millennium Falcon afer its shields were disabled with a Power gem

NAME: Saarn
INTERESTING: used for military training by Alliance, later a NR remote surveillance post; attacked in a hit-and-fade by ISD Stormhawk at beginning of Thrawn campaign, which wiped out New Republic personnel; Thrawn's forces set up a listening post there to protect Imperial Navy movements

NAME: Daluba
NOTES: Daluba misspelled once in WP article
INTERESTING: ruled by Tonkoss Rathba (tyrant) until he was thwarted by Leia during time of NR

NAME: Kushibah
INTERESTING: homeworld of Ikrit (Kushiban Jedi Master); Kushiban: mainly farmers, weavers famed for textiles incorporating silkweed and fur brushed daily from their coats, woven into cloth and tapestries in a wide variety of colors; home of xinkra (3m tall predators feared by other native species)

NAME: Mogoshyn
INTERESTING: run-down industrial world

NAME: Asusto
INTERESTING: small forested world; Presagers of Hakotei led Jedi Master Lene Kostana and her Padawan Sifo-Dyas into a trap here by tricking them into following a supposed trail for Sith artifacts from Karazak (Sujimis Sector)

NAME: Tamsis Nebula
INTERESTING: contained the planet Asusto

NAME: Betshish
INTERESTING: Lile Gorsek (scout) discovered the world but had to abandon his claim when sentient species discovered upon landing; interdicted by Empire yet it escaped exploitation

NAME: Kli'aar
INTERESTING: Kli'aari: four-armed species largely known for mechanical skills, whose enclaves could be found on planets around the Gordian Reach

NAME: Marrovia
INTERESTING: agriworld known for native Marrovian pig (hardy, fatty swine fed in huge numbers in giant farms and processed in many rendering stations; due to this, planet's smell was considered appalling

NAME: Ladarra
INTERESTING: New Hope Settlement located here; colonized during Old Republic, became a failed chromium mine; by time of Empire, people were dying out, leaving poor farmers, hermits, fugitives; Boba Fett traveled here to settle some personal business with the Storyteller (an old mark who fled here and took a new identity to entertain kids)

NAME: Krylon
INTERESTING: dominant planet of Pinooran Spur, but not very important in its region of space; polluted industrial world dominated by Hynese companies

NAME: Glade
INTERESTING: polluted industrial world; had acidic rains that rusted machinery within weeks

NAME: Lapez 3
INTERESTING: Luke confronted Reist (nightmare demon) here

NAME: Ord Radama
INTERESTING: homeworld of Wan Sandage (Devlikk podracer); most marshes and wetlands paved over with cities; conquered by Neo-Crusaders during Mandalorian Wars; later aligned with Sith Empire; a stricken Harrower-class dreadnaught fell on capital of Livien Magnus, destroying it during Great Galactic War; Empire took world as a staging post for pacifying Outer Rim; native Devlikks enslaved

NAME: Radama Void
INTERESTING: area of space surrounding Ord Radama

NAME: Droxine
INTERESTING: nightmare demons: intelligent, telepathic killers with small, fur-covered bodies and a hairless head that resembled a skull, who were supposedly eradicated by CW but some survived; one such being, Reist, was forced to work for the Empire and sent by Altin Wuho (Human Replica Droid) to kill Luke on Lapez 3, but Luke killed Reist with his lightsaber

NAME: Thule
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rocky plains, rich savannas, blackened hills, hollowed canyons
INTERESTING: dry, arid Force nexus steeped in the Dark Side; originally part of Xim's Empire; colonized by members of the Sith species in 6900 BBY; hidden Sith fortress world for most of its history; isolation allowed it to survive fall of Sith Empire in Great Hyperspace War; roughly a century prior to rise of Palpatine, Sith priests began receiving visions of Sith ascendancy; Palpatine scrubbed all records of Thule

NAME: Sivvi
INTERESTING: an asteroid captured by Thule's gravity and became its moon; often referred to simply as Thule Moon; Sih established a military training facility here c. 4000 BBY, using the moon's natural caves and tunnels to practice zero-G maneuvers; during CW, housed a planetary shield generator (destroyed by Anakin) to protect a CIS base on Thule, which was then assaulted by the Republic

NAME: Drezzi
INTERESTING: ruled by monarchy; st some point prior to 3954 BBY, Sith Empire conquered world; husband of Queen Ressa was killed by Dark Councilor Darth Nyriss; Ressa sent a decorative holoproection to the Sith Lord in gratitude for Nyriss' decision to spare her life and those of her children; Rane Kovach (intelligence operative) carried out task here to infiltrate dissident groups at the request of Theron Shan

NAME: Kursid
INTERESTING: Kursid natives: primitive humanoids whose sole contact with outer galaxy was through training missions conducted to the planet by the Order of the Sith Lords (beginning 654 BBY); many centuries before fall of the Republic, Kursid was deleted from Republic records; Sith came here to train by attacking natives; nevertheless a cult centered on periodic returns of sky visitors developed

NAME: Corbos
INTERESTING: rich in ores; had "Black Rain Seasons" during which whole sections of the planet became uninhabitable due to massive thunderstorms; in 6900 BBY it was site of Battle of Corbos, in which Dark Jedi lost and abandoned their Force-mutated Leviathans; afterwards, groups of colonists attempted to settle planet every few hundred years, but were always mysteriously wiped out (by Leviathans)

NAME: Odacer-Faustin
INTERESTING: heavy snow, high winds buffeted the world, which hosted a Sith academy founded by Darth Drear during the Cold War; Darth Scabrous kept a secret laboratory at the very top of the enormous black tower at the academy's center; Scabrous unlocked the secrets of Drear's holocron, which held the ingredients for a potion to grant immortality but which actually killed and zombified the subject

NAME: XV-344H
sector/route from Jaga's Cluster to Daragon Trail en route to Ord Radama
INTERESTING: while trying a shortcut from Jagomir in the Jaga Cluster to the Daragon Trail and then up an Imperial shipping lane to Ord Radama to catch a Rebel traitor, a hyperjump brought the Ardan resistance perilously close to this red dwarf star

NAME: Jaga's Cluster
INTERESTING: Cassus Fett led Mandalorians in annihilation of a major Republic force here in 3961 BBY

NAME: Jagomir
INTERESTING: humid, atmosphere sometimes uncomfortable to breathe; planet had 30 continents divided by number of deep seas; nearly 75% of surface was swampland; world of dangers (diseases, venomous or predatory animals, sinkholes, thick mist; home of azurdactyls (semi-sentient four-winged reptavians distantly related to thrantas and aiwha

NAME: Mannova
INTERESTING: industrial dumping ground: Mannovans: sardonic gray-furred species seemingly unruffled by ecological disaster; mountains of junk were picked over by scavengers; fighting after Battle of Yavin made fortunes here as scavengers hauled wrecked ship parts and equipment here in bulk

NAME: Troos
INTERESTING: wild, forested world on edge of Radama Void, home to a dizzying variety of arthropods; home of armored crebik (predatory, had thick, heavy shells, hunted other arthropods by hanging from trees and dropping onto prey to crush them) and Bahl flies

NAME: Wetyin's Colony
INTERESTING: dry agriworld settled by colonists from Setor c. 10 BBY, bringing freighters loaded with grain seed and nerf embryos; later largely abandoned due to Empire's shifting ministries' budgets; colonists continued searching for a new homeworld, investigating Betshish and Yavin 4 (shortly after Battle of Yavin); space around Wetyin's Colony incorporated into Zsinj's empire until his death in 8 ABY

NAME: The Roil
INTERESTING: rich star-filled nebula, largely unnavigable except for Korphir Trace, which connected the Loop Worlds with the Back Reach

NAME: Atorra
INTERESTING: B'trillans migrated here, giving rise to a sparsely populated agritultural colony; by 43 ABY, decades of drought had ruined the colony; it was rumored that an ancient battle had resulted in crash landing of alien starships in the badlands

NAME: Elamposnia
INTERESTING: monastery world reserved for the elect of the Church of the Light, who took vows of chastity and poverty; Recipients of the Light who fell into darkness were sometimes sent here by their communities for penance

NAME: Chenowei
INTERESTING: rustic, simple world dominated by Human worshipers of the Church of the Light (rejected technology and took vows of chastity and poverty)

NAME: B'trilla
INTERESTING: foggy, heavily populated homeworld of B'trillans: squeaky-voiced, vaguely felinoid species often encountered as laborers on Gordian Reach worlds such as Feldwes and nearby sectors

NAME: Feena
INTERESTING: originally known as Olgabl during Xim's reign (became part of Xim's Empire c. 25000 BBY)

NAME: Arcopola
INTERESTING: jatz musician Fitz Roi released his newest sound slug, "Tymin' Downband", during the Arcopola Baas Music Festival, held in Greccia (city) in 2 ABY;

NAME: Gambolla
INTERESTING: jatz musician Fitz Roi started his concert tour on Gambolla in 2 ABY; 2 months later, the art collection of Whiphid business tycoon Baron Galrowk was robbed by the art and jewel thief known as the Tombat

NAME: Kalsunor
INTERESTING: Sith used huge alchemically mutated silooths to wreak havoc here before warriors came to finish the battle; the Sith left the silooths behind o prowl the world; Battle of Kalsunor was only known substantial use of silooths, as they may have been too ferocious for even the ancient Sith to handle; captured by Republic in 3638 during Galactic War

NAME: Ashas Ree
INTERESTING: sole inhabited trading post was situated next to a Jedi Temple built to seal the power of an older Sith Temple beneath it; Mika Grey came here seeking a Sith relic to keep it out of First Order hands, but the trading post's population fled when she opened the temple, and she was trapped in the temple until released two days later by Kazuda Xiono

NAME: Nicht Ka
INTERESTING: cold barren rock with ammonia rains; uninhabitable, but a hexagonal structure was built as a reliquary or tomb in its mountains to contain Warb Null's unique lightsaber and suit of battle armor

NAME: Stygian Caldera
INTERESTING: large nebulosity surrounding the Sith Worlds region; acted as a hyperspatial breakwater, making navigation difficult; protected Sith from attack until Supreme Chancellor Pultimo ordered a counterinvasion of the region in aftermath of Great Hyperspace War

NAME: Khar Delba
INTERESTING: part of Sith Empire as of 5000 BBY; home to Sith war behemoth; Naga Sadow placed a citadel here as a decoy (real base on Khar Shian); attacked by Ludo Kressh, whose forces were smashed by Sadow's counterattack; Sadow rebuilt the Khar Delba citadel and then used it as the center of his power leading up to the Great Hyperspace War

NAME: Khar Shian
INTERESTING: this icy, barren moon was the true site of Naga Sadow's palace and center of power and hid his war fleet behind the moon, as he expected to be attacked by Ludo Kressh's forces; afterwards, used in preparations for Great Hyperspace War

NAME: Jaguada
INTERESTING: only inhabited planet in system; had only one city; controlled by Sith Empire at one point; site of Darth Gravid's fortress c. 550 BBY; allied with CIS during CW; by end of CW, Republic garrisoned clone troopers here; later occupied by Empire

NAME: Jaguada's moon
INTERESTING: had breathable atmosphere; once part of Sith Empire; Sith built large temples here, which Dooku turned into CIS comm facilities in 25 BBY, using equipment hauled there by Jula Shryne (freelance smuggler); left alone by Empire; after Order 66, several smugglers, Jedi survivors came to a temple to try to use equipment to access Coruscant Jedi Temple's memory core

NAME: Rhelg
INTERESTING: site of Ludo Kressh's private fortress before the Great Hyperspace War; one of Sith Space's few holy worlds

NAME: Dromund Kalakar
INTERESTING: shipyards here produced the VX-9 Mailoc gunship and the F-T2 Quell, FT-3C Imperium, and F-T6 Rycer strike fighters for the Sith Empire

NAME: Kalakar Six
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: volcanic, lava flows, crust riddled with magma tunnels
INTERESTING: Dark Side nexus once occupied by Sith Empire; during Cold War, old settlement discovered preserved by ash from an eruption; c. 100 BBY Baron Yorn and followers set up a fortress here, but supply ship later found only Yorn remained, who had gone mad and torn out his eyes and tongue; just before Yavin, Vader was lured into a trap to intercept DS plans, possibly a test by Palpatine

NAME: Dromund Kaas
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, swamps, jungles, temples, large oceans
INTERESTING: originally Sith Empire colony, location lost by time of Great Hyperspace War; Sith Emperor led 20-year odyssey ending with rediscovery of world in 4980 BBY; reconstituted Sith Empire used it as a capital and built skyscrapers of Kaas City; eventually fell into obscurity again; Prophets of the Dark Side ruled for almost 1000 years before incurring wrath of Sidious and fleeing to Bosthirda

NAME: Dromund Fels
INTERESTING: under control of Sith Empire until its collapse; reconstituted Sith Empire carried out archaeological excavations here; Darth Marr uncovered Tulak Hord's lightsaber (uncovered sometime before 3678), and the Imperial Reclamation Service discovered an oubliette (tomb of a Sith prisoner buried with a large number of artifacts and treasures); hosted significant criminal presence by time of Cold War

NAME: Empreror's Fortress
INTERESTING: possessed a Gree cloaking device and its security grid and power core utilized Rakata-built tech; after supposed death of Sith Emperor, Malgus took the station and moved it to Ilum

NAME: Bosthirda
INTERESTING: once a part of Sith Empire; in following millennia, location unknown to both Empire and New Republic (Palpatine may not have even known its location); dark side temple here was hidden retreat of Kadann (Supreme Prophet); eventually, Kadann and his prophets were massacred by Azrakel, Lumiya and Carnor Jax

NAME: Hallion
INTERESTING: lava fields here produced obsidian; decorative spheres made of polished obsidian were known for their dark luster

NAME: Upekzar
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ruins, circular ring of islands, seashores, volcanoes, expansive volcanic cave ssyetms, forests, mountains, plains, rainforests, polar ice caps, oceans
INTERESTING: mostly forgotten world unique among the worlds of the Caldera for its diversity of biomes; home to rhak-skuri (subspecies of diplura that hunted by pheromones known to cause nightmare-like hallucinations in certain humanoid species); Sith settlers incorporated rhak-skuri's visions into their Mysteries (Sith rituals); Luke investigated in 44 ABY during hunt for Abeloth and Ship

NAME: Moraband (Korriban, Pesegam)
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, cayons, dry riverbeds, swamps, deserts, temples, tombs, ruins
INTERESTING: original homeworld of Sith species; Killik colony here c. 30000 BBY; sacred planet for Sith Order; housed many tombs of ancient and powerful Dark Lords of the Sith; abandoned after Great Hyperspace War; site of Sith academy and became HQ of the One Sith; Sith cultist Granta Omega killed by Obi-Wan here in 24 BBY; taken over by Commerce Guild just prior to CW; Yoda traveled here and was assaulted by many visions

NAME: Cantonica
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: home to casino city Canto Bight (destination for wealthy tourists, gamblers, war profiteers); Finn, Rose, BB-8 traveled here to recruit the Master Codebreaker to disable First Order's hyperspace tracker; green pink and blue nebula was visible from planet's surface; artificial ocean continually evaporated, making cost of maintaining it astronomical; considered part of Corporate Sector

NAME: Lorattick Nebula
INTERESTING: used as a hyperspace jump point when the Ardan resistance was trying to use a shortcut to catch Var Narek (traitor to the Rebel Alliance) as he fled from Jagomir to Ord Radama; the nebula contained multiple young stars

NAME: Fromiria system
INTERESTING: home to Fromirian quegs (served roasted as a gourmet dish)

NAME: Meliflar Station
INTERESTING: spaceport made up of miscellaneous pods and modules, including a KDY deep-space warehousing module used for boarding; served as base for smugglers in Mendenbatt system; Luke and Ben Skywalker and Vestara Khai encountered the station while searching for Abeloth, deciding to board when they felt a dark side pulse and were ambushed by smugglers tainted by Abeloth's essence

NAME: Ranroon
NOTES: ("retaied some of the feel of the rancorous")
INTERESTING: matriarchal world with ancient proud traditions; outsiders regarded with deep suspicion; attacked by Xim c. 25100 BBY; site of a fierce battle in which Queen Hylei Indrexu Cortess's forces bravely resisted against Xim's janissaries; her forces were eventually defeated but she became a legendary figure equal to Xim; Far Indrexu (province) and Queen of Ranroon (treasure ship) named after her

NAME: Refrax
INTERESTING: contained an Imperial-controlled spaceport serving as a stopover for ships traveling through Mortex sector during GCW

NAME: Yalln
INTERESTING: outside of Imperial industrial complexes were vast, unsettled regions; inhabited by humans and their pet tals

NAME: Kestel system
INTERESTING: during GCW, system was used as replenishment point by Empire; sometime before capture of the Black Ice, Imperial Replenishment Fleet DK-209 proceeded on hyperlane GH972 to rendezvous with Assault Fleet EM4

NAME: Fluwhaka
INTERESTING: misty world with tall, needle-like spires with openings into caves (natural or delved) used as pirate strongholds; during NR era, some were used by pirates associated with Jerresk (Quarren pirate); Jodo Kast tracked Nosstrick (winged humanoid pirate) here and fell for one of his traps, but was able to poison his quarry with frinka venom; Dengar arrived to collect bounty but Kast drove him off

NAME: Vestral
INTERESTING: one of many planetary haunts frequented by Captain Ellin Lah (Togruta female) and the crew of the Woebegone

NAME: Yutusk
INTERESTING: temperate backwater; major planet in Xim's empire, having served as the Sixth Throne; subjugated by the Empire during GCW; homeworld of Vimran Trell (conscripted into Imperial Navy, parents killed when Empire rounded up and executed suspected Rebel sympathizers on Yutusk)

NAME: Draflago system
INTERESTING: Draflago: known to enjoy or need mudbaths (University of Rudrig had a number of luxury mud tanks available for visiting Draflago)

NAME: Typha-Dor
INTERESTING: Thik, crewmember of TY44 surveillance post, lamented to his coworkers that Tyha-Dor was lucky to have rich resources, yet hadn't figure out how to turn them into real wealth; abundant sunshine and water, two capital cities with two rulers, and a substantial workforce; in 25 BBY, Typha-Dor established a ceasefire with its longtime rival Vanquor thanks to mediation of Obi-Wan and Anakin

NAME: TY44
INTERESTING: one of a string of at least 3 satellite-moons; a surveillance outpost of Typha-Dor was located here by 25 BBY; several of its crewmembers were eliminated by an infiltrator-saboteur from Vanquo

NAME: Vanqor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, rocky areas, smoky crystalline formations, deserts, canyons, highlands, fertile valleys, caves, craters
INTERESTING: appeared blue-gray from space due to silica-dust storms; home of gundarks; about 6 parsecs from Florrum; mid-size cities strung along world's few fertile valleys; CIS established CW listening post; Anakin shot down Dooku here; Endurance (Venator-class SD) crashed during CW; Synara San (Mirialan female) was rescued from the streets of Vanquor by Kragan Gorr (Quarren pirate)

NAME: Florrum
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, dustbowls, canyons, sulfurous geysers in acid flats
INTERESTING: six parsecs from Vanqor; HQ of Weequay pirate gang led by Hondo Ohnaka; system held by Republic until c. 20 BBY, when it was captured by Grievous

NAME: Brachi
INTERESTING: home to Brachian beastlord (particularly vicious supspecies of gundark

NAME: Tervissis
INTERESTING: Tervigs and Bandies were at war, with the former subjugating the latter; in aftermath of CW, Tervissis resisted Imperial control; counted among "Seperatist holdouts"; planet continued to resist despite repeated assaults throughout Listehol Campaign; planet wasn't pacified until 13 BBY; home of Tervissian tick

NAME: Lamus
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, deserts pocked with sinkholes, farms
INTERESTING: inhabited by A'Mar people; gundarks and Brachian Beastlords inhabited this moon; Vidge-Ribu: low-tech agrarian community

NAME: Syngia
INTERESTING: orbited by a single moon; Remulus Dreypa (ancient Sith Lord) practiced his mastery over creation of life, and left his mysterious Genesis pool; mutated creatures, descended from those created by Sith alchemy, lived here; Yoda warned other Jedi of their existence through a notation in his copy of The Jedi Path

NAME: Ermi
INTERESTING: many years prior to CW, a number of Jedi were from Ermi, and were distinguished by crafting lightsabers with multifaceted gems that caused stray energy tendrils to spiral off of their blades

NAME: Qalydon
INTERESTING: around time of Revanite crisis, archaeologists discovered hieroglyphs carved into stone walls at the feet of mountains here depicting the cultural rise of the inhabitants; New Sith Wars were called the "Curse of Qalydon" here; Port Fyrin was HQ of Fellowship of Kooroo; Bail Organa visited during CW when it was a battlefront; later became part of Empire

NAME: Kejim
INTERESTING: Kejim Outpost (Imperial Remnant base believed to be abandoned after destruction of first Death Star) located here; messages apparently originating from the base were intercepted by NR Intelligence, prompting Mon Mothma to send Jan Ors and Kyle Katarn to investigate; they discovered the base was still occupied, with a lab running experiments regarding conferring Force-sensitivity

NAME: Curreck
INTERESTING: homeworld of Darren T. Weeb (captain of freighter Arcadia, smuggler)

NAME: Ord Dalet
INTERESTING: during Cold War, a member of the mysterious shapeshifting Shi'ido species was hospitalized here; one of several Ordnance/Regional Depot planets named with Common Sith letters

NAME: Drayberia system
INTERESTING: home to Drayberian hawks

NAME: Elom
INTERESTING: Elom: white-furred with mole-like features and large claws, lived in mountain caves; Elomin: horned humanoids who claimed large portions of the surface for mining and limited agriculture;vast tracts of wilderness nevertheless remained; Republic made contact with Elomin in 120 BBY, but with Eloms in 50 BBY; conquered by Empire; Elomin forced to toil in mines; liberated by NR; repelled YV

NAME: Sondarr
INTERESTING: during NR era, Star's Nova (mercenary organization) operated an HQ base in the Lunnes Wastes here

NAME: Tandgor
INTERESTING: known for its expensive gemstones

NAME: Arorua
INTERESTING: home to fierce natural predators such as the squollyhawlk, and monsters spawned from Sith sorcery such as the silan; Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan visited in 44 ABY; Obi-Wan was almost killed by a squollyhawlk; they met Mosko Bolpa (a Moggonite) who betrayed them, and destroyed an ancient silan

NAME: Hermos
INTERESTING: during GCW, Yesgar's pirates were spotted in the main spaceports here

NAME: Bravis system
INTERESTING: Bravis Sith wwee a group of Sith based in this system, considered ancient by time of CW; their lightsaber crystals gave their lightsabers a sparkling effect

NAME: Stenos
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named Maldont under Xim; several hundred years before Yavin, groundquakes and volcanic disturbances shook the world, burying a stone idol believed to be whe worldly avatar of their god, Vol; the winged Stenax refused to fly until it was found; many ancient buildings became ruins due to neglect, including the city of Farruz, which later became a crowded haven for offworld criminals

NAME: Tahlboor
INTERESTING: temperate world; Tahlboorians divided into two castes, perpetually at war; ancient Tahlboorean civilization constructed the Sky cannon (awesome weapon resulting in destruction of one of Tahlboor's twin moons as well as their civilization); later aligned with CIS and Empire

NAME: Almania
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: cold, windy world discovered between 3000 and 1000 BBY; ruled by Je'har (tyrannical upper caste); sat in shadow of its wealthiest moon (Pydyr); often raided for slaves by various pirate, slaver gangs; homeworld of Kueller, formerly Dolph (Jedi Initiate at Luke's Academy who fell to the dark side due to Order and NR's indifference to Almanians' poverty; he instigated a bloody coup

NAME: Pydyr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: cities here made of mudbrick decorated with native seafah jewels; Pydyrians: used droids extensively for monotonous tasks, were represented in Senate just before CW by Wuja Wojaine (arrested for allowing slavers to operate in system for a share of their wealth), had very lax security; Kueller killed all but 1000 Pydyrians, leaving their homes untouched for looting; Fallanassi settled here

NAME: Auyemesh
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Kueller killed most of population, in a similar genocide to Pydyr's

NAME: Drewwa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: colonized generations before Yavin; heavily industrialized moon with many companies from across the galaxy holding offices here, including Tendrando Arms, Trang Robotics, Lyster Innovations

NAME: Malkii
INTERESTING: remote world serving as refuge for insurrectionists, mercenaries and terrorists; Tu-Wane Jipps was involved in some 'nasty business' here that caused him to owe a huge favor to Tobias Beckett prior to Beckett's death in 10 BBY; perhaps most notorious as training ground of Malkite Poisoners (infamous assassins); one of the earliest worlds to adopt Pius Dea religion during Kymoodon Era

NAME: Shallow March
INTERESTING: site of Shallow March Supply Post (Imperial Army supply post commanded by Major Tarn Innis

NAME: Lotide
INTERESTING: home to Imperial Technical Branch Outpost used for weapons research & development; infiltrated by group of Rebels working out of Fangol; main settlement and spaceport was Market City

NAME: Choah Belt
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance operated a fuel refinery hereuntil shortly after Yavin; it was rumored that Shisha Mor (long-dead crimelord) had used an asteroid here as a hideout; Empire discovered Rebel fuel refinery and destroyed it, forcing the Alliance to try to hijack the Black Ice

NAME: Fangol
INTERESTING: small frozen world; icy crust; secret Rebel Mortex Sector HQ here; shrouded in poisonous icy white mist formed of water vapor contaminated with metals and other elements, which sprang from the ejecta of hundreds of ice volcanoes, reflecting all light from space, making the planet appear as solid ball of white, and blocking sensors; temperatures rarely exceeded -110 degrees Galactic Standard

NAME: artificial Rebel Alliance moon
INTERESTING: Alliance artificial moon in geosynchronous orbit over Fangol's Motex Sector HQ base; facilitated communication and sensor scans due to Fangol's sensor-blocking mists; the droids manning the station were programmed to shut down the station upon contact with potential hostile visitors to the system; destroyed by Empire during assault on Fangol

NAME: Kruskan
INTERESTING: some of population was made up of near-Humans, but planet was forgotten by the Galactic Republic; c. 3000 BBY, Sith acolytes hid a holocron in a mountain stronghold; the capital city later grew near the ruins; holocron was rediscovered by Regera Girawn, (noblewoman) who was driven mad by the visions it gave her and fled; years later upon Republic ship's arrival, she enslaved the crew

NAME: Muskree
INTERESTING: backwater world; lone settlement was failed mining colony Hardscrabble, population about 400 (all human)

NAME: Kashoon
INTERESTING: conquered by Empire and later freed with Rebel Alliance's help after a number of successful guerilla assaults; Kashoonara left to their own devices afterwards; based on their ancient folklore, they considered the humbaba (short-legged, bovine, swamp-dwelling animal, covered in dense fur, natural burrower) to be sacred and defended the creatures against any offworlder depredations

NAME: Qotile
INTERESTING: devastated during Stark Hyperspace Conflict; considered a desolate wasteland; ruled by a masked monarch; sometime prior to Hoth, Bossk collected a bounty on the ruler's head and assumed the title of ruler of Qotile and recalled the event as an example of his hunting prowess to his sister, who was unimpressed

NAME: Sonn Vilmari
INTERESTING: oceanic world; Pan-preneur: amphibious sentients with rust-orange skin spotted with blue; resembled other aquatic races and were believed to be distantly related to Mon Cal, though many aquatic species shared distant genetics

NAME: Minntaa
INTERESTING: Human-inhabited world liberated by Rebel Alliance when Jeph Shannessi (Imperial Colonel) was assassinated by Alliance Special Forces

NAME: Reaper's World system
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban cityplexes, glaciers, mountains, plateaus, taiga, tundra
INTERESTING: sector capital; colonized c. 5000 BBY when it was idyllic, with grean oceans and blue mountains; Nilgaard Bioprocessing used up the world's natural resources, leaving it in an ice age of glaciers; atmosphere varied from Type I to Type III by altitude, latitude and time of day; population 11.2 B (10.2 B Humans, 1 B others); capital: Vandalar City

NAME: Emmer (Umhul)
INTERESTING: high-gravity world that joined Republic prior to 45 BBY; Emmerian walker vehicles inspired KDY's (including AT-AT); Imperial fortress world by 4 ABY; NR-aligned Mon Cal defeated Imperial forces here after Endor, but Zsinj later took control; NR freed world during Post-Zsinj campaigns in 8.5 ABY; Emmerians: stout, developed walker tech due to fast-growing grasses making roads impractical

NAME: Emmer Belt
INTERESTING: extensively mined using Plasma-Jet Mole Miners, ore haulers; 30 K individuals lived and worked here

NAME: Dalos IV
INTERESTING: hot, humid with a single rainforest continent (Kavila); originally a penal colony; because planet was largely ignored by Empire, became a haven for those fleeing persecution; architecture was old-fashioned, but technology was modern; popular sport was Trophy Chase, in which the locals rode nephs (docile flying creatures); Lira Rimrunner (former smuggler) was elected Governor-General

NAME: Quermia
INTERESTING: terraformed heavenly planet; c. 17000 BBY during Indecta Era, the Arkanians settled Xexto subjects from nearby Troiken here for a genetic experiment; these Xexto became the Quermians; Arkanians later moved on and forgot Quermia; Troiken and Quermia were discovered by Republic and joined around same time; Xexto were outraged when they discovered Arkanian deception; in CIS space during CW; Quermians were secluded during Imperial Era due to Jedi link

NAME: Kaelta
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: class M star

NAME: Toola
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: glacier-encrusted mountains, tundra, windswept ice plains, snowy deserts, shifting snow dunes, hot springs, frozen ocean
INTERESTING: home of mastmots; Republic clone troopers served here during CW; homeworld of J'Quille (male Whiphid bounty hunter); thin atmopshere; highly elliptical orbit meant that summer lasted only 1/5 of the year and warmed only tropical regions, melting ice and growing vegetation; equatorial regions supported 90% of its lifeforms; tribal governments; exported ice, and at times furs and tusks

NAME: Ord Bueri
INTERESTING: Rebel base on Yavin 4 used H-60 Tempest bombers from here

NAME: Karkaris
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: its expansive oceans were home to much of its biodiversity; despite Republic membership, it declared itself neutral during CW; Karkarodons: lived in sprawling, decentralized unsersea cities powered by volcanic vent geothermal plants, many sided with CIS, developed Hydroid Medusa bio-weapons here, shipped them to Mon Cala to participate in a battle between the Mon Cals and Quarren

NAME: Makem
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Makem Pria
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: giant ball of searing rock

NAME: Makem Dua
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Makem Te
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: originally independent world ruled by Congress of Caliphs; conquered by Xim; discovered Republic, quickly joined between Kymoodon and Rianitus eras; Krath fled here during Great Sith War; invaded by Mandalorians during Mandalorian Wars; every Swokes Swokes who died was afforded a plot in the Tract of Makem Te (graveyard covering 10% of planet's surface); spice trade of high value

NAME: Makem Qat
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Makem Liva
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Makem Hek
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Makem Sup
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Gallshebbis Prime
INTERESTING: NR Officer Airen Cracken and his squad were once trapped in a warehouse by stomtroopers here; though they suffered losses, they were able to escape by exploiting slow recycle time on Stormtroopers' old BlasTech "PulseHammer" series repeating blasters

NAME: Nam Priax
INTERESTING: completely covered in warm oceans; home of Beck-tori, aquatic leech-like parasites that grew to extreme sizes, sometimes attacked boats and submersible craft, and had a strong connection to the Force, which they used to heal themselves; Republic took steps to prevent infestations, yet Beck-tori were spotted on Naboo and a Mon Cala outbreak took 50 years to eradicate

NAME: Ord Torrenze
INTERESTING: liberated from an invasion force during last decades of Old Republic; Republic CR90 Freedom's Messenger led the liberation fleet at the Battle of Ord Torrenze

NAME: Kazarak
INTERESTING: served as base of slavery ring operating in the Mahrusha subsector during early years of the New Order

NAME: Sembla
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: volcanic islands, coral reefs, shallow seas, ancient (non-Vurk) equatorial subaquatic ruins
INTERESTING: tidally and tectonically active thanks to its 4 moons, it was located far from any major trade routes and was rarely traveled to; Empire established research base here, and pressed VUrk as cheap labor in strip-mining operations; vast gardens of coral and valuable crystal in the oceans, targeted by offworld miners; Vurk: nomadic (few permanent settlements); ignored by YV

NAME: Vornax
INTERESTING: covered in factories (abandonded for centuries), piles of rusted scrap and garbage; only visitors were attempting to escape law or bounty hunters searching for a mark

NAME: Barundi
INTERESTING: Barundi: blue-skinned, prominent canines, no obvious sexual dimorphism, plugs of tightly-braided hair atop high-domed heads, coarse body hair on forearms, lower legs and chests; taken from their homeworld thousands of years before Yavin and deposited on an unnamed planet in Wild Space, where they worshiped the Yavin Vassilika as a god; primitive society built on maintaining harmony; any deviation from strict doctrines resulted in capital punishment

NAME: Estaria
INTERESTING: during Battle of Jakku, Nath Tensent noted he'd never seen so many starships in one place, even at Estaria's orbital ports; capital of Indrexu sector; served as spaceport servicing the many ships traveling between the Far Perlemian and the TIon Cluster; the Humans of the Tionese Cluster considered Estaria to be only moderately corrupt

NAME: Ank Ki'Shor
INTERESTING: discovered during Xim's expansion c. 25000 BBY; was gathered into Indrexu Confederation almost a century after XIm's death; during last years of Republic, Tion Cluster worlds joined CIS; later they joined the Empire; became key supplier to Rebel Alliance in its early years, who in turn defended the manufacturing world against Imperial bombing raids; willing to do business with most anybody

NAME: Janodral Mizar
NOTES: "Jandoral Mizar" in WP article
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders c. 25126 BBY; Han once defeated Zygerrian slavers in its vicinity, giving their ship over to their former slaves; among the slaves was Rebel Alliance historian Arhul Hextrophon and his family; Janodral Mizar had a law stating that pirate or slaver victims split the profits if the pirates were captured or killed; population 1 to 100 M

NAME: Shalyvane
INTERESTING: during Galactic War, rare lunar eclipse was prophesied to reveal location where the Em'liy god Kavaan left his mark on planet; Vader had Shalyvane bombed to support Shira Brie's backstory when she infiltrated the Alliance; Brie, Luke, and others visited but were attacked by Em'liy warriors; Luke later returned and discovered the truth after Brie's supposed death; became NR member

NAME: Endregaad
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: shallow seas, swamps (historic); rocky desert, valleys, plateaus, mesas, oases (modern)
INTERESTING: once a member of Xim's Empire; once a wet world, its seas evaporated, making it into an arid world with colorful rock formations of red standstone, blue granite; plagued by wind & sandstorms; geodes mined for their crystals; subjugated by Empire; quarantined by CSA after a plague sparked by the spice Tempest struck here in 19 BBY; inhabitants blamed non-Humans

NAME: Rhilithan
grid square/sector/"along Perlemian Trade Route bwtween Varl and Nal Hutta"
INTERESTING: lifeless world used as waypoint for transport ships working for Mika the Hutt, transporting spice to and from Varl following the end of the GCW

NAME: Kanaver
INTERESTING: ruled by Livien League before being conquered by Xim in 25130 BBY; later joined Republic and eventually Empire; by post-Imperial Period, it re-emerged as a prominent trading center near the Perlemian Trade Route, Back Spiral worlds and the Overic Griplink

NAME: Livien
INTERESTING: founding world of the Livien League; absorbed into Xim's Empire; neutral during Cold War, but ruled by a tyrannical royal family; Republic was secretly backing rebel factions against them with military shipments; shortly afterwards, Livien's Finance Minisher stole millions of credits and went into hiding; by GCW, lost all prominence; became subsistence agriworld with ancient ruins

HUMAN_READABLE_NAME: 1. Raxus Prime (Circlet of the Tion, Nikato's Shining Gem)
NAME: Raxus Prime (Circlet of the Tion, Nikato's Shining Gem)
ALT_NAMES (/ separated): Circlet of the Tion, Nikato's Shining Gem
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: historic: warm lagoons, beaches; modern: industrial factories, sealed living habitats, streams of superheated runoff, rough-hewn quarry pits, vast junkscapes, toxic lakes and waste pools
INTERESTING: by time of CW, once-beautiful world had been polluted and littered with junk of ages; General Draven supplied Mon Mothma with a map showing locations of active investigations into mining guild operations, one of which was at Raxus Prime; held many secrets, including the Force Harvester (ancient buried Sith artifact) used by CIS to activate the Dark Reaper (superweapon buried on Thule)

NAME: Raxus II
INTERESTING: during the Cold War, studies of relics suggested Raxus II was once inhabied by ancient Tionese Empire

NAME: Raxus Secundus
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, grassy hills, light forests, plains, oceans
INTERESTING: capital of CIS; temperate world renowned for beauty; locals attributed longevity to indigenous shemble-berry; site of Seperatist Parliament during CW; heavily guarded by fleet of Seperatist frigates and battleships; Mina Bonteri (Seperatist Senator) and her family lived here near a spaceport in one of the planet's cities; Amidala and Ahsoka secretly traveled here to meet with Bonteri

NAME: Tion
INTERESTING: orbited two brilliant cyan stars; namesake of Tion Cluster, but one of its minor worlds; covered by world-spanning ocean; orbited by 3 industrialized moons, with one hosting a spaceport; one of the worlds of the Kingdom of Cron; absorbed into Xim's Empire; eventually became part of Tion Hegemony when the Tion Cluser joined Republic; later joined CIS, then Empire

NAME: Folende
INTERESTING: agriworld ag output was moderate for centuries (Omman considered its competitor); in last decades of Republic (c. 21 BBY), Folende commissioned Kaminoan cloners to create a force of ag laborers and experienced a marked rise in production, becoming an important provider of staple foods to poverty-stricken worlds of the Far Perlemian; its yield increase was considered a mystery

NAME: Risban
INTERESTING: Keremark (river town) was located between 3 naturally defensible ridges, and was dominated by Fortress Keremark (originally a ground-defense zone near the town which was fortified and re-fortified, and eventually incorporated state-of-the-art defensive systems; ruled by Neolsse family, who opposed Imperial subjugation

NAME: Cholganna
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, jungles, rainforests, mountains, river valleys, oceans
INTERESTING: known for cool forests, dangerous creatures, including nexu (predatory feline native to continent of Indona); arboreal octopus and bark rat were both prey of Nexu; a settlement called the Retreat was founded in the jungle by survivors of the CW crash of the Sa Nalaor (Munificent-class star frigate), including Rel Harsol (Seperatist captain), Cratala (Arkanian cyberneticist) and others

NAME: Zandrax system
INTERESTING: uninhabited; site of rendezvous between Resurgence (Alderaanian Resistance Nebulon-B in service of Bail Organa) and Banshee (modified Baudo-class star yacht used by smuggler Sirona Okeefe for Alderaanian Resistance missions after CW), following Mission to Felucia

NAME: Yaronn
INTERESTING: waterworld with only 1 significant landmass (200-square km forested "continent" with negligible fauna); a bounty hunter named the Claw invited a group of smugglers here who he held responsible for the death of his brother (an Imperial officer); he offered to let them go if they survived his attempts to hunt them; located at star coordinates 2839.23 893.84

NAME: Drongar Prime
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: "clone wars"
INTERESTING: approximately same size as Coruscant Prime but burned hotter, giving Drongar a tropical climate; orbited by Drongar and 3 additional planets

NAME: Drongar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rainforests, bota fields, swampland, seas, highlands, steppes
INTERESTING: mostly uninhabitable; discovered by Nikto scouts in 220 BBY; native airborne spores caused death to unprotected beings; monsoons, electrical storms common; inhabited by both Republic and CIS during CW, who fought over Bota (miracle plant); Jedi healer in one of the Republic Mobile Surgical units used Bota to see the Force in completeness, foiled a plot to destroy Republic RMSUs

NAME: Seidhkona
INTERESTING: the mind-witch S'ybll used this world as her base of operations during GCW

NAME: Florn (Tinatorn)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: dense jungles, a few large oceans
INTERESTING: jungles of Florn said to be so deadly that any sentient on the surface without hyperaccelerated nerve implants or a similar level of natural reflexes risked certain death; between 4 and 40 ABY, galactic community became aware Florn was Lamproid homeworld; prior to that the Lamproid homeworld was a mystery due to their many colony worlds and were sometimes thought nonsentient

NAME: Syruss system
INTERESTING: at some point during GCW, a Rebel strike force was launched against an Imperial station in order to liberate the system

NAME: Ton-Falk
INTERESTING: Battle of Ton-Falk took place here during GCW, during which the Empire lost 2 frigates and a Dreadnaught-class heavy cruiser due to lack of fighter support against Rebel Alliance's Renegade Flight, leading to development of TOn-Falk-class escort carrier

NAME: Daltarra
INTERESTING: early in GCW, served as listening outpost for Rebels monitoring Imperial fleet movements; Rebel activity discovered and eliminated by Vader and a group of Imperial Storm Commandos prior to Yavin; capital city of Quenin was located on the northern continent and featured a spaceport

NAME: Cujicor
INTERESTING: NR member world on UV invasion path; YV promised to spare world in return for captured Jedi; Peace Brigade captured Swilja Fenn (female Twi'lek Jedi Knight) here

NAME: Crseih
INTERESTING: crystallized white dwarf star influenced by extradimensional entity Waru; disrupted the Force when in close proximity; destroyed in 14 ABY when it collapsed into nearby black hole

NAME: Crseih Black Hole
INTERESTING: swallowed nearby crystallized white dwarf star in 14 ABY

HUMAN_READABLE_NAME: Crseih Station (Asylum Station, Crseih Research Station)
NAME: Crseih Station (Asylum Station, Crseih Research Station)
INTERESTING: Imperial asteroid prison run by Hethrir, who used it as a research center testing the limits of realspace, hyperspace and otherspace; consisted of habitat domes, docking tubes arranged in elaborate and decadent bazaar; hyperdrive-equipped; relocated to Crseih system, orbiting black hole after Hoth in 3 ABY; Waru brought here; station moved to Pakuuni after destruction of crystal star

NAME: Durace
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: volcanic mountains, caves, sharp rocks, toxic seas
INTERESTING: barren, stormy & toxic

NAME: Parnassos
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, valleys, greenery, crystal blue oceans (prior to nuclear disaster); settlements, purple-sand desert, mountains, black rock spires, caves, cliffs, plateaus, valleys, radioactive wastelands, grasslands, forests, farms, dark risen oceans, tide pools (after nuclear disaster)
INTERESTING: once lush and enjoyable (at least as portrayed by Con Star Mining Corporation in advertising); nuclear disaster at Calliope Station caused a dramatic change in planet's environment, leading to sea level rise, desertification, acid rain, and death of most food animals; clans feuded for territory; oceans became home to ravenous creatures with meter-long teeth; homeworld of Phasma

HUMAN_READABLE_NAME: Unknown blue gas giant w frozen moon
NAME: Unknown blue gas giant w frozen moon
244Core (Sraato)
INTERESTING: controlled by corporations; dangerous & destructive meteor showers

NAME: Flacharia system
INTERESTING: in 22 ABY, Dean Jinzler (Human male technician) intercepted message from Chaf'orm'bintrano that was intended for Luke that was transmitted through sector comm relay post on Comra; Jinzler took a courier ship from the post and headed for Crustai (rendezvous point mentioned in the message), but his hyperdrive broke down here; Jorj Car'das arrived and gave him a lift to Crustai

NAME: Far Cradle
INTERESTING: Republic space station serving as refueling station for Republic Navy forces in Unknown Regions during the Galactic War; destroyed when Sith Empire forces tracked short-range Republic fighters back to the station and launched an assault

NAME: Kro Var
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren wastes, valleys, volcanoes, lava flows
INTERESTING: during New Sith Wars, ship of refugees form Ruusan campaign exited hyperspace at wrong coordinates, crashed here; survivors divided into clans to fight for planet's limited resources; eventually, Shapers of Kro Var (organization of Force-Sensitives) developed & played key role in inter-clan conflicts; world eventually discovered by Republic; Jedi Order tried to help population reintegrate

NAME: Veroleem
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: arid; deserts, mountains, hilly rock-cut warrens
INTERESTING: proselytizing cult sought new members in various periods when they could keep their world low-profile; processed narcotic drugs for funding

NAME: Thuna III
INTERESTING: located in a small system near the Unknown Regions; at some point by 32 BBY, a colony here was devastated by a groundquake; in the wake of the disaster, a band of raiders intended to pillage the settlement; Besalisk arms dealer Mavven recruited a group of individuals with a MEV-series medical evacuation droid to travel here and assist the colonists with evacuating

NAME: Kariek
NOTES: "ans"
INTERESTING: cities dominated by towering fortresses & watchtowers, connected by a network of underground tunnels; Eickaries: humanoid reptilian race with green and orange skin and patterns of black scales around eyes and across backs of heads, divided into various tribes who fought long and disastrous civil wars until invasion by mercenary army of Lakran in 28 BBY; later joined Empire of the Hand

NAME: Lakra system
INTERESTING: Lakra: had torso plates, large hands, were possibly insectile; at some point a group of them were hired as mercenaries by the Warlord and aided him in conquering Kariek c. 28 BBY; they served him until his defeat by the Eickaries and the Empire of the Hand in the Battle of Kariek

NAME: Esfandia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: free-floating proto-world; once orbited star but eventually broke away; even on its own, planet had enough interior radioactivity in its core to support a liquid atmosphere of hydrogen and methane; one of only 2 planets containing HoloNet Relays to Unknown Regions; Esfandia Long-Range Communications base: mobile relay base, crew of 12; Brrbrlpp race of thrill-seeking, flower-like Amoebas

NAME: Frunchettan system
INTERESTING: lay outside borders of NR-controlled space in 12 ABY; Frunchettan-sai: peaceful race that enjoyed art and culture, inhabiting several colonies in the Outer Rim, had one more joint than humans between wrists and elbows, and saw in blue-ultraviolet light

NAME: Taloron system
INTERESTING: home to the Taloron Hunters (group of elite mercenaries and hunters who operated after fall of the Republic)

NAME: Dbari system
INTERESTING: Dbarians: had large number of flexible, unsegmented tentacles and warts, had chromaphores that flashed blue when surprised, maroon when confused, could also flash pink, were worrisome and spent lots of time weighing outcomes of actions

NAME: Namadii
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ansion
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Aeten II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Diab
INTERESTING: planet's electrical storms wreaked havoc with sensors

NAME: Diab 6
INTERESTING: orbited by The Prism, also known as the Ghost Prison (secret Jedi-run prison facility)

NAME: The Prism (The Ghost Prison)
INTERESTING: secret Jedi-run prison facility known only to the Jedi Council; constructed during Second Great Schism; used to house incredibly dangerous criminals during CW; 3-day trip from Coruscant (even with a presumably fast hyperdrive); Diab's electrical storms wreaked havoc with sensors; no communications allowed in or out; had skeleton crew of 100 security droids and Skein (Jedi Master)

NAME: Adumar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Drompani system
grid square/sector/near NR borders with Imperial Remnant, Empire of the Hand

NAME: Nosken system
INTERESTING: Errant Venture stationed here for complete refurbishment in 19 ABY; at beginning of Caamas Document Crisis, system was visited by unidentified starfighter

NAME: Imdaar
INTERESTING: base of Phantom TIE project; mynocks lived here; Ru Murleen and Rookie One hijacked a Lambda shuttle here in order to board the Terror

NAME: Imdaar Alpha
INTERESTING: production facility of Phantom TIE project

NAME: Dreighton Nebula
PARENT: Outer Rim/Dreighton Nebula//Dantus/Aeten, Arah, Dreighton, Imdaar
INTERESTING: CW Battle of Dreighton fought here; contained Dreighton Triangle, where ships were believed to disappear; avoided by superstitious

NAME: Belt of Arah
INTERESTING: Voolvif Monn (Shistavenan Jedi Master) was orphaned as an infant on a desolate world near Arah belt (another planet in system?); Imperial oridium ore mining facility here for Phantom TIE project (destroyed by Rebel Rascal Group), and derillium mines throughout belt

NAME: Dreighton
INTERESTING: Imperial base here with kilomeers of pipe lines and tunnels below the surface; Rookie One and Kirby were attacked by TIEs and Rookie One eventually escaped the base in the Corellia Star (YT-1300)

NAME: Troska
INTERESTING: minor Imperial outpost grudgingly supported by ruling Kyber family; home to Refinery Six-Two-Two; Imperial officer Treyz Manech hired Fett to depose Kyber monarchy

NAME: Harridan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, wild rocky hills, dim forests, tempestuous seas
INTERESTING: former prison colony; later continued to attract rogues, rebels; minimal laws; healthy mix of rarely seen aliens lived here alongside humans; cities had high populations and intense round-the-clock traffic, were haphazardly laid out, including Spaceport City; most businesses small, intensely independent; large police force willing to dispense own brand of justice in streets

NAME: Kobbahn
INTERESTING: location of one of earliest Rebel cells following declaration of New Order

NAME: Sorl
INTERESTING: homeworld of Jedi Master Noor R'aya

NAME: Oracaia system
INTERESTING: origin system of Oracaian customs frigate

NAME: Ganlihk
INTERESTING: human-inhabited; home of ryless trees, rippers, ludos (tentacled bioluminescent pets), and zuxu; Hendrixen led friends on fishing trip here

NAME: Dontamo
INTERESTING: Ferus Olin, Clive Flax held at Dontamo prison for crimes against the Empire and compelled to work in a factory building parts of the Death Star I

NAME: Cirrus
INTERESTING: orbited 2 orange suns; capital city: Ciran (near bay); homeworld of Talesan Fry and his parents

NAME: Quadrant Seven
INTERESTING: Quadrant Seven species: humanoids with collection of antennae which resembled human hair, as of Cw had not warred for 573 years, shunned technology and preserved environment; Settlement 5 was a city with no parks or other amusements

NAME: Uba
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Uba I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Ubese colony here was destroyed when Jedi bombardment of Uba system ignited Ubese superweapon caches during New Sith Wars in 1800 BBY

NAME: Uba II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Ubese colony here was destroyed when Jedi bombardment of Uba system ignited Ubese superweapon caches during New Sith Wars in 1800 BBY

NAME: Uba III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: original Ubese homeworld?; completely destroyed when Jedi bombardment of Uba system ignited Ubese superweapon caches during New Sith Wars in 1800 BBY; became asteroid belt; Epsis birds went extinct

NAME: Uba IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: home of Ubese after destruction of Uba III; heavily poisoned, irradiated at end of First Battle of Uba IV; joined CIS in 22 BBY

NAME: Uba V
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Ubese colony here was destroyed when Jedi bombardment of Uba system ignited Ubese superweapon caches during New Sith Wars in 1800 BBY

NAME: Ubertica
INTERESTING: relatively low atmospheric oxygen; settled by Ubese refugees after destruction of Uba III in 1800 BBY; many settlements bombarded, destroyed by Ubese warlord Savax; complete genocide prevented by Empire

NAME: Parliock
INTERESTING: shared name with the Peacekeeping of Parliock (conflict involving Jedi Order prior to CW)

NAME: Alderbathe
INTERESTING: Alderbathe Monastery (noted religious retreat)

NAME: Bardelberan 7
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Poressi system
INTERESTING: Leveler (Republic Acclamator-class assault ship) accidentally traveled here due to hyperdrive fault

NAME: Deadon
INTERESTING: site of several xenoarchaeological Ice Temples discovered by Doctor Angrail Ryhl

NAME: Kemla
INTERESTING: Kemlans: able to identify close relative by scent alone

NAME: Kemla Yard
INTERESTING: several Republic shipyards located here during CW; Leveler (Republic Acclamator-class assault ship) visited here for refit to add experimental weapons around 22 BBY

NAME: Kareas
INTERESTING: origin point of Kareas brandy (alcoholic beverage)

NAME: Domgrin
INTERESTING: located relatively close to Gonmore

NAME: Otomok system
INTERESTING: name of system and presumably its star

NAME: Ord Mynock
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungles, mountains, swamps, plentiful surface water
INTERESTING: originally settled as comm relay; trade lanes shifted elsewhere and planet fell into relative obscurity; much hostile flora, fauna (crushing vines, hover vehicle-eating plants); pirates a threat here; believed to be Mynock homeworld; ComNet Corporation based in Ord Mynock Freeport (originally part of early protective fortress, later became bustling modern spaceport built on air-filled caissons to prevent it sinking into the mire

NAME: Urthha (Earth)
INTERESTING: composed of various nation-states, though the Intergalactic Passport was useless as a planetary passport between said states; Star Tours operated here

NAME: Tomorrowland Spaceport
INTERESTING: Star Tours operated here

NAME: Spaceport THX1138
INTERESTING: used as starliner terminal by travel agencies that were members of Galactic Tourist Bureau, including Star Tours

NAME: Yarille
INTERESTING: suffered heavy damage during CW

NAME: JanFathal
INTERESTING: capital: Athar; major city: Nuth; seized by CIS during CW

NAME: Ardennia
INTERESTING: mynock roasts were held here; also homeworld of Topi Topi (a Wayuning) and Juronus Opto (a human)

NAME: Angrallia system
INTERESTING: home of Angrallian Toobirs (subject of a popular joke circulated by the Intergalactic Joke Group)

NAME: Wistril
INTERESTING: known for its smugglers; Chimera stopped here for supplies; remained under Imperial control even after Endor

NAME: Merikon
INTERESTING: Imperial training facility here

NAME: Tangar
INTERESTING: site of CIS activity during CW

NAME: Gonmore
INTERESTING: location of one of Talon Karrde's clearinghouse

NAME: Miro asteroid field
INTERESTING: Stellar Damsel (CR90) once hid here to escape Imperial pursuit until its crew could be rescued; field infested with Mynocks

NAME: Smarck
INTERESTING: seemingly uninhabited; Black Sun maintained a presence here, led by Macus Kayniph, and kept a storehouse of Spaarti cloning cylinders

NAME: Ord Cantrell
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Ancient Colony of Duros settled here and reverted to simple technology. Remains of wooden sailing ship dredged from waters during Cold War; served as capital of Imperial Interim Ruling Council after destruction of Byss

NAME: Recluse's Nebula
INTERESTING: portions of the Imperial fleet hid here after Endor, though not as large a group as the one that hid in the Vulpinus Nebula; despite this there were still hundreds of Star Destroyers and thousands of smaller craft

NAME: Orinda
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas/Alphabet Squadron p. 216 (204th link to Orinda, Operation: Cinder)
INTERESTING: represented in the Galactic Senate by senator Fatil in decades after GCW; after Endor, Orinda was part of Imperial Space until 9 ABY; after loss of Coruscant and Ysanne Isard's retreat to Thyferra, Ars Dangor and Imperial Ruling Council relocated here, making it Empire's new capital; changed hands several times, then conquered by YV and finally retaken by Imperial Remnant

NAME: Elegasso
INTERESTING: minor world under Imperial Control; in 0 ABY a local election was blatantly rigged, drawing attention of Mara Jade and Hand of Judgment stormtrooper team

NAME: Selnesh
INTERESTING: frigid prison world with Type II atmosphere, devoid of vegetation or color; Gapgrin Dozito and Sart Juloss each served 25-year sentences here for attempted shipjacking; planet had one building, the white-domed Selnesh Imperial Detention Center; Rebels rescued Gebnerret Vibrion from here

NAME: Burna system
INTERESTING: shared name with Burna Trade Route

NAME: Port Haven
INTERESTING: third of seven planets; failed colony from Salliche ~250 BBY because colonists were unprepared to live off land & defend against fauna; during GCW settlers returned to sart a shadowport; Bounty Hunters' Guildhouse here with motor pool of missile-equipped LUX-3 landspeeders

NAME: Entana system
INTERESTING: shared name with Entana Run

NAME: Phaeda
INTERESTING: during OR, had its own defense fleet; homeworld of Zayne Carrick; of little strategic or commercial value; haven for smugglers, thieves, fringers; capital: Chinesti; captured by YV, later freed by Imperial Remnant; by 40 ABY Phaeda made Nar Shaddaa look classy

NAME: Phaedacomm
INTERESTING: Bith-managed high-security comm traffic station at edge of system; had med station with quarantine area; protected by mine field; captured by Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders in 3962 BBY, cutting off all communications of Dantooine

NAME: Lenico system
INTERESTING: contained many asteroids; worlds here known to have enormous, msyerious stone monuments

NAME: Lenico IV
INTERESTING: small tribe of Ortolans found refuge here around time of Great Galactic War until they were massacred by passing Sith Apprentive Exal Kressh; Jedi later took part in battle on the Ash Plains

NAME: Lenico Colony Blue
INTERESTING: medical treatment station; commanded by Hutt Baron-Surgeon Ybann; destroyed in 3678 BBY when its orbital stabilizers were destroyed by rogue Sith apprentice Exal Kressh and it fall into atmosphere

NAME: Lenico Belt
INTERESTING: miners, prospectors and pirates earned a living off radioactive asteroids here around 3678 BBY

NAME: Cairn Installation
INTERESTING: home to Imperial Remnant operation

NAME: Magagran
INTERESTING: Imperial world where Grodin Tierce helped break up a Rebel cell at the time of the Battle of Endor

NAME: Drada system
INTERESTING: Dradans hailed from unknown planet in this system; Dradans gave safe haven to Jedi after Order 66 and were exterminated, and planet scorched; nothing remained by 1 BBY

NAME: Janguine
INTERESTING: Mooloolians overran and absorbed language of jungle barbarians by 275 BBY

NAME: Tel IV
INTERESTING: home of sliideptra (poisonous annelidians which hung from tree branches by many tentacles, then incapacitate prey with a cloud of poisonous gas and dissolve them with corrosive saliva

NAME: Trinta
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fetid swamp (90%), wooded islands, mudbanks, polar ice caps
INTERESTING: home to dark side nexus; first explored by Ithorians, who immediately disliked the world; named planet Trinta after realm of demons in Ithorian mythology; deemed worthless after several failed colonization attempts by Republic; Halagad Ventor (Jedi) fled here after brutal interrogation by Vader; years later, Rebel ship crashed here and rebels were attacked by illusions and storms made from Ventor's tortured, insane soul; eventually Rebels redeemed and laid Ventor to rest

NAME: Arthon
INTERESTING: originally colonized by Ithorians; inhabited by Ottegans; Lor San Tekka visited here by 32 ABY but later disappeared into hiding

NAME: Urce
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Lesser Plooriod Cluster
PARENT: Mid Rim/Lesser Plooriod Cluster//Urce Space, Ottega/various
INTERESTING: Urce Space & Ottega Sector lay in cluster; Burna Trade Route & Entana Run created border between Urce & Ottega

NAME: Oznek
INTERESTING: Toma: green fur, yellow eyes, brown skin; Griebs Kishpaugh considered Oznek key to holding Cademimu sector; locals claimed neutrality; during CW supposedly site of droid command center

NAME: Wilpiet
grid square/sector/near Granse Space (which is near Ord Mantell)
INTERESTING: site of Alliance Depot, where Milacass (bounty hunter) stole the Waterspire (Simiyiar-class light freighter) at least two months after joining Granse Confederacy; Milacass was thena dded to Alliance's "most wanted" list

NAME: Paarin Minor
INTERESTING: Republic stronghold during CW; Republic forces used weather machines to create artificial clod-cover to screen their forces from CIS forces; later belonged to Empire, Imperial Remnant

NAME: Cademimu V
INTERESTING: population: 10 billion (Old Republic); strong military tradition (considered war chest of the Outer Rim; major trade world; by GCW Cademimu system had become a shadowport

NAME: Patch-4
INTERESTING: used as dumping ground for unrecyclable machine parts, other garbage; Orion Ferret of Bazarre Station used it to discreetly store illegal goods and used Ceasar (Watchbeast) to guard them

NAME: Bazarre Station
INTERESTING: run by Orion Ferret (arms dealer); size of small city; hundred of onboard merchant kiosks, trading posts located in an expansive arcade; welcomed business interests of almost any variety, (including illegal) away from prying Imperial eyes; black-market Imperial fighter craft and slave-ring circuits could be found here; frequented by S'kytri merchants who sold trinkets and damatized Initiation Hunts

NAME: Sirdar
INTERESTING: in remote region; settlement: Jacelle; at some point, small population of insectivorous winged xendrites was placed here to help with insect control, but reproduced at an astounding rate and soon overran the planet

NAME: Tastiged system
INTERESTING: origin point of Tastiged Flu

NAME: Borgo Prime (Location 1)
INTERESTING: shadowport built into an asteroid, home to merchants, info brokers, and unsavory individuals; originally a Rakata colony that was eventually hollowed out by miners; by 23 (BBY?) miners had left it a bare, sponge-like rock with depleted resources; when miners left they also left behind habitation equipment and it soon turned into a bustling commerce & trade center; by 19 ABY it served as financial center of Imperial Remnant

NAME: Polus
INTERESTING: blizzards, ice storms often scoured the surface; avg day temp was 50 degrees below freezing; cities and settlements were shielded by heat generators; Pyn'gani: feared foreigners, but interested in new tech and played major role in inventing carbon freezing; substantial mining income; population 600,000 during GCW; there was a brief seasonal warming period when planet received light from both suns

NAME: Cardovyte
INTERESTING: the Crystal Chaos of Cardovyte was a legendary massive cavern-like structure featuring massive crystalline stalagmites; it was featured in several holo-adventures; Poe Dameron flew the Falcon here after hyperspace skipping from the Sinta Glacier, before skipping again to Ivexia

NAME: Veronia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Veronian berry wine

NAME: Azura system
INTERESTING: home of Azuran stingcrawler (deadly insects that resembled YV slayer ships)

NAME: Pleida
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: lowland vegetation on rocky shale, temperate, variety of ecologies
INTERESTING: conflict fought here in which one side abandoned front-line forifications and pulled back, but left mines and booby traps at strategic points; opposing side established Camp Kavel in recently evacuated zone, but some command officers were injured in the advance; due to lack of aerial superiority, Captain Roff Volane assigned a group of agents to escort surgeon Pleth Juun to camp

NAME: Targarth system
INTERESTING: after Yavin, Rebels had a preliminary base here but were forced to abandon plans of using it as a main abse after Imperial probes were spotted in the area

NAME: Essien
INTERESTING: attacked by Mandalorians (based under Mount Savage) during Mandalorian Wars; shipyard here

NAME: Viridia system
INTERESTING: Viridian system's name was in the logs of a ship at the Dathomir Imperial Prison; home of Viridian termites and Viridian crystals (lightsaber crystal that produced a silvery-green color)

NAME: Ottethan
INTERESTING: capital of Ottethan Empire (comprised of 12 systems; ruled by warlord who married Neema-Da-Boda, but later fed her to the native Rancors; Vima-Da-Boda killed him in revenge in 31 BBY

NAME: Idolia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Idolian fever

NAME: Rimbaux Four
INTERESTING: home to small colony of Ithorian settlers

NAME: Doan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: furrows, quarries, mountains, stone columns & plateaus, lichen and fungi caves, mines
INTERESTING: tiny planet; economy soley focused on mining; ruled by Doan Royal House; most of population were impoverished miners; surface scattered with 5km tall, several hundred meter diameter stone columns covered in mansions, castles and palaces; underground caverns contained rare lichens and fungi with remarkable properties; in 980 BBY war erupted between nobles and mining caste

NAME: Bazaar
INTERESTING: Dravian Starport-based cargo merchants Topatz Shipping were offering payment of 4,500 credits to transport one hundred tons of imitation gemstones to Bazaar

NAME: Noonar
INTERESTING: during Cold War, host to the pacifistic Noonar Confederacy, which controlled a key stretch of territory between Old Republic and Sith Empire; run by Trophan Thanis (Imperial governor) during GCW

NAME: Baskarn
INTERESTING: Yrashu: large, green-furred, Force-sensitive, tribal; they fought Empire instictively, feeling its ties to Dark Side; group of Rebels were adopted into a tribe and were taught jungle survival the Yrashu way; tribe participated in the Battle of Baskarn with the Rebels, emerging victorious against the Empire

NAME: Gobindi
INTERESTING: 5th of 12 planets in system; capital: Mah Dala; Imperial bioweapons lab here; source of Influenza necrosi

NAME: Movris
INTERESTING: Rebel cell surmisede to be located here, as foodstuffs stolen from Nebula Consumables were traced to here

NAME: Rial Kroon system
INTERESTING: advanced vulture droids first seen here, fighting against Rodian Jedi Master Toluz Cheq and his Padawan, who were both killed in the battle

NAME: Er'Kit
INTERESTING: population 1 M - 10 M; climate similar to Tatooine's; represented in Galactic Senate by Danry Ledwellow (arrested in 22 BBY for allowing Thalassian slavers to operate here); attacked by YV

NAME: Rol II
INTERESTING: planet with Imperial prison facility; Zayl Braith sentenced to serve here but escaped in transit there

NAME: Tikath
INTERESTING: Imperial fortress world; had notoriously strong defense; group of Rebel operatives traveled here in pursuit of Etha Naru (Imperial scientist)

NAME: Balanor
INTERESTING: home of Balanoro Force mite (insects that fed on the Force)

NAME: Toskhowwl VI
INTERESTING: Jalitiri tribes known to stack severed heads of enemies into pyramids

NAME: Ithor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Vessitoar
INTERESTING: NR military training facility here

NAME: Mackar
INTERESTING: Frid: telepathic, fish-like aquatic sentients; cataclysm occurred here ~5000 BBY; spacefaring benefactors transported Frid to Iskalon

NAME: Homana system
INTERESTING: Homanans: mysterious shape-shifters who could change from Wookiee-size to Ewok-size, could mimic clothes, were slightly telepathic, numbered less than 1M by 25 ABY; explored between 3000 and 1000 BBY

NAME: Zongorlu
INTERESTING: Republic planet; conquered by Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders during Mandalorian Wars

NAME: Corosia system
INTERESTING: home to Corosian phoenix (bird renowned for beauty)

NAME: Vesla system
INTERESTING: system's star was siphoned by Darth Mekhis's Sun Razer superweapon until it was destroyed by Theron Shan

NAME: Vesla Two
INTERESTING: Darth Mekhis tested a new superweapon on the planet, poisoning the atmosphere and puncturing the crust

NAME: Vesla Three
INTERESTING: Darth Mekhis tested a new superweapon on the planet, ripping it apart with gravity-manipulating technology

NAME: unnamed planetoid
INTERESTING: a predator species here began to suffer when the planetoid's previously warm climate was affected as Darth Mekhis's Sun Razer began to destroy the system's star

NAME: Sun Razer
INTERESTING: this giant space station encompassed the Vesla system's star and siphoned its energy to create numerous superweapons until it was destroyed by Theron Shan

NAME: Prolifera system
INTERESTING: Proliferans: non-humanoid insectoids who resembled large red ants and were skilled diggers; shared name with Proliferan Empire, ruled by a monarch (Queen Yentuki during GCW)

NAME: Vnex
INTERESTING: in weeks after Endor in 4 ABY, Squadron Four of 204th Imperial Fighter Wing undertook mission to Vnex, during which no Imperial forces were lost; upon returning to Pandem Nai, where the 204th had fortified itself following Endor, Squadron Four provided Colonel Shakara Nuress with a report that summarized its mission

NAME: Cathar
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: savannas, veldts, rough uplands, city-trees, many ecological niches
INTERESTING: natives lived in city-trees; wide areas made barren by kiltik beetles; home of huge insect predators; Cathar almost wiped out by Mandalorians; survivors fled offworld but resettled after Mandalorian Wars; recovered by time of GCW; conquered by YV

NAME: Sintheti
INTERESTING: in 402 BBY, rival claimants to Sintheti's Horned Throne hired Mandalorian and Sun Guard mercenary groups; forces fought each other for 3 years amid crags and catacombs

NAME: Takobo
INTERESTING: peaceful world that boasted colorful architecture; Imperial Inquisitors captured a Force-sensitive Ithorian child here before he was rescued by Ezra Bridger and the crew of the Ghost
