NAME: Revery
INTERESTING: known for wealthy inhabitants and for its privacy; appeared blue from space; pink clouds, green and gold land, aquamarine seas

NAME: Ord Sigatt
INTERESTING: originally settled as Ordnance/Regional Depot but soon evolved into mining colony after discovery of carvanium; main settlement consisted of spaceport, energy station and water treatment facility; Dexter Jettster once owned bar here

NAME: Tangrada
INTERESTING: Tangrada-Nii (culture that later begat the Tagra-Tel culture) believed the Oridol star cluster was the face of their god; the Tagra-Tel sent starships into the cluster over a number of centuries and concluded it was alive after experiencing paranormal activity

NAME: Storinal
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: graceful urban; tropical flower gardens, countryside, rivers, hills, beaches, seas
INTERESTING: tourism was chief economic resource; Scohar Xenohealth Institute located here; homeworld of Storini glass prowlers; Ithorian starfruit grown here

NAME: Kurluvion system
INTERESTING: a Snivvian patron of Chalmun's Cantina approached Han with a shipment of holographic Hutt-smut to be delivered here, where it was extremely popular

NAME: Guuko system
INTERESTING: origin point of Guukosi (group) as well as Guuko Pure Light party (organization that once carried out genocide against Guukosi and used a winged circle as their symbol)

NAME: Jeosyn
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rocky hills, caverns, dense trees, glowing lichen; extremely slow rotation resulting in 3-month dawn & dusk cycles; temperate band at planet's dusk area
INTERESTING: extinct sentients built humanoid "droids" made of stone and crystal that collected dead bodies and carried them off to resting places; anything not rooted eitherr migrates or hibernates

NAME: Borcorash
INTERESTING: had incredibly beautiful sunsets; home to blufferavians; location of high-tech Resinem Entertainment Complex (run by Mazzic), which was damaged when a neighboring casino was bombed shortly before Endor

NAME: G'wenee
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Imperial tradeworld; operations overseen by Tarrant Snil (adversary to Grappa the Hutt captured by Kenix Kil); major city: Lay Pa-Sidian

NAME: Jussafet Four
INTERESTING: Imperial Remnant mining world attacked by warlord Zsinj; inhabitants also mined Jussafet asteroids

NAME: Jussafet Asteroids
INTERESTING: mined by inhabitants of Jussafet Four

NAME: Barpine
INTERESTING: system contained shipyards used as hq of rogue Imperial Lon Donell, who had usurped command of the Interdictor Detainer and gone pirate; planet contained a large prison facility in which captured starship crews were held

NAME: Harrikos system
NOTES: could add more info to WP
INTERESTING: system had blue sun orbited by vast ring of frozen methane, with some blocks of methane larger than cities

NAME: Harrikos-Fifteen
NOTES: could add more info to WP
INTERESTING: space station research facility studying nearby Oridol Cluster; speck of metal in vast ring of frozen methane; standard design for no more than 30 residents: two tapering metallic spires connected by slender docking strip (SWG design?)

NAME: Oridol Cluster
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron p. 86 (desc, 2nd short jump from Jiruus) p. 176 (Tangrada-Nii and Tagra-Tel legends of Oridol Cluster)/
INTERESTING: a short hyperspace jump from Jiruus; source of legends by the Tangrada-Nii and subsequent Tagra-Tel cultures); site of running battle between NR Nebulon-B frigate Hellion's Dare and the Imperial Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier Aerie (carrying two squadrons of the 204th Imperial Fighter wing, also known as Shadow Wing; the Hellion's Dare was destroyed here

NAME: Daro
INTERESTING: though data claimed the planet lacked settlements or installations, the Empire had a secret military base here within a mountain, shortly after the regime's formation, where troopers were recruited as part of Project War-Mantle. Gregor, one of the instructors, attempted to desert and was captured, but was able to send a message to fellow deserter Rex; Clone Force 99 was able to save him, but Hunter was captured

NAME: Jiruus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron p. 30, 32 (revelry) p. 152 (prize jewel of "the sector's" Imperial Moff, muster point for a missing NR recon expedition, condition, discovery of battle site by Quell on last discovery jump), p. 157 (no galactic comms; Oridol Cluster nearby)/
INTERESTING: pilots of the NR's Hound and Riot Squadrons celebrated on Jiruus some time after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY when the NR Nebulon-B frigate Hellion's Dare was attacked by the Galactic Empire above Jiruus, setting off a chase into the nearby Oridol Cluster

NAME: The Grinning Moon
INTERESTING: visible in the sky as pilots of the New Republic's Hound and Riot Squadrons celebrated on Jiruus some time after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY

NAME: Vahaba Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: home to ore miners, skilled metal fabricators; once had trade ties with Alderaan; part of Zsinj space; Battle of Selaggis began here

NAME: Halmad
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: trade center at hub of several hyperroutes; mining industry failed between 200 and 100 BBY but planet remained important due to hyperroutes; origin point of Halmad Prime (expensive exported grain alcohol only available on-planet through black market); site of Quelii Sector Academy; many Axxilans relocated here during CW; chosen as target for raids by Wraith Squadron while disguised as Hawk-bat pirates and stole TIE Interceptors from an Imperial base here

NAME: Selaggis VI
INTERESTING: yellow-orange gas giant with constantly changing storm patterns; circled by heavy debris ring that may have been another moon; site of Battle of Selaggis

NAME: Selcaron
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: brown soil, gray seas, barren rock
INTERESTING: colonized by humans without Zsinj's permission, leading him to decimate the colonists

NAME: Marcellus Nebula
INTERESTING: contained Marcellus system

NAME: Marca
INTERESTING: constant daylight; in Marcellus Nebula; c. 30 years prior to Endor, Dynamic Synergetics, Inc. established a Hyperbaride synthesis plant here, overseen by Vost Tyne (former retired Imperial Admiral); Rebels stumbled across the planet, met up with local Sekcts, and destroyed the plant

NAME: Quelii
INTERESTING: humans lived in villages here; devastated by Mandalorian attack leading up to Mandalorian Wars; some natives escaped to Republic Space, including young man from village Squinquargesimus named Alek who later became a Jedi, then fell to the Dark Side, becoming Darth Malak

NAME: Ord Cestus
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountain ranges, caves, volcanoes, craters, red deserts, hills, plains
INTERESTING: exported droids, fungi; over 800 types of medicinal or edible fungi grew here; planet's water contained microorganisms lethal to offworlders, however a cheese-like product of local chitliks (creatures) was an antidote; planet scouted by Kilaphor Dashta c. 422 BBY; joined Republic, made prison world c. 321 BBY; 150 years prior to CW, Yoda saved X'Ting from a disaster; 50 years later, populace hit by Cestus Cybernetics-released plague, resulting in the company seizing the planet; during CW, X'Ting population dropped to only a few thousand

NAME: Lorardia system
INTERESTING: during Cold War, survey team charting uninhabited terrestrial world in system recieved unusual readings caused by large deposits of maranium under the surface

NAME: Lorardia (Lorardian)
INTERESTING: one of the Mistryl worlds destroyed by Cavrilhu Pirates

NAME: Pedd Four
INTERESTING: by 25 ABY, NR stronghold; during YV invasion, Mandalorian Protectors and Boba Fett covertly provided intel to NR, who disregarded it, believing it false; NR redeployed troops to defend Pedd Four, causing New Holgha to fall to YV; fell to YV in 27 ABY anyway

NAME: Nalros
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Celanon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban sprawl, advertising screens, farms, plains, forests, oceans
INTERESTING: six continents; important trade world (comparable to Byblos, Yaga Minor); capital: Celanon City; controlled by Mandalorians during Mandalorian Wars; important regional power broker in millennium after Ruusan Reformations; prosperous, populous port that attracted investment; CIS stronghold and Republic target; Pellaeon's flagship Reaper lost at Battle of Celanon

NAME: Flyntaria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Flyntarian tabac stick

NAME: Doli
INTERESTING: rumored location of Sith holocron

NAME: Varkana
INTERESTING: following the Hosnian Cataclysm in 34 ABY, Resistance spy Norath Kev operated here; Kazuda Xiono, Jarek Yeager, CB-23 and Synara San took a transport here to search for the spy

NAME: Morseer
INTERESTING: Morseerian colony (Morseerian homeworld unknown); Morseerians were underlings of Drackmarians

NAME: Corstris
INTERESTING: Imperial Intelligence suspected Corstris as location of hidden Rebel base before Yavin; its forested terrain didn't impress Han during his time serving there

NAME: Fere
INTERESTING: famed for shipyards that produced most luxurious ships of their age; by 192 BBY populace & culture still stable, but later died out due to plague brought in from offworlders searching for a hideaway during a war

NAME: Ova
INTERESTING: presumably sucked into infinity by an Infinity Wave in 30 BBY

NAME: Varn
INTERESTING: home to amphibious fishers and ocean farmers who lived on archipelagos; immortalized in dull holodocumentary "Varn, World of Water" which later served as basis for the Kamarians' Cult of Varn (causing no end of irritation for Varn locals)

NAME: Battlemoon
INTERESTING: airless moon, converted to hold a superlaser dish, later destroyed by Luke

NAME: Drackmar
INTERESTING: methane atmosphere; Drackmarians: had to wear special helmets when offworld; some Morseerians lived here as well

NAME: Akiva
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, catacombs, jungles, canyons, bays, oceans
NOTES: Closest planets to "Raydonia" listed as: Akiva, Tatooine, Geonosis, Mustafar (?) and Dermos
INTERESTING: remote world once part of CIS, who built a large droid factory under the surface; fell under occupation of the Empire after CW; Satrapy of Myrra collaborated with Empire; Imperial Remnant gathered for a summit above Akiva after Endor; Akiva became first Outer Rim world to join NR as Imperials fled and natives rebelled; experienced "mausim" rainy season; famed for thunder, flash floods

NAME: Dathomir
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: thick forests, snow-capped mountains, coastal lakes, tar-pits, powerful rivers, broad savannas, small ice caps; dramatic rift valleys, volcanoes
INTERESTING: obscure world somewhat smaller than Coruscant; even under NR, 9/10s of planet remained unexplored (inhabited area limited to small area along edge of one of three main continents -- zone of uplands and river plains boredered by ocean on one side, vast desert on other

NAME: Koratas
INTERESTING: deposits of neutronium, lommite and zersium; mined by Empire for use in making durasteel

NAME: Dathomir Station
INTERESTING: Imperial space station established in orbit after Imperial penal colony established on planet; ships that brought supplies or required emergency repairs were allowed to dock with appropriate Imperial authorizations

NAME: Last Nav Station
INTERESTING: (presumably Imperial) stpace station orbiting Dathomir

NAME: Rancor Base
INTERESTING: Warlord Zsinj's secret hq, orbiting Dathomir; contained shipyard with drydock to servide Zsinj's fleet, including Iron Fist TIE Raptors developed here; destroyed in 8 ABY by Hapans

NAME: Babygnon
NOTES: fix weird capitalization?

NAME: Mining Outpost
INTERESTING: traders of the Miners' Alliance bought mining resources from independent space miners

NAME: Heart of Dathomir/Heart of Dathomir Nebula
INTERESTING: pulsating red nebula believed by the sisterhood of the Dark Veil order that a powerful raging entity called Dathomir's Vitality existed at the heart of the nebula and sacrificed beings to it

NAME: Dark Force Nebula
INTERESTING: nebula located in quadrant of Dathomir system; interdicted by Empire after Yavin, when Imperial forces established a base behind the rings of asteroids surrounding the nebula

NAME: Asteroid rings
INTERESTING: rings of asteroids surrounded Dark Force Nebula

NAME: Cedre system
INTERESTING: system contained 6 stars; roughly 3 light-years from Dathomir

NAME: Pil Diller
INTERESTING: once home to singing fig trees (now extinct)

NAME: Orimanther
INTERESTING: visted by Chevin slaver Phylus Mon during waning years of Republic; rumor said he knocked a flcok of battlebirds out of the sky with a Force storm when he was unsuccessful at capturing them

NAME: Landor system
INTERESTING: known to be pirate-infested c. 44 BBY

NAME: Ferrous Aurora Nebula
INTERESTING: travel through nebula considered dangerous due to presence of Ni'lyahin Smugglers

NAME: Quyste
INTERESTING: Talon Karrde had a training center here; he sent H'sishi (Togorian female) there before 18 ABY to study starship operations

NAME: Merj
INTERESTING: had a Type II atmosphere (breath masks required); homeworld of the methane-breathing Morseerians; CIS member during CW; around this time it received clandestine support and equipment from smugglers, including Has Obitt; as part of the war effort against the Republic, Morseerian scientists developed a biological warfare agent against clone troopers, prompting a mission to capture scientists and end the research

NAME: Moseum
INTERESTING: believed to have been homeworld of Jenna Zan Arbor

NAME: Tierell
INTERESTING: Tierell and Feriae Junction were the two worlds with the most traffic coming and going from Loop Worlds of the Gordian Reach

NAME: Galltine
INTERESTING: Elea Poista (Rebel operative, Bespin Motors Exex) created a false identity ("Kel" from Galltine) to sell contraband on black market

NAME: Ventrux
INTERESTING: homeworld of Jenna Zan Arbor; original HQ of Arbor Industries, but labs were closed when Jenna relocated to Simpla-12

NAME: Katalia
INTERESTING: home of Katalian Apes

NAME: Druulgotha system
INTERESTING: Druulgothans: lizard-like

NAME: Amorris
INTERESTING: small world ruled by Drackmarians, who contested Imperial rule, but were eventually pushed out; occupied by Cavrilhu Pirates around 0 BBY but their base was shut down after the base's operator was arrested by NRI officer; Lando fold Niles Ferrier he might be able to seal a couple of old IPV-1 System Patrol Craft from the abandoned base

NAME: Wol Cabassh
INTERESTING: home of Wol Cabasshites, plasma leeches

NAME: Praven Prime
INTERESTING: contained nations of L'Xing and Guvandi Collective, who may have controlled star system itself; nations incited into long war by HK-47 sometime after 3959 BBY, which forced the Republic out of Gu-vandi space

NAME: Gorm
INTERESTING: home of gorm-worm; academy here whose architect held several secrets and was guarded by keepers who only let archaeologists study in exchange for a donation

NAME: Wrodi system
INTERESTING: origin point of Wrodian carpets

NAME: Bandomeer
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Envos
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Bandomeer
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ag fields, rolling plains (historical), industrial wastes, mountains, rocky plains, oceans, desert
INTERESTING: known for high concentration of ionite; roughly divided in half between giant landmass and the Great Sea of Bandomeer; many predators; strip-mined by companies such as Offworld Mining Corporation; even orbiting asteroids were rich in minerals but couldn't be mined due to collision risk; Ithorian colony here

NAME: Fitee
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Thomquizzar system
INTERESTING: location of dirtside Thomquizzar (Imperial) Naval Base, constructed before 0 BBY

NAME: Vanquo
INTERESTING: mining world; site of one of the early Mandalorian Wars battles; resource world for Taris; haven for refugees of early Mandalorian conquests; part of Jebble-Vanquo-Tarnith Republic Navy security cordon; Mandalorians conquered the world in 3964 BBY; rugged world with harsh winter, brilliant starry sky, at least one moon with green appearance

NAME: Botajef
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: HQ of Botajef Shipyards (connected to surface by 325 km space elevator cables); after CW, ruled by Empire through a governorship, but governor Quesl declared secession; Thrawn defused situation by revealing it was a ruse to steal valuable Jefi artwork; Eravana (bulk freighter) suffered a malfunction here; southern continent covered in shipbuilding facilities; homeworld of Natasi Daala

NAME: Qualtrough
NOTES: "Outer Rim" misspelled in WP page for Qualtrough System
INTERESTING: c. 500 BBY, Chu'unthor (Jedi Order's mobile praxeum ship) visited here; Jedi helped negotiate a truce amongst the populace

NAME: Shadren V
INTERESTING: home to an Imperial laval base, which was attacked by Rebel Alliance during GCW

NAME: Crombach Nebula
INTERESTING: Irmenu system was located in fringes of nebula; navigational hazard for centuries; bridged by Freia Kallea in 3705 BBY when she linked the Mandalorian Road to the Sprizen End Run as part of her blazing of the Hydian Way; site of Battle of Crombach Nebula during CW, where Wom-Nii Gnaden (Jedi Master) was killed

NAME: Irmenu
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: island archipelagos covered with sand, forests, and meadowlands; rough oceans
INTERESTING: located in fringes of Crombach Nebula; isolated for millennia; ocean-covered with a single continental shelf covering half its surface, mostly covered with shallow seas; its highest points formed island archipelagos, ranging from sandy spits to towering craggy islands; feudal world known for its seafaring and stern religious traditions; single large moon had eccentric orbit, causing dramatic tides

NAME: Narigus III
INTERESTING: Lauren and Sam (thieves) once stole the Kubaz Insect (valuable statue) from Rock'co's art collection on this planet, but the statue turned out to be a fake

NAME: Harloen
INTERESTING: considered to be the swoop racing capital of Outer Rim

NAME: New Bornalex
INTERESTING: CIS-aligned; homeworld of Cyl Sant and daughter Rystall; during Serenno theater of Outer Rim Sieges, Jedi-led fleets assaulted the world and Ord Redama in attempt to attack CIS strongholds of Celanon and Serreno

NAME: Raydonia
INTERESTING: similar to Felucia in size, color (blue-green), and being completely covered in flora, fauna; sky filled with crimson clouds, like Dathomir's; Obi-Wan and Asajj Ventress fought Darth Maul and his brother Savage Opress aboard a Turtle Tanker above Raydonia

NAME: Sheris
INTERESTING: NR defended Bhir'khi Pass from Thrawn's forces to keep them from reaching Marter An spaceport

NAME: Belsmuth II
INTERESTING: had Imperial technical university, converted to a pilot training academy by Zsinj (Imperial warlord); Rogue and Nova squadrons assaulted the academy to confuse Zsinj as to the location of Han Solo's task force

NAME: Mepha'as Prime
INTERESTING: had many casinos, gaming halls, arenas, racing tracks

NAME: Rirsack
INTERESTING: Lar Ndigo (NR Lieutenant) fought bravely here sometime during or prior to 13 ABY

NAME: Katraasii
INTERESTING: site of a CW battle; Clone Commander CT-55/11-9009 embarassed himself during a retreat here and was demoted to captain; helf by Imperial Remnant for several years after fall of Empire; by 40 ABY it was a member world of Galactic Federation of Free Alliances; hosted at least one spaceport, also called Katraasii

NAME: Borkeen Belt
INTERESTING: belt of stone and iron asteroids; said to be the remains of a destroyed planet; notorious for destroying ships that entered it; as of 22 BBY, largest space slug ever recorded was discovered here (80 m); Rogar Farnoster (bestselling author who accompanied the scientists who investigated the slug) wrote a novel about a ship's captain and crew pursuing a massive slug through the Borkeen Belt

NAME: Solaest
INTERESTING: site of Solaest uprising, suppressed by Imperial Navy; Leia (aboard Tantiv IV) secretly aised those fleeing Empire

NAME: Alba-16
INTERESTING: discovered by Republic scouts between Great Hyperspace War and Kanz Disorders; joined Republic as early as Great Sith War; joined Revan's Sith Empire during Jedi Civil War; joined Republic when Brotherhood of Darkness fell; remained Republic-loyal for several millennia; in midst of civil war in 44 BBY; used as penal camp; joined CIS then returned to Republic then Empire

NAME: Tertiary Feswe
INTERESTING: notable only for being on emergency routes blazed by Rebel scouts ahead of Evacuation of Yavin; Rebel forces originally intended to jump from Feswe Corridor to Tertiary Feswe before making getaway to Feriae Junction and Hydian Way, but Empire cut off that route, forcing them to try to escape past Feswe Prime

NAME: Yavin
INTERESTING: orbited by two planets and a captured comet

NAME: Fiddanl (96NK3F2
INTERESTING: dense, spherical core of gold-platinum alloys and other pure ores; orbited close to its sun; upper mantle was a shallow layer of liquid mercury, which reflected a lot of light; continental plates constantly shifted atop an underground sea of mercury, sometimes up to 630km per day; 18 continent-sized landmasses; rapid crystal growth beneath continents; thin but stable atmosphere

NAME: Stroiketcy
INTERESTING: comet whose rocky core (with deposits of iridium, heglum and malsarr) only reached the surface in small pockets; during its summer most ice melted and sea levels rose; almost all water frozen during winter; weather dominated by rain, storms and fog; small part of atmosphere "leaked" into space, forming a small but visible tail; first charted by Corellian explorers; water was relatively pure

NAME: Yavin Prime
INTERESTING: four years after Battle of Yavin, Wedge and Vanguard Squadron were sent here to steal the Victorum (ISD-II) for NR's Project Starhawk

NAME: Yavin 4
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungles, rainforests, mountains, hills, valleys, ruined temples
INTERESTING: ancient warrior Massassi enslaved by Sith, and constructed temples c. 5000 BBY; temples later home to Rebel HQ and launched strike against Death Star here; Rebels evacuated after Battle of Yavin to escape reprisals, but later sent missions to retrieve data center left behind; Shara Bey and Kes Dameron settled here 6 months after Endor; later site of a Jedi Academy

NAME: Yavin 7
INTERESTING: one of four moons shown on Death Star's tactical map during Battle of Yavin (may have been a larger moon, or capable of sustaining life and therefore a Rebel presence)

NAME: Yavin 8
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: equatorial purple mountain ranges with attendant rivers and lakes, vast expanses of snow & tundra
INTERESTING: Massassi traveled here to seek aid from Melodies against Exar Kun, who had imprisoned Massassi children in the Golden Globe; arid, cold world capable of supporting life; only liquid water found in equatorial lakes and rivers, home to Melodies: amphibious humanoids who only lived underwater after age 20; another humanoid race lived here until Palpatine carried out a genocide against them

NAME: Yavin 13
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, rocky plains, cacti forests, grassy plains, open shallow seas
INTERESTING: hot, arid moon with a surface resmbling Byss cheese from space; no planetary government; ruled by separate tribes; occaionally visited by treasure hunters; Slith: serpentine with nomadic hunter-gatherer society concentrated in rocky areas; Gerbs: rodentlike, lived in underground warrens, farmed moon's grasslands; neither left Yavin 13; YV wiped out all life after 26 ABY

NAME: Yavin 22
INTERESTING: originally an asteroid captured by Yavin Prime's gravity; uninhabitable; Suz Tanwa (Rodian treasure hunter, archaeologist) found remains of Yavin Station and her ancestor Suvam Tan (Rodian scavenger, former slave of Exar Kun) here

NAME: Yavin Station
INTERESTING: Republic supply depot built during Great Sith War; abandoned after Exar Kun's defeat; Suvam Tan (formerly Kun's slave) used it as a scavenging, trading post; eventually the station began to crumble; Suvam hid prized possessions on Yavin's 3 habitable moons and sent a data crystal to his son on Rodia; station exploded and crashed into Yavin 22 sometime after Galactic War 3 centuries later

NAME: Victory Station
INTERESTING: space habitat built by entrepreneurs after Endor, offering tours of the Battlefield of Yavin; only operated briefly under NR and later closed and stripped for salvage

NAME: Vaal
INTERESTING: trajectory around its sun intersected several asteroid fields; Vader crash-landed here in TIE Advanced after escaping Battle of Yavin, near the remote Imperial Relay Outpost V-798; Vader saved several native Hyenax creatures from a large predator, and later left them to maul to death several lax Stormtrooper guards while he took the base's Lambda-class shuttle' population less than 1 M c. 25 ABY

NAME: Rukabi Major
INTERESTING: Glorzo (Hutt) issued a contest here during the Cold War in which inner would aquire a hologram program named Holiday, who later belonged to Tharan Cedrax

NAME: Selitan
INTERESTING: mining planet

NAME: Denarii Station
INTERESTING: scientific observation post in Denarii Nebula; orignally used by astrophysicists for studying the nebula; fell into disuse centuries befoe 43 ABY, but still used by desperate as a hideout

NAME: Pinoora
NOTES: hyperlanes not listed in sidebar
INTERESTING: served as one of the most strategic trade worlds in Gordian Reach; active entertainment hub for spacers between hyperjumps; inhabited by hardy insects domesticated by Human colonists for their meat, eggs and chitin (could be used to make ceramics); during Blockade of Yavin in 0 ABY, a Mon Cal task force attacked Imperial units stationed on the planet to assist Rebels' evacuation

NAME: Denarii N.
INTERESTING: remnant of double-star supernova destroyed by Naga Sadow during Great Hyperspace War of 5000 BBY

NAME: Torque
INTERESTING: sector capital; "Torqua-na" in Huttese; HQ of Bwahl the Hutt; important commercial hub in Gordian Reach; one of the busiest spaceports on the Junction-Tierell Loop; nevertheless, most of its cities lacked the glitz of oher sector world capitals

NAME: Torque High Port
NOTES: could use WP article (source: EA Gordian Reach pages)
INTERESTING: most sector-government business was conducted on this old space station

NAME: Jovan system
INTERESTING: uneventful system focused on agricultural activities, according to Sax Hastur (TIE Pilot); Empire was to send a task force to Jovan system right after Battle of Portocari

NAME: Jovan III
INTERESTING: fertile agriworld crisscrossed by robo-harvesters, dotted with agricultural research labs

NAME: Jovan Station
INTERESTING: primary Republic station in Gordian Reach during CW; after Yavin, Empire converted Jovan station to HQ of Yavin Blockade, seriously affecting commerce of entire system; eight bulk freighters (or ISDs) could dock here at once; Yoda bought the B-7 light freighter Nighthawk at a junkyard here;

NAME: Presbalin
INTERESTING: one of the Loop Worlds' primary commerce hubs after Humans settled here; discovered to be dotted with abandoned alien cities with strange architecture

NAME: Kravos system
INTERESTING: dead system on the edge of Sith Empire space, filled with ionized gas, due to a partially dispersed accretion disk; orange-colored gas giant formed nearby; Zeerid Korr and Aryn Leneer traveled there while trying to get to Sith Empire-held Coruscant by using an electromagnetic clamp to latch onto a ship in an Imperial convoy

NAME: Near Indosa
INTERESTING: heavily excavated by miners for millennia; most of planet's mineral resources were drained, so many miners traveled to Far Indosa during last days of the Republic

NAME: Jalindi
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: colossal red rock pillars surrounded by mist
INTERESTING: around 1 BBY, the Rebel Alliance intended to hack an Imperial relay station but ended up destroying the facility instead

NAME: Far Indosa system
INTERESTING: many miners left Near Indosa for this system because it held more prospects for continued mining after millennia of mining drained Near Indosa of its mineral resources

NAME: Trinovat
INTERESTING: sunny world; Trinovates: three-eyed

NAME: Durgen's Star debris field
INTERESTING: debris field of tumbling rock and ice; remants of ancient supernova; spacer tales told of prospectors finding unimaginably ancient technology of unknown purpose here; by 43 ABY generations of mining operations lured by rumors had searched debreis field for anything worth extracting

NAME: Bronsoon
INTERESTING: founded by Human colonists from the Core in ancient times; Bronsoonians had strict rules about gender relations, with laws governing everything from marriage between castes to eye contact and who could walk where; Bronsoonian dramas were consequently all about forbidden love between castes; slow, little-used route connected Bronsoon with Maridun

NAME: Xochtl
INTERESTING: Bagmims: tall, had reputation as good fighters when angered; in last days of GCW, a committee of Bagmims commanded an Assault Frigate that patrolled near the Imperial Remnant as part of fleet commanded by Vriss (NR Admiral)

NAME: Povanaria
INTERESTING: windswept world; Povanarians: froglike, NR member in 19 ABY who served in NR defense fleet

NAME: Wentrion Gaps
INTERESTING: CIS had major logistics issues here during CW

NAME: Algarra II
INTERESTING: Tord Gamb (con man) ran several schemes here, which contributed to the 25,000-credit bounty placed on him by the NR

NAME: Pandem Nai
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron p. 138, 215; Timelines map/p. 355 (Argai Minor supply lines maybe ran all the way to Pandem Nai?) ; p. 373 (53 hours until in position) p. 375 (fortifications) p. 407 (attacks granting access to Skangravi-Mestun), p. 410 (system desc, methane belt); p. 412 (desc planet, one black moon) p. 477 (desc Induchron) p. 369 (Syndulla's Barma battle group secured 6 systems over 8 days, positioning fleet to take control of Skangravi-Mestun Regional Hyperlane without exposing newly freed systems to counterattack; hyperlane led 9/10ths of way to Pandem Nai, close enough to open dozens of potential paths for final leg; Celanon Spur was among the longer, easier, more obvious routes to the system, or the winding path through H'grathi where the scouts of the Hellion's Dare were originally spotted; access to the Hyperlane multiplied route options tenfold)
INTERESTING: gas mining world shrouded in scarlet clouds; one black moon; atmosphere highly reactive to turbolaser fire; resource-rich; fortified by 204th Imperial Fighter "Shadow" Wing after Endor; city of Induchron composed of low warehouses, processing facilities, prefab housing; Orbital One (204th base) and other Tibanna refineries in upper atmosphere; Orbital One destroyed by Alphabet Squadron

NAME: Ie-Tikkaht
INTERESTING: (placeholder name given); ashen planet; by 4 ABY, spice-mining outpost of no more than a few thousand colonists; Imperial colonel Shakara Nuress traveled here aboard the ISD Pursuer and obliterated the colony from orbit to protect the location of the 204th Imperial Fighter Wing's nearby base on Pandem Nai; afterward, 4 other outposts in 3 nearby systems remained nearby to target

NAME: Phatrong
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: thin and roughly linear continents, hills, mountains, canyons, fjords, plains, oceans
INTERESTING: gravity heavier than standard; atmosphere uncommon; thin, roughly linear continents stretched in bands running between poles; Republic member and later Imperial world; after dissolution of Imperial Senate, local governor oversaw planet directly; only dealt with Kyuzo clovocs (tribes) when necessary, as long as taxes were paid; Kyuzo rebels nevertheless tried to bolster the Alliance

NAME: Altair
NOTES: name misspelled on sidebar of Altair system WP page

NAME: Altair 9
INTERESTING: dark, swampy world; during Galactic War between Republic and Sith Empire, Vander (Republic general) waged a 10-month siege of Klemark (capital) to free it from Empire; Eclipse squad disabled city's defenses but later went insane; on the edge of CIS space during CW; small skirmish here in which ARC Trooper Alpha-98 was attacked by a broca (large, aggressive reptilian) while fighting Seperatists

NAME: Uhltenden
INTERESTING: surrounded by debris ring from many wrecked starships; toxic atmosphere; no natural life resided on the planet; BOba Fett captured Ob Fortuna above Uhltenden

NAME: Vispil
INTERESTING: planet that refused warlord Zsinj's bribes and fought against him

NAME: Traptoforia system
INTERESTING: home to Traptoforian razor-slugs

NAME: Syndaar
INTERESTING: capital of Thrasybule sector; location of Syndaar Military Prep School

NAME: Bakkah
INTERESTING: Sith amulet discovered here at height of GCW; Vader and Luke both raced to secure it

NAME: Zona Miki system
INTERESTING: by 1750 BBY, Dark underlord (new Sith leader) assailed the space stations along the Zona Miki route with his Black Knights; the Republic hired Mandalorian mercenaries who helped defeat him on Malrev IV

NAME: Malrev IV
INTERESTING: history strongly associated with Sith; Palpatine visited Sith temple here; after battle of Endor, temple used by Cartariun to force indigenous Irrukiine to attack Rogue Squadron

NAME: Keros
INTERESTING: home of cidwen (predatory black winged insects with dangerous beaks and claws, which grew up to a 1m wingspan

NAME: Edonaaris
INTERESTING: obscure; the Malka'an Eternal (enormous pleasure cruiser) crashed here after crew was forced to abandon it, leaving behind all its droids; ship was later found by a crew of Human scavengers who were killed by the surviving maintenance droid SCr-114, who then stole their ship

NAME: Hettsk
INTERESTING: NR world conquered by Imperial forces during Thrawn campaign; location of successful rescue mission by Katarn Commandos (Rebel/NR commando group later known as Page's Commandos)

NAME: Azna
INTERESTING: between Tintel and Fodro on Dahvil-Fodro Hyperspace Promenade (illegal starship race)

NAME: Phindar
INTERESTING: attacked by CIS during CW; later affiliated with Galactic Empire; later host to a battle during GCW; controlled by the Syndicat (criminal organization) until 44 BBY, then overthrown by Obi-Wan and Anakin; Phindians then elected a governor; an early member of NR

NAME: Phindar Station
INTERESTING: major spaceport (either orbiting or above) Phindar; HQ of Sentient Property Crime Bureau; Captain Quecks was the maxiumum authority in the station; Quecks and his troops couldn;t stop Asajj Ventress and her assassin droids here in 20 BBY

NAME: Althir III
INTERESTING: remote, independent planet with a system of rocky planetary rings; discovered by Mandalorians early during the Old Sith Wars and had to defend themselves; first battle in 3976 BBY; eventually fell to forces of Canderous Ordo; liberated when Republic stormed the world in 3960 BBY under Revan (Jedi Knight); remained in contested space through New Sith Wars until it was deemed safe to remain independent at time of Ruusan Reformation; remained free of Galactic Empire

NAME: Barison
INTERESTING: waterworld which supplied fish, kelp, and seafood to worlds in the Back Reach; Barisoni: many renounced technology for religious reasons; Airen Cracken had to rescue his droid Vee Gee from Barisoni pirates using a restraining bolt deactivator

NAME: Quanducial
INTERESTING: known to greater galaxy by last millennium of Republic

NAME: Usta
INTERESTING: run as a joint venture between Ardans of Ardan system and T'sarki of Kalishik; energy mining left the world cratered and poisonous

NAME: Kalishik
INTERESTING: T'sarki: seal-like, regarded as friendly, but were wuick to take offense at perceived dishonesty by other species; played a part in industry of Back Reach, seeking work permits for the factories of Feldwes; mining on Usta was a joint venture between T'sarki and Ardans of Ardan system

NAME: Vallusk Cluster
INTERESTING: no habitable worlds; common location for starships to exit hyperspace and recalibrate navicomputers for a trip to Arkuda; Ackbar engaged four ISDs here as a distraction so Rebels at Massassi Station could run the Imperial blockade during the Evacuation of Yavin 4

NAME: Arda system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: the Steadfast (Jedi Master Eeth Koth's cruiser) attacked near this system during CW; Koth taken hostage by Grievous;

NAME: Arda I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: a canyon known as the Gauntlet concealed a hidden Rebel base; native Doran'enoks were semi-sentient

NAME: Arda II (Ethain System)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: small world that maintained neutrality during GCW; Mag Doum (spy) reported a rebel presence here, and rulers then openly supported Rebellion in fear of Imperial reprisal; invaded in Stenax Massacres in 4 ABY, after Endor; T-6 diodems (home appliance units which could be built into X-wings or TIEs) were manufactured in city of Tun Wala

NAME: Arda III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: part of Xim's Empire; only Humans were known to colonize this world

NAME: Feldwes
INTERESTING: industrial powerhouse of the Back Reach; work prospects drew numerous T'sarki, B'trillans, and Humans to seek work permits here

NAME: Pygorix
NOTES: add info from Gordian Reach section to WP page
INTERESTING: religious retreat known for centuries of study of various species' religious beliefs and experiences; made rich by port fees collected by the customs station in orbit

NAME: Pygorix Station *
INTERESTING: served as customs port; port fees here made the world below rich

NAME: The Cometwash
INTERESTING: surrounded by swarms of comets; stopping point for many spacers rechecking jump calculaions after navigating around the Roil; popular with tourists

NAME: Karsten's World
NOTES: no WP page for Karsten's World; add info to system page?
INTERESTING: system closed to all but the high abbots of Pygorix

NAME: Arkuda
INTERESTING: renowned for its night skies due to proximity to the Roil (large stellar nursery/nebula); Arkudans: squad, vaguely ursine, produced highly ornamental jewelled gaming cubes for hundred of years prior to Yavin, and which were believed by some to bring good luck; Tionne Solusar (Jedi) owned a fluffy pair she hung from the ceiling of the Lore Seeker (her starship)

NAME: Gulvitch
NOTES: Junction-Tierell Loop not listed on sidebar
INTERESTING: home to a struggling colony founded by Povanarians and Bagmim; rarely visited by those who could afford to go elsewhere

NAME: Korphir
INTERESTING: temporary home to Havet Storm (young Force-sentitive Human, later a Rebel agent) in 1 BBY, who found employ as a mind-reader in a circus until his fellow performers grew suspicious of his strange abilities and made an attempt on his life, after which he fled; known home of pirates

NAME: Tenara
INTERESTING: centuries before 43 ABY, planet served as a bolt-hole for pirates from Korphir, who used hidden vaults to store their loot; planet gained reputation as a fabled treasure world as a result; by 43 ABY it was a farming world; inhabitants offered sightseeing tours of old and dusty pirate hiding places to earn extra credits

NAME: Capella
INTERESTING: mining world mostly worked by droids and robominers of Ardan manufacture; source of Capellan turg-roots

NAME: Little Capella
INTERESTING: Rapora Mining (company) operated Rapora Mining Center here in 2 ABY as one of many new facilities throughout the Outer Rim

NAME: Randorn 2
INTERESTING: home of primitive Mizx species, who developed myths in which native ibliton (dominant predators) originated from the demented soul of Hershoon the Destroyer (being of immense evil)

NAME: Belderone Sector Prison Asteroid *
INTERESTING: Lemo and Sanda (gang leaders) incarcerated here after being captured by bounty hunters in Keyorin system; Han and Luke traveled here to obtain info on location of a Dancing Goddess statue they possessed

NAME: Maridun
INTERESTING: comfortable climate; a colony of Lurmen wishing to escape war settled here during CW; Seperatist general Lok Durd sought an alliance with Lurmen while plotting to test a weapon called the Defoliator on them; Jedi defended them and captured Durd; in 11 BBY, Empire officially discovered planet and set up mining colonies; after Empire reduced its presence, Hutts enslaced much of planet

NAME: Chirrion
INTERESTING: home to Imperial military base

NAME: Fara's Belt
INTERESTING: site of Imperial communication station

NAME: Fara's Belt Station
INTERESTING: Imperial communication station; target of Rebel raid in 0 ABY; unbeknownst to Rebels, but Imperial Intelligence had broken their codes and intercepted their plans, so the Rebel defeat here was total

NAME: Nadhe
INTERESTING: remote world that defied Palpatine shortly after rise of Empire and suffered an unspecified devastation as a result

NAME: Spintir
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, villages, mountains, caves, farms, fields
INTERESTING: wealthy trade world; home to a Jedi Temple called the Dawn Temple

NAME: Quell
INTERESTING: system contested throughout CW; high atmosphere was site of Battle of Quell in 21 BBY, which resulted in eradication of Aayla Secura's Republic fleet

NAME: Mazuma
INTERESTING: site of Lucre Cosminational Bank where Han and Lando were to pick up 200k credits courtesy of Rebel Fighter COmmand

NAME: Ceriun
INTERESTING: a tattooed Sith Lord journeyed here c. 1000 BBY to retrieve a Sith holocron taken there by a Jedi

NAME: Lucazec
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: joined Republic after fall of Xim's Empire in 25100 BBY; a group of Rebels once stole an Imperial corvette called the Carrion Spike and launched an attack on Imperial mining operations before broadcasting a holovid of their activities; Fallanassi world of origin, but fled when Cassio Tagge tried to recruit them to the Empire; conquered by the YV

NAME: Stygeon Prime
INTERESTING: mountainous, snowy planet; almost completely devoid of life except for Tibidees (silicon-based manta-like creatures distantly related to Neebrays and mynocks); prison world where Sidious and Tyranus imprisoned Maul in the Spire, a Confederate prison; Maul later broken out by Mandalorian forces that were part of the Shadow Collective

NAME: Noryath
INTERESTING: source of Noryath meatbread

NAME: Vjun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: in the wake of the Emergences of the Great Hyperspace Disaster, Vjun was among many Outer Rim locations whose hospitals were overrun with victims; home to famous tailors who wove Dooku's elegant cloak; location of Bast Castle (fortress used by Dooku and later Vader); dark, almost lifeless rock known for acidic rainfall and resultant lack of plant life

NAME: Divac 7
INTERESTING: site of a battle Lonkin (Imperial trooper) hailed as a hero for participating in

NAME: Paklan
INTERESTING: Maul and Savage Opress took refuge here in 20 BBY after a bounty was placed on their heads by Ja'Boag (Gossam leader of Rim Commercial Mining corporation); Savage and Maul brutally killed a band of bounty hunters who tried to capture them in a local diner, then fled the planet

NAME: Kodai
INTERESTING: remote world; sometime prior to 29 BBY, entire surface flooded except for Rena (capital); Jedi Order disposed of Sith holocron of King Adas at some point; a Quermian professor retrieved the holocron from deep in an underwater geyser crater; Obi-Wan and Anakin recovered it and returned it to Jocasta Nu in the Jedi Temple to secure it in the archival vaults

NAME: Bragkis
INTERESTING: gambling world with a million-credit-minimum betting parlor once visited by Han

NAME: Ychthyton system
INTERESTING: Ychthytonians: 4-armed, a few were known as bartenders

NAME: Ord Marsax
INTERESTING: colonized by Republic sometime before Pius Dea era

NAME: Galsol
INTERESTING: had a strip known for its casinos

NAME: Tiems
INTERESTING: location of a city called Tiems; a ground battle was fought between Rebel and Empire near the city during GCW

NAME: Keyorin
INTERESTING: also known as the Hunter's World; common destination for retired or semi-retired smugglers seeking second careers as entrepreneurs or bankrollers of those still smuggling; informal ruler of Keyorin given title The Boss (usually the most respected retiree); Boss Tinketh Fo controlled Keyorin as of 4 ABY; many hunters came here to track down retired smugglers

NAME: Lola Sayu
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: caves, hills, mountains, volcanoes, sulfur sea
INTERESTING: site of CIS prison during CW; brittle, volcanic planet with a purple northern hemisphere and a vast missing portion of southern hemisphere revealing a vast yellow Sulfur Sea beneath; despite such massive damage, planet managed to cling to a thin yet breathable atmosphere; in 522 BBY, Jedi built the Citadel here to imprison rogue Jedi; conquered by CIS early in CW; site of a large CW battle

NAME: Belderone system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Belderone (Vartholium)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: had 2 inhabited moons; part of Xim's Empire (known then as Vartholium); involved in Belderone Contention with Republic in 1000 BBY; hosted cottage industry of treasure hunters who made dangerous jumps in direction of Ossus in millennia after Cron Supernova; CIS tried to conquer during CW (thwarted by Obi-Wan & Anakin); KDY built an AT-AT factory here; heavily fortified by Empire

NAME: Kulthis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: site of Rebel Alliance base; Belderone and Kulthis both had Stenax colonies, which remained isolated from other inhabitants of the world; these colonies did not participate in Stenax massacres

NAME: R/M Facility Number Four
NOTES: moved from Belderone? (placed there in Tarkin) to Mahrusha sector? (placed there in WEG Imperial Sourcebook)
INTERESTING: largest Imperial Navy deepdock in operation during GCW; had 125 modular work bays, all of which were large enough to hold a strike cruiser; four could be combined to fit a VSD, 15 for an ISD, 18 for a Torpedo Sphere; modules were connected by Akinetic fields produced by Voorson power generators; new modules were constantly being added to existing structure

NAME: Antamont
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: farms, fields, forests, mountains, rolling hills, rivers
INTERESTING: site of a Republic stronghold during CW; CIS tried to take the agriworld; a single B1 Battle droid "awoke" (became independent) and tried to defect after it was damaged by a mine; a CIS grapple droid tried to take it back to the Seperatist army; both droids fell off a cliff during a struggle; the Grapple droid was damaged and consoled by the B1 as it shut down; B1 sat under a tree and ran out of power

NAME: Helix IX
INTERESTING: native species were methane-breathers

NAME: Till Chorios
INTERESTING: represented in Galactic Senate by Bufus Ritsomas, who allowed Thalassian slavers to operate in the sector in exchange for a share of their profits until he was exposed and arrested in 22 BBY, just before the CW

NAME: Nyemari
INTERESTING: by 1 ABY, capital city of Anem (a maze of skyscrapers) had the most modern, sophisticated spaceport in the Meridian sector; hosted an Imperial military installation; visted by a team of Rebel operatives to steal the Duchess' access codes to the installation; during GCW, descended into civil war, causing several Nyemarians to flee, despite one sect threatening to kill all deserters

NAME: Nam (Chorios II)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: provided only dim, dusky light to Nam Chorios

NAME: Nam Chorios
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: desolate planet; brachniel and gomex moss grew despite dim light; colonized by refugees from Meridian c. 752 BBY; Meridian's Grissmath Dynasty established prison colony here c. 700 BBY and introduced drochs in failed attempt to kill prisoners; centuries later, Beldorion (Hutt) discovered that Tsil crystals magnified his Force abilities, became tyrant; Seti Ashgad exiled here by Palpatine

NAME: Tandankin
INTERESTING: during GCW, the unsolved murder of a popular governor brough tensions between ethnic factions to the brink of descent into chaos; after Endor, Grand Moff Nivers occupied the planet, but the world was liberated by Luke, Wedge, and Rogue Squadron; Wedge shot down a tall tower that fell onto a squadron of TIEs, but the populace was incensed because it was their most cherished monument

NAME: Mazhar
INTERESTING: jungle world located near the Gordian Reach; Embra the hutt based his operations here

NAME: N'dian
INTERESTING: several urban centers here by time of CW; CIS group believed to be hiding in one of the cities; during first year of the war, Ordo (Republic Army Null-class Advanced Recon Commando)was sent to assault the city; Ordo almost completely destroyed the city singlehandedly in order to achieve his objectives

NAME: Graal'diin
INTERESTING: planet under control of Empire; Brenn and Dellis Tantor were told their father died in a Rebel attack while delivering grain here, but this was a lie to cover that the Empire executed him for losing his cargo to pirates as an example to other freighter pilots

NAME: Kadril
NOTES: physiology section of Kadrillian WP page confusingly worded
INTERESTING: inhospitable, irregularly-shaped planetoid colonized by the reptilian Kadrillians in 6 BBY; source of kunda stones (had many practical applications in lightsaber construction, medicine, communications); Vader developed pacifog here; Kadrillians: smaller than humans, turtle-like features, were only inhabitants to survive Stenax Massacres bombardment in 4 ABY

NAME: Tharkos
INTERESTING: HQ of Millennium Astro-Engineering; millions died here in Stenax Massacres invasion in 5 ABY

NAME: Thanium
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's Empire

NAME: Elerion
INTERESTING: notorious gambling world; during Cold War, casino of Elerion collected evidence one of its richest gamblers was cheating and hired a slicer to hack the cheater's bank account to discreetly transfer the undeserved credits back; Leia traveled here during GCW to recover stolen Rebel intel; Lucky Star casino was located in the capital city, Kushak Vogh; M'a Jong (Duros) once owned a casino here

NAME: Felix
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: its UV light irradiated its orbiting planets

NAME: Coccia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: arid world

NAME: Brembo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Albata Ing

NAME: Felucia Medical Station HCTFF2
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic Haven-class medical station orbiting Felucia, active during CW to care for wounded clone troopers; assigned to Twelfth Army; eventually CIS destroyed the station c. 21 BBY

NAME: Phoebus
INTERESTING: during Galactic War, large deposits of fossilized amber were found on Phoebus, including many preserved specimens of plants and insects

NAME: Mossak
INTERESTING: part of Xim's Empire

NAME: Falang Minor
INTERESTING: cold and rainy with no animal or plant life; was among speculated origin worlds of Jedi Order; after defeat of Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion in the Tionese War, it was among a number of Jedi / Galactic Republic fortress worlds from which Jedi and Republic soldiers watched over the Tion Cluster; one soldier served there for 12 years, monitoring starships, intelligence, and transmissions

NAME: Sooma
INTERESTING: oxygen-filled atmosphere; R2 & C-3PO dispatched to Sooma as diplomatic couriers in decade prior to Yavin; attacked by Stenax in Stenax Massacres about 10 months after Endor

NAME: Galidraan system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Galidraan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: absorbed by Xim's Empire c. 25126 BBY; joined Republic after 25100 BBY; controlled by a planetary governor by 44 BBY (lived in opulent castle); Mandalore Jango Fett and the True Mandalorians were hired to put down an insurrection here, but the governor afterwards framed them and begged the Jedi order to come stop them; MAster Dooku and Padawan Komari Vosa killed all but Jango and SIlas

NAME: Galidraan III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Galidraan Wheel
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Imperial space station of an outmoded rim-shaped design with numerous perimetral space docks jutting out from its central hull; about 5 years after CW ended, station came under attack from Berch eller's insugent cell using Tarkin's stolen Carrion Spike; colonel in command helped Vader and Tarkin calculate possible hyperspace egress points for the stolen vessel

NAME: Galidraan IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Draukyze
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's Empire; NR member world hit by an ISD in a hit and fade attack early in Thrawn Crisis, months before the NR discovered Thrawn's existence; attack was a thing of rumor amongst smugglers, and Lachton reported it to his copilots Talon Karrde and Mara Jade, having been present at a similar attack at Bpfassh

NAME: Sikkem IV
INTERESTING: one of many planetary haunts of Captain Ellin Lah and the crew of the Woebegone

NAME: Alzar
INTERESTING: discovered at birth of Galactic Republic; forgotten for a brief time; settled by Human colonists during Tionese War; native Alzarians ruled by monarchy, accepted colonists and lived in peace for several millennia; engulfed by Mandalorians, then Revan's Empire during Jedi Civil War, Alzar eventually joined Republic, then conquered by CIS; devastated during Stenax massacres in 4 ABY

NAME: Tobali system/Nabali system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Tor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Rhen Var
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: vegetation, beaches (sometime prior to 3986 BBY); glaciers, frozen tundra, snow-covered mountains (by 3986 BBY)
INTERESTING: atmospheric cataclysm thousands of years before CW sent planet into an ice age; after Great Sith War in 3986 BBY, former Jedi Ulic Qel-Droma sought refuge here and trained Vima Sunrider; Satele Shan & Republic Army battled Darth Mekhis & Sith forces; Republic set up supply base, listening post here prior to CW; CIS forced evacuation; Alliance captured, then lost Imperial listening post here

NAME: Bardo Verwen
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Mash Shareo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: article worded confusingly about system order "second planet" vs 3rd orbital position not explained

NAME: Dungal Lem
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kilmaulsias
INTERESTING: Kilmaulsi: avians with colorful ruffs of feathers under their jaws, no wings, curious but devout, commonly seen as guards and soldiers, especially throughout the Vorzyd Cluster, and a society split into various tribes, each with its own religious views

NAME: Vorzyd
INTERESTING: may have had companion stars according to Jedi Apprentice: The THreat Within

NAME: Vorzyd I
NOTES: WP page lacks "known environment" info

NAME: Vorzyd II
NOTES: WP page lacks "known environment" info

NAME: Vorzyd III
NOTES: WP page lacks "known environment" info

NAME: Vorzyd IV
INTERESTING: manufacturing world; Vorzydiaks: tall, gaunt, yellowish-green skin, large eyes, pair of antenna; prior to CW, older generation was disdainful of fun and games; Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan discovered the Freelies (youth gang) were sabotaging production facilities to protest the out-of-balance work ethic

NAME: Vorzyd V
INTERESTING: wealthy democratic world with lavish casinos built starting in 39 BBY (also known as Gambler's World); once a colony of Vorzyd IV; Vorzydiaks here transferred all physical labor to droids, valuing leisure and games over work; located in CIS space during CW; during GCW, President became a Rebel sympathizer due to heavy taxation and strict gaming laws of the Empire

NAME: Hraki
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: soaring mountains, dense steaming jungles, rainforests
INTERESTING: Hraki expanded to become a trading post in the region due to growth of Vorzyd V and other nearby species Hrakians: recognizable by their yellowish skin and a kind of fat bulky hair growing on their heads and eyebrows

NAME: Seftek
INTERESTING: home to a lost colony of Selonians

NAME: Paigu
INTERESTING: center of innovation in logic, mathematics; Paigun-built structures were powered by lightning harnessed from frequent thunderstorms--a ready and sustainable source of power maintained by engineers called "amptechs"; Paiguns: toadlike, narrow heads, slightly resembling Muuns but with knobby, scaly skin

NAME: Aurell
INTERESTING: larger of the two stars in the binary Auratera system; the planet Auratera and two other worlds orbited this star only

NAME: Auratera
INTERESTING: low-gravity world that contained a powerful vergence in the Force, centered at the structure known as Acablas; despite its placement on the busy Salin Corridor and location near many worlds of historic importance to the Jedi, Sith, and other Force users in the Outer Rim, the world was near-forgotten; during GCW, had only scattered settlements, some of which had reverted to primitive tech

NAME: Columex
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: conquered by Xim; became capital of Commonality (confederacy of 5 sectors); within a few generations it became a major trade world, dominated by Humans known as Columexi; seceded during CW; Senator Simon Greyshade allowed the Empire to take some Commonality gambling profits in exchange for control of the Wheel (space station); ruled by Teradoc after Endor; razed by YV

NAME: Yablari
INTERESTING: agriworld with advanced agritech; sometimes prone to mass droughts, but fertile land; joined Republic between 25000 and 22000 BBY; Anomids: wealthy pacifists, discovered hyperdrive centuries before being discovered; first encounter with alien life was with a small Duros colony as they searched for fertile soils offworld; Central Council later agreed to support Empire for good of the people

NAME: Farbog
INTERESTING: visited by Leia during GCW

NAME: Cron Drift (Cron Cluster)
INTERESTING: originally a small, beautiful, dynamic nebula; during Great Sith War, Aleema Keto used Sith device used to manipulate star matter to supernova nearby Cron Cluster (10 stars), destroying nearby planets and forming a giant asteroid field; later held a reputation as a hiding place for all sorts of illegal activity, pirating, looting, and smuggling; Rebel comm outpost here

NAME: Kemplex IX
INTERESTING: Old Republic jump station; one of only inhabited outposts in Auril Sector before 3996 BBY; during Sith War, Ulic Qel-Droma feinted an attack here (true target was Coruscant); later he attacked here to draw a Jedi/Republic task force into a trap, leading Aleema Keto and Crado to accidentally destroy themselves and the Republic fleet by setting off the Cron supernova with a Sith weapon

NAME: AX-235
INTERESTING: Rebel communications/listening outpost hidden in asteroids of the Cron Drift; supposedly the Death Star plans were intercepted here as a transmission and personally ferried to Mon Cal Cruiser Independence by Biggs Darklighter;

NAME: Epsilon Nine
INTERESTING: Communications Research Station located in Cron Drift; asked with developing new spy satellites for Imperial Intelligence; attempted to defect to NR after final battle of Galactic Civil War; Lumiya was dispatched here by Ysanne Isard to forcibly bring them back under Imperial jurisdiction

NAME: Ossus (Idux)
INTERESTING: possible site of 1st Jedi Temple (other candidates: Tython, Ahch-To, Coruscant, Jedha); orbited binary stars in figure-8 pattern; once the main source of Adegan crystal (used for lightsabers before discovery of Ilum); housed Great Jedi Library; decimated during nearby Cron supernova; Luke later discovered original Rammahgon text, thought to have been destroyed over 5000 years beforehand

NAME: Mim
INTERESTING: rocky, airless; Jedi occasionally used it for training in low-gravity environments

NAME: Nerit
INTERESTING: according to the Qel-Droma Epics, the forest moon was home to a number of expatriate Neti (treelike beings), including the female Jedi Master T'alla; temperate with varied ecosystem and 125% of standard gravity; a large Republic military complex existed there during Mandalorian Wars

NAME: Space City
INTERESTING: constructed during dawn of the Galactic Republic; listed as on of the Twenty Wonders of the Galaxy as of 10000 BBY; survived Cron Supernova but largely abandoned by time of CW; contained murals depicting Jedi exploits of the Sith War; contained Jedi library; Aidan Bok (Jedi) killed here by Vader during Great Purge; occupied by NR during Shadow Hand crisis; destroyed by Galaxy Gun in 11 ABY

NAME: Five Points system
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here

NAME: Hirara
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: small, inhabitable world; there were guesses that rebels had set up a base on the planet

NAME: Rumitaka
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: small, inhabitable world

NAME: Five Points
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: system's namesake; station sat in system's center in gap between Rumitaka and Satotai, allowing it an ideal location to reach all five planets with relative ease; entire system was littered with space debris such as asteroids, forcing starships to limp along from planet to planet in a series of short, inconvenient sublight speed routes

NAME: Satotai
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: small, inhabitable world

NAME: Uchinao
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: pale, non-water liquid surface with dark, yellow-veined icebergs floating on surface; massive metal rigs were built on the surface of the bergs; cities had cramped streets filled with garbage; Uchinao was shown on the ancient star chart in the Jedi temple located on the moon of Harkrova I

NAME: Watassay
region/Jyn sent to Wobani after being captured here
INTERESTING: small, inhabitable world; blockaded by Empire at some point

NAME: Shaltin system
INTERESTING: shared name with Shaltin Tunnels hyperlane

NAME: Desev
INTERESTING: had been red giant for millions of years before colonization of system; Humans of Desevro bitterly joked that Desev had been a bright yellow star until the first traders from the Core Worlds arrived

NAME: Maugina
INTERESTING: apparently orbited Desev at edge of system, like another planet

NAME: Arjus
INTERESTING: this huge gas giant was orbited by 38 moons

NAME: Desevro
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: decaying urban sprawl, mountains, tundra, swamps
INTERESTING: heavily-urbanized; ancient; capital of LIvien League until taken by Xim c. 25130 BBY; one of two of Xim's capitals; after 25100 BBY, became capital of Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion (oligarchy); got into bombing match with Coruscant in 24000 BBY; sterilized as a lesson to Tionese; joined Republic by 23900 BBY; became political backwater; xenophobid (called all non-Humans Hutts)

NAME: Jhantoria
INTERESTING: origin point of Jhantorian wine

NAME: Lorrad
INTERESTING: dirty, urbanized planet; Lorradians dominated by Barseg for millennia, forced into servitude in heavy-machinery factories; Republic liberated from Kingdom of Barseg c. 300 BBY; Barseg's economic domination continued, however; HQ of Lorrad Flightworks

NAME: Barseg
INTERESTING: ancient world that ruled Kingdom of Barseg (small space empire long before Kingdom of Cron's foundation) prior to 25150 BBY; one of the Three Allied Kingdoms along with Cadinth and Jaminere; conquered by pirate king Xer VIII, then Xim the Despot; enslaved Lorrad for millennia, forcing Lorradians to live in miserable conditions and only freed c. 300 BBY; had extremely rigid caste system

NAME: Lianna
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Devato
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Geminor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: atmosphere consisted of hot, dense, poisonous gas

NAME: Aradian
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: had an atmosphere mildly poisonous to most aliens

NAME: Lianna
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of the busiest ports in Tion Cluster; homeworld of House Santhe, HQ of Santhe/Sienar Technologies; bleak agriworld with population 1 K during Xim's reign; Galactic Senate overlooked Lianna; c. 300 BBY, Republic Senate decided to take control; Battle of Lianna during CW destroyed much of Lianna's urban sprawl; Firebird Society founded here;

NAME: Indinor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Adinai
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Niddion
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Omman
INTERESTING: legends told of a Tionese king "buried" on an adrift starship; agriworld whose production made it a competitor of Folende; became site of Imperial garrison after Declaration of a New Order; Empire used base here to keep watch on Calamari sector, monitor Rebel activity in troubled Back Spiral region of Tion Hegemony

NAME: Amarin
INTERESTING: discovered c. 25127 BBY; became a hunting reserve in Xim's Empire; one of the busiest agriworlds of the Tion Cluster; member of Cron Kingdom, Revan's Sith Empire, Brotherhood of Darkness (New Sith Wars), seized from Sith several years before Ruusan Reformation; Republic, CIS, seized by Empire at end of CW; joined in Thrawn's Confederacy, Allied Tion (avoided YV war), Krayt's Empire

NAME: Corlax 4
INTERESTING: unremarkable industrial world; population of almost 300 M Humans during CW (most worked as laborers); launching pount for Xer VIII's attack against Livien League; spent centuries changing hands between Jaminere and Desevro; joined CIS, who wanted its raw materials; Palpatine ordered Jarrus Jeht (Jedi Master) to eliminate Seperatist holdings, but he disobeyed

NAME: Abraxin
INTERESTING: member state of Xim's Empire; later joined Republic; group of Barabel founded colony at some point; c. 67 BBY Naat Lare (Sith apprentice, escapee from Bedlam Institution) visited to hunt marsh haunts; Jedi Exploration Corps dispatched Ur-Sema Du and her padawan Kai Justiss here, where the pair captured a marsh haunt for study by the Jedi Archives; later seceded from Republic

NAME: Indrexu Spiral/Ihala Spiral
INTERESTING: originally known as Ihala Spiral; renamed in honor of Indrexu, Queen of Ranroon who resisted Xim; almost impassible; composed of proto-matter, gas, comet debris, asteroid fields; Mika the Hutt;s pilots had to choose between his wrath or risking accident in the Spiral; they found route through the Spiral but crashed on Endregaad; route offered to independent team if they rescued Mika

NAME: Argoon
INTERESTING: site of Imperial manufacturing facility abandoned after numerous rebel attacks; system was involved in an Imperial campaign led by Rear Admiral Thrawn to secure outer systems from pirate threats

NAME: Crucival
INTERESTING: homeworld of Rebel Alliance soldier Hazram Namir

NAME: Rudrig
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: lush terrestrial, gray soil, purple grasses, vast university
INTERESTING: quiet home to vast University of Rudrig, with campuses scattered across the face of the planet; Lyra Erso studied here in 29 BBY; weapons officially prohibited; homeworld of Ton Phanan (Wraith Squadron pilot); original member-world of Kingdom of Cron; later in Xim's Empire, Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion, CIS, Empire; Han & Chewie had high-speed freeway chase here

NAME: Clariv
INTERESTING: its shipyards mostly did business in Pakuuni and Keldrath sectors; before Yavin, Clariv was brutally subjugated by Empire for harboring Rebel sympathies

NAME: Kaon
INTERESTING: Back Spiral world with a royal family and its own security force; trade hub within Xim's Empire; centuries later when Tion Hegemony fractured, Prince Matteus Zaym fled here to escape assassination but ended up restoring trade ports and planet's glory; site of rakghoul plague during Galactic War; Dooku's castle here served as primary HQ after fleeing Vjun; home of scranges

NAME: Stalimur
INTERESTING: stormy poor and undeveloped world in Back Spiral; conquered by Xer VIII prior to 25,130 BBY; joined Kingdom of Cron, Empire of Xim; after rise of Empire, Back Spiral worlds joined with Livien Worlds to form Tion Hegemony; farmers here known for surliness, dourness, vicious pirates had long history of operating from system's asteroid belts; observed The Devouring (somber winter holiday)

NAME: Saheelindeel
INTERESTING: backwater agriworld; Saheelindeeli: green-furred, intelligent primates led by a matriarch and had affinity for grandiose actions; high festival was a time for tribal hunting rituals, harvest ceremonies (and more recently, farm machinery exhibits, shock-ball matches, airshows); orbital Imperial listening post installed after Yavin to hunt for Rebel presence; far from Alliance territory, but post destroyed by Rebels to divert Empire from actual location

NAME: Dravione
NOTES: "notably only"
INTERESTING: bleak agriworld; one of Xer VIII's first conquests; prominence rapidly eclipsed by nearby Jaminere; notable only for its Xim-era aeries in mountains (remarkably well-preserved by thin air); Bleys Harand visited here in hopes of finding an accurate representation of the face of Xim the Despot, but in the empty courtyards, the statue he found was broken above the ankles

NAME: Xifal
INTERESTING: inhabited by Colicoids

NAME: Jaminere
INTERESTING: capital of Kingdom of Jaminere prior to 25150 BBY; later, capital of Allied Tion sector; later one of the Three Allied Kingdoms; Xer VIII conquered them; became center of Jaminere Marches (after 25100 BBY); in following centuries, Jaminere's rule stretched from Embaril and Desagorr ro Amarin and Argai; after Tionese War, world joined Republic; joined CIS; later subjugated by Empire

NAME: Voss
INTERESTING: originally Gormak were only sentient species; ancient Sith discovered world, used it for its resources; seeking allies among the neighbors, the Sith taught some of the Gormak tribes how to use the Force, but they were unprepared and those tribes evolved into the Voss; Voss-Ka (capital) established on a high peak; by GCW, known as unremarkable mining world

NAME: Desargorr
INTERESTING: known for its beautiful mountain ranges; rich in minerals; pitted by millennia of ruthless mining, as were the star system's numerous moons, asteroids, and comets

NAME: Embaril
INTERESTING: beautiful planet notable for its rolling green hills; crystalline lakes attracted nobles from across Tion Cluster

NAME: Cadinth
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: black sand deserts, wastes, ruins, urban industrial
INTERESTING: capital of ancient Kingdom of Cadinth; one of Three Allied Kingdoms (with Barseg and Jaminere); became Xim's Third Throne world; original Kingdom of Cron world; wealthy port; natural beauty desroyed by industrialization; howling winds; populace concentrated in gloomy, sharp-featured cities (self-consciously evoked distant past); tried to remain neutral in CW; subjugated by Empire

NAME: Spinax III
INTERESTING: waterworld viewed romantically by many within Tion Cluster; had a famous tradition of leviathan-hunters; hunters took to the sea to hunt immense crustaceans; undersea mining polluted Spinax's seas; last leviathans died centuries before Yavin

NAME: Argai
INTERESTING: homeworld of Xim the Despot and site of his grandest palace, but over the eons it was reduced to little more than scattered stones; Argaians known as hard-bitten traders and daring pilots with a habit of piracy, little-changed since Xim's days; later intigrated into the Jaminere Marches and eventually the Republic; joined CIS during CW, and later was a member of the Empire

NAME: Arcan IV
INTERESTING: part of Kingdom of Cron; later absorbed into Xim's Empire; continued to thrive after Xim's fall, eventually joining Cronese Mandate in Imperial era; principal spaceport of the Mandate; by Endor, its commercial district served as den of smugglers, thieves, pirates, con artists; Lando & Chewie searched for clues to Han's whereabouts; later, Luke and Han searched for the Dancing Goddess here

NAME: Corlass
INTERESTING: home of seafaring and spacefaring pirates; original member-world of Kingdom of Cron; absorbed into Xim's Empire; Xim used many Corlassi pirates as warship captains; after collapse of Xim's Empire, Corlass continued to be a source of piracy, only sullenly and occasionally accepting lawfulness; joined Cronese Mandate after rise of Empire

NAME: Janilis VII
INTERESTING: sleeper ships colonized the system sometime after 27500 BBY; ancient world that was a retreat for nobles of the Kingdom of Cron prior to conquest by Xer VIII; after collapse of Xim's empire it became a rundown world with subsistence economy; had extensive libraries dating back to Xim's time, but Cronese were known to charge high rates to researchers seeking access

NAME: Chandaar
INTERESTING: throneworld of Kingdom of Cron following death of Xim; later became capital of Cronese Mandate under Galactic Empire; HQ of numerous Cronese mining companies; known as "Jewel of the Tion" but Cronese kings were mere figureheads by time of GCW, and planet was a polluted urban world covered in decaying cities and ancient ruins

NAME: Oor VII
INTERESTING: a humming factory world in ancient times; millennia of environmental degradation left it parched and thinly populated; known for its annual spelling bees

NAME: Galdria system
INTERESTING: home to Galdrian mustang (type of horse that served as the favored mount of the Duinarbulon Star Lancers)

NAME: Barancar
INTERESTING: part of Kingdom of Cron, eventually conquered by Xer VIII; site of thriving merchant port and numerous shipyards under Xim, but by Imperial period, millennia of decay and war left most of the shipyards derelict; fitful industry still struggled along; many ancient docks had become lairs of smugglers and outlaws

NAME: Soruus
INTERESTING: thriving trade world during Xim's reign; known for use of capital punishment and its gladiator fights in a large arena (endured even after Xim's fall and Soruus' decline as a trade world); some time after TIon Cluster joined Republic, during Kirbat the Unready's chancellorship, a large polysteel statue of Xim was raised above the arena; Bleys Harand (historian) dismissed it as inaccurate

NAME: Kismaano
INTERESTING: rich windswept mining world, part of the Kingdom of Cron and Xim's Empire; member of Cronese Mandate by Imperial era; throughout its history it always stood apart from the rest of Cron, which had never trusted Kismaano's merchants; oldest settlements were built in side of canyons and rifts, and these had been tourist attractions for millennia (similar to those on Zonama Sekot)

NAME: Gadon 3
INTERESTING: noted for its Kif mines; historically fell under influence of Kismaano (resented by locals); center of a dispute in 71 BBY when Kif miners began selling ore to Gadons' enemies; Republic ruled in favor of the miners

NAME: Arramanx
INTERESTING: run-down, urbanized planet controlled by Empire throughout GCW

NAME: Pasmin
INTERESTING: an original member-world of Kingdom of Cron absorbed into Xim's Empire; eventually joined Republic after fall of Xim's Empire; continued to thrive, joining Cronese Mandate during Imperial Era; known for its weavers who created extremely light yet warm blankets and clothes; site of the Timber Palace of Pasmin, where Xer VIII led an attack that left no one alive while consolidating his control of the Kingdom of Cron

NAME: Duinarbulon
INTERESTING: belonged to Kingdom of Cron, then Xim's Empire; home to Duinarbulon Star Lancers (Xim's elite soldiers); later legends said massive polished ebon stones marked their Parade Grounds; Ximologists considered surviving Grounds to be obvious fakes; after Xim's empire, became pastoral world; Henrietya Antilles recovered the Antilles Map in the Great Duinarbulon Mausoleum (Xim-era structure)

NAME: Derellium
INTERESTING: leading agriworld of Tion Cluster; famous locally for wines; some Cronese wine collections included centuries-old Derellium vintages; an original member-world of Kingdom of Cron; absorbed into Xim's Empire; continued to thrive as a world of the Kingdeom of Cron after collapse of Xim's Empire, joining Cronese Mandate when Tion Cluster joined the Republic; later in CIS and then Empire

NAME: Panna system
INTERESTING: populace consisted mostly of pirates, traders, prospectors; contained 7 planets (including 3 gas giants with extensive asteroid belts) and 35 moons; Xer VIII (pirate-lord) gathered a sizeable fleet here while he prepared to overthrow Ferece (Cronese king)

NAME: Panna
INTERESTING: one of many planets conquered by Xer VIII (pirate chieftain) and integrated into his Empire

NAME: Panna Prime
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: domed urban, red mud, vast gelid oceans
INTERESTING: entire moon covered in a gelid ocean consisting at least partly of mud, in which large creatures lived; Imperial presence during GCW; Han, Chewie and Luke crash-landed in 0 ABY while transporting a mystical talisman; Boba rescued them from a Panna dragon but his intentions to find Rebel base were discovered; inhabitants known for their distinct Panna cakes (hotcakes)

NAME: Nuswatta
INTERESTING: early in its history, it was a theocracy ruled from the High Fane of Xo by hierophants who practiced ritual sacrifice; an original member-world of Cron, absorbed by the Empire of Xim the Despot, who built the famous Forbidden Gardens of Nuswatta, a royal retreat later considered one of the Twenty Wonders of the Galaxy, which only Cronese could legally visit (though bribery was an option)

NAME: Eibon
INTERESTING: an original member-world of Kingdom of Cron absorbed into Xim's Empire; Xer VIII and Xim respected the world; one of Xim's flagships was named the Eibon Scimitar; continued to thrive after Xim's Empire collapsed; joined Cronese Mandate after rise of the Empire; considered one of the most powerful worlds of the Cron region

NAME: Algor
INTERESTING: famous as a homeworld of pirates, smugglers, lawyers; Algorian people known for disputatiousness (subject of humor throughout Tion Cluster); homeworld of Shamus Falconi; part of Kingdom of Cron; absorbed into Xim's Empire, though Algorians not proud of it; group of Algorian pirates rescued Grasheel (Wookiee who later owned share in Airlock Cantina), taught him starship engineering

NAME: Foran Tutha
INTERESTING: like nearby Belderone, host to a cottage industry supporting treasure hunters for the planet Ossus, who made the dangerous jumps towards that world; unremarkable; shot to prominence after discovery of Foran Tutha star probe c. 500 BBY, though scientists never reached a consensus regarding its origins

NAME: Murkhana
