INTERESTING: major tourist attraction at end of Republic era; major CIS bastion and Corporate Alliance HQ during CW; Republic bombardment left it impoverished, polluted crime haven by Imperial era; crippled by Imperial sanctions and ruined environment; dominated by smugglers, crimelords such as Sugi Faazah; Berch Teller stole Carrion Spike while Tarkin was here with Vader investigating a comm cache

NAME: Weytta
INTERESTING: homeworld of Roan Shryne (Jedi Master) and his parents Jula and Jen

NAME: Chashima
INTERESTING: during YV War, Vong set up a shaper research facility to develop the combuzzer, a type of beetle designed to home in on comlink transmissions (sabotaged by Wraih Squadron in 29 ABY)

NAME: Fial system
near Belderone/still considered far removed from major hyperlane such as Perlemian/coreward of Murkhana
INTERESTING: located near Belderone, in Tion Cluster; coreward of Murkhana but still considered far removed from major hyperlanes such as the Perlemian; Empire had no presence here, but nearby Belderone was heavily fortified

NAME: Kintoni
INTERESTING: ruled by Empire under Governor Sanz; competed against Lothal (under Arihnda Pryce) for contracts by Select Committee of Imperial High Command to build new facilities and factories to expand Outer Rim naval operations; NR forces occupied a former Imperial garrison on Kintoni c. 4 ABY where Governor Barkale was imprisoned; Mara Jade infiltrated, assassinated him on behalf of Emperor

NAME: Pakuuni system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: major haven for pirates, smugglers around the time of Hoth, causing galactic trade to be difficult or dangerous at best; Thrawn established outpost NL-1 in system before Endor

NAME: Pakuuni
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: member of Xim's Empire; still under Imperial control by Thrawn Campaign; under NR control after Thrawn's death; NR moved Crseih Station to Pakuuni system after Codru-Ji wanted to banish it from Munto Codru orbit; solar eclipse every 76 years, and legend said this revealed a hidden tomb of the first settler and its treasures

NAME: NL-1
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: in 3 ABY Vice Admiral Thrawn discovered Pakuuni system was abandoned by Empire due to possibility of Rebel attacks and constructed this XQ1 Platform (overseen by Commander Maloc) to bring order; a Pakuuni Pirate outpost consisting of containers and 3 CR90 Corvettes was destroyed to make way for Imperial outpost; pirate and Rebel attacks thwarted by Maarek Stele and wingmates

NAME: Escarte
INTERESTING: Commerce Guild had major interests here; around time of CW, Guild sided with CIS and planet was defended by Diamond-class cruisers and Recusant-class light destroyers supported by Guild corvettes and bombers; elite Escarte Guard, which served in Guild's Punitive Security Forces, provided bodyguard service to important Guild personnel

NAME: Escarte Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: orbited between massive, multi-mooned gas giants; mining operations commenced in 39 BBY; used by Commerce Guild by 19 BBY; Guild mined neighboring asteroids using tractor beams, which drew them directly into facility; Commerce guild controlled the facility with the Escarte Judiciary and Escarte Guard; visited by Obi-Wan and Anakin late in CW during search for Sidious

NAME: Geillia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Geillian ale (beverage)

NAME: Gbu
INTERESTING: high-gravity environment uninhabitable to any non-adapted species; Veubgri: insectoid species highly prized as valuable laborers able to work in highly pressurized atmospheres; discovered c. 25100 BBY during Xim's expansion; gathered into Keldrath Alignment almost a century after Xim's death; Tion Cluster joined CIS during CW, later carved out of Hegemony by Empire; Leia and NR delegation had to meet Veubgri ambassadors on a satellite due to gravity in 14 ABY

NAME: Mullan
INTERESTING: capital of Keldrath sector; history seemed to have skipped Mullan, long known for placid people, steady flow of good, simple wines, hearty foodstuffs; discovered c. 25100 BBY; gathered into Keldrath Alignment about a century after Xim's death; was part of Tion Hegemony when the Cluster joined the Republic; later joined CIS; Mullan carved out of Hegemony by Empire, made into capital

NAME: Junobia system
INTERESTING: home of Junobian soft-shell sand flier (crustaceans whose delicate, sweet-tasting meat was considered a delicacy throughout the galaxy; tasted best right after molting, when new shells were soft enough to eat)

NAME: Shaylin 18
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Shaylin 18 during GCW

NAME: Turkana
INTERESTING: homeworld of Koffi Arana (human male Jedi master during CW); sparsely populated; for some time prior to Yavin, a Rebel fleet was based here; included in Alliance map listing safeworlds, level 5 and above starfighter hubs, regional HQs and deep space caches; site of Battle of Turkana, where T-65 X-wing debuted in its first major military role, surprising Imperials

NAME: Killun 71
INTERESTING: the Empire operated an outpost known as Killun Station here to try to acquire codes relevant to Rebel operations on Lothal; the Rebel Alliance cell Phoenix Squadron (specifically, Wedge Antilles, Chopper, and AP-5) infiltrated the outpost and stole sensitive information

NAME: Refnar
INTERESTING: Rebel base here; Empire defeated Rebels in "Last Stand at Refnar" (Rebel name); Imperial task force arrived to find Rebel fighters and transports on the surface, forcing the Rebels to make a run for i; 70% of transports and almost every Rebel starfighter survived, though it was still considered a Rebel loss; "Pepper" Flarestream's "over-under" formation against incoming TIEs saved many lives

NAME: Codru
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Munto Codru
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, mountains, temperate forests, deep canyons, wide oceans
INTERESTING: remote backwater; much of planet's landmass covered by rugged mountains interlocked by large forests; large proportion also covered by oceans; capital: Codru (site of government, planetary spaceport, Forbidden Castle); ornate stone castles scattered across world were built from thin translucent stone by an unknown extinct civilization; in CIS space during CW; Solo kids kidnapped here

NAME: Telaris system
INTERESTING: remote system used to convert Mon Cal city-ships into capital ships ready for combat in 0 ABY; when Gial Ackbar was promoted to lead Alliance Fleet, he was ordered to proceed here, where the fleet was based at the time, to assume command

NAME: Telaris
INTERESTING: during early GCW, Rebellion utilized UT-60D U-wing as a cargo and VIP escort between Mon Cala and Telaris; info was on a report later incorporated into The Rebel Files

NAME: Telaris cometary cloud
INTERESTING: nascent Rebel Alliance used rebel stardocks converted from Mon Cala city-ships to convert Mon Calamari Star Cruisers into warships; in 3 BBY the Profundity was first to enter war production and Anj Zavor (Colonel of Rebel Fleet Command) sent a report to Commander-in-Chief Mon Mothma with an update of Telaris system operations; Profundity was also first to be completed, followed by Home One and Nautilian

NAME: Reginard
INTERESTING: uninhabited planet except for Rebels' hidden Reginard base, located in a cliff on an island, on opposite side of planet from main continent and populated by Humans and a Mon Cal; when base set up a passive sensor array, it activated a hidden beacon identifying itself as a Stellar Class Spaceport, drawing the Queen's VIctory here as it was fleeing an Imperial Customs Frigate

NAME: Vaenrood
INTERESTING: several months before liberation of Kal'Shebbol (Kathol sector), NR battled Imperial forces here; in a mountainous area, NR ground forces supported by X-wing air support engaged Imperial units supported by artillery; Darryn Thyte's X-wing was clipped by artillery fire and crashed, taking his right arm above elbow; he got a clunky cybernetic replacement and was removed from active duty

NAME: Eredenn Prime
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: snowy plains, ice lakes, frozen wastes
INTERESTING: orbited by 3 uninhabitable moons; fertile land during brief warm season, but most remote regions saw no light for half the year; original Back Spiral member world; conquered by Xer VIII, later part of Xim's Empire, Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion; joined Republic c. 24000 BBY; mostly abandoned by time of Empire; Republic weapons testing site of Decimators (CIS attacked & stole them)

NAME: Brigia
INTERESTING: poor, world, economically dominated by the Pakuuni; rulers refused external assistance; Brigians: tall, purple-skinned humanoids; affiliated with Kingdom of Cron, Xim's Empire, Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion, Republic, CIS, Empire; c. 2 BBY small group of colonists left to found New Brigia (chromite-mining operation in Koornacht Cluster); main Rebel base here after Chrellis, evacuated

NAME: Orion IV
INTERESTING: at edge of Indrexu Spiral; had violet-colored sky; poor manufacturing world in Back Spiral; tipped into near-open Rebellion shortly before Yavin; hosted a Rebel base destroyed by Empire as part of Operation Strike Fear

NAME: Caluula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: part of Kingdom of Cron, Xim's Empire, Tion Hegemony; conquered by YV near end of war; about 1/3 of population sent to Coruscant for sacrifice; YV here killed in 29 ABY as first test subjects of Alpha Red (largely Chiss-created Vong-targeting virus), which mutated, began to decimate native flora, fauna; quarantine attempts failed; emigrants subject to strict decontamination procedures

NAME: Caluula Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: haven for spacers in need of spare parts; environmental scientists came here to study Caluula; officially under auspices of NR military; under heavy YV assault after disastrous Operation Trinity; because nearby HoloNet relay stations destroyed by mabugat kan, unable to call for NR reinforcements; YV used a ychna to draw out Han and destroy station (most staff evacuated to surface)

NAME: Dellalt
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, 3 smallish continents, lakes, mountains, plains
INTERESTING: gravity slightly stronger than standard; Dellaltians: known as Dellalt Swimming People (huge sentient lake-dwelling reptiles who would ferry riders and cargo for a fee; southern continent was site of Xim's vas treasure vaults, situated below dummy vaults, once surrounded by an advanced city, which crumbled into ruins over the ages; allied with CIS during CW; battle here during Outer Rim Sieges; Han & Chewie found Xim's treasure in 1 BBY; Imperial staging point

NAME: Ashbo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: Lasat named Atollon system's star Ashbo, meaning "steady" or "balanced" and used its constant position in Lasan's night sky to navigate via bo-rifle

NAME: Atollon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu, Timelines map/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: desert, mesas, coral formations, hot-spring caverns
INTERESTING: lies in uncharted region of Lothal sector; city-sized mesas topped by massive coral formations; no recorded surveys or settlements; site of Rebel Alliance's Chopper Base during early GCW; inhabited by native krykna (spider-like white creatures) and dokma (snail-like prey) as well as non-native convorees (owl-like creatures)

NAME: Sran
INTERESTING: Andrik Keller (Nihil Strike) visited here after escaping Battle of Galov; after hearing from Keller that Tempest Runner Lourna Dee was captured by the Republic, a Dowutin former Tempest Runner killed Keller and departed Sran; site of Rebel base that was successfully defended sometime before 2 ABY; Risiev Credal (tactician trooper) was promoted to officer for his part in the victory

NAME: New Alderaan
INTERESTING: home to Alderaanian survivors; governed by Alderaan Alliance; established by Alliance Support Services; safeworld whose location only known to a selec few NR leaders; devastated by Zsinj in 7 ABY and forces of revived Palpatine in 10 ABY; reclaimed by NR after Palpatine's final death in 11 ABY; Lieda Mothma recuperated here during GCW; Jan Dodonna retired here, dying in 24 ABY

NAME: Eridicon IV
INTERESTING: planet to which an old Quarren retired after owning the Limping Lady (modified YT-1300)

NAME: Hast
INTERESTING: site of secret NR shipyards that came under Imperial attack

NAME: Zigoola
INTERESTING: Sith temple here was used by Order of the Sith Lords fo hoarding artifacts; strong with dark side of the Force, which severely affected Obi-Wan when he was here with Bail Organa; did not appear in Jedi Archives; location kept secret by Sith; Obi-Wan and Bail destroyed the temple but were unable to recover any artifacts for study; they were rescued by Padme and clone troopers

NAME: Giryulan system
INTERESTING: Giryulan Findings took place here; loyal Imperial Stren Grier was accused of forging reports about the Giryulan Findings by a corrupt Imperial officer, forcing him to become a fugitive

NAME: Icindra
INTERESTING: origin point of Icindric caviar

NAME: Ruisto
INTERESTING: one of the first world colonized by Mon Cals outside their own star system; Old Republic scouts made first contacts with Mon Cala ships near Ruisto during the expansion of the Perlemian Trade Route in 4166 BBY

NAME: Daca
INTERESTING: primary star of binary Mon Cala system

NAME: Mon Cala
NATIVE_SPECIES: Mon Cala, Quarren, Moappa, Amphi-Hydrus, Whaladons
INTERESTING: native species called it Dac; Human explorers named it Mon Calamari; home to 27.5 B Mon Cala and Quarren; floating cities such as Coral City and Foamwander City (capitals), Crystal Reef and Heurkea floated on the surface or beneath the waves; native Quarren and Mon Cals had tempestuous history; attacked multiple times by CIS; subjugated and enslaved by Empire; sterlized 137 ABY

NAME: Mon Calamari Shipyards
INTERESTING: constructed by joint group of Mon Cala and Quarren before 4000 BBY; owned by a corporation of the same name but occupied by Empire during GCW, which delegated control to Loronar; during Calamarian Revolt, Alliance and its Mon Cala supporters took over the shipyards and used them to modify a number of Mon Cal Cruisers for battle

NAME: Dac's Moon
INTERESTING: during Daala's invasion of Dac in 11 ABY, she hid the Manticore behind the moon, planning to launch a surprise attack that was foiled when Gial Ackbar crashed the half-constructed Startide (MC90 star cruiser) into the ISD; explosion was described as having created a brief eclipse of the moon

NAME: Mon Eron
INTERESTING: settled by Mon Cala c. 4400 BBY; colonists eventually terraformed oceans

NAME: Sep Elopon
INTERESTING: gas giant with beautiful set of rings; used as staging area in Defense of Mon Calamari during YV war in 29 ABY

NAME: Iceberg III
INTERESTING: captured in Daca's 7th orbit; Republic controlled comet, using it as a military outpost, holding transports and tanks; site of a Republic listening post; CIS invaded the comet in effort to gain foothold in system prior to CW Battle of Mon Calamari; used as Galactic Alliance staging ground in Defense of Mon Calamari during YV war in 29 ABY

NAME: Iceberg IV
INTERESTING: used as Galactic Alliance staging ground in Defense of Mon Calamari during YV war in 29 ABY

NAME: Pammant
NOTES: WP: On Prously's, not Overic
INTERESTING: home to Pammant Docks, where Free Dac Colunteers Engineering Corps (Quarren starship manufacturer) built Invisible Hand and Malevolence during CW; the Quarren staked claims to the world before 4155 BBY; devastated in 19 BBY when the Quaestor (Republic Praetor-class star Battlecruiser) suffered a hyperspace accident and collided, fracturing the planet & dousing with radiation

NAME: Mantan
NOTES: add Prously's Rim Run?
INTERESTING: one of the first worlds colonized by Mon Cals outside their own system, between 4400 and 4200 BBY; Rebels operated a Mon Cal Cruiser named Mantan Wanderer in tribute to Mantan

NAME: New Heurkea
INTERESTING: presumably named after Heurkea (city on Dac)

NAME: Buchich
INTERESTING: the Quarren colonized the world for mining resources to keep up with the Mon Cals' shipbuilding

NAME: Krinemonen
INTERESTING: system destroyed by Galaxy Gun in 11 ABY

NAME: Krinemonen III
NOTES: comma not period? in WP article
INTERESTING: this moon supported a ring of Mon Cala shipyards, which produced cruisers such as the MC30a light cruiser and the MC40a light cruiser, which were based on stolen Strike-class cruiser designs; Rebel Alliance stronghold; served as refuge world for aquatic species seeking asylum from Imperials, such as Priapulins and Iyra; entire system destroyed by Galaxy Gun in 11 ABY

NAME: Hinakuu
INTERESTING: colonized by the Mon Cals between 4400 and 4200 BBY after Q-Viza invented the cavitation hyperdrive

NAME: Exegol
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where in the Galaxy Are the Worlds of The Rise of Skywalker (FanthaTracks.com)/

NAME: Griq
INTERESTING: home to the Pits of Griq, where Finn feared the First Order would throw members of the Resistance if they were captured

NAME: Dassal system
INTERESTING: upon investigating First Order activity in the system, Kazuda Xiono and Poe Dameron discovered that the system's star had disappeared and its planets had been cored out

NAME: Najra-Va
INTERESTING: this planet was cored out during a test of the Starkiller Base in 34 ABY, though it remained otherwise largely intact; Kazuda Xiono and Poe Dameron flew through the core shaft while investigating First Order activity in the system

NAME: Najra-Va's moon
INTERESTING: after the system's star disappeared during the test of Starkiller Base, this rocky moon became cold and lifeless, and the inhabitants of a village here were massacred by the First Order; Kazuda Xiono and Poe Dameron later encountered a spider probe droid here

NAME: Fhost
INTERESTING: backwater in Wild Space at edge of Unknown Regions; beautiful; Farpoint (largest population center) built on remains of a spaceship that crashed there long before YV war; the Black Hole cantina was build in the remains of the ship's bridge; Farpoint tower was located here as well; so far out from main hyperlanes that all available HoloNet shows were at least 4 months old

NAME: UR-5292-FH system
INTERESTING: contained a red dwarf starm an asteroid belt and two gas giants

NAME: Volik
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: canyons, grasslands, mountains, waterfalls, caverns, forests or jungles, seas, abandoned resort

NAME: Jwlio
INTERESTING: food world of the Colony (Killik) and home to the Taat nest; home of wabas (small mammals)

NAME: Eyyl
INTERESTING: food world of the Colony (Killik) and home to the Mueum nest

NAME: Zvbo
INTERESTING: food world of the Colony (Killik) and home to the Alaala nest

NAME: Ruu
INTERESTING: food world of the Colony (Killik) and home to the Saras nest

NAME: Nrogu
INTERESTING: uninhabited

NAME: Kr
INTERESTING: diameter of 80 km; covered in ethmane (dense gas) in the form of frozen ice jungles, and which also vaporized into the moon's atmosphere, blocking scanners or sensors and causing problems for any who flew among the ice structures on Kr; home to the Dark Nest Killik colony

NAME: Brask Oto Command Station
INTERESTING: battlestation shaped like double pyramid

NAME: The Redoubt/Chiss Redoubt
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Bloxia system
INTERESTING: Bloxians: large size (avg height 2 m), red-hued skin

NAME: Acherin
INTERESTING: joined CIS during CW; Garen Muln (Jedi Master) led Republic army against CIS droid army; Muln managed to negotiate a treaty with CIS, but soon fled with the help fo former CIS operatives when Order 66 was given; Seperatists resisted when Empire was formed; several months after rise of Empire, Obi-Wan , Feris Olin, and Trever Flume landed here, fleeing Boba Fett; bombarded by Empire

NAME: Regel Eight
INTERESTING: was the 8th planet in Regel system

NAME: Tehar
INTERESTING: in 34 ABY, Tehar was attacked by First Order forces led by Kylo Ren; siblings Eila & Kel were the only survivors, and escaped aboard a cargo ship while their world was reduced to ash

NAME: Ankus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ma'alkerr system
INTERESTING: several Ma'alkerrite ape-men were present in a cantina on Toprawa in 0 BBY

NAME: Vixnix
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Rago
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: closest Galactic Alliance planet to the Colony of the Killiks

NAME: Murgo system
INTERESTING: just outside of NR borders in 12 ABY

NAME: Voniss
INTERESTING: dust storms happened here

NAME: Marasaln system
INTERESTING: Marasaln Conflict likely took place here

NAME: Evas VI
INTERESTING: could rain for 3 days straight; one would freeze to death except for occasional sunlight; by 0 BBY, Linkas (Pliith corporate criminal, president of Linkaas Corporation) lived here

NAME: Iridia
INTERESTING: Zabrak colony-world

NAME: Feldrona
INTERESTING: Zabrak colony from Iridonia; colonies rebelled against Krayt's Empire and two were destroyed, remaining surrendered; Feldrona transformed into prison planet under tight control

NAME: Pugal system
INTERESTING: most likely origin point of Pugali language

NAME: Lorista
INTERESTING: Zabrak colony

NAME: Shu-Torun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Fornax
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Altarrn
INTERESTING: home to rare spidery nightgliders (premium pets); discovered between 3000 BBY - 1000 BBY; located in Republic space; after fall of Empire, engulfed in Thrawn's campaign, fell to NR, later Imperial Remnant; 137 ABY controlled by Krayt's Empire

NAME: Jaloria
INTERESTING: home of Jalorian Sodality (political or criminal group)

NAME: Junction V
INTERESTING: people of Junction V and Delaluna warred, made peace shortly before CW, joined with people of Vicondor, Bezim to declare loyalty to Republic and build Station 88 Spaceport

NAME: Delaluna
INTERESTING: before Battle of Naboo, inhabitants falsely accused of developing superweapon called the Annihilator, causing population of Junction V to live in fear until proved false by Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan

NAME: Bezim
INTERESTING: Bezim joined with people of Junction V, Delaluna, Vicondor to build Station 88 Spaceport; coalition stayed loyal to Republic during CW

NAME: Maicombe
INTERESTING: in 21 BBY Luke and Mara Jade spent second honeymoon here

NAME: Frithia
INTERESTING: Zabrak colony world; krag (herd animal) and poth (carnivorous animal) native here

NAME: Captivity
INTERESTING: cloudy, violent storms; Empire exiled prisoners here; TIEs from Grehollo Station patrolled the moon; Rebel soldiers infiltrated moon, located important political prisoners, and all escaped aboard the Millennium Falcon

NAME: Peldon Major *
INTERESTING: Peldon Minor suggests existence of Peldon Major

NAME: Mengjini system
INTERESTING: part of NR in 19 ABY; location of HoloNet relay attacked during Caamas Document Crisis, probably by Vengeance terrorists

NAME: Numidian Prime
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: a haven of smugglers and thieves; Falleen bounty hunter Shenda Mol had a stronghold and several followers here until Jedi Qui-Gon Jinn and Dooku tracked her here and apprehended her; Han later won the Falcon from Lando here. Numidian Prime had its own sabacc rules variant

NAME: Pickerin
INTERESTING: under Imperial control in 0 ABY when Hand of Judgment stormtrooper team visited after hearing government had enslaved local artisans

NAME: Kordu
INTERESTING: home to ratter thists, also known as Kordulian Krisses (small, agile creatures with striped tan fur and retractable claws, kept as pets or used to guard livestock in mountain valleys

NAME: Octavia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Octavian fruit pudding

NAME: Melus
INTERESTING: namesake of Melusi Uprising (conflict ended by Judicial Forces of Galactic Republic ~900 BBY)

NAME: Pa'hir'al system
INTERESTING: Pa'hir'al City located in this system (Rebel operative Tirranna captured by Empire here)

NAME: Nilg system
INTERESTING: Tolad Dor (Ithorian gangster) operated here

NAME: Wynkahthu
INTERESTING: in 2 BBY, Spectres traveled here with Hondo Ohnaka and Azmorigan to retrieve proton bombs and other treasure from an adrift Imperial cargo ship as it slowly sank into an atmospheric storm

NAME: Agriworld-2079
INTERESTING: non-native M'shinni discovered world around 3000 BBY, colonized as agriworld, placing native Skrillings in reservations, causing mass exodus; during Galactic Civil War some Skrillings were active in movement to free homeworld

NAME: VV-99-7JE-2N71 system
INTERESTING: system: orange-yellow star with 16 planets (9 gas giants, 7 solid. 5 of terrestrial worlds had atmospheres, while one supported life; during GCW, Sig Coven (fortune hunter) discovered the Kragg's Fury (starship of pirate Hez Kragg) abandoned here, informed Jonas Durns (scholar), who recruited a boarding crew and salvaged a chest before the Kragg's Fury flew into the system's star

HUMAN_READABLE_NAME: Bright Jewel Cluster/Bright Jewel Systems Cluster
NAME: Bright Jewel Cluster
Genassa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Thairwsthis 12
NOTES: from non-canonical source but included in EA Appendix, thereby canonized?
INTERESTING: lent name to The Relevant Farm Act of Thairwsthis 12

NAME: Far Dostany
NOTES: NO WP ARTICLE

NAME: Moer
INTERESTING: homeworld of Liadden (human female who was a free-trader by 18 years old)

NAME: Nacronis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron trilogy; Timelines map/Alphabet Squadron p. 477
INTERESTING: all life eradicated by Empire during Operation Cinder, which used specialized vortex denonators launched from TIE Bombers to amplify the naturally occurring siltstorms until they covered the planet, burying cities and knocking airspeeders from the sky; citadels here were considered beautiful

NAME: Oordo III
INTERESTING: known for its flatsculpts (2D form of art popularized by Vaathkree)

NAME: Verossia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Verossian computers (devices that communicated in Binary)

NAME: Carnth
INTERESTING: ruled by Empire, who told local farmers Alliance was nothing but a group of pirates; Airen Cracken convinced them to support Alliance after a brief show of force by using stun beams on farmers

NAME: Yde
INTERESTING: Desultori (city?); Aanxi Raanxi Laanxi (alien inventor and scholar) chaired four subcommittees for University of Desulto

NAME: Wyveral
INTERESTING: many advances in forensic medicine made here

NAME: Pendal
INTERESTING: inhabited by humans who lagged behind galaxy in weapons tech (still used slugthrowers); capital: Tilam city, where inhabitants often survived off street crime; bounty hunter Callandri born here

NAME: Homon
INTERESTING: Rebel flight school by 5 BBY, later considered at least level 5 starfighter hub

NAME: Otavon XII
INTERESTING: 2 close-orbiting moons; Imperial-occupied; in early years of New Order, Empire established Tremor Base (AT-AT production facility destroyed by Ovoni rebels in 19 BBY)

NAME: Viga
PARENT: Expansion Region/Outer Expansion Zone, Northern Dependencies//Lostar/

NAME: Blackfel
INTERESTING: whole moon was Imperial training facility

NAME: Telkadis
INTERESTING: inhabited; taku forests harvested for wood; home of Telkadis hiding tree spider

NAME: Denuhi-Eight
INTERESTING: home to Baragwin colony

NAME: Mikkia
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic member for thousands of years; destruction of the Jedi order contributed to a high level of anti-Imperial sentiment here

NAME: Corsin
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Greater Plooriod Cluster/Plooriods
INTERESTING: contained many Imperial agricultural worlds

NAME: Rijel-12
INTERESTING: Doolb Snoil engaged in negotiations here that kept planet from seceding to Galactic Republic

NAME: Pallaxides
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: scenic canyon vistas, temperate rainforests, icy polar regions
INTERESTING: 12 hours from Celanon by hyperspace; private resort world owned by TaggeCo; starships not allowed to arrive without an express invitation; even ignored distress calls; constantly guarded by 3 IPV-1 System Patrol Craft; freed by NR fleet led by Han after long campaign in 13 ABY

NAME: Odryn
INTERESTING: chief colony of Feeorin; climatic extremes;

NAME: Surdapan Station
NOTES: no coords on WP

NAME: Denova
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: high-peaked mountains, woods, coastlines, ancient ruins, baradium deposits, mines
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic discovered world and its baradium deposits during Cold War; due to Republic Military personnel shortages, Republic hired Trandoshan Warstalkers to guard the world but they went rogue and formed alliance with renegade Imperial Army forces

NAME: Taris (4 moons)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Rogue
INTERESTING: sat in asteroid field; but with retrograde orbit; heavily bombarded; low gravity; site of Jedi trials in 3964 BBY

NAME: Talu
INTERESTING: planet in Zsinj space where Han executed the Talu insertion mission during hunt for Zsinj

NAME: Otor's Hub system
NOTES: lacks grid square on WP page

NAME: Otor's Hub's system
NOTES: lacks grid square on WP page

NAME: Otor's Hub
NOTES: lacks grid square on WP page
INTERESTING: black market space station orbiting a planet; during CW, Obi-Wan and Asajj Ventress stopped here together after losing confrontation against Maul and Savage Opress over Raydonia

NAME: Tarnith
INTERESTING: resource world for Taris; threatened by Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders in 3966 BBY, which compelled Lhosan Industries to obtain a seat for Taris in Galactic Senate

NAME: Cardellia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Cardellian mints

NAME: Jebble
INTERESTING: target for ice miners; served as resource world for nearby Taris; Mandalorian Neo-Crusader hordes captured Jebble as a main staging point and gathered thousands of local recruits for planned attack on Alderaan, but Muur Talisman's influence turned entire army into rakghouls; Cassus Fett wiped out all life on surface and altered Jebble's ecosystem with massive salvo of nuclear weapons; Celeste Morne survived in Dreypa's Oubliette; by 1419 BBY Jebble's landscape had re-frozen and the capsule was unearthed; the "Jebble Box" became object of intense intrigue around the galaxy for years

NAME: Suurja
INTERESTING: ag world with 16 M colonists; by 3966 BBY, served as resource world for nearby Taris; large group of Jedi captured in 3964 BBY were given to Demagol as research subjects at his Flashpoint Stellar Research Station

NAME: Ferros VI
INTERESTING: Imperial prison camp located here

NAME: Okyaab 6
INTERESTING: small frontier system; Okyaab 6 inhabited by farmers and artisans; during Mandalorian Wars, the Okyaabi were conquered and enslaved by Mandalorians for less than a week before they revolted and retook the planet

NAME: Wayland
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: discovered, colonized during Republic's second wave of expansion; field hospital during Mandalorian Wars; filing error removed all record of planet from astrogation charts, planetary logs; later, world rediscovered by Palpatine and used as storehouse of arcane artifacts, secret technologies; population: 28 million

NAME: Null
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Nyriaan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: plains, low hills, boggy valleys, many shallow, rocky valleys with mines in northern hemisphere, lakes, seas
INTERESTING: discovered 4129; exploration ship Starveil crashed in 4067 BBY; Sith & Republic cruisers crashed here, among others; landing hazardous & comm traffic and force use blocked due to atmosphere & magnetic field; rich in madilon (rare alloy allowing for miniaturization of hyperdrives); Imperial ion shielding station completed in 8 BBY

NAME: Platform Trill 92
INTERESTING: had limited facilities, including a cantina with attached hotel, some repair facilities, expensive general store; during wane of Republic, Republic agents landed here while en route to Nyriaan and met with Hyperspace Navigator's Guild members who fitted their ship with laser transport array to allow it to land on the planet

NAME: Caillte
INTERESTING: first settled by Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders in 3964 BBY and built Unity outpost beneath crust; Feruun Lern became dominant figure here and invited other Mandalorians; Lern and many others left to participate in Battle of Malachor V, returned after defeat to find base stripped by other Mandalorians; CSA arrived in 405 BBY and established scientific outpost here, finding ruin sof Mandalorian base

NAME: Skorrupon
INTERESTING: Kamala (NR pilot) met a male Twi'lek here and requested he be informed first in the event of her death

NAME: Plooriod III
INTERESTING: Overlord Ghorin lived here in a mansion atop island spire

NAME: Plooriod IV
INTERESTING: Imperial Overlord Ghorin's CR90 Corvette disabled over Plooriod IV during Operation Grain Snatch; Imperial ship Red Wind (Nebulon-B) destroyed near planet

NAME: Ploo (conjectural name)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ploo II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ploo IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, marshes, floating cities connected by underwater tubes

NAME: Gerinia system
INTERESTING: major export Gerinian star-stones (precious gemstones)

NAME: Myrkr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Oolex Pulsar
INTERESTING: it was said the hatred between the Mandalorians and Sun Guard of Thyrsus burned brighter than the Oolex Pulsar

NAME: Alk'Lellish III
INTERESTING: established economically by hosting hunting tours

NAME: Geedon V
INTERESTING: site of former pirate base, planet singlehandedly captured by Gallandro in early exploits

NAME: Aquaris
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Tocan system
INTERESTING: U-wing used as gunship during an extraction here; Alliance forces heavily defeated by Empire's Tierfon Sector Fleet here

NAME: VIamarr 4
INTERESTING: Viamarr Blackroot Fungus grown in caves here; small air force of Z-95 Headhunters in 7 ABY

NAME: Thorsgild
INTERESTING: location of Blood Bucket (cantina), frequented by Simms Jonndril in his youth

NAME: Flashpoint
INTERESTING: orbited closely by Flashpoint (planet)

NAME: Flashpoint
INTERESTING: airless; day lasted only 1 standard hour; before Great Sith War, scientific stellar research station set up here but captured by Mandalorians in 3965 BBY; Demagol experimented on Jedi here

NAME: Cheravh
INTERESTING: backwater; came under Mandalorian control following conquest of sector by Mandalorian Crusaders; in 19 BBY Kal Skirata considered establishing a secondary base on Cheravh in case the Empire attacked his clan home on Mandalore, since he was harboring Clone deserters; the need to import supplies to such a backwater made it an illogical choice

NAME: Gargon
INTERESTING: settled by Old Mandalorians, exiled from Mandalore by pacifist New Mandalorians c. 42 BBY; dominated by gangsters; known for spice production; Cloud-Riders as well as Han / Chewie pulled off spice heists here prior to Yavin; homeworld of Miltin Takel (Grand Admiral); Josef Grunger (Grand Admiral) betrayed Takel and took planet after Endor and held it until killed in 5 ABY at Battle of Tralus

NAME: Gargon Two
INTERESTING: during Cold War, rumors spread that the Taung (extinct) were alive in jungles of Gargon Two, but archaeologists discovered it was actually a primitive species trained by the Taung

NAME: Zanbar
INTERESTING: Death Watch relocated from Carlac to here and established a camp; moon was covered with stretches of marshy plants separated by colossal plateaus and mesas

NAME: Ordo
INTERESTING: homeworld of Clan Ordo, Canderous Ordo (became Mandalore in 3954 BBY); Mand'alor promised Dorjander Kace a training center to be used training a group of Jedi younglings but stopped by Zayne Carrick

NAME: Breshig
INTERESTING: home to small but dangerous trill beasts; when Mandalorian Crusaders set out for conquest, the Breshig system came under their control, along with the rest of the secor; warships constructed here in run-up to Mandalorian Wars, using caches of war materials stolen from Foerost and Abhean

NAME: Nog
INTERESTING: after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Nog

NAME: Akaan
INTERESTING: name came from Mando'a word akaan, meaning "war"; after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Nog

NAME: Tracyn
INTERESTING: name came from Mando'a word tracyn, meaning "fire"; after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Tracyn

NAME: Kalevala
INTERESTING: host to New Mandalorians; homeworld of House Kryze; site of terrorist bombing by Death Watch; expensive wine, fabrics produced here; Kalevala Spaceworks based here

NAME: Mandalore
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, deserts, forests, grass plains, jungles, seas, rivers
INTERESTING: origin point of beskar iron ore; gargantuan mythosaurs roamed the planet until arrival of Taung warriors, who slew them; native veshok trees covered much of northern hemisphere; Keldabe (set into bend of Kelita river on flat-topped granite hill) served as capital from at least 3960 BBY; after foundation of New Mandalorians they declared domed city of Sundari (located over active beskar mine in white-sand desert) new capital

NAME: Concordia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: dense forests, mountains, beskar mines, stone outcroppings
INTERESTING: originally settled by Mandalorians as ag colony, but soon established beskar mining, which nearly wiped out the forests (made partial recovery by 22 BBY)

NAME: Mandallia
INTERESTING: a failed invasion of Mandallia displayed the fighting prowess of Mandallian Giants

NAME: Bonagal
INTERESTING: after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Bonagal

NAME: Shukut
INTERESTING: after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Shukut

NAME: Werda
INTERESTING: name came from Mando'a word werda, meaning "darkness"; after Taung forces of Mandalore the First journeyed from Roon to conquer the then-uninhabited planet that became Mandalore, newly renamed Mandalorians spread out to conquer surrounding planets, including Werda

NAME: Jakelia
INTERESTING: one of the first worlds to join Mandalorian space when they welcomed invading Taung Mandalorian Crusaders; Jakelians were among first non-Taung beings welcomed into Mandalorian clans as equals; Tuft-oak wood was a popular luxury wood and used to panel halls of Duchess Satine Kryze's Coronet

NAME: Draboon
INTERESTING: source of high-quality lapis; Obi-Wan defended Satine Kryze (Mandalorian Duchess) against a swarm of venom-mites here; she later had the Coronet (her starship) furnished with Draboon lapis

NAME: Krownest
INTERESTING: ancestral home of Mandalorian Clan Wren and site of their stronghold, on the edge of a frozen lake. 2 years prior to the Battle of Yavin, Sabine Wren travelled here to petition her estranged family for help against the Empire; after initial difficulties, the clan sent warriors and Fang starfighters to cover the Rebels' retreat from Atollon base

NAME: Harswee
INTERESTING: luxurious loom-woven rugs manufactured here, considered among finest in Mandalorian worlds; Duchess Satine Kryze's Coronet (personal starship) made extensive use of Harswee carpeting; homeworld of Mandalore the Binder (son of a rug weaver)

NAME: Vorpa'ya
grid square/sector/not far from Concord Dawn
INTERESTING: conquered by Mandalorian Crusaders; land degraded from nerfs' overgrazing; by 25 ABY, just landing a ship would kick up great gritty dust clouds

NAME: Hrthging
INTERESTING: origin point of Hrthgingian Firegems

NAME: Concord Dawn
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, forests, jungles, plains, ag fields
INTERESTING: conquered by Mandalorian Crusaders thousands of years before Mandalorian Civil War; devastated during one of hundreds of wars, with roughly 1/3 of its mass blasted away into debris; during Imperial era, ruled by Mandalorian Protectors under Fenn Rau; homeworld of many elite warriors

NAME: Third Moon of Concord Dawn
INTERESTING: Mandalorian Protectors had a base here, where the Spectres kidnapped their leader Fenn Rau ; Rau's rival Gar Saxon (Imperial Viceroy) launched an attack here and slaughtered Rau's followers, after which he joined the Rebellion

NAME: Ord Fanthal
INTERESTING: colonized by Republic before Pius Dea Era

NAME: Xartun
INTERESTING: orbited 2 stars; near Zsinj's territory; involved in manufacturing; signatory to NR but deal brought about by previous planetary leader allied it secretly with Zsinj

NAME: Fenel
INTERESTING: homeworld of isolationist Fenelar species: known for producing powerful dreadnaughts, resilient armor; attacked by Mandalorian Crusaders who raided world and pillaged technology, driving the Fenelar to extinction; Mandalorians claimed the shipyards and produced massive Kandosii-type dreadnaughts based on Fenalar designs; severe Republic bombardment in 738 BBY

NAME: Belthu
INTERESTING: unaligned world located near warlord Zsinj's territory; wealthy planet controlled by a coalition of mining companies led by corporate executives; had a durasteel foundry owned by an alias of Zsinj that was completely destroyed by Wraith Swuadron and NR forces

NAME: Thustra
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Reegian system
INTERESTING: used by Rebel Alliance to store deep space caches of fuel, weaponry

NAME: Flax
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, seas, high coastal mountain ranges
INTERESTING: most areas deserts due to coastal ranges preventing moisture transference from seas; entire sector joined CIS; Flakax later enslaved by Empire

NAME: Bedlam
INTERESTING: at least one moon; Bedlam Institution for Criminally Demented here; Leia forced o land here while pursued by Imperials, encountered Bedlam Spirits here; as of 67 BBY, only direct transport connections were to Felucia, Caluula, Abraxin

NAME: Bedlam Pulsar
INTERESTING: notable only as hyperspace transit point

NAME: Dahgee
INTERESTING: small group of Jedi with unique robes lived here; unique lightsaber crystals mined here which gave blades black core, zigzagging blade almost like tree branch

NAME: Ramorea system
INTERESTING: Ramorean capanata dish originated here

NAME: Biravia
INTERESTING: home to group called Biravians

NAME: Mes Cavoli
INTERESTING: Kal Skirata spent some time there with Mandalorians 50 years prior to First Battle of Geonosis

NAME: Liul
INTERESTING: RC-5108/8843 (clone trooper munitions disposal specialist nicknamed Corr) blew up a gas storage facility here in 21 BBY

NAME: Demigue
INTERESTING: distant from Gascon; connected to Gascon via Demigue Terror (dangerous trade route plagued by pirates and hijackers)

NAME: Krake's Planet
INTERESTING: inhabited by giant slugs known as Mind Spiders, whose secretions were shaped by Imperial Engineers to form a complex matrix known as the Krake Data Vault (located in a canyon protected by an energy field), used by the Empire to store data on Imperial personnel; Luke discovered the truth about Shira Brie here, thereby clearing himself from charges of her murder; he then destroyed the vault

NAME: Tln
INTERESTING: depopulated and incinerated by 6100s BBY

NAME: Obinipor
INTERESTING: unaligned world; near warlord Zsinj's territory; its volcanoes spewed out metals used to fabricate power generators

NAME: Bompreil
INTERESTING: site of a battle during GCW; Imperial forces, including Daric LaRone (Stormtrooper), destroyed an Alliance Resistance cell, resulting in many civilian casualties

NAME: Nag Ubdur
INTERESTING: Binjai-Tin was considered a large merchant city here; up until a few months after Endor it was under control of the Empire, which strip-mined the world for zersium; sometime after the rebellion on Akiva, the NR attempred to liberate the world but was met with increasingly desperate Imperial defense

NAME: Yalbec Prime
INTERESTING: Hunter apologized to Cody for being late after running into complications putting down an insurrection on Yalbec Prime, after Wrecker cut off the stinger of a Yalbec queen, leading a number of Yalbec males to try to mate with them

NAME: Aestilan
INTERESTING: scouted for new rebel base after Yavin; known for rock worms that made planetary mantle very fragile

NAME: New Canistel
INTERESTING: homeworld of senoti (species of deep-rooted tree which needed alkaline soil, and which produced a sap used for medicinal purposes; a small number of these trees also grew on Endor's Forest Moon)

NAME: Reega system
INTERESTING: Brandei (Imperial Lieutenant) completed a mission in the Reega system before delivering the young girl Alex to Tork and Sali Winger on Garos IV; system was organized around a dying red star and contained 25 uninhabited planets; there was a secret military laboratory from the CW era on 7th planet

NAME: Keresia
INTERESTING: when Empire used the sliideptra (annelidians that hung from trees and expelled poisonous gases onto prey below) to research chemical weapons, their research led to the creation of a paralytic grain mold that decimated Keresia (mentioned in a holobrochure for Chandrila's Tagge Holographic Museum

NAME: Todirium III
INTERESTING: near warlord Zsinj's territory; bleak iron mining colony that refined durasteel; Wraith Squadron raided the world in the guise of Rogue Squadron during their campaign against Zsinj

NAME: Fenion
INTERESTING: unaligned planet near Zsinj's territory; only planet not on Night Caller's agenda not visited by Wraith Squadron

NAME: Joran Station
NOTES: WP page lacks coords
INTERESTING: used as stopover point betwenn Phindar and Vjun; during CW, Jai Maruk, Maks Leem, Tallisibeth Enwandung-Esterhazy and Whie Malreaux traveled through here on their way to Vjun

NAME: Farseen system
INTERESTING: NR maintained a base here, eventually taken by the Empire and the mercenary unit Star's Nova

NAME: Cadannia
INTERESTING: produced some of the galaxy's strongest toxins; Senflax (plant which secreted a powerful paralytic neutotoxin, temporarily severed Force connection) only found here)

NAME: Mon Torri
grid square/sector/between Ord Mantell and Tatooine
INTERESTING: surrounded by seven rings, each a different color, composition; in 0 ABY the Eradicator was impounding a starship near here when the Millennium Falcon came out of hyperspace

NAME: Garos IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dagro
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rift canyons, plains, homesteads, farms, fields
INTERESTING: remote agriworld growing various grains including sargheet; secret Seperatist base here destroyed by Obi-Wan and Anakin

NAME: Nuala system
INTERESTING: origin point of Nuala Marauders (pirate group)

NAME: Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: Blood Nest pirates made bases here

NAME: Blood Nest (M2398-3)
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: brown & red desert, high mountains, foothills, craters
INTERESTING: Blood Nest pirates made base here out of Blood Nest (damaged Super Transport VI); half standard gravity

NAME: Velmor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Tantajoc V
INTERESTING: orbited binary star; uninhabited by sentients by 3 ABY; crown prince Denid and retainer Jedidiah of Velmor fled a coup and crash-landed here in 17 BBY and survived for 20 years until rescued by Luke and Leia in 3 ABY, allowing Denid to reclaim his throne

NAME: Atraken
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, craters, caves, oceans (poisoned during CW)
INTERESTING: doonium-rich plane conquered by CIS; Republic tried to liberate it in 22 BBY but weren't successful until a year later; CIS released a biochemical plague into the water tabel that killed 90% of the population; survivors mostly relocated to Trilos or other neighboring worlds; once-beautiful planet was now a desolate, bombed-out husk; some oceans boiled away, air and remaining water poisoned

NAME: Trilon
INTERESTING: Atraken's only moon with breathable atmosphere; Atrakenite mining colony established here several years prior to CW; after Battle of Atraken, the Refugee Relief Movement had to wait for an orbital minefield to be cleared before examining refugee settlements on the moon

NAME: Lobaq Station
INTERESTING: one of 752 Imperial military bases in the Rolion Sector

NAME: Pouffra
INTERESTING: site of Pouffra Circuit, an amateur podracing circuit notorious for being one of the safest tracks and therefore looked down upon by the professional podracers

NAME: Carpastor system
INTERESTING: location of Carpastor Comet Swarm

NAME: Disim
NATIVE_SPECIES: unidentified Disim avian species; later: Tarongs
INTERESTING: discovered c. 5000 BBY by Republic, which crossbred is native avians with those of Iri, resulting in the Tarongs, which drove their parent species on both worlds extinct

NAME: Iri
NATIVE_SPECIES: unidentified Iri avian species; later: Tarongs

NAME: Indu San
INTERESTING: after Endor in 4 ABY, 204th Imperial Fighter Wing operated here and lost a number of members; first Imperial governor achieved a smooth transition of power; second governor was New Order fanatic, resulting in a rebellious populace; Chief Councillor of Indu Council, President Shek Barayel, was convinced to sign a treaty to joining NR but assassinated by Imperial loyalist Kaleb Darme, who tried to frame NR

NAME: Gala
INTERESTING: beautiful and wealthy world; natives divided into 3 adversarial tribes (city people, sea people, hill people); after death of King Cana, Queen Veda realized monarchy was growing weaker and people wanted democratic elections; she relented and held election in 44 ABY; Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan were sent to facilitate and foiled a plot by the head of the Council of Ministers to seize control

NAME: Point Nadir (Resh 9376)
PARENT: Outer Rim/unknown//Nuiri/none (passed close to several systems)
INTERESTING: discovered c. 25,000 BBY; Platt Okeefe included Resh 9376 on a list of various shadowports and noted one should be sure to bring their own atmosphere supply; the comet Resh 9376 (30km long, 10km wide, composed of ice, several basic ores, gypsum and granite) followed an elliptical route traveling many light-years; home to native arachnids known as Nadir spiders

NAME: Vandos
INTERESTING: controlled by CIS during CW; in 20 BBY the Republic sent several Jedi to rescue Ambassador Quiyyen from CIS forces here, but it was a trap laid by Grievous; one Jedi escaped with the ambassador, but two other Jedi were killed

NAME: Gromas
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Maarka
INTERESTING: Republic base here during CW; while on a mission to deliver important intelligence data file, Ahsoka ambushed by 6 Vulture droid starfighters in nearby asteroid field

NAME: Maarka Belt
INTERESTING: Ahsoka ambushed by CIS Vulture droids here en route to Maarka

NAME: Daminia
INTERESTING: known for Damind lightsaber crystals

NAME: Mooga
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Tabiid
INTERESTING: served as base for Antarian Rangers during Galactic Civil War

NAME: Ggy-ynt system
INTERESTING: origin point of Bandits of Ggy-ynt

NAME: Delphania
INTERESTING: Delphanians: had scaly, claw-like hands used as weapons, bellows-shaped noses, protuberant lips (usually pierced after defeating a rival), some were rotund, could wear boots; Delphania system explored by 4000 BBY, part of the Republic by 1004 BBY, by 9 ABY considered to be in Borderlands Regions, by 137 ABY within Krayt's Empire

NAME: Santheria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Santherian tenho-root (plant whose extract was also a potent escapist drug)

NAME: Ubuuga
INTERESTING: known for caviar; home of Ubuugan fleshborers; Ubuugans: grayish skin, heavy brow with three eyes, long triple-snout, considered fleshborers a delicacy

NAME: Italbos
INTERESTING: discovered by 3963 BBY; rights were being sold in auction by Metellos Exchange

NAME: Gestron
INTERESTING: site of Imperial Base raided by Garm Bel Iblis's forces

NAME: Ivexia
INTERESTING: site of the city of Ivexia and its Mirror-Spires, kilometer-high mirrored buildings, through which Poe Dameron flew the Falcon during a hyperspace skipping retreat from the Sinta Glacier while fleeing the First Order

NAME: Nath Goordi
INTERESTING: home to a procession or royal heirs; prior to CW, Jedi Seek ryontarr tasked with finding & rescuing heirs and succeeded but heirs chose not to return home, sending planet into civil war

NAME: Kem Stor Ai
INTERESTING: during Second Galactic Civil War, Kem Stor Ai talked of war with Murkhana, which was of great concern to the Verpine, who felt Murkhana might opportunistically attack them too

NAME: Alagon
INTERESTING: Xeran Mining Corporation ran operation here; fired sentient workers fired, replaced with mining droids; miners staged uprising

NAME: Cortilium Major
INTERESTING: settled by Republic colonists during Tionese War

NAME: Uthtara
INTERESTING: during Tionese War, site of Republic orbital hyperspace jump-beacon, which was damaged in an attack by the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion

NAME: Okator VIII
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: poor soil, chilly forests, tree-covered hills, orchards
INTERESTING: single sun; chilly climate; soil poor but could be improved with effort; farmers grew charsby orchards, galt-gourds, saria and domesticated shakwulfs and whellays; Tionjack warships destroyed several settlements here during Tionese War

NAME: Matabre
INTERESTING: settled by Republic colonists during Tionese War

NAME: Ilamna
INTERESTING: settled by Republic colonists during Tionese War

NAME: Hleua
INTERESTING: couriers from Hleua regularly visited Okator VIII on business errands during/prior to Tionese War

NAME: Euceron
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: major tourist attraction at end of Republic era; major CIS bastion and Corporate Alliance HQ during CW; Republic bombardment left it impoverished, polluted crime haven by Imperial era; crippled by Imperial sanctions and ruined environment; dominated by smugglers, crimelords such as Sugi Faazah; Berch Teller stole Carrion Spike while Tarkin was here with Vader investigating a comm cache
INTERESTING: known for its smugglers and illegal activities; hosted the Galactic Games in 26 BBY in its capital of Eusebus; Ruling Power (government) felt underrepresented in Senate and used games to prove their stability and gain more power; Anakin won Djulla Tyerell's freedom from Sebulba by winning a celebrated (though illegal) podrace in the Great Dordon Caves despite rigging and sabotage

NAME: Jolia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Jolian freighters

NAME: Gormen
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Gormen, which Rebels had won until AT-ATs appeared out of the fog; locals scattered; experienced soldiers surrendered; Rebel front lines were decimated

NAME: Caarimon
INTERESTING: housed one of the head offices of Metatheran Cartel (Caarite-dominated trade organization); many millennia before CW, a tremendous atmosphere strike shifted the planet's axis, shortening the world's seasons dramatically, leading to a new tropical environment that was more sensitive to toxic runoff from cities; the Caarites built floating cities to preserve the new jungle plant life below

NAME: Ord Adinorr
INTERESTING: Moff Zerex (governor of Ord Adinorr) eventually became Moff of Meridian system

NAME: Pedducis Chorios
INTERESTING: after her retirement from the Imperial Starfleet, Daala led a group of Imperial Remnant settlers here; Warlord K'iin also resided here; world was home to several pirate bases

NAME: Ampliquen
INTERESTING: originally ruled by Grissmath Dynasty; after Endor, Ampliquen attempted to band together with Republic world of Budpock by signing a treaty; Seti Ashgad of Nam Chorios instigated several pirate attacks in system in a successful plot to disrupt the treaty

NAME: Sorjus
INTERESTING: true name of the world only pronounceable and understandable by the Paaerduag; Paaerduag: symbionts consisting of a large, yellowish, hunchbacked, two-legged creature with a small green four-eyed creature sprouting out of its back; these two beings were separate at birth but fused together as they grew

NAME: Brachnis Chorios
INTERESTING: cold, greenish-lavender-colored planet; on outer edge of Chorios systems, far from triple stars; deep within Meridian sector; fairly unpopulated; largest moon was designated as meeting site between Leia and Seti Ashgad just prior to Death Seed outbreak

NAME: Calgon
INTERESTING: site of a Rebel Alliance operation in which the Rebels planned to use stealth, but things didn't go according to plan

NAME: Meridian
INTERESTING: inhabited by Humans which formed the Grissmath Dynasty, and used as a capital by that government; nearby bleak desert world of Nam Chorios was used as a penal colony from c. 700 BBY and prisoners were sent there for generations; Meridian's surface eventually reduced to a charred radioactive wasteland and Grissmath Dynasty faded out of history, but those on Nam Chorios survived

NAME: Budpock
INTERESTING: longtime Rebel Alliance supporter, later a NR member; also a haven for pirate gangs, some of whom were provoked by Dyzm to attack neighboring Ampliquen to break its alliance talks with Budpock

NAME: Damonite Yors-B
INTERESTING: cold, icy planet; Leia may have been held here during her kidnapping 9 years after Endor; Seti Ashgad disposed of the Corbantis (Death Seed plague-infested NR cruiser) here, but 17 crewmembers survived by huddling around the reactor core for warmth, killing the droch infecting them with radiation until they were rescued by Han and Lando; they were taken to Nim Drovis for treatment

NAME: Ryvester
INTERESTING: Admiral Kosh Teradoc presumed dead here during a Wraith Squadron mission here in 13 ABY

NAME: Cybloc
INTERESTING: greenish planet, presumably with at least 12 moons and an orbiting InterGalactic Banking Clan transfer station during CW

NAME: Cybloc XII
INTERESTING: home of Transit Galactic Shipping; housed a NR trade base; region was purged during Death Seed incident in 13 ABY

NAME: Cycloc Transfer Station
INTERESTING: Maul and his brother Savage Opress broke into an orbiting InterGalactic Banking Clan transfer station during CW c. 20 BBY and stole credits to draw the attention of Obi-Wan; equipped with a hyperdrive

NAME: Dandrian
INTERESTING: called the "crossroads of the galaxy"; its ring was formed when its moon struck the planet during formation; thick atmosphere; home to indigenous bonecrushers

NAME: Dandrian's Ring
INTERESTING: formed when Dandrian's moon struck the planet during formation; included the asteroid Alpha-Omega

NAME: Alpha-Omega
INTERESTING: location of Alpha-Omega Prison (high-security Imperial facility)

NAME: Urkupp
INTERESTING: destroyed by Cron supernova in 3996 BBY during Great Sith War; Dashade survived by having offworld colonies

NAME: Bal'demnic
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: vast azure oceans, rocky tropical islands, giant rock cliffs, pristine beaches
INTERESTING: ocean world; harsh climate discouraged visitors despite natural beauty; mostly visited by cartographers, xenobiologists, fisherfolk; Sith Lords Tenebrous and Plagueis (who killed Tenebrous here) learned of its rich desposits of Cortosis ore; Plagueis acquired mining rights to main continent; CIS invaded, but hostile Kon'me drove away CIS and Republic (latter maintained presence in system)

NAME: Exis Station
INTERESTING: when Cron shockwave endangered Great Jedi Library on Ossus, Jedi moved as many texts as they could to this Jedi space station; Nomi Sunrider held Jedi convocation here after Great Sith War; eventually abandoned and drifted close to its star; energy miners set up ion and solar flare gathering operation; Republic staging area during CW; Luke met Tionne saved Exis from falling into sun

NAME: Forscan IV
INTERESTING: at some time prior to Ord Cestus mission, Obi-Wan traveled here for a mission, involving several close calls; during one of these missions, Anakin saved his life

NAME: Forscan VI
INTERESTING: colony planet on edge of Cron Drift; had been neutral during CW, but in 21 BBY CIS agents established a training camp here, disturbing the settlers, who complained to the Galactic Senate; Obi-Wan and Anakin dispatched here in 20 BBY to covertly aid the settlers without letting either side know of their presence, but were summoned back to Coruscant for emergency before they could finish

NAME: Keedad
INTERESTING: home of Lettrani fruit trees

NAME: Cardooine
INTERESTING: Zann Consortium active here; during Imperial era, the leader of Crimson Dawn asked a group of spacers to make by eliminating its Zann Consortium rivals on Cardooine; Rebel Alliance built A-wings used at Endor here; origin point of Fijisi wood (used in Coruscant's Imperial Palace) and Cardooine Chills (disease); Rebel base hosting prototype A-wings assaulted by Empire in 0 ABY, 2 pilots lived

NAME: Trogan (Ethullum)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: had an Imperial outpost; known for strong tides, natural beauty, terrible weather, and lush vegetation springing from desolate wasteland; planet's residents failed to turn it into a tourist hotspot; economy stagnated at a subsistence level; absorbed into Xim's Empire (underr name Ethullum); located in CIS space during CW and eventually joined Empire; Smugglers' Alliance formed here

NAME: Chad
INTERESTING: orbited by at least 4 planets including Chad

NAME: Chad (Chadra, Chad III)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: bayous, marshes, bogs, mountains, wetlands, oceans
INTERESTING: origin point of Chadian dressing (blue); had unusual elliptical orbit causing it to vary between 3rd or 4th planet from its star; had 9 small moons, creating a gentle, pulsing system of tides; 3/4 of surface covered in water; ridge-like, mountainous continents were divided by broad bands of tidal marshes; only narrow mountains were considered dry; frequent hurricanes and tsunamis

NAME: Moorjhone
INTERESTING: normally planet was lit by 2 of its 3 suns at any given time; on Day of Three Suns (once every 10 years) all 3 suns would rise on same side of planet and inhabitants needed to take cover; mine operated by Rim Commercial Mining here, headed by Ja'Boag (Gossam male), who cast inhabitants from their cave homes; Maul led residents against Ja'Boag to rescue Opress; Moorjhoni: felinoid

NAME: Grathus
NOTES: no mention of Grathus (or coords) on Grathus system WP page
INTERESTING: known for its muddy landscapes; water could be extracted from mud using expensive machinery; Xig Rollem (male native of Grathus) operated a cantina near one of the larger mud basins during GCW

NAME: Engira
INTERESTING: Trench (employed by Corporate Alliance) destroyed pirate base here c. 34 BBY; prior to destruction of first Death Star, served as supply colony for Empire; supply convoys from Engira dispatched to Imperial garrisons, facilities throughout galaxy, making it prime target for pirates; during GCW, convoy of 3 freighters carrying several hundred tons of food, ammo ambushed (valued 18.2 M credits)

NAME: Jomark (Bynas)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of 6 worlds in Jomark system; mostly covered by ocean, with a small continent called Kalish and thousands of small islands; population of 2.8 M (spread across Kalish) who mostly lived by fishing and sea farming; Joruus C'baoth had a residence here; C'baoth solved local disputes, sometimes attacking rowdy colonists with Force lightning; YV captured Jomark

NAME: Dar'Or (OM973)
INTERESTING: orbited an orange star; low-gravity, forested; on Imperial nav charts as OM973; Ri'Dar: intelligent flying mammals, who inhabited the middle levels of a dense network of 200m waze trees that covered the planet; predators of the Ri'Dar (including the sabertoothed indola and avian elix) were brought here by ecologists to save them from a supernova; Imperial-conquered before Yavin

NAME: Yhuli
INTERESTING: visited by Kwa at some point; Kwa constructed a Star Temple on the surface, though it wasn't discovered until COld War era; thousands of years later during GCW, Alliance generals Wuvnir and Tfin were captured by Kal-tan-shi (bounty hunter) here

NAME: Waskiro
INTERESTING: heavily involved in trade, namely mining; at some point in history, contact with mining colony was lost; Ampuroon was a mining district here

NAME: Gnithia system
INTERESTING: home of Gnithian oeps (native animal, normal host of ix dbukrii parasite) and Gnithian insects (nearly extinct, bloodsuckers that fed on oeps, transmission vector of ix dbukrii in the wild)

NAME: Krevas system
INTERESTING: Krevaaki: had exoskeletons, 8 tentacles, faces with shifting chitinous plates with limited range of expression (could be difficult for non-Krevaaki to read); to appear more humanoid, they often used their tentacles as arms and legs, concealing remaining tentacles beneath clothing to appear more humanoid

NAME: Xxan
INTERESTING: underwater city of Acquos was connected to a small spaceport on the surface via a turbolift

NAME: Aralia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: semi-tropical mountain jungles, grassy inland steppes, rocky coasts
INTERESTING: tiny world; spice-smuggling made a capital offense in 980 BBY; continued to see success as a resort world but suffered a setback c. 200 BBY when a spice-smuggler crash-landed in the jungles with a nest of Ranats (semi-intelligent species from Rydar II) aboard; calling themselves the Con Queecon ("the conquerors"), massively multiplied and built underground warrens, harming the ecosystem

NAME: Septevorres system
INTERESTING: trinary star system; site of an incident in which an ISD drifted into one of the stars because a Galactic Weekly NewsStack posting overrode its command control systems

NAME: Rydar II
NOTES: Rydans? not on WP page
INTERESTING: original homeworld of Ranat species; in Revan's territory during Jedi Civil War; in CIS space during CW; Rydans: humanoid species who didn't understand the Ranats and tried to eradicate them; local Human governor had Ranats exterminated in 200 BBY

NAME: Antemeridias
INTERESTING: under control of Moff Tol Getelles after Endor; home to Loronar Corporation facility that produced CCIR needle fighters; Death Seed Plague plot to conquer the Meridian sector was foiled when the Republic halted the plague, killed Seti Ashgad and seized the planet; captured by Imperial Remnant and later recaptured by Ackbar for the NR

NAME: Hagamoor 3
INTERESTING: home of scientists who created nanovirus that targeted Boba Fett's family; dark side entity Abeloth based herself here as she led Daala's campaign against Head of State Jagged Fel in first Imperial election; Tahiri Veila (former Jedi) tracked Abeloth down here at Fel's behest and teamed with Boba Fett to try to reverse the virus and destroy Abeloth's current form

NAME: Prishardia
INTERESTING: backwater agriworld near Chad; near Cold War, the Exchange taught a renegade employee a lesson by detonating his valuable agricultural silos on Prishardia

NAME: Mesens Corporation orbital shipyards
INTERESTING: SCT scout craft produced here decades before battle of Yavin

NAME: Centares
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Mileva
INTERESTING: Siniteen homeworld

NAME: Jendiria
INTERESTING: shared name with starships Jendirian Valley and Jendirian Valley III

NAME: The Wheel (Space Station BDT-0978)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Abhean
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Farwell Station
INTERESTING: space station where Nescan Tal'yo killed a Rebel courier, gained a holocube detailing Rebellion's main bases

NAME: Del Zennis system
INTERESTING: restricted by the Empire; used to test the Empire's new Interdictor cruiser in 4 BBY

NAME: Darlon
INTERESTING: represented by Jonas Wallen in Republic's Galactic Senate

NAME: Zuliria
INTERESTING: home of Ruori (flying animal mounts used as personal transport in cities)

NAME: Ringo Vinda
INTERESTING: encircled by a massive ring space station serving as distribution center for all incoming/outgoing resources; by 20 BBY (3rd year of CW), controlled by Admiral Trench; during Battle of Ringo Vinda, a clone's Order 66 chip was accidentally activated, leading to Jedi Master Tiplar's death, leading the Republic to withdraw

NAME: Loken III
INTERESTING: headquarters of TransTech Droidworks; location of Power Station TD-332, which Seperatist Geonosians failed to protect from Republic attack during CW

NAME: Viidaav
INTERESTING: Viidav: thin green-skinned, three-fingered, two-toed beings with large, expressive eyes, no visible nose, angular projections on heads; many worked as miners, shipbuilders, soldiers; site of CIS base found by Republic scouts during early CW; Dooku and Grievous allowed Clone troopers to land to spring a trap

NAME: No-ad system
INTERESTING: Fire crystals found here

NAME: Anzat
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Phinel's Folly
NOTES: "surveilance"
INTERESTING: small moon; Vordell (smuggler) made a deal to meet some freelance agents here to swap surveillance and detection equipment for some blaster rifles, but when Vordell was captured by Imperial Customs corvette Auditor before the deal, he agreed to help the Imperials recover the rifles to buy his freedom; Imperials set up an ambush for the freelance agents on the moon

NAME: Repea
INTERESTING: protected by Crimson Aces (independent merc strike force) during GCW, until politicians feared the squadron might turn on them and sought aid from the Empire in razing Aces' planet-side base; Gikkin (Crimson Aces commander) used the Stacked Deck and disguised ships (captured Nebulon-B) to attack Empire and Repea, sowing dissent and inviting reprisal on Repea by pair of ISDs

NAME: Haashimut
INTERESTING: Republic fortress world colonized c. 24000 BBY; site of Jedi enclave and stronghold, from where they kept a watchful eye on the hostile Tion Cluster

NAME: Wyndigal 2
INTERESTING: once a prominent world of the Kiirium Reaches; conquered by Xim and became his Seventh Throne (as Huronom); after Xim's defeat it lost its importance and identity; its former identity as Huronom was rediscovered by Bleys Harand and Henrietya Antilles; its star emitted intense UV radiation; home of aquatic creatures such as croator and nyantolo (named for a Rodian scout)

NAME: Abyss
INTERESTING: the planet of Byss orbited the stars Byss and Abyss in a unique figure-eight pattern

NAME: Byss
INTERESTING: the planet of Byss orbited the stars Byss and Abyss in a unique figure-eight pattern

NAME: Byss
INTERESTING: orbited in unique figure-8 around two stars, and nightless period when planet passed between both stars called "The Burning"; most plant life utilized extensive taproots to extract underground water; discovered between Kymoodon Era and Rianitus Period; long served as source for slaves; Empire allowed slave trade to thrive

NAME: Xuaquarres
INTERESTING: site of Graveyard of the Dragons (series of honeycombed caves, allgedly where Duinuogwuins went to die; location of a secret storehouse belonging to Emperor Palpatine

NAME: Altratonne Prime
NOTES: "showed"
INTERESTING: solar flares regularly showered the planet in ionic storms, halting all communications

NAME: Altratonne (Kveror)
INTERESTING: absorved into Xim's Empire (as Kveror) Palpatine's Empire constructed a primary Imperial HoloNet relay communications base called Altratonne Station on the surface to facilitate communication with this part of the Rim, but communications were often disrupted by star's solar flares; Rebels destroyed the comm station early in the GCW, as its Imperial operators fled

NAME: Voxx Cluster
INTERESTING: this asteroid field was located in a purple nebulous region; Vranki's Hotel & Casino was located here; Vranki, the owner, also ran a starfighter racing circuit among the cluster's asteroids; Hype Fazon learned to race here; Kazuda Xiono won a race here to earn credits for the Colossus

NAME: Gligger
INTERESTING: 563 LIN demolitionmech autonomous minelayers were destroyed while trying to clear mines from Marrow's Moor on Gligger during CW

NAME: Aldo Spachian Comet
INTERESTING: comet captured between the two stars of the Aldo Spachian system; Han and Chewie carried dust from the comet on board their freighter, the Eravana; the beauty of the comet was so famously spectacular that many pilots risked death by piloting between the stars in order to approach and observe the comet

NAME: Ramsir
NOTES: confusingly worded WP article
INTERESTING: Hu Jibwe (scholar of military history at Salmagodro Academy) cited potential recreation of Imperial siege of Ramsir (with Imperial Army's weaponry limited to parade sabers) when explaining why he felt an epic poem was actually figuratively referring to later events such as the conflicts involving Mandalore the Ultimate, and that re-enactments of various battles via Zhells were inaccurate

NAME: Parabaw Station
INTERESTING: used as a holding station for NR troops and supplies before all station's pilots and troops went out to help against Empire; later accidentally destroyed due to major malfunctions

NAME: Sy Myrth
INTERESTING: known as Far Barseg by 25100 BBY; absorbed into Xim's Empire; eventually became a Republic world; site of battle won by Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders during Mandalorian Wars; site of battle won by Jedi during New Sith Wars; seceded in 23 BBY during CW, became founding CIS world; one of CIS's most important factory worlds; continued to fight Empire after CW and was besieged in 19 BBY

NAME: Ord Zat
INTERESTING: established as Ordnance/Regional Depot; Belle (smuggling vessel) became infested with rat roaches after docking at Ord Zat's spaceport

NAME: Naldar
INTERESTING: many refugees from nearby Belderone fled here when their homeworld was subjugated by Empire after Hoth; Prince Denin killed while defending royal family; eventually conquered by Flint (Dark Jedi) after Endor; Princess Vila impersonated her brother Denin; Luke redeemed Flint, who destroyed the Imperial planetary energy cannon; Vila took a blaster bolt for Flint and died

NAME: Zabian system
grid square/sector/located near helium gas cloud containing Hologram Fun World

NAME: Hologram Fun World
grid square/sector/in blue helium gas cloud near Zabian system
INTERESTING: amusement park in a transparent 40km wide dome floating in a blue helium gas cloud near Zabian system; numerous attractions that used holograms to create illusory surroundings, simulating exotic locations of exciting situations, including the Joy Domes and the Anywhere Room; secret site of Imperial Project Starscream experiments; Han and Leia once planned on marrying there

NAME: Kyryll's World
INTERESTING: Pui-ui: had small bodies formed by two spheres separated by a short neck, and were up to 1.25 m tall; the lower sphere had a number of cilia projecting from it, facilitating movement; reproduced hermaphrodically; active in galaxy in early Imperial years, with luxury facilities on University of Rudrig campus and had their data programmed into 2-1B surgical droids; spoke a shrill language

NAME: Handooine
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's Empire (known then as Gwynhes); eventually joined Republic; staging site for Republic warships in 22 BBY, including the Gibbon (one of first Tector-class Star Destroyers, infected by CIS computer virus); later served again as a staging ground before Battle of Jabiim in 21 BBY

NAME: Talvaria
INTERESTING: origin point of Talvarians (group whose speeder salesmen were known for lack of scruples)

NAME: Naraka
INTERESTING: the Empire built a prison here into the rock of the planet itself; in 2 BBY, the Spectres rescued Hondo Ohnaka from Naraka prison

NAME: Trasemene
INTERESTING: site of battle between Empire and CIS remnants after CW, marking end of the Sy Myrthian insurrection; later it was the site of a siege

NAME: Harda system
INTERESTING: origin point of Hardan plague (deadly disease that could be carried by rodents known as Bogan's brown nafen)

NAME: Elkasinn
INTERESTING: many gunrunners of the Sendav Shared Interest Collective were from Elkkasinn and Sunin (mostly K'rrandin, some Humans)

NAME: Kile II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: had intense seismic activity; Imperial sector capital; home to the Enclave (enormous facility that supported Imperial naval operations in sector); Rogue Squadron launched an assault on the Imperial spaceport, barracks, and long range sensor outpost in an attempt to hamper Imperial operations in the area

NAME: Alliga
INTERESTING: represented in Galactic Senate by Rogwa Wodrata who pledged CIS loyalty at Geonosis before CW; became member of Seperatist Council and allowed Grievous's droid army to use Alliga as staging area for Outer Rim Sieges; hosted Seperatist Council as they plotted war games shortly before Siege of Saleucami; turned over to Empire after Council was executed on Mustafar at end of war

NAME: Khoan system
INTERESTING: home of Khoanian slime crabs; Khoan: shorter than Humans but twice the average weight of a Wookiee, with yellow skin, a dorsal fin, and spikes that fanned around the face, forming a spiked collar, who imagined themselves as the fairest of all intergalactic races; Han played fan-tan against a Khoan at the Fifteen Moons casino on Ord Mantell shortly after Yavin

NAME: Vunakia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Vunakians (group that included Human colonel Kohn Doil)

NAME: Sundered Veil N.
INTERESTING: located by frontier of Republic Space by 15000 BBY; site of conflict with Hutts, leading to intervention by newly restored Republic Navy, reducing number of border incidents and becoming prominent in Navy lore; during Fourth Pius Dea Crusades in 11920 BBY, site of actions between Pius Dea Republic and Hutts, as Republic Fleets pushed down the Pabol Hutta to Boonta and Kossimur

NAME: Orixon Nebula
INTERESTING: remnant of the supernova that destroyed the Kashi system

NAME: Kashi
INTERESTING: Kashi Mer Dynasty (isolationist Human civilization) reached its height as the Guardians of the Breath (Force Tradition) discovered ways to control and manipulate "the Breath" (also known as the Force); Kashi Mer talisman stolen from planet; wiped out c. 25000 BBY when its star went nova after thief returned to ask forgiveness; Orixon Nebula's black halo was remnant of the planet

NAME: Colunda Prime
INTERESTING: capital of Colunda Subsector; represented in Galactic Senate by Char Bibbeck during CW; capital Basbik

NAME: Nyasko
INTERESTING: backwater; site of AT-AT battalion; due to strong Rebel presence, garrison was constantly busy repairing sabotaged and battle-damaged wrecks from frequent clashes; Deppo (Calibration Engineer once assigned here

NAME: Jabiim
