PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Jabiim (Gwynhes Minor)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: small, muddy world; site of three fierce battles; deluged by torrential rains, experiencing fewer than 5 days per standard year without precipitation; muddy surface shifted constantly from weight of rains; had unstable electrical field with frequent electric storms affecting air and repulsorcraft; decimated by Vader from orbit; First Order sent slaves to mine ore here

NAME: Pzandias
INTERESTING: during CW, CIS established training facility here

NAME: Sulorine
NOTES: Jason Fry: originally a typo of Soulriep, but it was decided to keep it
INTERESTING: Obi-Wan was scheduled to attend to this world before being reassigned to the Outbound Flight Project in 27 BBY

NAME: Nalyd
INTERESTING: planet of swirling orange fog; cities built around pinnacles; home to giant spiders and floating jellyfish; inhabitants carried out death penalties against lawbreakers; visited by Ania Solo and Jao Assam (who remarked the planet was less cosmopolitan than he hoped) during their search for Darth Wredd's minion Dieben in 138 ABY

NAME: Taskeed
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: originally known as Taskored under Xim's Empire; Xim tested a powerful weapon on Taskeed, leaving behinf the massive Pentakus Crater; located in Hutt Space as of Great Sith War; by 52 BBY, Hutts retreated; in CIS space during CW

NAME: OHS2132-04
INTERESTING: known as Ulonsus system between 25120 - 25096 BBY; situated in Kiirium Reaches (part of Xim's Empire); Xim moved his forces from Pakuuni to Ulonsus and then to Xoraes

NAME: Mykapo
INTERESTING: location of a space battle between Iron Squadron, Phoenix Squadron, and the Empire; later the Krawg pirates raided Mykapo; at some point Mykapo created its own military to patrol the system; one of its leaders, Idrosen Gawat, later joined the Resistance High Command

NAME: OHS4140-02 (Balshebr)
INTERESTING: known as Balshebr system between 25120 - 25096 BBY; situated in Kiirium Reaches (part of Xim's Empire); Xim moved his forces here from Dellalt

NAME: OHS3842-03 (Astigone)
INTERESTING: originally known as Astigone; abosrbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron

NAME: Nyny
INTERESTING: homeworld of a sentient species with three heads, who leaked black ichor when wounded; a member of this species represented Nyny in NR Senate in 17 ABY but was killed in the bombing of the Sanate Hall orchestrated by Kueller

NAME: Cophrigin system
INTERESTING: contained at least 5 planets and an asteroid belt; despite relative isolation, many governments annexed this area of space over the millennia; Mara Jade located the mysterious Jedi known as the Dark Woman here during GCW

NAME: Cophrigin V
INTERESTING: no notable colony or civilization; remained out of galactic affairs and conflicts; home to Cophrigin monkey, Cophrigin horned goat, and a rare species of flower on verge of extinction during GCW; attracted An'ya Kuro due to its peaceful vistas and quiet retreats; Mara Jade was able to track her here; Palpatine dispatched Vader to slay her; her Force ghost taunted him after her death

NAME: Iego (Maelibo)
INTERESTING: semi-mythical, oft-dismissed; did not orbit a star; warmed by stellar gases; home of reeksa (huge carnivorous planets with teeth and thorns, whose roots were the only known antidote to the Blue Shadow virus); CIS invaded Iego and built a laser web security system to blockade inhabitants from leaving, then droid-garrisoned and abandoned system; many pilots died trying to leave

NAME: The Thicket
INTERESTING: Obi-Wan and Anakin sent two V-19 fighters into the Thicket to search for evidence the CIS had returned; one was destroyed by IG-86 sentinel droid HELIOS-3D, while the other was destroyed by the reactivated LaserWeb Defense Station

NAME: Millius Prime
INTERESTING: largest of Iego's 1000 moons; pockmarked by large craters; by 21 BBY, CIS drove Diathim (beautiful, luminous beings) from their homes on Millius Prime, then embedded primary node of a LaserWeb Defense Station in the moon's surface to prevent anyone from leaving Iego (later destroyed by Obi-Wan and Anakin, liberating the world)

NAME: Flitrude
INTERESTING: mysterious, like the rest of Iego's 1000 moons

NAME: Uncovalor
INTERESTING: mysterious with a pink-and-brown surface

NAME: Rawnde
INTERESTING: had a pinkish surface with a large, mysterious blue fissure running down one side

NAME: Winlion
INTERESTING: gray surface dotted with numerous craters

NAME: Clepresdan
INTERESTING: had a singular massive crater with canyons radiating outward from it

NAME: Cobarb
INTERESTING: mysterious; irregular shape with uneven, brown surface

NAME: Chiron
INTERESTING: Chironians: centauriforms; homeworld of Lusa (NJO Jedi Knight), killed here by a voxyn (YV creature adept at hunting Jedi)

NAME: Extrictarium Nebula
INTERESTING: did not appear on any star charts

NAME: Agon Nine (Turallon)
INTERESTING: originally known as Turallon when Xim's Empire absorbed it; abandoned and forgotten for several centuries until rediscovered by Imperial scouts; CIS discovered routes into system during CW and invaded nearby Iego; managed to avoid the war until the Empire formed in 19 BBY and established penal colonies here to hold POWs and traitors, including clones who disobeyed Order 66 (Ion Team)

NAME: Archeon Nebula
INTERESTING: stellar nursery; its gases could be ignited by proton torpedoes; the Archeon Pass, a dangerous smuggling route, traversed the nebula; in 2 BBY, the crew of the Ghost used the route as a shortcut to smuggle Mon Mothma to Dantooine

NAME: OHS 17822-03 (Xoraes)
INTERESTING: known as Xoraes system between 25120 - 25096 BBY; situated in Kiirium Reaches (part of Xim's Empire); Xim moved his forces from Pakuuni to Ulonsus and then to Xoraes

NAME: Sereeda
INTERESTING: located in Mining Guild claims territory; the Spectres, travelling from Atollon to the Yarma system, had to stop at the waypoint to recalculate navigation coordinates

NAME: Toong'L
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: hit by two comets in 45 BBY; many survivors relocated to Tund or other plnets; others rebuilt under King Kikipi; left Republic in 22 BBY; issued new currency by InterGalactic Banking Clan (exchange rate: one Republic Credit could buy 15 M King Kikipi credits); HQ of Toong'L Security Systems; YV established a yammosk outpost on planet in preparation for Defense of Mon Calamari

NAME: Jubilar
INTERESTING: used as a prison by CIS and half a dozen neighboring worlds; majority of Seperatists' prisoners sent here; remained a prison after rise of NR; Borbin Todds sent here for a 25-year sentence for harboring a wanted fugitive; spice trade here controlled by Hutts; first (indirect) meeting of Han and Boba in 12 BBY; settled feud here in 19 ABY; Dying Slowly was a notable town here

NAME: Yaled
INTERESTING: home to group of cyborgs who worshiped the war robot deity ZIMM (according to ZIMM'S sacred punch-cards, the robot connected itself to Xim the Despot via a mind probe and transferred his memories into the droid's Verbobrain)

NAME: Taral V
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: tropical mountains, hills, tall grass plains
INTERESTING: controlled by Sith Empire during Cold War, when Oteg (Jedi Master) sent a Republic strike team here to assault a heavily guarded Sith Empire compound and retrieve location of a prison somewhere in the Maelstrom Nebula (where a missing Jedi was held prisoner); frequent lightning strikes powerful enough to bring down an Imperial shuttle; home to many dangerous native species

NAME: Sanctuary
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: small rocky islands, farms, deep green oceans
INTERESTING: well-known Alliance safeworld, predating Declaration of Rebellion; colonized by pacificsts dodging Imperial draft, who joined the Rebellion on the condition they wouldn't have to fight; colonists accepted refugees of all types in exchange for tech to boost ag output; population later swelled to nearly 30 K; food production surplus exported to Rebel cause; prolific seaweed

NAME: Talas
INTERESTING: HQ of Tallet (scarred Quarren male, underworld contact of Senator Tikkes) and Lekket (his egg-mate, smuggler)

NAME: unidentified jungle planet (Kamdon?)
INTERESTING: An'ya Kuro (Jedi Master) traveled here after failed training of Padawan Aurra Sing during height of Republic, and meditated on her failure for 12 years before returning to Coruscant for active duty

NAME: Lothal
INTERESTING: yellow star with a least a couple of billion years left before going supernova

NAME: Lothal
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: prairies, mountains, rock formations, semi-arid savannas, marshes, shallow inland seas
INTERESTING: in economic disrepair during the early Imperial era; home of the Spectres (Rebel cell); former governor Ryder Azadi started another cell after the Spectres joined the larger rebellion; in 2 BBY, governor Arihnda Pryce invited Grand Admiral Thrawn to establish a presence; by 1 BBY it was under heavy Imperial blockade until the Spectres returned and spearheaded a successful effort to oust the Imperial presence, giving the planet's ecosystem a chance to recover

NAME: Garel
INTERESTING: known for tall, wind-carved sedimentary rock formations; temporarily home to Rebel Phoenix Cell until they were forced to flee by the Empire

NAME: Solay
INTERESTING: rare decuple star system with 10 stars orbiting a common center of mass, and planet Solay orbiting them; remained in the hands of King Blackart (despot who ruled as a vassal of Palpatine) until Luke came to the assistance of local resistance; unfortunately, the victory was short-lived, as the Empire stepped in, forcing Luke to flee;

NAME: Trailia
INTERESTING: low-tech world; Cronal (Emperor's Hand) had a hidden lab here in the jungles, guarded by dangerous animals and twisted villagers, where he experimented on transforming Trailians into a race of dark warriors; he was defeated by a group of adventurers but survived

NAME: Dornea
INTERESTING: successfully defended itself with the Dorenan Navy; successfully resisted against Imperial forces; Dornea was not officially part of the Rebel Alliance but contributed several Braha'tok-class Gunships to the war effort, which served at Endor; the class's namesake and lead ship returned home as a war museum after being heavily damaged at Endor

NAME: Dominus III
INTERESTING: Imperial science vessel Empirical was plunged into system's star by PROXY; 2 months after Yavin, Alliance considered establishing a new base here; Leia, Luke and Wedge were ambushed here by an ISD and TIEs; Leia and a TIE Interceptor were shot down; Leia killed the TIE pilot and was reunited wih the others, who all reunited at the Redemption (the Rebels' temporary base)

NAME: Bari
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: high gravity (2.9x galactic standard); frequent windstorms; dry, arid, dusty; plenty of solar radiation but few organic nutrients, resulting in infertile soil and meager plant life; captured by Thrawn in 9 ABY; region around Baros explored 5000 - 3000 BBY, but Baros didn't come to galactic attention until Imperial era when Brubb astronomers coded messages intercepted by a freighter

NAME: Baros
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ruac system
INTERESTING: system was site of Ruac Outpost, where Derembus Sitnalta and Sergeant Clenna met

NAME: Dark Nebula
INTERESTING: shared its name with ISD Dark Nebula

NAME: Solanus
INTERESTING: home to a sentient ocean, a murky seas so rich in chemicals that it could perform billions of thought processes within its depths, classifying it as a super-brain; it refrained from participating in galactic affairs, instead spending time playing with itself by forming and reshiping intricate crystal structures; Luke had seen pictures by 0 BBY believing it to be one of the strangest super-brains

NAME: Bulwark
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance safe world with v-150 Planet Defender ion cannon

NAME: Targonn
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Tililix
INTERESTING: destroyed in 100 BBY afer sun's supernova

NAME: The Black Hole
NOTES: "Unidentified black hole" article uses some interesting coords & doesn't link several planets

NAME: Supply Depot Thrago
INTERESTING: 10km end to end, hubba-shaped, with Chiss supply depot

NAME: Tusken's Eye
PARENT: Mid Rim / Wild Space/unknown//Utegetu Nebula/Tusken's Eye
INTERESTING: G-class star orbited by a cloudy planet where the Dark Nest resided following the destruction of Kr; 15 nest ships were built (one for Gorog and one for each of the 14 nests that abandoned the Utegetu Nebula in 36 ABY); with Tarfang and Jae Juun's help, Luke and Han traced the Dark Nest from Woteba to the Eye aboard the DR919a; there they infiltrated the Gorog nest ship

NAME: unidentified cloudy planet
PARENT: Mid Rim / Wild Space/unknown/2163/Utegetu Nebula/Tusken's Eye
INTERESTING: cloudy planet where the Dark Nest resided following the destruction of Kr; 15 nest ships were built (one for Gorog and one for each of the 14 nests that abandoned the Utegetu Nebula in 36 ABY); with Tarfang and Jae Juun's help, Luke and Han traced the Dark Nest from Woteba to the Eye aboard the DR919a; there they infiltrated the Gorog nest ship

NAME: Utegetu Nebula
PARENT: Mid Rim / Wild Space/unknown//Utegetu Nebula/Tenupe, Sarm, Tusken's Eye

NAME: Sarm
NOTES: fix tense issues and writing on Battle of Sarm page
INTERESTING: yellow world once inhabited by an unknown species that built a vast irrigation canal network across the planet; when Utegetu Nebula erupted, it scoured the planet clean of its population, leaving only the canal network behind; Killik fleet later massed here, setting stage for Battle of Sarm, in which Luke, Mara and Jacen attempted to kill Lomi Plo aboard the Gorog nest ship; all escaped

NAME: Woteba
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: swamps, bogs, marshes, mountains, conifer hamogoni forests
INTERESTING: discovered 10 BBY; Killiks settled Woteba & 13 other worlds in Utegetu Nebula rather than continuing expansion into Chiss space under Qoribu Truce; Woteba settled by Saras hive; after being hit by the Utegetu nova, an unusual ancient environmental defense system restored its plant life within two years; the Killiks were attacked by a corrosive substance called "Fizz" from the defense system

NAME: Tenupe
INTERESTING: mountainous, tropical planet controlled by the Killiks; captured by the Chiss during the Battle of Tenupe in 36 ABY during the Swarm War; Jagged Fel and Alema Rar spent 2 years marooned here after the Dark Nest Crisis taking away a Twi'lek story-chain from there

NAME: The Shattered Moon
INTERESTING: red-hued moon that at some point broke up into over fifty large fragments; a Killik fleet hid here in 36 ABY in preparation to ambush Chiss forces during the Battle of Tenupe

NAME: Thedavio VII
INTERESTING: prior to Battle of Hoth, fleet of unidentified black starships spotted here; unknown if new Imperial design

NAME: Kur Minor
INTERESTING: Casti Tholon visited here during her career in the Galactic Outdoor Survival School; she was injured by the forest's poisonous thorn vines and aquired numerous black scars

NAME: Gargolyn IV
INTERESTING: garden paradise world lush with vegetation and animal life; Cor: 1 m tall furred felines with long, thin tail, tapered snout, long pointed ears and 4 limbs, each ending in 5 sharp claws; huge beast erupted from the ground and destroyed the settlement the scouting Karflo Corporation initiated, after they forcibly relocated a tribe of Cor; only the return of the tribe mollified the beast

NAME: Pesitiin
INTERESTING: massive atmospheric storms; Boskin & Boskin mining center here tried to mine gases & failed due to storms; Pellaeon & Bel Iblis tried to meet here to work out treaty but were attacked

NAME: Lysatra
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map/by 16 BBY, considered to be in Wild Space, close to Unknown Regions
INTERESTING: isolated; Eli Vanto grew up here, where he heard stories about the Chiss and worked in a shipping company; besides Galactic Basic Standard, many Trade languages of Wild Space were spoken here, including Sy Bisti

NAME: Wizar II
INTERESTING: at some point, a high-end StelProbe V exploration/contact droid sent here by the Karflo Corporation crash-landed, stopped sending reports back; company put out a call for independent spacers to recover it for a reward of 10 K credits; a group discovered it had been captured by the native Uroths (sentient cephalopods), who were worshiping it as their god of death; they recovered the droid

NAME: Dhandu 3
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: Feathered, flightless alien species

NAME: Kilia IV
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, badlands, one lush valley with rural farms
INTERESTING: only habitable planet in system; Kilians: descendants of Core world Human settlers from before 1000 BBY, settled in one lush valley, in one town and scattered rural farms, fortresses, no contact with Republic or Empire; commoners lived at medieval tech level; nobles had some remaining science, tech; no speeders, vibroweapons; home of Kilian Rangers (knight-like Force Adepts)

NAME: Ultaar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

INTERESTING: homeworld of needle beast

NAME: Kijimi
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu, Timelines map/
INTERESTING: once home to Dai Bendu monks and their monastery c. 1000 BBY in the center of what became Kijimi City; after the Fall of the Galactic Empire, a shake-up in the spice trade on Kessel led to increased competition, and the pirates of Kijimi struck a deal with Kessel mine owners for an extended Kessel Run here; Resistance heroes sought the help of Anzellan droidsmith Babu Frik here before the world was destroyed by the First Order's Xyston Star Destroyers

NAME: Gosfambling
INTERESTING: Gosfamlings: delicately-furred, soft-spoken, whiskered, distrustful of anyone who lost power or an election even once; Cybot Galactica halted production of LIN minelayer droid after one detonated in a mine on Gosfambling, killing 600 miners

NAME: Vilosoria
INTERESTING: Vilosorians: bodies followed seasonal cycle (calm, docile in cold months, but powerful carnivores during warm seasons); liberated from Empire by Alliance due to heroism of Koedi Raef and Toozy

NAME: Maltoria system
INTERESTING: system contained Maltorian mining belt, which was part of the Galactic Alliance until pirates took control of the system, trying to force an enormous bribe from RePlanetHab (massive conglomerate); Jedi and Galactic Alliance intervened

NAME: Stronghold
INTERESTING: cold, stormy, remote world used by Rebel Alliance as safe world and occasionally prison world; 250 non-combat people could be held in undergound Rebel base; Charon invaded Stronghold from Otherspace

NAME: Komnor
INTERESTING: once part of Xim's Empire; a few years before GCW, Han met Chewie during a skirmish near Komnor; home to a large clan of hutts before they were evicted by a vicious warlord who arrived c. 0 ABY; the homeless Hutts complained to Jabba, who assigned Dyyz Nataz with the job of assassinating the warlord

NAME: Hypotria
INTERESTING: R2z-DL stationed here, in Laboi crime lord Qa'till's labor pool; R2z-DL stole info from landing starships and relayed important data back to Alliance, which helped liberate Vilosoria from Empire

NAME: Resilon
INTERESTING: mining world where 8D smelter droids once led a droid revolt against owners, refusing to work until they were treated fairly; unconfirmed death of one of the droid owners during revolt

NAME: Lythia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Lythian pirates

NAME: Saleucami
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, deserts, oases, mountains, swamps, caves, volcanoes, craters, farms, seas
INTERESTING: economic powerhouse; major trade center in Outer Rim; dim, arid with scattered oases of plant growth; politically powerful during Great Galactic War; strategically held by CIS during CW (held by Techno Union); liberated by Republic and spared retribution of other CIS worlds; supplied by cargo ships heading from Perlemian to Kuthic Worlds; meteor craters were later filled with water

NAME: Laboi II
INTERESTING: small planet with slow retrograde rotation (nearly tidally locked); one side baked while other side froze, leading to high winds that exchanged heat to moderate the extreme temperatures; plant life could not survive; much of the night side was covered in mineral forests formed by cooling pools of molten rock; Laboi: hairy serpentine predatory mammals

NAME: Solarine
INTERESTING: known for its sunsets; Ziro and Sy Snootles had planned to go there to share the rest of their lives together, but Snootles killed Ziro, believing he had abandoned her; Val (Beckett's gang) grew up here

NAME: Vespaara
INTERESTING: site of the Arena, where individuals from across the Galaxy competed in the Hunters of the Outer Rim tournament; the Arena was located at the southern pole, which existed in a state of perpetual twilight

NAME: Boonta (Ko Vari)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: colonized by Hutts long ago; famous for podracing and speeder races; fourth of seven worlds in its system, notable for spice smuggling; one of three planets (along with Tatooine and Arami) where Boonta podracing races were organized to honor Boonta the Hutt after he defeated Xim; a major cataclysm may have occurred sometime after the Xim wars and was devastated during Pius Dea era

NAME: Timja system
INTERESTING: contained the Timja Suns, whose radiation was strong enough to affect people who spent too much time under their light; Beatas (Klatooinian) had dark green skin but his eyebrows were yellowed by his time spent working under the light of the Timja Suns

NAME: Nomaria system
INTERESTING: home of Nomarian thunder sharks

NAME: Suolriep
INTERESTING: sector capital of Suolriep sector

NAME: Kazlin system
NOTES: Kazlin 5 not mentioned on Kazlin System page
INTERESTING: during High Republic Era, it was located in a sector that had aligned with Rpublic only months prior to the Nihil attack on a Hutt Clan starship carrying Vratixian barley; an encoded distress signal was picked up by Starlight Beacon and a team of Jedi were dispatched in a shuttle to investigate

NAME: Kazlin 5
INTERESTING: HQ of Tyu (crimelord)

NAME: Alaspin
INTERESTING: Derla Pidys (trader) sold faintly poisonous wine from here; during GCW, Kassandre family killed in the Alaspin Casino when Limna Yith (bounty hunter) destroyed the structure

NAME: Lijuter
INTERESTING: homeworld of Skadge (male Houk criminal born 3678 BBY); during Galactic War, a mass exodus brought many Houks to Phorliss; during GCW an Imperial research station on Lijuter's 2nd moon was the site of experiments attempting to turn Houk subjects into "perfect slaves"

NAME: Moog Mot VI
INTERESTING: banking world under Imperial control; housed an Imperial garrison; Han and Billal Batross infiltrated it in 1 BBY to retrieve the accounting droid of Sollima (crimelord)

NAME: Dennogra (Tialval)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: part of Xim's Empire (as Tialvai); part of Hutt Space during Great Sith War, Jedi Civil War; Hutts hired Jawas to dig for artifacts here during Cold War, but they secretly planned to sell findings; Hutts relinquished world by 52 BBY; Yoda killed dark sider here at some point; in CIS space during CW; Han took 2 treasure crates to sell to Sprool the Trader (Ithorian) in Zio Snaffkin (major city) in 0 ABY

NAME: Aaron
INTERESTING: system was located in space hotly contested between Republic, CIS, and Hutts during CW; home to a Fromm Gang 8-level mining/manufacturing/research facility where R2 & C-3PO were imprisoned

NAME: Annoo system
INTERESTING: total of fourteen planets, seven of which were inhabited

NAME: Annoo (Gelefil)
INTERESTING: c. 322 BBY, Annoo-dat of neighboring Annoo abandoned their dying homeworld, conquered Gelefil, renaming it Annoo; agriculture on southern continent became highly industrialized (northern continent remained much as before); c. 27 BBY, General Ashaar Korda attempted a bloody coup but was defeated by Republic, forcing him into hiding; Sise Fromm (notorious crimelord) HQ here

NAME: Annoo
INTERESTING: discovered sometime between Kymoodon Era and Rianitus Period; under control of Hutt Empire as early as Great Sith War; remained under Hutt control for centuries; civil war erupted, leaving the world a barren wasteland, forcing the Annoo-dat to develop space travel and flee; they conquered neighboring Gelefil c. 322 BBY; world was abandoned by Hutts as well

NAME: Sunin
INTERESTING: many gunrunners of Sendav Shared Interest Collective (mostly K'rrandin, some Human) from Elkkasinn and Sunin

NAME: Heterkus
INTERESTING: the Empire's Commander Westen of the Relentless clashed with Adar Tallon and the Alliance here c. 0 BBY

NAME: Sargesso
INTERESTING: cluster of asteroids in Sargesso system where Meeko Ghintee once lured a Republic Tri-Mark VII Interceptor into an ambush; he killed the crew by destroying its life-support systems and kept the ship, renaming it the Longshot

NAME: Vartos' moon
INTERESTING: had thin but breathable atmosphere, no surface water; no native plants or animals; Madhi Vaandt (reporter) rendezvoused with "Blink" (pseudonym, Bothan mamber of Freedom Flight) in 44 ABY

NAME: Oovo
INTERESTING: yellow-orange gas giant orbited by an asteroid belt containing the Republic maximum security federal prison Deolation Alley

NAME: Oovo Belt
INTERESTING: Oovo IV was most famous asteroid in the belt

NAME: Oovo IV
INTERESTING: site of Desolation Alley, a maximum security federal prison for the Republic and a famous podrace track; energy shields protected the prison and kept the atmosphere in; access tightly restricted; Jango Fett and Zam Wesell both tried to recover Bendix Fust (smuggler) from the prison; Jango lost his ship, Jaster's Legacy, but stole a Firespray he renamed Slave I here; Reti operated as merc here before involvement with Nym; site of GCW Battle of Oovo IV; decimated by YV

NAME: B'nish
INTERESTING: Human girl known as First was held there as a slave until her escape around 41.5 ABY

NAME: Ord Namurt
INTERESTING: site of a Republic Ordnance/Regional Depot; An'ya Kuro (also known as the Dark Woman) had a training ground for Jedi students here; she was training Aurra Sing here when the girl was kidnapped by star pirates; Trench led the destruction of a pirate base here c. 34 BBY while in employ of Corporate Alliance

NAME: Carlix's Folly
INTERESTING: one of many planetary haunts of the Woebegone's Captain Ellin Lah and her crew

NAME: Raddan
INTERESTING: origin point of Raddan vermin-killer's vest (article of clothing)

NAME: Novor Major
INTERESTING: destroyed innermost 17 of its original 33 planets when it expanded to become a red giant, millennia before GCW

NAME: Novor Asteroid Field
INTERESTING: remains of 17 innermost planets of Novor system, blasted by the expansion of Novor Major into a red giant millennia before GCW

NAME: Novor 18
INTERESTING: innermost planet of Novor system since Novor Major's expansion into a red giant millennia before GCW

NAME: Novor 23
INTERESTING: 6th of 16 remaining planets in system; busy world with large Human and alien populations living in thriving cities; capital: Luj City (key financial center of Tharin sector despite location in the Periphery); local corporate offices of Jatayus Outbound here, as was villa of Sprax (Black Sun Vigo), which was built in Vos'yr valley

NAME: Novor 33
INTERESTING: uninhabitable; remarkably unaffected by expansion of Novor Major into its red giant phase; galactic explorers surveyed the region between 27500 - 25000 BBY; within Hutt Space at some point after 25096 BBY, remaining for at least 2900 years; after invention of hyperdrive, explorers reevaluated frontier between 20000 and 15000 BBY and was explored extensively by Republic by 5000 BBY

NAME: Bolad
INTERESTING: Tig Fromm accidentally destroyed his father Sise Fromm's vacation palace here

NAME: Vaathkree
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Iotra
INTERESTING: temperate, industrial world ruled by the Joint Council (8 top ranking members of the Iotran Police Force (IPF); southern latitudes were plagued by seasonal East Vacaliv windstorms; IPF often needed to provide rescue operations during these storms; Iotrans: smooth dark brown to black skin, a broad flat nose, no discerbible ears, four-digit hands, strong military traditions

NAME: Gettiarn Space Station
INTERESTING: operated by Iotran Police Force; rigidly-controlled space station complex serving as the hub of space traffic control for entire system; all non-Iotran traffic into system was routed here

NAME: Ques
INTERESTING: wet planet taxed by Hutts; population primarily consisted of scavengers such as Dec Hansen; home wof axton-tarsier, the ferin, the slime crab, and the Snarlap (creatures); motley spaceport at edge of Hutt Space, typically used by ships heading for the Si'Klaata Cluster; outlanders landing here were interrogated extensively

NAME: Ulkantha
INTERESTING: hosted a smuggler base attacked by Vader's Death Squadron shortly before Hoth, uncovering evidence of a Sakiyan smuggling ring headquartered in Syvris shadowport

NAME: Yoribuunt
INTERESTING: beautiful, swirling gas giant; popular tourist stop for sightseers on luxury liners

NAME: Ibaar
INTERESTING: fell under Imperial control in years before Battle of Yavin; the Empire blockaded the planet, cutting off the population from needed supplies; the Rebellion assisted an underground network of Ibaarians to deliver the needed goods, but the population continued to suffer under Imperial rule well into the Civil War. According to Imperial propaganda, Ibaar suffered from famine during New Republic rule

NAME: Sufezz
INTERESTING: a Shrine of Kooroo was located here

NAME: Gand
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: home of mystic, Force-based Findsman hunting tradition; Zuckuss one of the first to travel off-planet when these traditions began to die out; atmosphere lethal to most species; Sith had invaded at some point; Gand discovered by outsiders by 3951 BBY, during Kanz Disorders; remained independent during CW, GCW; isolated, not located on any major hyperlane; later overrun by Empire

NAME: Yarma
INTERESTING: home to Reklam Station, an Imperial salvage yard; in 2 BBY Phoenix Cell stole a squadron of Y-wing starfighters from the yard to give to the Rebellion, sabotaging the yard in the process and causing it to plummet to its doom

NAME: Marleyvane
INTERESTING: contained a major shipyard (only capable of serving cruisers), controlled directly by Imperial forces during GCW

NAME: Junkfort (Kossimur)
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron; orbited by Junkfort Station; YV seized world during their invasion, presumably destroying Junkfort Station

NAME: Junkfort Station
INTERESTING: civil spaceport where smugglers could get illegal ship modifications; Han and Chewie arrived them after Leia sent them in search of mythical shield-disrupting power gems once used by the Pirates of Iridium; Han met an agent of Mystra after getting into a fistfight in a cantina; Mystra's agent told them about Raskar (ex-pirate), who possessed the last known shield-disrupting gem

NAME: Nimat system
INTERESTING: shared name with the Nimat Corridor hyperlane

NAME: Jexeria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Jexerian cannon (primitive projectile launcher known for making high-volume noise when fired)

NAME: Tammar (Lelrais)
INTERESTING: no standing water; had unusually thin atmosphere; Tammarians: evolved a chemical pouch called a chaghizs torm to store oxygen, allowing them to survive the vacuum of space for short periods; absorbed into Xim's Empire (as Lelrais) c. 25130 BBY; homeworld of Ayddar Nylykerka (chief researcher of NR Asset Tracking Office)

NAME: Orranana system
INTERESTING: Orrananans: according to Evocar by Direus'Pei (Hutt playwright), Xim the Despot drove them extinct

NAME: Bresallis
INTERESTING: plagued by criminal underworld, run by Hutts; Ambassador Walads opposed the Hutts, but they hired Brahle Logris to assassinate the ambassador just as he was about to make a speech to the government on the subject

NAME: Simbarc
INTERESTING: mining world known for its rich ore and famous casinos on surface; Han and Chewie visited here while trying to pay a debt owed to Sollima (gangster)

NAME: Dagelin Minor
INTERESTING: 98% of population died of Hardan plague, brought here by Bogan's brown nafen (colloquially known as the "butterbat", imported to control local dhuru fly population); Leia led a mercy mission here sometime between 2 and 0 BBY

NAME: Rullag
INTERESTING: Dark Jedi Nax Cirvan claimed to have killed 8 Jedi and their Padawans on the plains of Rullag during CW

NAME: Garn
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren, craggy rock, temples, diseased trees, lethal fungus
INTERESTING: shrouded in dense yellow fog; ancient during Kymoodon Era, it was home to a dying civilization slustered into small towns of prefab homes during final days of Pius Dea Crusades; site of Cathedral ship crash; Carel Kapekos (Jedi Master) and his Pius Dea Jedi rescued the trapped crew; laid to waste millennia ago by Jedi trying to eliminate Order of the Terrible Glare; Luke defeated Rur here

NAME: Fortress of Garn
INTERESTING: Ordu Aspectu (Jedi splinter group) maintained this space station many standard years before Imperial Era

NAME: Maphus Tria
INTERESTING: Tord Gamb (con artist) ran a con here that netted him several hundred thousand credits

NAME: Oseon Sun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: every standard year, the star released its Flamewind that was a major tourist attraction in the galaxy

NAME: Oseon VII
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/

NAME: Oseon Asteroid Belts
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: home to a chain of the planetary development company Planet Dreams, Incorporated

NAME: unidentified subtropical moon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: when meeting Han, Lando boasted he once won a subtropical moon in the Oseon Belt while playing a card game

NAME: Oseon 2795
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: site of a mining colony; Lando played a game of sabacc here with the Ottdefa Osuno Whett, Vett Fori, Arun Feb, and T. Lund Phuna

NAME: Oseon 5631
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: Ema Slake (renowned singer) had the most luxurious of the Belt's estates here by 27 ABY; Sosten Freet (her agent) stole several of her trophies and sought to frame O'lif Khaz (former holovid director) for the theft, but the trophies were discovered in Freet's residence by a group of investigators

NAME: Oseon 5792
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: 15 km wide asteroid; private estate of Bohhuah Mutdah (retired industrialist, wealthiest person in the galaxy); destroyed when Klyn Shanga and his Renatasians crashed a hyperdrive engine into it

NAME: Oseon 6845
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: in Sixth Belt (of 7); largest asteroid (700 km wide) in system, airless iron-and-rock planetoid with weak gravity augmented by inhabitants; spaceport constructed at northern pole; honeycombed with luxurious hotels, night entertainment venues, stately residences; attracted affluent individuals for shopping, gambling; Flamewind stranded residents and visitors 3 weeks a year

NAME: Oseon 8920
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Smuggler's Guide/
INTERESTING: harbored criminal environment similar to Nar Shaddaa's; thrived on its resulting reputation; sheltered gamblers hiding from loan sharks, loan sharks seeking to evade racketeering charges, and occasionally tourists looking for safe lodging; O'lif Khaz (former holovid director) once maintained apartment here and was framed for theft by Sosten Freet (famous singer Ema Slake's agent)

NAME: Erilnar
INTERESTING: 300 K lakes forced its transportation underwater; at some point by Imperial Era, a terrorist attack destroyed most of its monorail network, resulting in a million casualties; Kulbart Zamoon (Erilnar native) blamed the Empire for its lack of response and joined the Alliance; Hutts manipulated Centrality government behind the scenes

NAME: Scillal system
INTERESTING: shipyards in this system were largest starship manufacturing facility in Centrality; though they were much smaller than many core facilities, they were adequate for most Centrality Navy wrship requests; Scillal Designs HQed here; hotspot for terrorist activity

NAME: Arleen system
INTERESTING: namesake of Arleen Loop hyperroute as well was the pleasure yacht Arleen, which ran yearlong tours from the Oseon system to the Antipose system

NAME: Rafa Sun
INTERESTING: Lando chronicled his adventures here (prior to being hired by Beckett's gang) in the Calrissian Chronicles; system's 11 planets and numerous moons covered with enormous plastic ruins of the ancient Sharu, which were impenetrable and among the largest constructions in the galaxy,; many human colonies (dating from early Republic days) sprung up around and between structures

NAME: Rafa III
INTERESTING: site of deep-bore hardrock mining operations that used giant laser drill-bits; a pair of these were gifted as souvenirs to the Poly Pyramid (bar on Rafa IV), which were used to prop open the inner doors of the establishment, frequented by vacationing miners from Rafa III

NAME: Rafa IV
INTERESTING: colony world of Sharu species; main city Teguta Lusat was capital of Rafa system before Sharu uprising in 4 BBY; governed by Duttes Mer (colonial governor of the Rafa

NAME: Rafa V
INTERESTING: c. 1 M BBY, Sharu felt threatened by the Celestials, and hid their cities beneath massive plastic pyramids and used crystalline life-orchards to temporarily drain their intelligence, becoming the primitive Toka or "Broken People", who were exploited by Human colonists as slaves; in 4 BBY Lando discovered the Mindharp and it was activated; pyramids crumbled and Sharu were restored

NAME: Rafa XI
INTERESTING: site of helium refinery & research installation; on Rafa V, Lando and Vuffi Raa disarmed a team of Colonial Constabulary troopers attempting to arrest Lando and forced them aboard their own cargo barge, which Raa reprogrammed to take them on a weeklong trip here; four months later, four of the troopers ahd returned to administrative building on Rava IV

NAME: Dela III
INTERESTING: financial center of the Centrality; those who stayed in the Oseon Belt for long periods of time often had an account on one of Dela II's banks; the system had strict security measures to protect the banks of Dela III from Renatasian terrorists and other pirate groups

NAME: Lekua V
INTERESTING: had several universities, including University of Lekua V

NAME: Cadma system
INTERESTING: shared name with Cadma Conduit (hyperlane) and neighboring Cadma Sector, through which said hyperlane ran

NAME: Zebitrope IV
INTERESTING: homeworld of a lizard species that produced lesai (illegal narcotic drug)

NAME: Zebitrope VIII
INTERESTING: one of the primary planets that cultivated lesai (illegal narcotic drug)

NAME: Ringneldia II
INTERESTING: Centrality's manufacturing center; used a unique local measurement system based around diameter of the Ringneldian bean, making their products totally incompatible with products using galactic standard measurements

NAME: Darvannis
INTERESTING: arid desert world discovered by spice smugglers about 500 years before Great Galactic War; Hutt Cartel built up military forces here during Galactic War; devoid of natural resources, native sentients; sourrounded by dense asteroid field, making approach difficult; little-visited; Hutts built market villas that prospered through illegal weapons trade and other black market goods

NAME: Danos V
INTERESTING: sting insects said to be large ("the size of a house") in comparison to other insects in the galaxy were found here

NAME: Maldra IV
INTERESTING: not long after Yavin, Empire sought to destroy a pirate base, but discovered it actually belonged to the Rebels; Empire claimed it was a munitions base, while Rebels claimed it was a refugee base; regardless, imperial forces led by Captain Briera's ISD Motivator demolished the base

NAME: Berzite
INTERESTING: 3 years before the Battle of Yavin, during the Rebellion's search for a new base, the Spectres cross-referenced Rebublic and Lasat star maps and identified Berzite's moon as suitable; however their stolen Imperial cruiser-carrier was low on fuel so they travelled to Horizon Base to steal more; AP-5, a defecting Imperial protocol droid, warned the Rebels that Berzite's moon was an Imperial trap, suggesting Atollon instead

NAME: Berzite's moon
INTERESTING: 3 years before the Battle of Yavin, during the Rebellion's search for a new base, the Spectres cross-referenced Rebublic and Lasat star maps and identified Berzite's moon as suitable; however their stolen Imperial cruiser-carrier was low on fuel so they travelled to Horizon Base to steal more; AP-5, a defecting Imperial protocol droid, warned the Rebels that Berzite's moon was an Imperial trap, suggesting Atollon instead

NAME: Skeebo
INTERESTING: had many pyramidal monuments; considered the "Jewel of the five systems"

NAME: Baummu
INTERESTING: violently attacked by Imperial forces under Captain Briera, later known as "The Butcher of Baummu"

NAME: Krozurbia
INTERESTING: Krozurbians: engaged in 200 years of war, until Zorneth (Ithorian) intervened, bringing peace

NAME: Pluthan Asteroid Field
INTERESTING: wide asteroid belt; Langro Dis tracked Krova he Hutt to this location shortly after Endor

NAME: Malagarr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: home to droids of Q-7N's type (Malagarrian mining droid); an Imperial incursion took place here in 0 ABY; destroyed when Q-7N discovered that Frap Radicon (Imperial scientis) was developing new gravity well projector technology, which would be detrimental to the Rebels; the droid overloaded the reactor, destroying the planet and himself

NAME: Dilonexa *
INTERESTING: only habitable planet in system was Dilonexa XXIII, with inner 22 worlds too hot and outer 17 too cold

NAME: Dilonexa XXIII
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: farms, fields, prairies, plains, small lakes
INTERESTING: agriworld with no bodies of water larger than small lakes; farms stretched across entire surface, providing food, fuels, plastics, and grain for native bovines; lack of heavy metals gave it a tolerable gravity despite its great size; colonists developed allergic reaction to heavy metals; frequent giant tornadoes until controlled by orbital weather stations, also used as method of control

NAME: Uaua
INTERESTING: most prominent planet in Ua system; Centrality colonists inadvertently introduced a virus to the planet that was carried by mammalian species but proved fatal to avians such as the Quor'sav; as a result, non-avian species were not welcome or trusted here; even insect life here seemed to harass offworlders with undue prejudice

NAME: Falko system
INTERESTING: shared its name with Falko Run hyperlane

NAME: Antipose system
NOTES: systems of Centrality not listed on Centrality WP page

NAME: Antipose IX
NOTES: systems of Centrality not listed on Centrality WP page
INTERESTING: sometime before GCW, pleasure yacht Arleen ran year-long tours from Oseon system to Antipose IX and Antipose XII

NAME: Antipose XII
NOTES: systems of Centrality not listed on Centrality WP page
INTERESTING: sometime before GCW, pleasure yacht Arleen ran year-long tours from Oseon system to Antipose IX and Antipose XII; sparsely populated; noted as having "most violet skies in the universe"; inhabitants used the term "dubesor" as an insult

NAME: Paulking XIV
INTERESTING: renowned for unusual water life, including fur-bearing trout, flying crabs, talking algae

NAME: Tund
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungles, forests, prairies, escarpments, rivers (prior to 5 BBY); radioactive wasteland (after 5 BBY)
INTERESTING: verdant world; Force Nexus on NE borders of Open Sea; remote Sith colony first settled c. 27700 BBY; prison for Sith heretics and exiles; HW of Sith-blooded Sorcerers of Tund (denied existence of light and dark sides; adopted homeworld of Toong; destroyed in 5 BBY by biological warhead released by Rokur Gepta (Croke who infiltrated Sorcerers to keep their knowledge for themselves)

NAME: Douglas III
INTERESTING: made famous by Mendel Douglas (game hunter), who sent back a native jackelope for his collection, yet failed to return himself; notorious for hostile wildlife; later attracted pirates and black-marketeers; of very little interest to galaxy at large;

NAME: Trammis III
INTERESTING: home to gigantic reptilians referred to as dinosaurs, including deadly akorec, which devoured first two teams of settlers; third team almost wiped out reptilians, which later attracted tourists; homeworld of Trammic momes, whose warrens were vast cave networks; some xenoarchaeologists thought it may have been homeworld of Sharu; many Toka spoke Old High Trammic dialect

NAME: Hosrel XI
INTERESTING: few lifeforms on harsh surface were by far considered some of most savage creatures in galaxy; site of top-secret Centrality Navy research base; shield camouflage developed there; Lehesu visited looking for help after escaping Imperial blockade of ThonBoka; Hosrel Perimeter Control issued code 666, signalling Yellow Nine squadron to investigate; they fired on Lehesu to his dismay

NAME: Open Sea
INTERESTING: region largely devoid of stars containing the ThonBoka; domain of the Oswaft; freighters that experienced a hyperdrive failure in the Open Sea could remain undiscovered for centuries; by 43 ABY a few hulks had been discovered and put into use as cautionary examples in the Hosrel system

NAME: StarCave N. (ThonBoka N.)
INTERESTING: sack-shaped nebula full of organic chemicals, gases, carapace creatures, interstellar plankton and Oswaft (giant sentient manta ray-like creatures that fed on nutrients in Nebula; contained hree blue-white stars in its center, which surrounded the only architectural structure in the Nebula, the Cave of Elders; Rokur Gepta tried to destroy the THonBoka but was stopped by Lando during the Battle of ThonBoka

NAME: Cave of Elders
INTERESTING: cave made entirely of precious gemstones processed by Oswaft; was a scale model of the ThonBoka Nebula; Oswaft Elders met here

NAME: Renatasia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: 8 planets in Renatasia system

NAME: Renatasia III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: agriworld; lost Human colony world, one of 14 colonization projects sponsored by Queen Tasia of Grizmallt in 3950 BBY; rediscoverd by Centrality in 13 BBY; Osuno Whett and Vuffi Raa were tasked by Centrality & Empire to win trust of Renatasians, then betrayed them to the Empire and Centran forces, earning Raa title of "Butcher of Renatasia" in brutal subjugation that followed

NAME: Renatasia IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Human-colonized planet

NAME: Kaski system
INTERESTING: Kaski throwing blades were produced here

NAME: Osseriton
INTERESTING: Hemes Arbora migrated from Carrivar to Umaren'k, then to Osseriton. penal colony or prison here, and at least 1 starship manufacturer

NAME: Carrivar
INTERESTING: Hemes Arbora migrated from Carrivar to Umaren'k, then to Osseriton

NAME: Umaren'k
INTERESTING: Hemes Arbora migrated from Carrivar to Umaren'k, then to Osseriton

NAME: Selvaris
INTERESTING: backwater of little significance; its forests and jungles produced plentiful fruit; oceans teemed with various forms of marine life; its twin suns created a tropical climate; said to be the closest inhabited planet to Bilbringi system; YV turned the world into a major POW camp under Malik Carr and began Vongforming; a few prisoners escaped while others were sent to Coruscant for sacrifice

NAME: Throffdon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Gwongdeen
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Galagolos V
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Horska
INTERESTING: site of Imperial Remnant HoloNet relay station

NAME: Dreffon IV
region/grid square/16 days to Dravian Starport with class 1 hyperdrive

NAME: Lontar system
INTERESTING: Lontars aggressively attacked & nearly eradicated Blood Carvers of Batorine

NAME: Flankers
INTERESTING: Imperial garrison abandoned and system destroyed when sun went supernova after Battle of Yavin

NAME: Tsukkia
INTERESTING: Tsukkian water freighters built here

NAME: Palanhi
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, valleys, farms, volcanic islands, small oceans n(less than 50% surface water)

NAME: Vakkar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Fakir
INTERESTING: strange illuminescent crystals formed in upper atmosphere; some Imperial wealth stored here

NAME: Alabash
INTERESTING: alantium for starship hulls mined by Empire

NAME: Halowan
INTERESTING: site of Holowan Labratories (creators of IG droids)

NAME: Mycroft
NOTES: frozen polar caps, hot arid deserts, forested mountains
INTERESTING: home of Intergalactic Zoological Society, branch of Jedi Exploration Corps, Imperial fueling / Repair Station M13

NAME: Iyuta
INTERESTING: Imperial Comm Center in major city of Takari

NAME: Sarnikken
NOTES: WP: Sarnikken Asteroid Belt doesn't link to Sarnikken system

NAME: Sinkar
NOTES: high gravity
INTERESTING: Sinkars are helium-based, black amoeba-like slugs, rumored to be long-lived, intelligent and telepathic -- or mindless energy-suckers

NAME: Yirt-4138-Grek-12
INTERESTING: Site of industrial espionage slicer training center, wiped out before Clone Wars

NAME: Mrisst
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Candovant
INTERESTING: a target of Operation Cinder in 4 ABY, it was eventually devastated by Imperial fleets; NR member world in 34 ABY; represented by Zygli Bruss in NR senate; Candovantans: had reddish-brown skin, dark eyes that could see in ultraviolet spectrum, flattened faces, no visible nose protrusion

NAME: Harix
INTERESTING: strong center of Rebel activity

NAME: Golkus
INTERESTING: Akanah stopped here to pick up fake ID papers from Talon Karrde's organization

NAME: Borleias / Blackmoon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Xa Fel
INTERESTING: Xa Fel: genetically damaged near-humans

NAME: Davnar II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: Davnarians: bipedal, scaly, long-snouted

NAME: Hoszh Iszhir
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: half arid deserts, half poisonous atmo

NAME: Torpris
INTERESTING: housed a slaving consortium headquarters

NAME: Makksre
INTERESTING: pirates active here

NAME: Cheeyoom Matee
INTERESTING: Rebel base here

NAME: Pakrik Major
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban (more densely populated than Pakrik Minor)

NAME: Cortella
INTERESTING: has hereditary monarchy

NAME: Espinar
INTERESTING: Lyra Erso led a survey team here and discovered and mapped a cave system that promised a bounty of rare crystalline deposits; she first met Galen Erso here; she served as his guide on a field team that studied minerals

NAME: Kamparas
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rainforests, grasslands, rolling hills, deep valleys
INTERESTING: Imperial archives here

NAME: Phorliss
INTERESTING: could support almost any kind of life; during Galactic War, Houks from Lijuter immigrated here; after Endor, Mara Jade briefly used aliases Karrinna Jansih and Chiara Lorn to work in a Phorliss cantina as a serving girl while hunting a top Imperial on the run

NAME: Dolomar
INTERESTING: colony world of Sharu species; main city Teguta Lusat was capital of Rafa system before Sharu uprising in 4 BBY; governed by Duttes Mer (colonial governor of the Rafa)

NAME: Pantolomin (Panto Prime)
INTERESTING: tropical tourism, resorts

NAME: Jervo's World
INTERESTING: swoop-duelling arenas

NAME: Toloran
INTERESTING: dedicated to winter tourism: repulsor skiing, hover sledding, wilderness survival camps, ice dragon hunting, ice barge cruises

NAME: Atloran
INTERESTING: zero-G campgrounds, amusement parks

NAME: Charmath
INTERESTING: University of Charmath had some of the most complete historical archives

NAME: Ghaina
INTERESTING: one of the earliest settled colony worlds in the Galactic Republic

NAME: Halpat
region/grid square/NR supply depot for blockade of Koornacht, but not close enough
INTERESTING: razing of gov't office in 3,639 BBY uncovered ancient underground labyrinth

NAME: Prekaz
INTERESTING: ruled by Golden Emperor of Prekaz

NAME: Melahna system
INTERESTING: source of Melahnese food (regional cuisine)

NAME: Vardos
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: home of Garrick and Iden Versio; location of Future Imperial Leaders Military Preparatory School; civilization leveled here during Operation Cinder; during First Order era ash like snow blanketed the ruins, left over from Cinder; by 34 ABY, Protectorate Gleb was overseeing the rebuilding of the planet when she was killed by First Order Commander Gideon Hask, who attempted to bring the planet under First Order rule

NAME: Coruscant system/Imperial system/Yuuzhan'tar system
NOTES: "Coruscant system is at origin coordinates (0

NAME: Coruscant Prime
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: tiny star; Coruscant orbited relatively far from it, varying from 207 to 251 M km; after YV war, many YV ships were emptied of crew, loaded with weapons and dropped into the star in accordance with negotiated peace terms; after Second Imperial Civil War, Kray's body was sent into the sun to incinerate it and prevent possibility of him returning from the dead once more

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Centax-1
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Centax-2
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Centax-3 ("The Aunt")

NAME: Hesperidium

NAME: Khorya system

NAME: Hollow Moon

NAME: Kintan

INTERESTING: after supernova explosion nearby, evolution divided Nikto into 5 subspecies; original homeworld of Kintan striders, found across the galaxy as Hutts' pets but were driven extinct here; c. 26000 BBY, Cult of M'dweshuu (worshiped supernova) formed here; Niktos permanently indentured to Hutts c. 25100 BBY; joined Republic at least 2 decades before CW, but Senators were puppets of Hutts

NAME: M'dweshuu system
INTERESTING: star went supernova tens of thousands of years before GCW, bathing Kintan in mutating radiation

NAME: Klatooine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: taken over by Hutts c. 25100 BBY; ruled by Council of Elders; Hutts controlled all Klatooinian activities offworld; pak'pah fruit was found only here, possibly due to soil's wintrium content; Fountain of Ancients (geyser of liquid wintrium) revered as holy site; most buildings built over wells; slave revolt broke out in 44 ABY; Leia and negotiators helped them gain admission to the Galactic Alliance

NAME: Vontor
INTERESTING: 3 battles fought between forces of Xim the Despot and Hutts here before founding of Republic--first two ended in stalemate, but in the third, Hutts (under Kossak) surprised Xim with hordes of new allies (Weequays, Vodrans, Nikto and Klatooinians), defeating him

NAME: Nimia

NAME: Kafane
INTERESTING: poor agriworld

NAME: Ac'fren system
INTERESTING: shared name with Ac'fren Spur hyperlane

NAME: Delassin Six

NAME: Morvogodine
INTERESTING: teemed with life; occupied by Empire during GCW; hosted notoriously vicious Stormtrooper training facility run by Commander Kayn Somos; Empire arrested famous vandfillist musician Maxa Jandovar here to suppress her politically outspoken artisic endeavors and she died in custody; Kardue'sai'Malloc (Devaronian male) had been arranging transport here when he heard of her death

NAME: Delacrix
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: absorbed into Xim's empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron; histories of the planet spoke of the ancient Hutts (previous to their civil war) with horror and fear; during the Fourth Pius Dea Crusade, the Pius Dea-controlled Republic launched assaults on Delacrix and other planets north of Hutt Space

NAME: Kegan
INTERESTING: By 8011 C.R.C., Kanjiklub (criminal organization) had attempted to intrude upon Kegan system during efforts to increase their territory, though the incursion was halted by local NR police forces

NAME: Bnach

NAME: Stieg
INTERESTING: during Kegan's isolationist period, The Learning (teaching curriculum on Kegan) taught that Stieg was a dangerous place to visit, surrounded by war and without any governing body (despite Stieg-Fan's actually peaceful government)

NAME: Akrit'tar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: inhospitable, barren, lifeless world where an Imperial prison was established for safekeeping of political prisoners; Tregga (one of Han's former smuggling associates) was sentenced to a life of hard labor after being caught with a smuggled cargo of chak-root; Tycho Celchu (Rogue Squadron pilot) held here after failed attempt at "brainwashing" aboard the Lusankya

NAME: F'tral
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: undersea urban, marshes, swamplands, volcanic islands, oceans
INTERESTING: large oceanic planet with 93% surface water; Iyra: cephalopods with four or more tentacles and one eyestalk for each tentacle, with more tentacles/eyes growing with age; caste system based on number of tentacles; Iyra inhabited undersea cities and developed many valuable technologies, including corrosion-resistant alloys, gravity well projectors and starship inertial devices

NAME: Vatleria
INTERESTING: foggy world; during last decades of Republic it was abandoned when its inhabtants moved to the Core worlds; Empire established a base here and a Rebel team tried to overthrow the garrison but was defeated by Vader

NAME: Seventh Moon of Zircon
INTERESTING: home to Lothar the Grouch

NAME: Jerijador

NAME: Gestrex III
INTERESTING: Imperial Navy Base here destroyed during GCW; Armx (espionage droid turned bounty hunter) was briefly assigned here

NAME: Koozebane

NAME: Freliq
INTERESTING: agriworld; home of Lepusas, whose sentience was debated; many of planet's inhabitants were farmers

NAME: Pa'Lowick system
INTERESTING: quarantined by Empire during GCW when Empire began to conduct experiments with Lowickan Firegems to use them as high-energy power sources; a task force of Star Destroyers and Imperial Customs cruisers patrolled the region to keep out trespassers

NAME: Lowick
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, rainforests, salt marshes, seas, oceans
INTERESTING: had equatorial rainforests; Pa'lowick hunted, fished and farmed in the salt marshes; planet abounded in fish, reptiles, marlello ducks, and veejy fruit; discovered in 10 BBY by miners exploiting the nearby Lowick Asteroid belt for Lowickan Firegems; quarantined while Empire conducted experiments with Lowickan Firegems during GCW; homeworld of Sy Snootles

NAME: Lowick Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: source of Lowickan Firegems; miners discovered Pa'Lowick while scouting for gems in the belt in 10 BBY; quarantined by Empire during GCW when Empire began to conduct experiments with Lowickan Firegems to use them as high-energy power sources; a task force of Star Destroyers and Imperial Customs cruisers patrolled the region to keep out trespassers

NAME: Sisk
INTERESTING: cooled when its star suffered partial atomic collapse; had considerable natural resources, but antisocial nature of Sic-Six made it impossible to exploit them in any organized way; Sic-Six had complex dining etiquette; origin point of Sic-Six-layer cake (popular dessert, also served in Dex's Diner on Coruscant)

NAME: Thraisai
INTERESTING: Beilert Valance (Human bounty hunter) led a group of mercenaries in capturing a ring of slavers on Thraisai at some point between 17 BBY and 0 ABY; this mission helped Valance attain elite hunter status

NAME: Er'stacia
INTERESTING: surface dominated by large tidal pools; Er'stacians: divided into clans based on lineages traced back to ancestors' tidal pools; all revered the Venerable One (single forbear represented by a massive stone called the Megalith); near-perpetual clan wars for possession of the stone; Jedi Council feared it might lead to genocide, sent Mace Windu, who cut stone into thousands of pieces

NAME: Hurikane
INTERESTING: unidentified natives were made of stone and purple Hurrikaine crystals; 58 BBY a young Mace Windu sent here to negotiate with natives to obtain some Hurikane crystals, but when things went poorly, some of the natives chased him; one fell into a canyon and shattered; after Mace mended him with the Force, the bing gave Mace som crystals from its own body

NAME: Yoon Cloud system
INTERESTING: home to a 12-armed glider species; a Nova scout on his or her way back from the initial exploration of the system stopped by the University of Sanbra to drop off a specimen of the glider species for study

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
NOTES: Wookieepedia needs grid square update
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance were briefly stationed here during a mission to contact the Partisans; pink oceans had crystalline formations jutting out from the waves, some topped with flat, solid rock large enough to land a starship on; some formations housed caves where structures could be built; Jedha's destruction pelted NaJedha with dust and fiery rocks

NAME: Jedha (Pilgrim Moon)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
NOTES: Wookieepedia needs grid square update
INTERESTING: small, cold desert moon; historical, spiritual significance made it a world of worship for Force believers, and a holy pilgrimage site for those who sought spiritual guidance; occupied by Empire before Yavin to control its kyber crystal resources, provoking an insurgency by Saw Gerrera's Partisans; test site of Death Star's superlaser, cracking its crust and obliterating the Holy City

NAME: Ianane III

NAME: Ianane Ring
INTERESTING: ring-like structure; its ruins orbited Ianane III; its surface features had been reduced to black ash at some point, which contrasted with the white surface of the planet (result of white sand reflecting sunlight); widely believed to have been constructed by the Celestials, who had disappeared by 30000 BBY

INTERESTING: a starship pilot discovered valuable ore for durasteel-making after crashing here, and attempted to make a claim, naming it after a god of death; Tangan Industries altered his claim after one of their cargo ships heard his transmission and established their own three mining cities after his rescue; their crews fought over claims; Revan traded tech for fuel and supplies here

INTERESTING: the sunward side baked in temperatures hot enough to melt droids; the dark side was humid and mostly covered in cities, but suffered from frequent groundquakes; by the Imperial era, Gorse had seemingly exhausted its thorilide reserves and turned to importing and refining the crystals from Cynda; a small rebel cell led by Hera Syndulla & Kanan Jarrus operated here; afterward, thorilide mining was reestablished on the sunward side while Cynda was reestablished as a nature preserve

NAME: Cynda
