INTERESTING: during Cold War, Archenar asteroid belt site of Republic victory

NAME: Chalacta
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Moobia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Moobian torsion valve (tool found in Watto's junk shop)

NAME: Katalla
INTERESTING: playground for rich and famous during CW

NAME: Haidoral Prime
NOTES: stated as being in Kontahr Sector, though it appears to exist in Kastolar sector
INTERESTING: considered a backwater by its governor, Everi Chalis. Haidoral Prime had at least three continents and a capital city that the Empire named Haidoral Administrative Center One, while the local populous named it "Glitter" after the crystal mountains that lined the horizon. The day after retreating from Haidoral, Twilight Company's Corvette Thunderstrike regrouped in Kontahr sector; native figs grew here & brandy was made here

NAME: Kwenn
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Keldooine
INTERESTING: Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide; minor trade world; served as a customs stop for ships leaving Hutt Space

NAME: Nar Bo Sholla
INTERESTING: homeworld of spor crawler (deadly, poisonous insect that was adapted to burrowing in dirt and sand); part of Hutt Empire c. 25000 BBY; Morteos (Human male assassin) born here in 25 BBY; in 28 BBY it was one of a number of worlds that suffered damage from a stone mite infestation (structure-damaging arthropods); conquered by YV

NAME: Mantilorr system
INTERESTING: Mantilorrians: some inhabited Kwenn Station; rat catchers of this species were hired to catch Salacious B. Crumb when he became too much of a pest on Kwenn Station

NAME: Yurb
INTERESTING: arid homeworld of razor-tailed tiger of the Dust Pits (particularly arid region on Yurb)

NAME: Nar Kreeta
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: enormous mountains, deep canyons, large deserts, alkaline oceans
NOTES: fun rancor poster
INTERESTING: Hutt colony; major trade world; focus of New Jedi Order's attention during Disciples of Ragnos crisis; mining guild here informed Jedi Praxeum that several guild elders had gone missing and suspected a Hutt connection, but local Hutt crimelord disavowed knowledge; Jaden Korr (Jedi Knight) investigated, found and rescued a number of captured Humans meant to be used as quarry in Rancor pit matches, escaping the complex in his master's ship; conquered by YV

NAME: Quesh
INTERESTING: riddled with toxic waste due to a period of geological instability in the past called the Quake; discovered by Republic during Great War; promptly abandoned due to poisonous atmosphere; Bardian Aelto (Republic chemist) realized potential for some chemicals here to be used for Republic; many chemicals could be used in adrenals; after Aelto's discovery, swiftly reoccupied by Republic

NAME: Nimban
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Add Sisar Run on Wookieepedia
INTERESTING: famous for voluntarily leaving Galactic Republic to join Hutts; victim of Third Pius Dea Crusade in 11939 BBY; HQs of Hoersch-Kessel Drive and Delban Faxicorp here; conquered by YV

NAME: Sionia
NOTES: Sionia not mentioned on Sionia system WP page
INTERESTING: homeworld of Sionian Skups; planet noted for number of master thieves it produced

NAME: Sleheyron
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: homeworld of Ziro; wealthy Hutts from here often wore golden tattoos; slave and tibanna-based economy second only to Nar Shaddaa amongst the Hutt worlds; volcanic world where few remaining wildernesses were uninhabitable, made of jagged spires of basaltic slag; most of planet was covered in urban areas, spaceports and refinery districts; much intrigue here

NAME: Ulmatra
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: minor trade world; Durga based here; home of Ulmatran condor; lay within Kajidier kajidic's sphere of influence; c. 3643 BBY, Ulmatra housed hundreds of corporations suspected of laundering; an individual visited, sliced the corporations' computers to find out which businesses laundered credits for the Exchange (criminal organization), and was rewarded by Hutts for the info

NAME: Zisia
INTERESTING: Zisians; had scaly green skin, orange eyes; often suffered from rheumy eyes and wrinkled skin hanging in loose flaps during old age, served as pliant Hutt slaves for millennia

NAME: Kor Nasirii
INTERESTING: throneworld of Nasirii Hutt kajidic; during Cold War in 3642 BBY, it housed databases maintained by the Hutts that contained information used to blackmail prominent figures throughout the galaxy

NAME: Kor Vosadii
INTERESTING: throneworld of Vosadii Hutt kajidic

NAME: Kor Besadii
INTERESTING: throneworld of Besadii Hutt kajidic; ancient palaces sprawled across its surface, including Gercor's Retreat, built across hundred of islands in center of a large swamp and had decentralized, village-like structure (included entertainment halls, vaults, private dwellings for clan members

NAME: Kor Nijiladii
INTERESTING: Hutt throneworld

NAME: Kor Hestilic
INTERESTING: throneworld of Hestilic Hutt kajidic

NAME: Mulatan
INTERESTING: served as guardian world dedicated to the defense of the Bootana Hutta and its throneworlds and was one of the few locations where Hutt warships were commonly found; outlanders were encouraged not to linger here; Bootana Hutta was believed by many outsiders to have escaped YV war devastation; affiliated with Qunaalac Hutt kajidic

NAME: Nar Chunna
INTERESTING: served primarily as trade outpost; said to be awash in priceless artifacts

NAME: Langoona
INTERESTING: Langoonans: specialized in making death-masks (decorated with gems, precious metals), were enslaved by Hutts, became a favored slave species, then rebelled and were crushed, with large numbers slaughtered; Hutts retaliated by stripping world of all technology, reducing Langoonans to primeval existence; turned into safari world and Langoonans hunted and killed in staged hunts

NAME: Fwillsving
grid square/sector/near Kessel, Honoghr, and Kubindi
INTERESTING: sometimes used by smugglers on the Kessel Run as a repair depot and hideaway from Imperial patrol ships; in 22 BBY overzealous celebrants of a limmie/bolo-ball victory over neighboring Kubindi severely damaged Svitalos (capital city)

NAME: Kessel Minor (Xo's Eye)
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: alkali flats, barren rocky mountains, extensive mines
INTERESTING: known as Xo's Eye under Xim's Empire, was a missshapen lump of a prison world home to the galaxy's largest glitterstim mining operation; under Imperial rule, slave labor was used extensively; thin atmosphere, with most surface air provided by air factories on the surface, though the produced air continually leaked away into space; ancient ruins dotted the landscape, possibly of Sith origin

NAME: Garrison Moon
INTERESTING: known by Kessel miners as the Sky Bogey; shattered by Death Star Prototype in 11 ABY, but a large fragment was still orbiting Kessel as of 43 ABY; apparently hollowed out to house Kessel Correctional Facility and a garrison; only a large docking bay and comm tower were visible on the surface; slave pens and processing centers took up first 4 levels and command center was on the lowest 5th level

NAME: Diamond Asteroids
INTERESTING: unusual asteroids containing large quantities of diamonds; hard and dangerous to mine

NAME: Maw Imperial Prison
INTERESTING: prison facility on a barren planetoid with magma spots; existed in almost total secrecy aside from occasional rumors; it included an environmental dome, main prison buildings, a weapons storage building, a series of 7 comm relays to nearby Imperial ships, and at least two landing platforms, including one for tankers, connected by a repulsorlift railway; destroyed by Rogues sometime after Hoth

NAME: Kessel
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Solo: ASWS Tales from Vandor/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren spice mines (northern hemisphere), lush sanctuaries (southern hemisphere)
NOTES: Kessel system (canon) article claims Oba Diah in same system (erroneously, Solo Guide cited shows differently)
INTERESTING: exported Kesselstone, coaxium; abuses of Pykes' slave labor mining operations here were overlooked by King Yaruba (lived at southern lush sanctuaries); hot and humid climate; hotbed of life; key world in spice trade; Han, Lando, Chewie, Qi'ra, L3-37 freed slaves and droids from Pykes before stealing coaxium in 10 BBY; Spectres rescued several Wookiees here in 5 ABY

NAME: Akkadese Maelstrom (Maw Nebulae)
PARENT: Outer Rim/Akkadese Maelstrom//Kessel/Aeneid, Drualkiin, Kessel, Honoghr, Litle Kessel, Randa, Zerm
INTERESTING: cluster of matter in Kessel sector containing interstellar gas, carbonbergs, ice chunks, other debris, and creatures known as summa-verminoth; the Kessel Run passed through the Maelstrom

NAME: The Pit
INTERESTING: area of stray asteroids throughout the arm of a nebula at the end of the Kessel Run; despite being easier to navigate than the Maw, pilots who made it by the black holes often lost focus entering the Pit and collided with an asteroid

NAME: The Maw
INTERESTING: mostly unnavigable cluster of black holes, visible due to ionizing gases; in 44 ABY it was discovered that the Killiks created the Maw to serve as a prison for Abeloth using Centerpoint Station to build the cluster and Sinkhole Station to maintain it; considered one of the Wonders of the Galaxy; site of Maw Installation, where Death Star prototype & other Imperial superweapons were built

NAME: Sinkhole Station
INTERESTING: used by Killiks to construct the Maw as prison for Abeloth; looked like Centerpoint Station but much smaller

NAME: Drualkiin system
INTERESTING: served as notable transshipment point for spice; during GCW, Ill Wind (spice-smuggling ship) made runs through Kessel and Drualkiin systems

NAME: Drualkiin system
INTERESTING: served as notable transshipment point for spice; during GCW, Ill Wind (spice-smuggling ship) made runs through Kessel and Drualkiin systems

NAME: Randa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: small Rebel base here during GCW where Luke took refuge briefly after Yavin; when Han and Chewie stopped to visit, they discovered Mira Volz had stowed away aboard the Falcon, fleeing the Empire; targeted for destruction by Gaen Drommel (Imperial Admiral); his success earned him command of the Guardian (Executor-class Star Dreadnaught)

NAME: Injopan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: the One Two Many (bulk cruiser operated by Corellians) once visited here before departing for the Maw

NAME: Zerm
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: once a planet with weird weather and killer storms, it became a verdant paradise with thriving farms run by human inhabitants and lush rainforests after professor Renn Volz and his daughter Mira tested the experimental Imperial ship Ionic Ring on the world; afterwards, Bzorn (Imperial captain) commandeered the ship, intending to destroy Rebel planets with it

NAME: Oba Diah
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: Pyke Syndicate HQ; Pykes managed spice distribution from here; Valorum sent aide Silman and Sifo-Dyas (Jedi Master) here to settle a dispute, but Pykes were hired by the Sith to shoot them down, killing Sifo-Dyas and capturing Silman as insurance against the Sith; after collapse of Empire, Oba Diah became too "embattled" and relinquished much of the spice trade to Spice Runners of Kijimi

NAME: Oba Diah's moon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: Valorum's aire Silman and Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas's shuttle shot down by Pykes and crashed here; requently ravaged by severe sandstorms; crash site discovered when Plo Koon and 104th battalion picked up distress signal

NAME: Mandrine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
INTERESTING: Nihil attacked Kiapene trading post here during High Republic era; crew of Capri Nitari (smuggling starship) visited several bars here to celebrate a successful spice run; Kronus and his thugs caused a brawl here and Kronus was killed by a thermal detonator

NAME: Tilurus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/

NAME: Aeneid system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Solo ASWS Tales from Vandor/
NOTES: Orbits: says 14 planets; article, image say 15; lacking canon article via Tales from Vandor
INTERESTING: contained 15 planets (13 inhabited, each represented on Aeneid Council of Elders); according to Squishmael (Sloogarian). a young Han was once tricked by Lando and Marshak into smuggling Kessel birds out of here

NAME: Rion
INTERESTING: multiple moons where Kanan and Hera spent time; crew of Uhumele traveled here in 19 BBY to search for Kai Hudorra (Jedi Master), as it was neither famous nor Hutt-affiliated; Rebel base here during GCW; Bzorn (Imperial captain) demanded arrest of all Rebels; when people of Rion refused, he used the experimental ship Ionic Ring to devastate the planet's climate, leading to mass starvation

NAME: Honoghr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Logru (Loghru)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: covered in molten lava

NAME: Ungr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Goettar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: barren rocky world with no atmosphere

NAME: Honoghr
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rainforests (before 20 BBY), poisonous desert plains (after 20 BBY)
INTERESTING: covered by a single globe-spanning continent; once part of Rakatan empire; Sith academy here during New Sith Wars; CIS ship crashed here and cargo of Trihexalophine1138 destroyed ecosystems except for small areas; Vader was impressed by locals and pledged to help clean the land but actually continued to poison them in exchange for Noghri serving as bodyguards

NAME: Andelich
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Fildrost
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kuthul
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: frozen giant ice ball devoid of life

NAME: Little Kessel
INTERESTING: ruled by Xim'tahal the Defaced (Kaleesh warlord) during Cold War; considered beautiful by inhabitants; tectonically stable by 0 ABY; had not experienced groundquakes in so many eons that its inhabitants didn't know what one was, but Empire's Ionic Ring (superweapon) caused groundquakes and formation of volcanoes

NAME: Prishella III
NOTES: disambiguation page?
INTERESTING: Imperial planet; Evar Orllincus (Imperial General) was taken prisoner by Alliance forces while inspecting its garrison

NAME: Formos
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: member of Xim's Empire; became smuggling haven near Kessel; late in CW, was heavily contested until CIS victory due to use of Scorpenek annihilator droids; during GCW, Quirt (Imperial officer) would collect criminals off the streets here and ship them to Kessel to work in the mines; had a spaceport but aside from its smuggling aspect, had little to offer visitors

NAME: Ashteri's Cloud
INTERESTING: vast drift of ionized tuderium gas that floated along one edge of the Kessel sector by 44 ABY, when Jaina and Lando (in his ship the Rockhound) were attacked by a group of Sith pirates looking for starships to capture for their fleet

NAME: Moralan
INTERESTING: Moralans: Hutt slave species; during Xim Wars, Xim's forces entered system; upon leaving, he convinced Moralans to launch a successful rebellion against Hutts; a parliament was established, but a Hutt counterattack led to the complete sterilization of the planet; hyperlanes once connecting Moralan to Honoghr and Hutt Space interior eventually ceased to exist

NAME: Elgit
INTERESTING: minor trade world; served as clearinghouse for goods that were reserved for the Bootana Hutta region; hyperlanes leading here were patrolled by fleet of Troonol the Hutt (of Qunaalac kajidic)

NAME: The Pearl
INTERESTING: in disrepair by time of GCW; despite this, it remained a major trading location because of its crossroads location; owned by Harke (Sakiyan male)

NAME: Usk
INTERESTING: homeworld of a sentient species enslaved at some point in their history; later went extinct, leaving their home planet a derelict world

NAME: Lexas Prime system
INTERESTING: Lexas systems included Lexas Prime system; at some point by 2 ABY, several petty crimelords operated here; Karalan )Krish smuggler) worked for the crimelords but got progressively deeper in debt; after losing his starship and almost being killed by a bounty hunter, Karalan instead became a member of the Mytaranor Slaving Council

NAME: P'frorin system
INTERESTING: home to P'frorin gotta-worm

NAME: Eadu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Where In the Galaxy Are the Worlds of Rogue One?/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jagged rock formations, broad mesas, black stone ridges, narrow spires, canyons, rivers, streams
INTERESTING: storm-wracked planet that hosted an Imperial Energy Conversion Laboratory where Galen Erso and Imperial scientists attempred to unlock secrets of the kyber crystals as part of the Death Star project; targeted by an Alliance strike, resulting in Erso's death and the destruction of the facility; southern hemisphere also contained a village cluster populated by nerf herders; population: 2.5 M

NAME: Bheriz
INTERESTING: remote mining planet; sometime during CW, contacted by CIS forces and Republic; native Bherizian were led by Viceroy of Bheriz

NAME: The Inamorata
INTERESTING: portions of the Imperial fleet hid here after Endor, though not as large a group as the one that hid in the Vulpinus Nebula; despite this there were still hundreds of Star Destroyers and thousands of smaller craft

NAME: Port Lasgo *
INTERESTING: unidentified planet containing at least one spaceport called Lasgo Port; surroundede by minefield left there during Second Imperial Civil War; in 139 ABY, AG-37 (assassin droid) and companions visited while delivering supplies

NAME: Minavar system
INTERESTING: at some point an expedition that included the Human infant Reina Gale and her family established a colony here, but by 0 ABY a virus ravaged the colony, killing nearly its entire population (including Reina's parents, leaving her in the care of her uncle)

NAME: Trigaskian Blur
INTERESTING: location relatively far from Mindor (Inner Rim); when Mindor resistance leader Aeona Cantor asked her fellow insurgent Tripp about the status of subspace jammers that Shadowspawn had installed on Mindor in 5 ABY, Tripp replied that the jammers were inoperative, and that they could send a subspace signal all the way to the Trigaskian Blur if they wanted

NAME: Mugg Fallow
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: lifeless continents, oceans & rivers of gray ooze, petrified trees

NAME: Persappa
INTERESTING: mutated inbred blue-spotted, amphibious rancors

NAME: Viis
INTERESTING: enslaved Aaroun, bred them as servants, gladiators. Viis Empire decimated by outbreak of Mnggal-Mnggal

NAME: Rakata Prime
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Byss / Relus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

INTERESTING: Type II atmosphere (breath mask suggested), lower than standard gravity

NAME: Gatalenta
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

INTERESTING: shared name with 12th Solassi Interzonals Challenge Match (gladiator walker competition)

NAME: Verdanaia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Verdanaian Sliding Hands (martial art)

NAME: Johria system
INTERESTING: Johrian whiskey from here

NAME: Columus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Recopia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: sulfuric oceans, poisonous clouds, km-high plateau islands

NAME: Fromish system
INTERESTING: Fromish ale from here

NAME: Verdoria system
INTERESTING: home of Verdorian fire rats

NAME: Seyugi
INTERESTING: Seyugi Dervishes: Force-using cult

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kamori
INTERESTING: at least 4 major cities - Kimora City, Tandaro, Hyra, Jandal

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Darakin system
INTERESTING: site of Darakin University

NAME: Ilthan system
INTERESTING: Ilthan space mine (weapon) from here

NAME: Corellia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, rolling hills, dense forests, lush fields, vast seas

NAME: Messia system
INTERESTING: homeworld of Messian flame lizard

NAME: New Plympto
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests of 200m hiakk trees, tangled thickets, meadows, swamps w algae mat coverings

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Suns of Fortune/

NAME: Zalso
INTERESTING: Cor'tan fruit grown here

NAME: Jalin system
INTERESTING: Jalinese knife from here

NAME: Vagneria system
INTERESTING: source of Vagnerian canaps

NAME: Koru Neimoidia
INTERESTING: Neimoidian purse world

NAME: Deko Neimoidia
INTERESTING: Neimoidian purse world

NAME: Hetnagaro
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron p. 422 (decimated or destroyed by Empire)/
INTERESTING: devastated by the Empire during its reign, at some point by 4 ABY; along with planets such as Alderaan and Nacronis, Hetnagaro was one of the worlds that the New Republic U-wing pilot Kairos wished to avenge through the destruction of the Empire

NAME: Anukara
INTERESTING: site of an Imperial Munitions Factory that was bombed by the Dreamers, a partisan splinter group infiltrated by the Imperial Inferno squad, upon its opening in 0 ABY

NAME: Cato Neimoidia
INTERESTING: Neimoidian purse world

NAME: Halanit
INTERESTING: gas giant's moon; colony built into ice fissure covered by transparisteel dome; wiped out by Imperials

NAME: Raed-7
INTERESTING: traded with its neighbor, Bellassa

NAME: Mennar-Daye
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance had base within cave systems here; 204th Imperial Fighter Wing flew bombing runs over cave systems for days; later had NR presence; starship Yissira Zyde traveled to the commerce center on Mennar-Daye, where it was screened by Republic authorities

NAME: Lankashiir
NOTES: WP: name could be reference to Lancashire, UK

NAME: Petrakis
INTERESTING: site of first B-wing engagement (convoy attack) with Imperial forces

NAME: Manaan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Chrome Citadel
INTERESTING: located in deep space; once inhabited by asteroid miners; abandoned decades before Galactic Civil War and eventually became home to smugglers and slavers; still inhabited by 28 ABY, but piecemeal repairs made the place look like it could fall apart at any moment

NAME: Teljkon system
INTERESTING: Teljkon Vagabond named because it was first sighted here by a Hrasskis monitor ship

NAME: Hrasskis
INTERESTING: NR member at time of Black Fleet Crisis; Hrasskis had large, veined air sacs on their backs

NAME: Belasco
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Urun Five
INTERESTING: natives sometimes stuck non-natives on top of their trees as decorations

NAME: Daroon
INTERESTING: Represented in Imperial Senate by Alku Vordu

NAME: Tambor Deep Space Centre
INTERESTING: mobile repair shipyard for CIS run by Gorgol the Handy (Geonosian); Jedi & clone troopers captured station

NAME: Khemerion
INTERESTING: Separatist Ruusaan Skirata detained here by Republic during CW

NAME: Hoth's Brand
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named after Hoth (Jedi Lord)

NAME: Pernicar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named after Pernicar (Jedi Master)

NAME: Charny
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named after Kiel Charny (Jedi Knight)

NAME: Ruusan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, rivers, lakes (pre-1000 BBY); deserts, canyons, caves (post-1000 BBY)
INTERESTING: three moons, referred to by locals as the "Three Sisters"; most famous for Ruusan campaign (last stand of the Brotherhood of Darkness under Lord Kaan); birthplace of Darth Bane's Order of the Sith Lords; lent its name to the Ruusan Reformations enacted after the battle; mineral deposits proved disappointing, but was only source of Ruusan crystal; mostly forgotten by Imperial Era

NAME: Ruusan 2
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of the "Three Sisters" (Ruusan's moons); had very turbulent atmosphere with frequent storms; lightning and giant clouds constantly raged over the surface; Skytop Station (CIS listening post) positioned there in 22 BBY during CW; Anakin and Ahsoka infiltrated station on a mission to retrieve the stolen R2-D2; station eventually destroyed after they had completed their mission

NAME: Turpimir
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: WP says 3rd orbit in text
INTERESTING: named after Turpimir (Jedi Knight)

NAME: Farfalla's Diamonds
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: divided space between the planets Turpimir and Zor Vlahu; named after Valenthyne Farfalla (Jedi Lord and Master)

NAME: Zor Vlahu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named for Zor Vlahu (Jedi who fought in the Ruusan campaign during the New Sith Wars)

NAME: Myl Vlahu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named after Myl Vlahu (Jedi who fought in the Ruusan campaign during the New Sith Wars)

NAME: Saleeh
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named for Saleeh (Jedi Lord who fought in the Ruusan campaign)

NAME: Gale
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named for Lord Gale, who fought in the Ruusan campaign

NAME: Othone
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named after Johun Othone, who was killed by Darth Zannah during the Duel on Tython

NAME: Petja
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: named for the Jedi Knight Petja, who fought in the Ruusan campaign

NAME: Danalbeth
INTERESTING: theoretical home of Graygl, aquatic sentients transported by unknown benefactors to Iskalon 5,000 years prior to Galactic Civil War afer a series of cataclysms affected several water worlds

NAME: Averill system
INTERESTING: mining world where Empire discovered rich quadrenium lode; native humans were originally divided into autonomous mineclans living in inherited mineholds

NAME: Jarbanov
INTERESTING: surrounded by rings of junk; home to a civilian outpost that processed the junk to supply to the New Republic

NAME: Jarbanov's moon
INTERESTING: the Imperial 204th Fighter Wing's Squadron Four rendezvoused with the cruiser-carrier Allegiance behind this moon in 5 ABY during an attack on Jarbanov's orbital colony

NAME: Bruvia system
INTERESTING: shared name with Bruvian social group

NAME: Xandonia system
INTERESTING: home of assassins known as Xandonian night terrors

NAME: Tyne's Horky
INTERESTING: streets full of mining and service droids used to mine Keschel, Nergon-14; in 22 BBY (shortly before CW) Zorba was imprisoned on Kip and holdings on Tyne's Horky were taken over by Jabba; Empire later controlled mining here; Jann Tosh and hus ungle Gundy lived here; Kleb Zellock was criminal underworld leader here, and ran a Nergon-14 mine

NAME: Istic II
INTERESTING: irradiated; ore-rich; human settlers hunted native Isticians as though they were vermin, with permission of local Imperial governor who labeled them subsentient; Isticians: radiation bombardment mutated into variety of forms, sizes, colors

NAME: Sebaddon
INTERESTING: located above galactic plane, near a black hole; scarred by tectonic activity; surface gray, red; dense stmosphere; no standing water; Lema Xandret went into hiding here and created hexes (combat droids); orbit knocked off-course, sending it towards black hole

NAME: Miko
NOTES: typo "knowe - known" on WP page
INTERESTING: Jedi of Miko known to wear a unique gear and unique pulsing crytals that produced powerful lightsabers; part of Moff Delurin's territory; Mikoans rebelled and were subjugated by bombardment from Delurin's Galaxy Dragon; after Palpatine's death NR diplomats arrived to try to sway Miko to join republic but Delurin reappeared; eventually Miko joined NR

NAME: Peridon's Folly
INTERESTING: weapons depot operated by traders who sold obsolete arms to crime lords; sectors were controlled by gunrunners and separated by wastelands used as testing ranges; IG-88B collected first bounty here

NAME: Freda
INTERESTING: Near Jante; locked in arms race against Jante until Freda attacked Jante industrial plants on Rett II; Empire ordered ceasefire, Freda eventually withdrew from ceasefire

NAME: Jante
INTERESTING: near Freda; capital city Reynols; locked in arms race against Freda until Freda attacked Jante industrial plants on Rett II; Empire ordered ceasefire, Freda eventually withdrew from ceasefire

INTERESTING: colonized by Humans at some point after 1000 BBY; lightly populated; considered within Hutt Space by time of CW; Imperial fort here during GCW; Ackbar crashed while traveling between Mon Calamari and Yavin 4 (side trip?); while landing here to rescue Ackbar from his escape pod the Falcon was dragged bottom of a lake by giant worms to the and had to be rescued by Ackbar and the Mon Cals

NAME: Omereth
INTERESTING: practically uninhabited, it had little to offer besides fish; in 0 ABY, Luke Skywalker and Nakari Kelen flew Kelen's ship Desert Jewel here to deliver the Givin informant Drusil Bephorin to her husband and their children; they were ambushed by bounty hunters who sank the ship and killed Kelen before they were defeated

NAME: Zoraster
INTERESTING: at some point by 28 BBY, the slaver Krayn (male T'surr slave-raider and pirate) captured Gondi (Human male), taking him offworld and forcing him to work aboard his starship among other slaves

NAME: Dodz
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, barren land, crystal caverns, mines
INTERESTING: tiny world; known throughout the galaxy for its crystal caverns and the wondrous crystals mined from its crust; colonized by miners who brought Ranger X-One defense droids with them; ruled by Citizen's Council of Dodz, though the people had to fight against oppressive rulers occasionally such as Kugg, who appointed himself governor; R2 & C-3PO helped Jost Ellon overthrow Kugg

NAME: Altor 14
INTERESTING: Mineral-rich world discovered in 15 BBY by Rego MIneral Company, whose representatives made mining deals with the Nuiwit, to the chagrin of the Avogwi, who viewed it as foolish to give away resources to outsiders; Avogwi: sentient birds (kill or be killed), Nuiwit: sentient lizards w eyestalks, detachable tails (pacifist); planet was subjugated by Empire

NAME: Giaca
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: dense Toroc tree forests, basaltic mesas, massive volcanic causeways
INTERESTING: localized hyperspace tangles made hyperroutes here very difficult

NAME: Altiria/Anarris
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, rolling plains, forests, oceans, islands

NAME: Iskadrell
INTERESTING: isolated, with only one known 13-day route leading to Brevost system; Iskalloni had hypercapable ships and made occasional slave-raiding expeditions into galaxy; when Imperials first contacted the Iskalloni, they attempted to form slave-trading alliance but Iskalloni enslaved Imperial emissaries instead; Imperials devastated much of planet with 3 VSDs before being forced to retreat

NAME: Bormter
INTERESTING: Bormterrans: four-armed reptiloids; after Moff Delurin broke with the Empire and declared himself Worlord of Wild Space he used Bormter as a base

NAME: Pacara
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Orroman
INTERESTING: at some point, a group of mercenaries caused a water crisis here; information about the disaster became widely known; Korren Starchaser (NR Scout Service captain) considered this mercenary group disreputable, comparing them to another mercenary group, the Happy Blasters

NAME: Jedd Six
INTERESTING: during last years of the Republic, Lexi Fernandin (Human male explorer) became the first individual to scout the planet; at some point after Yavin, Lexi experienced an incident that made him recall his time exploring Jedd Six

NAME: Frewwil
INTERESTING: explored by Republic Survey Corps scout Barosa Warren more than 50 years before 2 ABY, when it was considered one of the most dangerous worlds under Imperial jurisdiction

NAME: Kriekaal
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: hardened duranium continents, shallow molten duranium oceans
INTERESTING: in 2000000 BBY, an alien named Ssiskor came to Kriekaal but perished in a catastrophe wrapped in legends of supernatural forces that said the oceans themselves destroyed him; new continents were constantly forming; continent of Raltez finished forming by 3 ABY; planet was later rediscovered by NR; Krieks: tribal, sentient tortoises with thick, heat-resistant shells

NAME: Polyneus (Home)
INTERESTING: home to human population; home of sur-avkas (native flying creatures); homeworld of Wyl Lark (NR starfighter pilot who initially joined the Rebellion as part of the Hundred and Twenty), who often missed his homeworld; the Elders held high authority and respect on the planet

NAME: Ephemera
INTERESTING: remote resort world with many spas; Tibanna gas mined to extinction here by the Empire, at which point they abandoned the world; native inhabitants later discovered tuusah, a mine runoff with medicinal properties, leading to a new industry, turning it into one of the galaxy's most popular spas; capital was known as Outpost 665 but was renamed to Wish; despite no solid ground, a species of felines lived here whose excrement was found to have healing properties by a Rothkahar philosopher who tamed them; Poe visited here to recruit Maz Kanata's help during the First Order conflict

NAME: Guagenia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Fennesa
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, hills, rocky outcroppings, shallow caves

NAME: Xerthia
INTERESTING: xerthian hound-slugs native here

NAME: Tujiamoor

INTERESTING: visiting doctor who stole Gree artifact (Sharka'k Noor) visited here just before chain of volcanoes erupted, killing 400,000 colonists

NAME: Ithica system

INTERESTING: an undercover agent for the Rebel Alliance operated here

NAME: Tuttin IV
INTERESTING: inhabitants often joined Smashball teams, b'ssa nuuvu bands, or dusk bands for entertainment

NAME: Sarkania
INTERESTING: source of Sarkanian jelly

NAME: Fedovoi End

NAME: Qlothos
INTERESTING: TIE Bomber missiles intended for suspected Rebel Cell went off-target here & hit residential community 1km away due to atmosphere & cloud disruption

NAME: Mirak Major
INTERESTING: Population of at least 6 billion until safely evacuated after CIS sets off megavolcanoes

NAME: Arkam 13

NAME: Granus IV
NOTES: Coords missing from WP

NAME: Yorn Skot
INTERESTING: pressure pirates would push ships lower in atmo to be crushed, then salvage using industrial equipment

NAME: Chadawa
INTERESTING: reportedly built by an unknown species eons before 0 BBY, forming it to machine-exact specifications; engines powered its rotation and artificial heating warmed its oceans; radioactive particles from this process were siphoned by its satellite rings, periodically expelling them into space at a cyclical rhythm; at "low tide" the particles disrupted starship comms and scanners; at "high tide" other ship systems could be disrupted unless they were within the satellite rings; had a government and a sizable population

NAME: Chadawan moon
INTERESTING: barely larger than an asteroid; desolate

NAME: Perithal VI

INTERESTING: 8 spacedocks, the largest of which was Bacrana Orbital Spacedock A (KDY Orbital Spacedock III)

NAME: Carba Belt
INTERESTING: frequent asteroid collisions; Empire and Bacrana System Defense Force often swept area for rogue asteroids drifting into shipping lanes; two Alliance listening posts on larger asteroids: Outpost C-1 and Outpost C-2

NAME: Tomik (16 moons)
INTERESTING: bright orange & red bands of gases. Most moons captured from Carba belt. 3 moons strip-mined by Lant Mining Corp and abandoned

NAME: Namra (10 moons)
INTERESTING: yellow & orange. Four moons with thin atmospheres & cratered ice crust, and another 6 asteroidal

NAME: Savrant (6 moons)
INTERESTING: green-yellow. six moons, all strip-mined by Lant Mining Corp and abandoned.

NAME: Calito

INTERESTING: sometime before 3642 BBY, Bronzium Brigade operated here. Lant Mining Corp had surface mining operationhere during Galactic Civil War

INTERESTING: uninhabited until Rebels established a starfighter base (X-wing squadron) shortly before Battle of Yavin

NAME: Demar
INTERESTING: red supergiant

NAME: Gart

NAME: Latt (1 moon)

NAME: Demar (1 moon)

INTERESTING: cities built in valleys, atop plateaus, or on sides of mountains, mostly on largest continent. fortunes rose & fell with Lant Mining Corp

NAME: Lish V

NAME: Lish VI
INTERESTING: close to Lish V, causing strong tidal forces

NAME: Lish XI
INTERESTING: light gravity, population of 65,000. ore exports

INTERESTING: fallback Alliance base

NOTES: missing on WP list of orbits

INTERESTING: enviro suits required. location of Rebel Alliance Oracle base; skies greenish in color due to location in planetary nebulae

NAME: Latoma

INTERESTING: site of Eloinie Petro-Munitions factory on southern continent; by 4 ABY, the Neo-Fundamentalist Phlangites active in Fioer desert

NAME: Imberlin system
INTERESTING: at some point by 2 ABY, independent trader ran afoul of Imperial authorities here, was later captured by Gand findsman bounty hunter Lu'daal-ud

NAME: Holageus
INTERESTING: site of intense battle between NR and Imperial Remnant

NAME: Lorahns
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Morasil
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: main sequence star, accompanied by white dwarf Termadus; much older member of the pair, possibly as old as the galaxy itself; nassisted by Termadus, its cold, yellow light could not reach the asteroid belt, but together with Termadus and the gaseous haze between them, they gave off the equivalent light of a single bright star, and also created a much bigger hyperspace shadow

NAME: Termadus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: much younger star than its counterpart; gaseous haze arose between the two due to Termadus drawing gases from Morasil's corona; Termadus, Morasil, and their haze gave off a combined light equivalent to a single bright star; together, the two stars also created a much bigger hyperspace shadow than their individual profiles would

NAME: Acilaris
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: barely large enough to be considered a planetoid; had enough gravity to hold an atmosphere laden with sulfur, carbon, and boron; surface too hot even for a ship to land; was believed to be rich in natural minerals, crystals; temperature prohibited mining activities; in 31 BBY, rumors of the droids of Uffel accepting contracts to design mining machinery able to withstand the local conditions

NAME: Cularin
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: first charted during New Sith Wars, as Jedi expelled Darth Rivan from system; forgotten after 1250 BBY until rediscovery by Reidi Artom in 232 BBY; Tarasin revolted against TF from 161 - 154 BBY (resolved by the Jedi with Cularin Compact), but TF eventually exploited loopholes, gained control of the system, opposed only by Riboga's systemwide criminal Organization; known for exotic hardwoods, especially the ch'hala; whole planet was considered strong in the Force

NAME: Renokk
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: magma seas, rocky mountain islands, volcanoes
INTERESTING: molten planetoid; glow was visible on Cularin; Reidi Artom's survey indicated minerals of interest in planetoid's lava but nobody had attempted to reach them by 31 BBY; rocky outcroppings rising out of the magma; Reidi Artom landed on the tallest one and dubbed it Artom's Crest; rumored metallic city in a cave; Artom revisited and fled after being chased by some sort of large life-form

NAME: Tilnes
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren rock, caverns, subsurface crystal mines
INTERESTING: had atmosphere; barely capable of sustaining life; orbit sometimes took it too close to Morasil; only native life forms were hardy grass, yri worms; meteorite uncovered crystal deposits; crystals could be used for blasters, lightsabers; mining settlements moved underground; crystals, radiation, seismic activity combined to create pulses that interfered with the operation of droids

NAME: Genarius
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: floating cities viewed as relatively lawless by system's standards; mixture of gases rare in the galaxy (many existed in stable form due to radiation from planet's core, which gave off its own glow, heat and energy due to low-energy fusion); forceful windstorms, deadly radiation swept up from below, devastating unprotected cities; cochlera: native jellyfish-like creature

NAME: Ulbasca
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: occupied primary orbit around planet; orbited such that it was always in light of Cularin system's two suns; reflected from Genarius meant that even the side of Ulbasca facing away from sunlight never experienced true night; type II atmosphere requiring breath mask for visits of more than a few hours; only major life forms were lizards and snakes; largest could grow up to 40 meters

NAME: Uffel
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: droid manufacturing moon run, inhabited, owned entirely by droids; thick poisonous atmosphere; perpetually in twilight during its day; first droids came to Uffel with a pair of Twi'leks who were killed when ship crashed while surveying moon in 90 BBY; QS-2D (modified protocol droid) and two R4 units survived; QS-2D determined they were free, decided to mine the moon

NAME: Ostfrei
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: very dark; unique orbit kept it in the shadow of Genarius most of the time; thick atmosphere prevented most light from reaching surface; habitable at one time, but asteroid impacts from Oblis' destruction started seismic chain-reaction leaving the moon uninhabitable; ignored by most of the residents of system; Thaereian Navy had secret military base on Ostfrei since c. 31 BBY

NAME: Eskaron
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: originally inhabitable; perforated by tunnels made by space worms, exposing molten core, destroying local atmosphere and killing several worms; worms moved on after metal was depleted; most tunnels large enough for starships to fly through (some were kilometers wide); organized races set up by Riboga since 72 BBY; continued after Nirama took over in 53 BBY, still active in 32 BBY

NAME: Cularin Belt (Oblis)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Oblis originally a technologically-advanced jungle planet with large crystal deposits; destroyed by weapon powered by the Darkstaff before 1000 BBY; remnants became Cularin Belt; used as a hiding place by Nirama's smugglers; Nirama's criminal organization was based on largest asteroid (400 km diameter); rest of belt was pirate hideout; ships had to exit hyperspace to go further in-system

NAME: Crystal Snare
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of the stranger asteroids in the belt; remnant of the large crystal deposits in Oblis, the planet whose destruction formed the Cularin Belt

NAME: Almas
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: desolate wastelands, grasslands, 2 small mountain ranges
INTERESTING: received little sunlight; despite hot core, not very geologically active; atmosphere initially filled with poisonous gases until Darth Rivan developed kaluthin grass (leaves had glowing phosphorus deposits, lending the world a glowing aura) to alter the atmosphere and produce oxygen; no surface water, but grass drew upon underground lakes, to which settlers would later build wells

NAME: Dorumaa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: originally an inner planet, with orbit crossing Oblis'; Dorumaa was at its closest when Oblis was destroyed, flinging it outward to be captured by Almas, and froze; Dorumaa Investment Group began terraforming in 47 BBY, installing gravity and power generators near the moon's core to warm it and recycle atmosphere; became a top resort world, tourist destination in the Expansion Region

NAME: Morjakar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: planetoid originally from farway system; its star swelled into a red giant, swallowing all planets except Morjakar, sending it spiraling off into deep space, where it eventually entered the Cularin system, settling into an eccentric orbit at an odd angle from the rest of the system's planets; sometimes missed by scouts; not known to be inhabited; no proper research on it as of 31 BBY

NAME: Cularin comet cloud
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: dense cloud (remnants from the system's formation); most comets followed erratic courses; some had dense cores similar to the system's heavier planets; occasional collisions, leading to frozen debris resulting in creation of smaller comets; hyperspace interruptions it caused were an annoyance but contributed to system's defenses; Brin Hesk'l's ship once found floating abandoned here

NAME: Muntuur system
INTERESTING: origin point of Muntuur stones (well-known grouping of seven stones, each weighing at least five metric tons)

NAME: Kardava system
INTERESTING: origin point of Kardavan penitents (group whose membership included humans)

NAME: Ongary IX
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, hfredium mines with central shafts
INTERESTING: hfredium mines converted into CIS Vulture droid starfighter bases during CW; Z-95 pilots who destroyed the base needed helmets with opaque blast shields to block the bright light from their plasma charges; next day the starfighters traveled back to sector forces' base at Ividal aboard Venator-class Star Destroyer

NAME: Tomark II
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance starfighter base Chiron Base

NAME: Ividal

NAME: Fenn
INTERESTING: ganjuko (large creatures with beaks, thick fur coats, whip-like tails; beaks could be made into expensive daggers; were taken to Kothlis, Bothawui, other worlds in Dufilvian sector in pre-Republic days

NAME: The (Second) Wheel
INTERESTING: home of Freemaker Salvage and Repair and the scavenging family that ran it

NAME: Quilken
INTERESTING: Mungo Baobab, Auren Yomm settled here after marrying; they found new sources of roonstones, set up processing facilities and opened Club Baobab casino, targeted to visitors from Roon; security was increased to guard the precious gems; Lando was chased bere in 1 ABY by Thune (bounty hunter hired by Dominic Raynor, former owner of Cloud City); Lando set a trap for Thune in Baobab casino

NAME: Sucharme
INTERESTING: aligned with Trade Federation prior to Naboo; TF's Tallaga Garrison (primary garrison located in city of Tallaga); when government of Sucharme failed to pay an outstanding debt, Trade Federation blockaded planet; local armed forces stood up to TF; lessons learned here helped TF at Naboo

NAME: Felacat
INTERESTING: Felacatians: cat people who would transform into tiger-like creatures when in hyperspace for too long; CIS laid siege to the world during CW

NAME: Ostega
INTERESTING: civil war occurred here before CW

NAME: Ostega Orbital Yards
INTERESTING: shipyard used by cyborg Kligson to build Kligson's Moon

NAME: Elriss
INTERESTING: between 2 and 0 BBY, stomtroopers forced villagers to wait in rain for six hours while triple-checking indentities

NAME: Tenek
INTERESTING: somago (choking worm) and til (herbivores with long necks) native here; metallic bark of vinna trees conducted lightning strikes into soil, where native raen sovra (electrocution worms) fed on electrical charge; these became pests offworld due to their habit of feeding on electricity and metal and using a defensive electric shock when threatened

NAME: Sheela system
INTERESTING: shared name with Sheela Run (secret Mid Rim hyperlane used by Republic to transfer matriel throughout the galaxy during CW)

NAME: Pastil
INTERESTING: site of Republic listening station during CW; Cody and Rex (clone troopers) visited here to inspect the station before traveling to the Rishi system;

NAME: Hishyim
INTERESTING: site of an Imperial patrol station during the Thrawn crisis

NAME: Tau Sakar
INTERESTING: home to seven similar life-bearing worlds, including Garban (fourth planet), homeworld of Jenet; Empire controlled system, forcing Jenet to mine ores on all seven worlds

NAME: Garban
INTERESTING: many Jenet Community Heaps (administered by Jenets' government) were spread around the world and collected scavenged materials such as discarded food, tools, household items; riddled with profitable mines; not part of Republic, but was later controlled by Empire, under which Jenets were enslaved as ore miners in the system's seven worlds

NAME: Risha
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: toxic hothouse, molten rivers, steaming chemical lakes
INTERESTING: did not support Human-like life

NAME: Rishal
INTERESTING: barren, lifeless world rich in metal and ores

NAME: Rishi
INTERESTING: during Republic Era, Lene Kostana (Jedi Master) and Sifo-Dyas (her Padawan) discovered the Hand of Skrye here, and Kostana taught her apprentice a cleansing ritual; endpoint of only well-traveled route into the Rishi Maze; native Rishii lived in nests in mountainous regions; Humans and other natives lived in deep valleys; known for rich fossil fuel resources, especially exonium

NAME: Rishi Moon
INTERESTING: pelted by frequent meteor strikes; housed a Republic listening post known as Rishi Station (invaded and later destroyed by a CIS force led by Grievous in 22 BBY)

NAME: Rishos
INTERESTING: promising stores of gases were found here, waiting to be harvested by enterprising mining corporations

NAME: Hefi
INTERESTING: in wake of first Death Star's destruction, Imperial engineer Bevel Lemelisk fled to Hefi and went into hiding, but Imperial Intelligence agents located him here and the Emperor subsequently had him executed for his incompetence (later reports suggest this story may be apocryphal)

NAME: Phattro system
INTERESTING: origin point of Phattro (beverage)

NAME: Ukio
INTERESTING: agriworld, major producer of foodstuffs; Thrawn sought to conquer it during his campaign against NR

NAME: Varristad
INTERESTING: small mining world with no atmosphere; inhabitants all lived in a large habitation dome owned by a rival to Offworld Mining Corporation; when dome was compromised by Jemba the Hutt, over 250K people were killed; the mining company went bankrupt and mining rights were cheaply obtained by Offworld Mining Corporation

NAME: Shield Gate
INTERESTING: wheel-shaped Golan M3185 space station in Scarif orbit, serving as an opening in the planet's otherwise impenetrable deflector shield; Rebels launched a successful assault on the station, allowing them to attack Scarif's Imperial Security Complex

NAME: Gibad
INTERESTING: one of 200+ worlds that seceded during CW; represented in Seperatist Senate by Esu Rotsino; home to parks, beautiful cities; defied Palpatine during early Empire; home to respected Gibadan Academy of Life Sciences; Palpatine released a virus on the world, destroying Human population as the galaxy watched; Empire released a statement that planet would be ready for re-population within the year

NAME: Molavar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: backwater desert world with a number of seedy spaceports and low-income moisture farms; inhabited by a number of species, but especially by the native Molavarans; Darca Nyl chased Lycan to the planet; Molavarans: caramel-colored skin, long faces with stubby noses, pointed teeth and prominent cheekbones, as well as a head full of fleshy tendrils in place of hair

NAME: Abrion Major
INTERESTING: agriworld; sector capital; Senator Esu Rotsino led the sector and its 200+ agriworlds in defecting to CIS and represented the sector in the Seperatist Senate

NAME: Galpos II
INTERESTING: home to a nest of Thalassian slavers, cleared out by the Empire's 291st Legion using the newly released AT-DPs; suspected to be a base for pirate groups operating in the sector; pirate vessel GrimDeath I (converted Victory-class Star Destroyer crewed by more than 300 pirates) was once tracked traveling here

NAME: Tieos
INTERESTING: one of 200+ worlds that seceded during CW; represented in Seperatist Senate by Esu Rotsino; early in GCW, site of an Imperial base and considered to hold strong potential as a major agriworld

NAME: Roon
INTERESTING: tidally locked; no temperature extremes (cloud cover or extensive ozone layer?); located in Cloak of the Sith (nearly-impenetrable cosmic dust cloud); easily navigable routes long-lost; lockdown of info under Empire helped isolate Roon, whose inhabitants didn't mind; Roon Tours agency shared its name; famed for Roonstones; sought after by treasure hunters; orbited by dangerous asteroids

NAME: Galaxeed
INTERESTING: colony (location unknown, perhaps on a moon) in Roon system; a team from here competed against teams representing Umboo and Tawntoom in Roon Colonial Games in 15 BBY

NAME: Umboo Lightstation
INTERESTING: lightstation on an asteroid; guided vessels through the Roon system; operated by Noop Yeldarb until closed by Governor Koong; Yeldarb was captured, but freed with the help of Mungo Baobab and the lightstation came back into use

NAME: Tascollan Nebula
INTERESTING: contained a single star; during Great Hyperspace War, Sith consort Valik Kodank built Temple of Pain (Sith temple) in nebula and attempted to use Sith artifacts to move it into the center of a sun; when this failed, it was placed inside an asteroid instead; prior to CW, Gomalo (Rodian slaver) left a carbonite slab containing Ji-Ad Sarain (Jedi Knight) floating here, but recovered during CW

NAME: Intuci
INTERESTING: war criminal Gaar Suppoon (under alias of Sonopo Bomoor) sacked the city of Bonaka Nueno and massacred its citizens

NAME: Xilxash
INTERESTING: backwater agriworld; applied for, granted Galactic Alliance membership in 44 ABY; known for delicious brul fruit

NAME: Hrill
INTERESTING: reputed to be quiet, peaceful, and dull; Mungo Baobab was asigned a mission to Hrill by the Merchant Council of Manda, but he ignored the order and ventured in search of the Roon system and its fabled Roonstones, bringing R2 and C-3PO with him

NAME: Threndria system
INTERESTING: home to Threndrian snareflowers (large plants with movement-sensing tentacles)

NAME: Dozoisia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Dozoisian Snark Venom

NAME: Greater Marianas
INTERESTING: little-known dust-swept world subjugated by Empire sometime before Yavin; contained at least one Human settlement; permanent garrison deemed unnecessary as long as a mid- and end-season tax was collected; home to yaggie (creature hunted for skin and meat)

NAME: Lyran IV
INTERESTING: agriworld; Chass na Chadic (NR Alphabet Squadron pilot) once visited here and later recognized it in a holographic map found in a Jedi temple on Harkrova I in 4 ABY; served as a retreat for many smugglers during Imperial era; between Kessel and Ryloth; homeworld of Lyran bloodslug; exported wheat and other grains

NAME: Inat Prime
INTERESTING: Boba Fett had microscopic subdermal trackers placed on Rivo Xarran (later known as The Storyteller) on Inat Prime

NAME: Epsom Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: during GCW Sithless Leethe (Saurian crimelord) owned a summer residence in the belt

NAME: Deralia
INTERESTING: Revan's false memories implanted by the Jedi Council of Dantooine led him to believe he was a common Republic Military recruit from Deralia; 300 years later, the Republic cruiser Valor almost crashed into Deralia, narrowly averted by Nadia Grell, who managed to get the crew working together to pull the ship out of its dive; Dajasufer and Izmalay's Landing were low-lying coastal cities here

NAME: R-Duba
INTERESTING: minor trade world

NAME: Dorande
INTERESTING: Dorande race tried to conquer R-Duba during early Imperial era, but their plan was foiled by R2 and C-3PO

NAME: Rothana
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: sold to KDY c. 800 BBY, leading to Rothana Heavy Engineering's establishment as a subsidiary; home to Imperial shipyards; in 14 BBY, ships stationed here were deployed by Imperial Navy to locations considered to be targets of Berch Teller and his rebel group; largely abandoned in preparation for Battle of Jakku; surrounded by vast honeycomb of orbital shipyards, drydocks for secret projects

NAME: Quiberon V
INTERESTING: mining colony run by Gamorrean Interstellar (mining company)

NAME: Pzob
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: settled by Gamorreans from Gamorr long before Battle of Yavin; settler clans waged war amongst themselves; Empire established secret military base here in 18 BBY, intending to use troops here to crew Eye of Palpatine

NAME: Zybahhod system
INTERESTING: Zybahhod Yenyoni: humanoids with horned skulls, mottled white skin, small tails, thin strands of hair, salt glands behind eyes; played instrument known as udjudg; well-adapted to desert life; some migrated to Tatooine

NAME: V'shar
INTERESTING: home to Unfyr warrior culture centuries before 2 ABY; Ka'hren: tradition-bound, religious, isolationist; many organized faiths had a direct influence in government; long after Unfyr extinction, Kaltor Naklian (Ka'hren academic) researched, taught ancient history at a local university when a discovery of ancient writings in a cavern led to Naklian founding Ni'Shaw-Dak Ministry (new religion)

NAME: Lwhekk
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Yakorki
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Mokivj
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Timelines map, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: grasslands, forests (before cataclysm) lifeless plains, deserts (afterwards)
INTERESTING: spreading lava from an effort to destroy a Seperatist cortosis mine in 19 BBY by Anakin Skywalker, Padme, and Chiss Commander Thrawn caused a cataclysm here; following the Battle of Atollon, Thrawn and Vader were sent to investigate a Force disturbance felt by Palpatine; around this time the Grysks moved four of the planet's moons out of orbit and into the path of hyperlanes; they were stopped in the process of moving a fifth, leaving it drifting away from Mokivj

NAME: B'Knos
INTERESTING: asteroid mining colony within the Abran asteroid belt; in 0 ABY came under Ssi-ruuk attack; presumably all colonists killed or enteched; later, as part of Imperial cover-up, it was reported that supply ship Ambitious had crashed into colony due to unusual solar activity

NAME: G'rho
INTERESTING: in Shiritoku Spur region, but not on Shiritoku Way trade route; under nominal Imperial control only; juvica forests grew here; colonists raised duncows, built Boku Settlement near a rich vein of crimson ore; Dev Sibwarra's family moved here from Chindrila in 11 BBY shortly after his birth; attacked by Ssi-ruuk in 2 BBY (other colonists killed or enteched); Palpatine covered up incident

NAME: Bakura
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, oceans, forests, plains, mountains, small seas, rivers, valleys
INTERESTING: on isolated edge of Outer Rim; formally part of Wild Space; one of the largest commercial hubs in Wild Space region; site of historic truce between Empire and Alliance after Endor; Ssi-Ruuk (who called planet Xwhee) invaded shortly afer truce; exported repulsorlift coils, namana-based products; imported medicine, technology

NAME: Bakura Imperial Prison
INTERESTING: had two large solar sails, heavily armed with numerous turbolasers and seemingly endless complement of TIEs; rotated fairly quickly; Rebels raided in 3 ABY to rescue prisoners

NAME: Arden
INTERESTING: population: 10 M; named after Deredith Arden (founder of Bakura)

NAME: Bakura-6
INTERESTING: site of small Bakuran colony destroyed by Ssi-ruuk during battle of Bakura (apparently not rebuilt afterwards)

NAME: Kammia
INTERESTING: Human agriworld colony of the Empire; notable for rich soil; colonists grew Chandrilan grain; after Yavin, Palpatine ceded a number of colony worlds to the Ssi-ruuvi Imperium, allowing the Ssi-ruuk to capture and entech the colonists; the Empire released a news report claiming a mysterious virus had wiped out the colony to hide the truth

NAME: Cattamascar
INTERESTING: originally controlled by Empire, conquered by Ssi-ruuk in 4 ABY, shortly before invasion of Bakura; Ssi-ruuk won by narrow margin

NAME: Gymelo
INTERESTING: Bix Arden-Govia (human) left behind pampered life on Bakura, signed up as ship's boy aboard a freighter out of Gymelo but returned home by 4 ABY after learning much about the worlds of the Shiritoku Spur

NAME: Timora
INTERESTING: closest planet in the empire "proper" to Bakura; exported sunpetals (flowers suitable as gifts); served as shipping point for repulsorlift products from Bakura; major city: Tadarc

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

INTERESTING: during GCW, panathan flower (considered exinct for centuries) began to bloom again here; Epicanthix: mostly human in appearance with somewhat longer than usual faces, narrow eyes, natural unconscious resistance to Force mind tricks, influence, mind reading, or domination, making them in demand as spies during time of Sith Empire

NAME: Shalm
INTERESTING: Mount Ganton (highest peak in its range) was located here, and an Imperial garrison on its western face was abandoned after Endor, but became base of the Pendarran's Revenge (armed anti-Imperial insurgent group); capital: Hondan (located in valley with view of Mount Ganton)

NAME: Rodis
INTERESTING: Rodisars: crocodylomorphs; primitive planet, once site of Winter Wars (conflict) involving Rodis (Rodisar general who eneded up in slave arenas of Rattatak in 22 BBY)

NAME: Firrerre
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Fusai
INTERESTING: location of a branch of the Obroa-skai library; around 200 BBY, BRT supercomputer called Mistress Mnemos installed; Obroa-skai closed branch, but it was maintained locally; Fusai became Rebel safeworld; C-3PO reported Luke and Leia's adventures events on Vorzyd V to Mistress Mnemos, who helped the Alliance with tactics and long-term planning

NAME: Nibiru
INTERESTING: Leia was traveling on a transport that was shot down over Nibiru and crashed in a lake; there was a colony of tree-welling Ewoks here

NAME: Xal 3
INTERESTING: served as base of Armorers' Confederacy

NAME: Monsua N.
INTERESTING: unidentified planet in Nebula?

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

INTERESTING: acted almost like a third sun to its moons, reflecting light from its hydrogen clouds; orbited by 9 major moons and 48 "sub-lunar" objects; Galactic Senate attempted to rename the planet Tana (after the Ewoks' name for it) before the Hosnian Prime tragedy; diameter: 148,000 km

HUMAN_READABLE_NAME: 1. Endor (IX3244-A, Forest Moon of Endor, Sanctuary Moon)

NAME: Korkar (IX3244-B)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Hual Maka (IX3244-D)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: irregularly shaped; may once have been a comet captured by Endor's gravity

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Alprezar (IX3244-H)

NAME: Gouuls (IX3244-I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Empire established a mining colony here; after Endor, NR allowed a number of Sullustans to take over operations

NAME: Megiddo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: crust was incredibly rich in pure metals, alloys and crystals, including phobium, doonium, zersium, neutronium, iron, gold, and crystallized lommite; astrophysicists argued about how it got its riches; independent prospectors found its crust difficult to penetrate; the Empire used a massive concentration of firepower to crack open the crust, reducing it to a ragged, unstable world

NAME: Endor Gate
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: at some point during GCW, the University of Bar'leth chartered a scientific expedition to study the black hole, but were attacked by Imperial Navy , hinting that the Empire was hiding something in the system; well-scouted and not especially large; occasionally ships were found drifting here whose crew swore they were across the galaxy before their ship went dead

NAME: Qina
INTERESTING: periwinkle-colored moon; wild and beautiful; very short nights and constant green glow from Hanchin; periodically, Hanchin-set occurred when the gas giant set below the horizon, creating a much darker night; site of Inicus Mont (Vashan religious retreat; each year around mid-winter, millions of Vashan pilgrims made their way here to repent; ceremony was led by priests known as bohdis

NAME: Sanyassa IV
NOTES: Shares name with Abbaji Minor in Kalee system

NAME: Thonner
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, shallow salty seas, sandy islands

NAME: The Mote
INTERESTING: Shadowport

NAME: Aurimaus
INTERESTING: at some point during GCW, Empire's Tempest Force saw action at Aurimaus

NAME: Barabesh system
INTERESTING: the space station Colossus hid from the First Order here but was discovered when Jarek Yeager and Kazuda Xiodo attempted to rescue Tam Ryvora from the First Order, who sent the Star Destroyer Thunderer to attack the station; the Thunderer was destroyed and the Colossus was saved

NAME: Mhatma 5 system
INTERESTING: situated on galactic frontier during Galactic Civil War; popular holovid celebrity Shantee Ren launched a campaign to have stohls (elusive, furred serpent-like predators native to Ichtor 8) declared endangered, transplanted to Mhatma 5; Ren took up permanent residence here as well

NAME: Qaras
INTERESTING: in 44 ABY, Jessar revolted against Minyavish, who had formerly enslaved Jessar; Minyavish were forced to leave, then Qaras accepted into Galactic Alliance, with Rokari Kem as Senator

NAME: Xoemefel
INTERESTING: site of Ops Post (NR Scout Service base)

NAME: Castilon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: over the millenia a number of battles were fought here, leaving the seafloor scattered with wreckage; the Colossus (racer destination and refueling station platform) located here until it was forced to flee First Order

NAME: Chalcedon
INTERESTING: colony of boneless beings with crystalline eyes

NAME: Hyborea
INTERESTING: presumably orbited by the Hyborean Moon

NAME: Hyborean Moon
INTERESTING: served as an Imperial black-site prison during the Galactic Civil War; also contained housing for Imperial employees; hot spring lakes were a favorite recreational site; after the Battle of Endor, a New Republic fleet attacked the facilities here and liberated the prison, forcing Romwell Krass Junior to flee offworld into hiding

NAME: Manakron system
INTERESTING: by 32 BBY, C-3PO had served as protocol droid/ emissary for chief negotiator of Manakron system

NAME: Dlor 3
INTERESTING: about 2 ABY, Secure Passage seminar scheduled to take place on Dlor 3

NAME: Dononter Minor
INTERESTING: homeworld of widowmaker (plant useable as a weapon)

NAME: Semag system
INTERESTING: Thrawn continued his campaign to destroy traitorous Grand Admiral Zaarin here

NAME: Duron
INTERESTING: Obo Rin first learned of Charon species here

NAME: Dohnia
INTERESTING: Dohnia free colony (first colony) established here before end of CW; Cerean Ruf-Asti-Viarffli was President

NAME: Cheelit
INTERESTING: Hex thought J'feh were related to Pomojema

NAME: Dolva Prime
INTERESTING: at least 3 moons; Boba Fett ambushed Edo and Rolu Strom in the Old Hallet prairie in 2 ABY to recover a fake Arachedron sculpture

NAME: Ghothia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Ghothian slime pools

NAME: Stensen's Colony
INTERESTING: GHothian Slime existed here

NAME: Kartoosh

NAME: Meruud
INTERESTING: location of Meruud Memorial Spaceport

NAME: Teledian
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
NOTES: No entry yet

NAME: Jidlor system
INTERESTING: Swaze: technologically advanced, but revered wisdom of comparatively primitive Rellarin people of Rellnas Minor and each year, sent their rulers to consult un'Yala (Rellarin tribal leaders and sages)

NAME: Serenity
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Serenity (battle during Zaarin insurrection) in 4 ABY

NAME: Takodana
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Eeyyon
INTERESTING: saved by Jedi prior to CW; inhabited by species of tall, pale-skinned humanoids

NAME: Unidentified moon system
INTERESTING: populated; shortly after Rebels established large base here, Empire carefully planned an assault, using Interdictor Cruiser to prevent escape and take Rebel prisoners

NAME: Polomie
INTERESTING: by 1 BBY, Rebel stronghold here attacked by Imperial Nemesis-class gunship in first field test

NAME: The Black Delve
INTERESTING: Battles of the Black Delve in 690s BBY presumably took place here

NAME: Rellnas Minor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: varied; islands, archipelagoes, peninsulas, oceans, polar ice caps
INTERESTING: Rellarin were tall, imposing, with thick brown shell plates, feeding spikes on faces; were humble, wise & ethical; mostly lived in frigid polar regions

NAME: Nilgaria system
INTERESTING: home of Nilgarian worms

NAME: Hendrix
INTERESTING: prior to Hoth, Han Solo planned to run weapons from Minoth to Hendrix for Rebel Alliance

NAME: Threfal
INTERESTING: homeworld of meatvine (edible plant)

NAME: Stennaros
INTERESTING: Stennes Shifters almost wiped out by Jedi 5000 BBY

NAME: Ohratuu
INTERESTING: Rebel base here; deripors (docile herd animals) modified with toxins by Rebel Alliance general and used them in hit-and-run attacks

NAME: Vulpinus Nebula
NOTES: why not placed closer to the UR?
INTERESTING: nebula on the edge of the galaxy; shortly before the Battle of Endor, Gallius Rax was sent here aboard the Super Star Destroyer Ravager by Palpatine; by 5 ABY it was home to a large Imperial fleet led by Grand Admiral Rae Sloane; Rax and Sloane convened the first Shadow Council meeting there before sending the fleet to Jakku; Imperial survivors used this Nebula as a refuge for decades after the Empire's fall

NAME: Jardeen IV
INTERESTING: site of Imperial Army training center, training walker tactics; shortly after Endor, Imperials fled before arrival of NR

NAME: Edatha
INTERESTING: represented in NR by Krall Praget

NAME: Sarrish
NOTES: On Corellian Trade Spine?

NAME: Blutopia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Goratak
INTERESTING: site of messy Rebel/Imperial conflict

NAME: Etorasp
INTERESTING: Imperial prison here

NAME: Hakartha Space Station
INTERESTING: Imperial-controlled at height of Galactic Civil War

NAME: Mutanda
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, jungles, rolling hills, temperate & arid plains, grasslands, rainforests, rare rivers, streams, and watering holes, oceans
INTERESTING: many big game animals, resulting in booming legalized safari trade; easily accessible due to spaceport on moon of Justa; poachers drove many species to extinction; water precious here

NAME: Justa
INTERESTING: site of only spaceport in system: vast subterranean complex with surface-level docking for up to 50 light transports and orbit assignments for bulk transports; garrisoned by Empire, supposedly to protect interests of BlasTech, Blethern Gas Industries, and Czerka

NAME: Bomis Koori
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kriselist
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ternin system
INTERESTING: origin point of Ternin tree slings (low-technology sling weapon)

NAME: Ganoidia system
INTERESTING: shared name with Ganoidian tri-deck cruiser, a type of sparely designed yacht

NAME: Vulcusion system
INTERESTING: shared name with Battle of Vulcusion

NAME: Urajab
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Alchenaut
INTERESTING: native creatures, o'cerrys, were palm-sized furballs that acted as a predator warning system for other herbivores. Visited by Jedi biologist Bowspritz in 990 BBY

NAME: Qat Chrystac
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: radioactive lava seas, volcanic glass Plateaus

NAME: Haurgab
INTERESTING: allied with Seperatists; Republic's Omega Squad battled local forces in Battle of Haurgab; local Mauja clan members (humans) called Maujasi

NAME: Krykas
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mud, craters, briers, thorny plants, fog
INTERESTING: planet located in asteroid field; blanketed in thick tan fog with elecromagnetic charges strong enough to knock out most ship sensors; covered in mud, briers, thorns

NAME: Amorphiia
INTERESTING: discovered ~3000 BBY; Amorphiians: sentient humanoid android species with motor control problems; changed hands from Empire to NR, avoided Yuuzhan Vong war; later part of Krayt's Empire

NAME: Wen'he'dinae
INTERESTING: Cha'wen'he: bird-like herbivores who evolved to be nervous, excitable and prone to sudden, quick motions due to evolving alongside many predators, and roamed planet according to seasons

NAME: Oolidi
INTERESTING: Oolids round-bodied; represented in NR by Tolik Yar

NAME: Asturias
INTERESTING: factory moon abandoned before Clone Wars when star turned red giant, and radiation rose to levels too dangerous for prolonged exposure

NAME: Woostri
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Hewl
INTERESTING: Karap Valley's fog banks were infamous; Rebel Colonel Yerac was tracking an independent bounty hunter group here

NAME: Mesula Remnants Belt
INTERESTING: many eons before 10 BBY, Mesula underwent a cataclysmic rupture, causing it to shatter, resulting in the Mesula Remnants Belt, a field of ice asteroids that the Pau'an gangster Fyzen Gor later used to hide the Phylanx Redux Transmitter, which Gor hoped to use to initiate a droid revolution across the galaxy

NAME: Naator
vague/in Mid Rim near Rimma Trade Route
INTERESTING: contributed to the Empire's war effort; Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry fought on Naator as part of its Operation: Ringbreaker campaign to prepare for a Kuat assault by attacking targets surrounding the Rimma Trade Route; at another point, a rebel strike team spotted a crashed GX1 Short Hauler in mountains, with records suggesting it could have been a starship called the Intrepid Heart

NAME: Eidoloni system
INTERESTING: Xizor Transport Systems transported wide range of heavy DSII construction materials here

NAME: Outpost DX-11a
INTERESTING: XQ6 Platform used by Empire; carried 2 TIE/ln squadrons; destroyed after Rebel X-wings sent by the LIberty liberated fleeing Imperial defector Commander Zaletta

NAME: Ventran system
INTERESTING: system loyal to Republic; Republic medium cruiser Halleck stationed here until summoned to Haruun Kal to extract Depa Billaba

NAME: Bamayar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Rogue One Novelization, Battlefront: Twilight Company/
INTERESTING: Imperial cargo pilot Bodhi Rook met and fell in love with a woman on Bamayar, who rejected him between 3 BBY and 0 BBY. The Ducal Palace and Port of Chenodra were captured by the Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry during the Rebel Alliance's Mid Rim offensive.

NAME: Bamayar IX
INTERESTING: Between 7 and 5 BBY, Bodhi Rook, a pilot-in-training at the Galactic Empire's Terrabe Sector Service Academy, flew an old Nu-class transport, which was in a poor state for flight, through the clouds of Bamayar IX with a number of his classmates as passengers.

NAME: Adner
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: towns, farms, compounds, pleasure resorts, casinos, theme parks
NOTES: Binary star system; hot days, cold, arid nights

NAME: Nigel III
INTERESTING: Imperial base here

NAME: Nigel IV
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: glaciers, plains, large polar ice caps
INTERESTING: population 3.2m; governed by local Republic that mainly focused on combating crime; no trade connections with rest of galaxy until time of NR

NAME: Pormthulis system
INTERESTING: the disabled ISD-II Edict was under guard by NR forces here; around 5 ABY, the Imperial 204th Fighter Wing defeated the NR escorts and captured the destroyer, cannibalizing their Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier Allegiance for parts to make the Edict hyperspace-capable again

NAME: Pax
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Plagen
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: "anouther route connected it to Vondarc..." (That's Enarc Run)

NAME: Suria
INTERESTING: origin point of Surian tea (beverage)

NAME: Zelos II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, forests, hills, valleys, mountains, islands, seas
INTERESTING: population 10M; Zelosians: human-appearing sentient plants; Imperial-aligned; important source of ore; Kryndyn (capital city) held most of population, connected via road and rail to 5 smaller cities near mines (Lyn, Lyrd, Drev, Tolk, Nul); ore transported to Kryndyn, then shipped offworld on ore freighters

NAME: Yeshocq
INTERESTING: colonized temperate planet with local year lasting 13 standard months; local year divided into 455 local days; homeworld of qormots (omnivorous stocky quadrupeds with single eye and quills sticking out of flanks and spine

NAME: Tyus Cluster
INTERESTING: cluster of black holes, an obstacle Freia Kallea encountered when charting Hydian Way; many ships lost there, famously the Ashanda Ray, in which Kinnin Vo-Shay disappeared and reappeared 50 years later without having aged

NAME: ZeHeth
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Gammalin
INTERESTING: populace wiped out by Emperor's Plague; capital: Gammalin Colony

NAME: Conjenus system
INTERESTING: Conjeni resembled red-furred starfish

NAME: Dustig system
INTERESTING: namesake of Dustig Trace (hyperroute)

NAME: Opari
INTERESTING: provided Balawai gov't on Haruun Kal with gunships

NAME: Sayblohn
INTERESTING: Imperial-occupied by time of Galactic Civil War; Rebel Alliance tasked a special ops team with retrieving a stolen art object of religious significance to Okfili species here, but they were ambushed by local pirates from a hidden base in the badlands

NAME: Krnay
INTERESTING: homeworld of Rith Murisson

NAME: Prine
grid square/sector/on the way between Telerath & Vondarc
INTERESTING: possessed grasslands where agriculture was possible; Dass Jennir and Ember Chankeli crash-landed here aboard Dezono Qua's starship after being attacked by two V-wings

NAME: Prima
INTERESTING: uninhabitable

NAME: Rhiannon
INTERESTING: uninhabitable

NAME: Kirima
