INTERESTING: population 900M; many natural resources; capital: Verena City; headquarters of Vespula Manufacturing & Exports (destroyed by bounty hunteres hired by Commerce Guild); local monarchy dwelt in Shamd City; after Endor, Imperial Intelligence Lieutenant Cor Mynus assigned here

NAME: Liyha
INTERESTING: orbited within Kalinda Asteroid Belt

NAME: Kalinda Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: icy planet Liyha orbited within belt

NAME: Bretie Facility
INTERESTING: Bretie Facility (VenteX Construction Yards Cargo Facility 1 involved as production center in Imperial TIE Experimental Project) raided & destroyed by Alliance pilots

NAME: Oshira
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Nerrif
NOTES: Add Enarc Run

NAME: Belat system
INTERESTING: notable only as hyperspace transit point

NAME: Bromlarch
INTERESTING: prior to 20 BBY, Amidala and Rush Clovis prepared a Galactic Senate hearing to save Bromlarch's population from drought and famine when its planetary aqueduct system was damaged

NAME: Ansarra
INTERESTING: bounty hunter Devon Fuller made supply runs to rebel base here; discovered by Empire; ISD attacked base & Fuller's ship destroyed, though he survived

NAME: Deersheba
INTERESTING: large part of population wiped out by an epidemic spread by Neimoidians

NAME: Remmon Nebula
INTERESTING: red and orange nebula; in 5000 BBY Jedi Master Relin Druur and Padawan Drev Hassin passed through nebula in their Infiltrator starfighter while hunting Sith Lord Saes Rrogon

NAME: Nelvana Gas Cluster
INTERESTING: group of Rebel agents claimed to be survey crew heading to the Nelvana Gas CLuster when they were challenged by Bannistar Station officials

NAME: Kishpaugh
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban skyscrapers, landing pads, arched walkway bridges between buildings
INTERESTING: deep inside Nelvana Gas Cluster; smuggling hub, attracting all types of criminals; Han Solo visited in 2 ABY to deliver a shipment of parts to Tookra

NAME: Iskin system
INTERESTING: shared name with freighter Star of Iskin

NAME: Kreeling
INTERESTING: mining world hosting many refineries, and person in charge of refineries considered to be more or less in charge of planet; atmosphere breathable but had permanent effect on eyesight of human population; Moranda Savich evaded capture by Hal Horn here

NAME: Necr'ygor system
INTERESTING: origin point of Necr'ygor Omic wine

NAME: Jafan
INTERESTING: Jafani arrived as colonists ~300 years before Battle of Naboo from somewhere outside Chommell sector, ruled by Jafan family; opened themselves to trade and interaction shortly before Battle of Naboo; by 32 BBY, about 3000 Jafani citizens lived on Naboo, some of whom came to raise their profile as artists

NAME: Phorsa Gedd
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Battlefront: Twilight Company, Alphabet Squadron/Alphabet Squadron p. 205 (Vryant served 2 years in Imperial Army here in trenches) p. 318 (either Wyl Lark or Nath Tensent spent nights in the wilderness / factory-deserts of Phorsa Gedd, desc)
INTERESTING: sunset saw venting of heat until sunrise next day; Vryant (Imperial deserter) served in trenches here for 2 years; 61st Mobile Infantry fought on Phorsa Gedd as a part of Alliance's Mid Rim campaign c. 1 ABY and they remembered the battle later, in 3 ABY; in 4 ABY, Obi-Wan's Force ghost told Luke that the fate of Phorsa and many other planets depended on his final confrontation with Vader

NAME: Desstious
INTERESTING: homeworld of Moff Par Lankin

NAME: Xandil VII
INTERESTING: shared name with Far Xandil sector; Par Lankin (secretive Imperial Moff of Lambda sector) rumored to only leave palace for occasional hunting forays to Equatorial Reserves

NAME: Ro-Loo Triangle
INTERESTING: portions of the Imperial fleet hid here after Endor, though not as large a group as the one that hid in the Vulpinus Nebula; despite this there were still hundreds of Star Destroyers and thousands of smaller craft

NAME: Rintonne
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Mordis VI
INTERESTING: corrosive acid storms happened here

NAME: Rethel Point system
NOTES: not listed on WP; original source unknown - Razor's Edge?

NAME: Demnadi
INTERESTING: during Galactic Civil War, a planet-wide riot erupted, which local Imperial governor believed was instagated by a local Rebel cell; Empire dispatched one man to pacify planet, having heard there was only "one planetary riot"

NAME: Haluria system
INTERESTING: home to Halurian ice-boars

NAME: Vendusii system
INTERESTING: origin point of Vendusii Crystal (mineral)

NAME: Mon Gazza
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/Alphabet Squadron p. 381 (Kreize was caught up in a war between rival spice traders here after Mrinzebon)

NAME: Moravia system
INTERESTING: origin point of the Moravian maneuver (combat maneuver)

NAME: Herdessa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas/Alphabet Squadron p. 205 (Vryant served 6 years in Imperial Army here)
INTERESTING: part of Exar Kun's Sith Empire during Great Sith War; First Battle of Herdessa occurred 6 days after Geonosis; peaceful world; many diplomats and others of affluence could remain neutral in debates; represented in the Galactic Senate by Shea Sadashassa; Leia first encountered Lumiya during a diplomatic mission to Herdessa with Mon Mothma to overthrow the Herdessan Guild

NAME: Cificap VII
INTERESTING: after Yavin, Rebel Alliance freed Habassa slaves near here before they could be loaded onto an Imperial frigate

NAME: U-Tendik
INTERESTING: used as refuge by Rodian Tetsu clan; Nok and Teeku (Rodians) herded Tree-Botts (arboreal creatures) here for milk, meat; bo-toads and manka cats also native here

NAME: Ghishi
INTERESTING: Ghishi: warrior-mantids, thin and lanky, with long insectile limbs and orange eyes

NAME: Daimar
INTERESTING: located at center of a trade route through Mid Rim, in sector of space settled largely by Rodians (Rodian neighbors disliked Daimar for becoming too prominent/wealthy); cities built using a mix of ancient design & modern techniques; monarchy liked by population (King appointed planet's senator); Daimar resisted Empire & was blockaded/bombarded

NAME: Ooo-sek
INTERESTING: one of the first Rodian colony worlds; swamps were home to carnivorous yo'uqiol ("Hand of Death") plants; ideal hunting grounds for training Rodian bounty hunters

NAME: Radnor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, urban, plains, underground canyons, seas

NAME: Fordon system
INTERESTING: Jerresk (Quarren pirate) was last sighted here after carrying out a raid on a NR supply ship traveling to the Musson system

NAME: Hetzal C *
INTERESTING: largest of 3 stars of Hetzal system; a large tank of supercooled liquid tibanna was hurled into the system towards this star during the Great Hyperspace Disaster; because the star was R-class, a collision would have set off a chain reaction that would have caused the star to surge and flare to nearly double its size as well as frying the system with deadly radiation

NAME: Solar Array 22-X
INTERESTING: situated equidistant from each of system's three suns; staffed by a crew of 8; during Great Hyperspace Disaster, it was destroyed despite the efforts of the Republic Longbeam Aurora IX; the ship's crew tried to rescue survivors from the wreckage

NAME: Hetzal Prime
INTERESTING: the moon's primary landmass but held back from destroying it when they sensed survivors aboard

NAME: Fruited moon
INTERESTING: population: 4 B; agriworld renowned for its bounty; a group of Jedi pilots gathered to destroy a fragment of the freighter Legacy Run on a collision course with

NAME: Rooted moon
INTERESTING: agriworld with a spaceport where Sella (Twi'lek bartender) worked

NAME: Hetzal system monitoring station
INTERESTING: logges starship traffic in and out of star system; sent out a system-wide alert in 232 BBY when several hyperspace anomalies entered the system (fragments of the freighter Legacy Run, destroyed in hyperspace); destroyed when another exiting anomaly atomized the station and its crew

NAME: Christophsis
INTERESTING: covered in forests of turquoise crystal spires; invaded by CIS but repelled by Jedi, Clones; during GCW, Spectres (Rebel cell) raided Imperial convoy bound for the planet; Rebellious elements found responsible for theft of Imperial medical frigate; prime minister executed for treason; around time of Battle of Jakku, Church of the Force members traveled here to return stolen Kyber crystals

NAME: Leesis
INTERESTING: light-colored surface with large, lengthy fissures; at Battle of Christophsis, Anakin hid a Republic fleet behind the moon after first attempt to breach the CIS blockade

NAME: Gellefon
INTERESTING: cool climate; inhabited by Humans and other sapients as well as semi-sentient indigenous gellbeasts known as wardogs; ruled by Schennt (Imperial Governor) from his domicile in the center of Kig Dannen spaceport; Pinnacle Keep (Imperial detention center) also located here

NAME: Savareen
INTERESTING: known for Savareen brandy; when the natives tried to rise up against Crimson Dawn, the syndicate had all of their tongues cut out; after Han's Kessel run, he and Beckett's gang went to Savareen to refine the coaxium; shared its name with luxury liner Savareen Dancer and Savareen whist (card game)

NAME: Apatros
INTERESTING: moon-sized; orbited dim orange star; as of 1003 BBY, fell under control of Outer Rim Oreworks Company (maintained a cortosis mine here); homeworld of Darth Bane; had a thin atmopshere and some indigenous plant life

NAME: Tythe
INTERESTING: once as lush as Naboo until it became HQ of LiMerge Power, which stripped it of its resources to exploit its natural plasma reserves; later abandoned leaving only a desert wasteland; vegetation then found only in its red-water lakes; only tactical value was as a hyperspace jump point; garrisoned by Republic, then taken by CIS in 19 BBY

NAME: Nelvaan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mesas, mountains, rivers, forests, glaciers, oceans
INTERESTING: 85% gravity, allowing for odd landscapes that would have toppled under 1 G; during CW, explitation rights were ceded to CIS by Onaconda Farr (Rodia's senator); CIS-aligned Techno Union turned natives into cyborg monsters; Nelvaanians regarded planet itself as the Great Mother (a religious figure); Techno Union siphoned geothermal energy here, plunging planet into an ice age (stopped by Anakin)

NAME: Hismaul system
INTERESTING: home to Hismauli hawk-snake

NAME: Llanic
INTERESTING: widely considered a shadowport due to high volume of spice and other illicit cargo passing through system; novice smugglers often got their start by picking up short hauls at some of Llanic's infamous cantinas; battle occurred in orbit during Cold War; Sith developed Ziroxin-12 (bioweapon) at a station in orbit; during GCW, Imperial Navy known to patrol here and launch raids

NAME: Musson system
INTERESTING: Jerresk (pirate) once ambushed a Republic convoy bringing supplies here; system aligned itself with NR following Endor

NAME: Ord Celbus
INTERESTING: colonized by Republic sometime before Pius Dea Era

NAME: Ord Pardron
INTERESTING: small planetoid or large asteroid; thin atmo

NAME: Vestor Nebula
INTERESTING: location of Vestor Pulsar

NAME: Vestor Pulsar
INTERESTING: relatively stable pulsar; served as navigation beacon

NAME: Hikil
INTERESTING: lulari trees were exported from here

NAME: Koiogra
INTERESTING: world visited by Chass na Chadic (NR pilot), who found a recording of Jyn Erso's pre-Scarif speech while here and realized she had met Erso on Uchinao a year before; Kendra Novar (pilot during Old Republic era) was native here and developed the Koiogran turn, naming it after her home system

NAME: Korseg IV
INTERESTING: remote, mountainous world; site of Alliance's Flare Base; Empire assaulted the base in Battle of Korseg IV

NAME: Calast
INTERESTING: civilian Golan Space Colony 2 space station orbiting a water-rich world; Rebel forces attacked the Imperial Dreadnaught cruiser VTR-LTX while it was refueling here, on its way to deliver Rebel prisoners captured at Echo Base during Battle of Hoth to the Bundi II prison station

NAME: Pii II
INTERESTING: above the world, Habassan freighter Jess was assaulted by Imperial ships, but Rebels moved in to help their new allies

NAME: Pii III
INTERESTING: famed for native luxury greel wood; was one of "Teeda's Eyes"; averaged 105 cm precipitation annually; site of a Duros colony, later abdandoned; Rebel cell here before 2 ABY; Greel Wood Logging Corporation had significant presence here

NAME: Pii IV
INTERESTING: logging world; one of "Teeda's Eyes"

NAME: Pii
INTERESTING: source of greel-wood

NAME: D'Anjon N.
INTERESTING: expansive nebula in northernmost Arkanis sector, just north of the Gulf of Tatooine (starless void); formed as result of an ancient supernova; posed a navigational hazard; young stars inside nebula were unexplored and barely surveyed

NAME: Rodia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban domes, jungles, swamps, oceans, urban, rainforests, islands
INTERESTING: around 15,000 BBY Rodia joined Republic; with permission of Grand Protector (rodian ruler), Rodians were allowed to leave the planet to work offworld; Rodians built their cities on waterways, protecting them with environmental shields, bubble domes which protected against extreme temperatures; Rodia later occupied by Empire; after Yavin Luke tried to recruit Chekkoo clan to Alliance

NAME: Yasooska
INTERESTING: "true" moon (not captured asteroid)

NAME: Enak
INTERESTING: "true" moon (not captured asteroid)

NAME: Eiska
INTERESTING: captured asteroid

NAME: Soomana
INTERESTING: captured asteroid

NAME: Pirdia
INTERESTING: in 3638 BBY, gas miners here stumbled upon a long-abandoned fortress in the gas giant's atmosphere

NAME: Austan Asteroid Cluster
INTERESTING: site of mining operations and resorts; site of skirmish between Republic and CIS during CW

NAME: Gulf of Tatooine
INTERESTING: near-starless void located within Arkanis sector in the Outer Rim Territories, north of Tatooine and south of the D'Anjon Nebula; in 14 BBY an Imperial convoy was attacked near this region by Berch Teller's rebel cell

NAME: Vuzsa
INTERESTING: used as refueling point for ships crossing the Arkanis sector; site of Alliance safehouse during GCW

NAME: Piroket
INTERESTING: some residents and transients of Mos Eisley spaceport had travelled to Tatooine from here; trading planet, controlled by a BOthan shipping company; had large population of Hutts, Bothans; Riij Winward (Rebel) desposited a stolen droid here which contained technical readouts of the Hammertong

NAME: A-Foroon
INTERESTING: homeworld of Arok the Hutt; windy world located in the Spice Triangle; remade into the throne world of the Jahibakti Hutts in last century of Republic; run by gangs of Yahk-Tosh in the name of the Jahibakti kajidic

NAME: B-Foroon
INTERESTING: remade into the throneworld of the Faljozic Hutt clan and their Toydarian retainers during last century of the Republic; area annexed by the Empire between 19 and 17 BBY; located in Spice Triangle

NAME: C-Foroon
INTERESTING: remade into the throneworld of the Besadii Hutt kajidic during last century of the Republic; center of a thriving spice smuggling business in years surrounding Invasion of Naboo; owned by Gardulla the Hutt at one point (and harbored her daughter Decca's HQ), but eventually taken by Jabba during Imperial period, ruining Besadii fortunes in the sector

NAME: Utaruun
INTERESTING: abandoned when Corellian Run's path shifted; later on Rodian colonists began to move here

NAME: Ooo-temiuk
INTERESTING: colonized c. 75 BBY by Rodian migrants fleeing their troubled homeworld; Greel Wood Logging Corporation later established a harvesting facility here

NAME: Dermos
NOTES: Closest planets to "Raydonia" listed as: Akiva, Tatooine, Geonosis, Mustafar (?) and Dermos

NAME: Zaadja
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: snowy plains surrounded by impervious icy mountains, caves
INTERESTING: Onaconda Farr (Rodia's Senator) bartered exploitation rights to Zaadja to Trade Federation in exchange for food during a famine; Geonosians established a hive factory-fortress here during CW; at some point, factory was littered with Mandalorian corpses; Obi-Wan, Anakin and Tohno were sent to destroy the factory; Jodo Kast salvaged Mandalorian armor here to impersonate Boba Fett

NAME: Tatoo I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: G1-type main sequence binary star; twin suns known as "Gi Dopa Gasha" in Huttese; formed when a hydrogen molecular cloud collapsed; children on Tatooine told stories of powerful dragons that lived inside the suns

NAME: Tatoo II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: G2-type main sequence binary star; twin suns known as "Gi Dopa Gasha" in Huttese; formed when a hydrogen molecular cloud collapsed; children on Tatooine told stories of powerful dragons that lived inside the suns

NAME: Tatooine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, rainforests (distant past) canyons, deserts, mountains, rocky bluffs (current)

NAME: Ghomrassen
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: primary moon of Tatooine

NAME: Guermessa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: secondary moon of Tatooine, with an angular diameter of 26 arcminutes from Tatooine's surface

NAME: Chenini
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: tertiary moon of Tatooine, with a large, elliptical orbit, taking it as far as 4 M miles from the planet at its apogee; overlooked on many planetary surveys; erratic appearance and disappearance led to many Tatooine superstitions; Tusken Raiders planned rituals around the moon's cycle; Jawas used moons just before storm season to time their annual swap meets

NAME: Station-Star 1
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: original landing station for Tatooine; both Hutts and Valarians believed control of the station would grant control over all Tatooine; constantly targeted by multiple factions and destroyed by 1 ABY; after its destruction, Tatooine Space Station became primary space station in system

NAME: Tatooine Space Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: not the friendliest station, but could be persuaded to perform repairs for the right price; notorious for clearing anyone to land at any of Tatooine's starports without even the most basic security protocols; station manager gave missions to Smugglers' Alliance pilots, privateers, smugglers and bounty hunters so they could earn landing access to Jabba's Palace

NAME: Rebel Space Station (Rebel Ruins)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: once-prominent station was the base of operations for most Alliance activity in Tatoo system; Empire wrecked it at height of GCW; afterward known as Rebel Ruins

NAME: Tatooine Star Fortress
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of dozens if not hundreds of Star Fortresses deployed by Emperor Arcann of the Eternal Empire to watch for possible uprising son subjugated worlds; it interfered in the gang wars on the surface, causing the locals to feel an extra layer of repression

NAME: Dragon's Spine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: used as navigation point by local explorers; hosted a conflict between Lady Valarian and Jabba during GCW; occasionally ships traveling to or from Tatooine collided wih asteroids here

NAME: Ohann
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Adriana
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: most important source of water for Tatooine (orbited by several ice rings, often mined and brought to Tatooine); shortly before Yavin, Garouf Lafoe (Human) used this as his business plan; orbited by 4 lifeless moons

NAME: Jabba's Star
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: naval base owned by Jabba; served as a shining example of Jabba's cunning and manipulation skills; provided a point of origin for Jabba's illegal operations; Jabba's thugs drove off anyone who didn't have business here

NAME: Iron Planet
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: "quelch"?
INTERESTING: material was substantially different than other asteroids near the Trader's Grotto; mined during the GCW in the hopes it would help ease resource demands on Tatooine

NAME: Ghost Tide Nebula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: took up nearly a whole quadrant of the Tatooine system; although a handful of trade routes passed nearby, travelers were warned to stay away, as the thick nebula completely blocked sensors, rendering navicomputers useless, providing cover pirates hoping to ambush unsuspecting freighters

NAME: Sentinel Moon
PARENT: Outer Rim/The Slice, Spice Triangle//Arkanis/Sentinel Base
INTERESTING: location of Sentinel Base, one of several prefabricated Sentinel bases designed to be deployed via a Victory-Class Star Destroyer to protect construction of the Death Star; originally a cramped garrison base, it grew to become a large complex of interconnected domes and hangars, as well as an adjacent landing field and deflector shield generator; failed attack by Rebels in 14 BBY

NAME: Bahryn
INTERESTING: frigid moon of Geonosis; Garazeb Orrelios (Rebel Spectres) and Alexsandr Kallus of the Empire crashed here and were trapped but were eventually rescued

NAME: Orbital Foundry 7
INTERESTING: assisted in construction of Death Star; second largest pstructure then viewable from command habit; 10,000s of Geonosian drones transferred here to oversee production;

NAME: Mabonte
NOTES: EA says 3 moons; Geonosis & OR Worlds says 2

NAME: Andooweel
INTERESTING: discovered during Great Manifest Period; impoverished world; small industrial and acrigultural districts were unsuccessful; mining operations never uncovered anything of value; some citizens were recruited into Imperial Army (some chose this over jail for petty theft or illegal speeder racing); c. 15 ABY, Cronal established himself as a warlord here, hoping to used advanced cybernetics to overthrow both the Imperial Remnant and NR and create an "Empire of art"

NAME: Kemal
INTERESTING: site for Tibanna gas mining

NAME: Kemal Station
NOTES: On Triellus?
INTERESTING: damp, foggy moon used as a trading post used by both smugglers and legitimate businesses

NAME: New Ator
INTERESTING: founded in 80 BBY by Atorese colonists

NAME: Obana Belt
INTERESTING: site of small amounts of mining and pirate activity

NAME: Gedi 4
INTERESTING: orbited a double star; 4th of 5 planets (all gas giants); its collection of moons rich in various minerals, originally mined by a front company owned by the Besadii Hutt kajidic; the Empire took over operations shortly after the rise of the New Order

NAME: Cranan 12
NOTES: "Behin the Scenes"
INTERESTING: controlled by the Mining Guild; identified as the system where Han fought off pirates who attacked Jabba's ship (in The Hutt Gambit, p100)

NAME: Melnea's World
INTERESTING: murky, swampy world with poor mines; settled by miners from Tatooine after local mining operations failed and the arrival of the Hutts; world transformed into a smugglers' hideout

NAME: Vactooine
INTERESTING: mining colony with dense jungles; during the Cold War, a scientist lost an incredibly valuable anode no bigger than a grain of sand somewhere in the desert; Sith invaded the colony but driven out by the natives in 2560 BBY; colony subsequently disappeared (some said destroyed by Sith); it was also said the colony was destroyed in 6 ABY (never confirmed); location of Battle of Vactooine

NAME: Moon of Vactooine
INTERESTING: the largest of Vactooine's moons

NAME: Tozeer
INTERESTING: desert world with Jawas and Tusken Raiders living here

NAME: Ferrelia system
INTERESTING: home of the Ferrelian ant

NAME: Rainbow Nebulae
INTERESTING: multicolored nebulae located "between Naboo and nowhere"

NAME: Stellan
INTERESTING: Stellan: isolationist, peaceful, relatively passive with white skin, large mouth with big square teeth and black, pupil-less eyes; due to the Stellan belief in the "Vain Goddess" who had provoked the galaxy to war, any children deemed mentally ill or too aggressive such as Jeigh Esse were labeled "ter-Stellan" and cast out into space; Esse was discovered by Rodians and became a bounty hunter

NAME: Trendivar
INTERESTING: skirmish between forces of the Vanderijar kajidic and the bounty hunters of Grim Destiny took place here

NAME: Porpor system
INTERESTING: Porporites: exterminated by Gank mercenaries in 4800 BBY

NAME: Kowak
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Drusil Bephorin (Givin) analyzed the system to be possible location of the Rebel fleet just after Yavin; home to monkey-lizards, ape-lizards, mole-fleas; University of Coruscant zoologists once visited to study monkey-lizards' sentience, but driven away by the mischevious creatures' cruel pranks; Zygerrian slave world under a colonial governorship; population 40-60K free, 200-400K slaves

NAME: Bundil
INTERESTING: population: less than 1 M; affiliated with the Empire; during GCW, several Imperial prison barges en route to the Bundil system were attacked by the Icarii-7

NAME: Bundil II
INTERESTING: Imperial XQ2 Platform; prison station; Dreadnaught VTR-LX was transporting Rebel prisoners from Echo Base when it was attacked at Calast but managed to escape to Bundil, where it was disabled by Rebel Y-wings; the station launched its TIEs, which were all destroyed; by the time the Nebulon-B frigate Archon arrived, the Rebel prisoners had been rescued and the VTR-LX destroyed by a bomb

NAME: Hypori
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Hypori
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: a battle took place in orbit here during the Galactic War; in 37 BBY Sidious commanded Maul to spend a month here with no food or water, concluding with a duel in which Maul lost but was given the title of Sith Lord; transformed into (CIS droid) factory world after Naboo; Grievous and CIS army defeated Republic here; at some point Tyber Zann and Zann Consortium took the world from Jabba

NAME: Naps Fral Cluster
grid square/sector/along hyperlanes that connected Ryloth to Nal Hutta
INTERESTING: located along hyperlanes that connected Ryloth to Nal Hutta; frequent site of ambushes masterminded by the Karazak Slavers Cooperative, who attacked ship sin search of Twi'lek women to enslave

NAME: Xorrn
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: factories, rocky deserts, small oceans, starship ruins
INTERESTING: young world with recently-cooled crust that provided access to mineral resources within the magma below (unstable tectonics prevented most mining operations from succeeding; Geonosians hid illegal battle droid factories here shortly before CW; during CW the factories were discovered by the Republic and bombarded; during GCW Empire attacked a clan of former CIS sympathizers from Gall

NAME: Ferra Sector Shipyard
INTERESTING: 800m-long repair slip concealed along the exposed underside of a derelict Acclamator assault ship orbiting Xorrn; though the name was grander than the facility, it kept the Empire looking for a larger shipyard; primary purpose was to repair ships unable to use Imperial ports; refitted ships for Hutts, Rebels, pirates; made judicious use of shipyard droids

NAME: Dagu
INTERESTING: Rybet colony liberated from CIS by Shaak Ti during CW in 22 BBY

NAME: Vlemoth Port
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: industrial urban, dense conifer forests, swamps, tundras, oceans, rivers, undersea volcanoes
INTERESTING: population 525 K (15% Humans, 13% Talz, 6% Muun, 66% other; all lived in Sanshur Flats (industrial city that sat close to a continent-dividing river) and Arumorut settlements (enclave of Mandalorian immigrants); 30m conifers grew in dense forests in northern foothills; Vlemoth Station was a towering orbiting Muun defense platform later grounded on the surface; owned by (Muun) Hill family

NAME: Wick 111
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
NOTES: Add Cranan - Excarga Hyperspace Route?
INTERESTING: Short Species w face tentacles

NAME: Venedlia system
INTERESTING: home to Venedlian sandmoles

NAME: Sevetta
NOTES: no mention of Polydroxols in article
INTERESTING: atmosphere toxic to Humans; Polydroxols: denantium-based shapeshifters resembling two hundred kg masses of liquid mercury and could mimic oher species' shapes and languages, but not skin texture; complex circulatory system passed electroglobins throughout bodies; could survive without ogygen; typically traveled in pairs; superficial wounds could heal instantaneously, but needed extended rest to replace electroglobins

NAME: Woldona system
INTERESTING: by time period between 0 and 3 ABY, GrimDeath I (converted Victory-Class Star Destroyer) was used by a gang of pirates to conduct a series of raids throughout the system

NAME: Herios IV
INTERESTING: jungle world; home to Imperial colony; at some point during GCW, a group of slavers brought Baraduk (Barabel) to the Imperial colony, but Baraduk escaped into jungle, stealing several weapons on the way; after 6-month hunt failed and resulted in deaths of 15 Imperial Army soldiers, the governor granted amnesty in return for fugitive's departure from the planet

NAME: Illarreen
INTERESTING: discovered 100 BBY; joined galactic community 90 BBY; Poss'Nomin: thickly built humanoids with 3 eyes, shovel-shaped jaws who evolved on eastern shores of island continent of Vhin but were forced to sail overseas to find fertile lands when a sudden and intense climate change (theorized to be due to a solar flare) rendered it uninhabitable

NAME: Excarga
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: mining world with ties to Mining Guild; site of First Battle of Excarga (captured by CIS) and Second (liberated by Republic) in 22 BBY during CW; Republic fleet under Anakin attempted to destroy droid transports before they escaped to hyperspace; later fell under Empire; represented in Imperial Senate by Drextar Pym; secretly supplied Rebel Alliance with materials; GCW battle here between 0 and 4 ABY; later NR member

NAME: Holador
INTERESTING: home to crashed colony of Squibs

NAME: Moonflower Nebula
INTERESTING: speckled with asteroids; during its mission of destruction, the Eye of Palpatine (Imperial battlemoon) was stopped by Jedi Knights Callista Ming and Geith Eris inside the nebula

NAME: Verkuyl system
INTERESTING: alazhi grown here; bought by Corlin Quarle Deld (founder of Verkuylian BactaCo: HQ on Dalos Peninsula, employees signed 10-year labor contracts, nationalized by Empire); in 3 ABY, GalFactorial bid to build bacta refinery here; NR liberated world; population: 220,000

NAME: Dakuyl system
INTERESTING: alazhi grown here; secondary bacta production was begun here, but halted after Endor

NAME: Magar's World
INTERESTING: brutal, inconsequential world omitted on many star charts; known only for its gladatorial games, controlled by despot Magar

NAME: Caaraz
INTERESTING: tide-locked, tectonically active; night side frozen with glaciers; day side scorching; terminator region thin but habitable; both sides of planet tetonically active with subterranean gases, lava, steam ejected into atmopshere; Empire discovered world while looking for Rebel bases and later mined planet; two moons provided night-side illumination

NAME: Livno III
INTERESTING: saved by an ancient group called The Architects through the construction of Breeze, Rain, and Solstice Globes. Together, the globes powered a machine which regulated the planet's environment within a partially underground chamber called the Chamber of the Sun

NAME: Benkal system
INTERESTING: origin point of Benkal plagues

NAME: Bursoll II
INTERESTING: upon discovery, SoroSuub Corporation wished to use a rare radioactive mineral found here in its manufacturing, and attempted to appease native Prince Geben Arrulis during his visit to Sullust by bringing rurylis flowers (plant with psychoactive effect) from Bursoll II

NAME: Tholon
INTERESTING: desolate world with rich desposits of various ores; first planet discovered by Casti Tholon (Human scout for Rim Commerical Mining) by 2 ABY; the world proved very profitable for Rim Commercial, which named it after her; it was considered the most important planet she had ever discovered

NAME: Nagi
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: high peaks, deep wide valleys, wastes
INTERESTING: arid world; thin upper atmosphere relatively ineffective at blocking solar radiation, in which high peaks were bathed; Nagai built cities in deep shaded valleys; beautiful cities constructed of wire and crystal at height of civilization (just prior to Tof invasion c. 296 BBY); Nagai survived Tof invasion, 300 years of Tof oppression; Nagai invaded the main galaxy to gather resources to fight back

NAME: Spunchina
NOTES: no mention of Spunchina system on Spunchina planet WP page
INTERESTING: known for its wild orgies; Jabba once participated in one such orgy and survived

NAME: Tof
NOTES: Tof (planet) article could use more info drawn from Tof (species) article
INTERESTING: oceans inhabited by titanic predators; island chains site of artificial ports; Tofs: green-skinned race of space pirates ruled by patriarchs who usually had military experience; history of piracy at sea, and later space travel reignited spirit of piracy; they often preyed on other worlds they discovered, defeating the Faruun and Maccabree and attacking the Nagai, who resisted strongly

NAME: Sareet system
INTERESTING: Sareeta: vaguely humanoid with dark, lidless eyes, pink skin and reached atomic-age technology before encountering galactic community; Sareeta leadership encouraged their people to explore the galaxy with the hope they would later return and raise Sareet's development level

NAME: Chibbier
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Elatha system
INTERESTING: shared name with Elathans (group)

NAME: Kaellin III
NOTES: misspelled in EA Appendix
INTERESTING: backwater planet inhabited by primitive human hunters; Rebel Alliance attaked Imperial supply convoy near planet; DX-9 stormtrooper transport crashed near local village, slaughtered villagers after mistaking peace offering for attack

NAME: Taronda
INTERESTING: remote mining world where Anakin and Ahsoka sent to negotiate a trading agreement with miners when it was attacked by CIS

NAME: Graador
INTERESTING: cavers large enough to fit entire fleets of starships, home to immense exogorths and intelligent terrestial mynocks; scouted for Rebel Base until Rebel agents determined local myocks were sentient, hostile, and controlled the Exogorths

NAME: Orellon II
INTERESTING: 35.9% surface water

NAME: Orellon I
INTERESTING: thought to be a planet when first discovered

NAME: Vorkaa system
INTERESTING: shared name with Vorkaan delegation, which met with Mokka Falanthas (NR Minister of State) in 16 ABY

NAME: Bri'ahl
INTERESTING: neutral during most of CW; Amidala and Typho tried to persuade President Vuul to ally with Republic, but activists dressed as Clone Troopers tried to assassinate them both; R2 and C-3PO prevented them; Bri'ahl likely joined the Republic and then likely was subsumed into the Empire

NAME: Lanteeb
INTERESTING: neutral, backwater, pastoral world aligned with Republic, but no representation; colonized by settlers from highly xenophobic Rocantor c. 421 BBY; specialized in agriculture and mining; as market for damotite dwindled, many Lanteebans were forced to take offworld jobs, where their xenophobic natures caused many problems; no records of Lanteeb in Jedi Archives, but Ahsoka found mention of the world in Kaliida Shoals Medical Center financial records

NAME: Kalzeron
NOTES: update Kalzeron w info from Kalzerian WP page
INTERESTING: feudal civilization; Kalzerians: near-humans with gray, leather-like skin, black teeth, yellow eyes; subjugated by Empire; freed following Endor

NAME: Vassek
INTERESTING: blue-and-green world; far enough off Koda Spur that it didn't get many visitors; offered no uncommon resources that couldn't be obtained elsewhere more easily;

NAME: Vassek's Third Moon
INTERESTING: Grievous had castle here; Dooku allowed Jedi to track Nute Gunray here as a test of Grievous, though Gunray actually wasn't present; all Jedi who tried to apprehend him were killed except for Kit Fisto, who fled

NAME: Hassaria system
INTERESTING: Hassarians: NR members with willowy physiques, lilac hair, long scouts, had centuries-long rivalry with the Skembo

NAME: Dorriella
INTERESTING: family with 3 children (including human girl Shanna Kinn and two older brothers,all of whom learned to repair starships) lived here; Empire eventually occupied Dorriella; Shanna's family killed during Imperial raid on suspected Rebel hideout; Shanna resorted to thievery to survive on streets, eventually stowed away on freighter to get offworld

NAME: Ryoone
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: dismal; had seemingly permanent suspension of ash in upper atmosphere

NAME: Lotho Minor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: junkyards, mountains of refuse, toxic sludge pools, starship wrecks
INTERESTING: used as dumping ground for generations, which attracted salvagers; Maul went into exile here until being found by Savage Opress; roamed by colossal incinerator droids

NAME: Narrant system
INTERESTING: home to a number of liege-holder clans (loose confederations of genetically-linked species, with complex layers of ritual obeisance and blood oaths maintaining their unity

NAME: Minoth
INTERESTING: prior to Hoth, Han Solo planned to run weapons from Minoth to Hendrix for Rebel Alliance

NAME: Thaldo
INTERESTING: Rebel outpost (one of many infiltrated by Nagai spies after Yavin), site of Battle of Thaldo

NAME: Winagrew system
INTERESTING: around 1 ABY, Leia was supposed to visit on diplomatic mission but was captured by rogue Imperial Commander Rezi Soresh before she could arrive

NAME: Almak
INTERESTING: Leffingites had two pairs of eyes , were subdued by AT walkers in Battle of Almak; origin point of Almakian apples

NAME: Jiaan
INTERESTING: during early years of Empire, one of many planets decimated and subjugated; Tyneir Renz was a native

NAME: Entropian Hive
INTERESTING: asteroid used as black market trading post, controlled by the Entropian Hive Trading Council; Yrica Quell was sent here by Caern Adan to recruit Nath Tensent into what became Alphabet Squadron

NAME: Aldin
INTERESTING: Mace Windu and Kit Fisto had an unpleasant, dangerous experience here

NAME: Tay'ah'loo
INTERESTING: in 1 ABY, unscheduled capsule carrying Bledsoe's disease landed here and released the plague, decimating population within days; Stormtroopers arrived soon after to cart away dead and disinfect planet

NAME: Kholes
INTERESTING: in Imperial space; home to Rebel outpost; in 1 ABY, shortly after an outbreak of Bledsoe's disease on nearby planet Tay'ah'loo, outpost was wiped out by Imperial TIE Fighters

NAME: Gendius V
INTERESTING: 5th orbital position; inhabitants were threatened by a plague; individuals visiting from offworld saved locals from disease; several young adventurers from Gendius V joined the group, following one of their saviors

NAME: Quaensan Prime
INTERESTING: Inhabitants wiped out by Reslian Purge (like Tunroth)

NAME: Lorta
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Paradise Station
INTERESTING: known for pirates & slavers, gambling, pleasure slaves, illegal narcotics more than shipping or goods; in 980 BBY Lucia met Huntress, who wanted to hire her to assassinate Rebel leader Gelba

NAME: Kaliska
INTERESTING: during time of the Old Republic Cold War, Techno-priests of Kaliska developed the Visualization Engine (capable of predicting future events based on user input)

NAME: Sibisime
INTERESTING: capital: Saraban City; in 4 ABY Zakarisz Ghent was living here when he was approached by a man sho offere him a job if he went to Chibias, and gave him a spaceliner ticket

NAME: Chibias
INTERESTING: Zakarisz Ghent traveled here after being offered a job but got caught up in a plot involving stolen gov't secrets before being rescued by Mara Jade; eventually he connected with his new employer, Talon Karrde

NAME: Cimarosa
INTERESTING: Von Longo and two sons lived here until they were arrested in 1 BBY and loaded onto the prison barge Purge

NAME: Ebenmal
INTERESTING: between 2 and 1 BBY battle between Rebel Alliance & Empire fought in the ancient citadel of Ebenmal, said never to have fallen to an invader for over 10,000 years; in 1 hour, 85 Imperial jumptroopers caused 3,000 Rebels to surrender

NAME: Lopor Station
INTERESTING: Quantana (bounty hunter) started career as child in the streets here

NAME: Yartiga system
INTERESTING: origin point of Yartigan well water (beverage served at Farrimmer Cafe)

NAME: Chroman
INTERESTING: location of the Chroman Labor Pits, which were owned by the Empire

NAME: Tallaso
INTERESTING: ruled by Imperial Governor Riggins Delahrg; planet ignored by Empire after Endor, allowing Delahrg to be overthrown in coup -- he subsequently fled to Vandron

NAME: Japai system
INTERESTING: Rebel pilots Kraigg, Tabba and Lady Blue killed here after embarking on a recon mission

NAME: Sorotarr VI
INTERESTING: location of The Game (luxurious casino)

NAME: Kaal
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Abelor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Bhuna Sound
INTERESTING: joined NR shortly after Endor; NR sent Dewback's Burden (freighter) with supplies here but captured & attacked by TIE Pirates

NAME: Little Petrovi
NOTES: Add Corellian Trade Spine

NAME: Jiroch-Reslia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Geal system
INTERESTING: group of NR soldiers were re-establishing gov't of a colony in this system when a bounty hunter killed their captain & claimed bounty on his head

NAME: Feris
INTERESTING: in mid-3600s BBY, archaeologists discovered frost-preserved remnants of a millennia-old civilization here; capital: Feris City (bounty hunters could be hired here during Galactic Civil War

NAME: Ixzinia system
INTERESTING: home of Ixzinian rock rams

NAME: Pyjridj
INTERESTING: planet where a pickpocket gave Lando some information

NAME: Kaump III
INTERESTING: Kaump heavyworlders had short stature, dense structure, short limbs, flat faces

NAME: Derricon
INTERESTING: rebel base here

NAME: Lenthalis
INTERESTING: Spirva sector capital; largest continent: Basin; capital city: Hreas Port City, headquarters of Galladinium Galactic Exports; Commerce Concourse was site of gang-rivalry riots shortly before Hoth

NAME: Aybar system
INTERESTING: shared name with Aybarians; Aybarians: at some point before taking back control of Cloud City, Baron Administrator Lando Calrissian played a game of Six-Card Gizka Limit against a spice-drunk Aybarian diplomat, in which he won a Rossmoyne Vitiator Pistol from the diplomat

NAME: Sileron
INTERESTING: hostile world with constant dangerous storms due to extreme axial tilt; simple plants as well as defensive and carnivorous plants; many poisonous/venomous animals

NAME: Veron Minor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, rainforests, tropical jungles, oceans, tree-cities
INTERESTING: population 84M; Gazaran ruled by ancient noble house of Araba; "rustic" trade world with thriving tourism; fevvenor trees covered 3/4 of land mass (mountains and shores didn't support trees); complex biosphere with many unusual life forms; 4 continents (Vusl, Ganzka, Ablor, Norol) and 3 oceans (Alboz Sea, Sea of Graves, Dizenk-Olvod Ocean; main starport Trelbio

NAME: Trieron
INTERESTING: research planet; several learning institutions had oceanographic research bases here, including Academy at Sab Rufo, Metharg's University, and UnitedChem/Corosuub University

NAME: Maro Della
INTERESTING: when Hyannis's grenade launcher jammed in a firefight here, they had to throw it away before it exploded

NAME: Manalin
INTERESTING: commercially worthless

NAME: Grall
INTERESTING: commercially worthless

NAME: Joralla
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: high mountain ranges, tropical jungles, forests
INTERESTING: Tikiarri: population 10M, aggressive, unruly tribal avians caused troubles in neighboring systems; humanoid Wasilsi thought to have originated offplanet, eventually went extinct; plague here in 3643 BBY; mineral deposits including Jorallan opals (valuable offworld)

NAME: Eiattu 6
INTERESTING: ruled for centuries by royal house of Eiattu; king forced to make humiliating concessions to prevent deployment of Imperial forces, but after 5 years the Empire garrisoned the world anyway; nobles overthrew and planned to exile royal family, but a small faction murdered them instead; later Rogue Squadron pilot Plourr Ilo revealed herself as heiress Isplourrdacartha Estillo

NAME: Yankirk system
INTERESTING: shared name with Yankirk Route,a local route that intersected a number of larger hyperlanes at Eriadu

NAME: Silvestri system
INTERESTING: shared name with the Silvestri Trace

NAME: Sinded
INTERESTING: assassin Morteos killed NR General Crix Masst here with a speeder-bomb and barely escaped from pursuing Y-wings in his modified freighter

NAME: Mima II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, jungles, mountains, volcanoes, oceans, rivers, seas
INTERESTING: orbited star closely; very geologically active due to solar tidal forces; tall (hundred of meters) jungles of yellow, blue, and green; in 3638 BBY a groundquake sent a business district slowly sliding into a magma pool; moons inhabited; Bilars were hive minds of 4 - 10

NAME: Vandron system
INTERESTING: run by Empire-affiliated gov't during Galactic Civil War; after Endor, Riggins Delahrg (former Imperial governor of Tallaso) became employed at Imperial Administration building of Vandron system but fled months later when Vandronian gov't collapsed

NAME: Argul
INTERESTING: Argullians: near-human with yellow irises & broad, flat noses; thriving commerce center before CW; Senex / Juvex merchant consortiums settled here; Republic member; major cities devastated during CW

NAME: Veron
NOTES: Where is Veron Minor?

NAME: Yagara system
INTERESTING: home of Yagaran aleudrupe (plant), origin point of Yagaran Four (bounty hunter team)

NAME: Grizal
INTERESTING: during the High Republic era, it was home to an abandoned prison complex used as a base by the Nihil marauders

NAME: Grizal's moon
NOTES: not mentioned on Grizal's Wook page
INTERESTING: after the Nihil attack on Valo, Temprest Runner Lourna Dee kept her ship in geostationary orbit while in a holo-call with Pan Eyta

NAME: Asmeru
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ice-capped mountain ranges, arid plateaus, cultured terraced hillsides, ancient ruins

NAME: Nymalia
INTERESTING: home to Nymalian water-ox

NAME: Asyrphus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Battlefront: Twilight Company/could have been during the Mid Rim push; placed in Mid Rim not too far from Coyerti (last planet abandoned furing Mid Rim retreat)
INTERESTING: a comm tech from Twilight Company died here along with her droid sometime between 0 ABY and 3 ABY

NAME: Ch'manss system
INTERESTING: inhabitants loyal to Republic during CW

NAME: Haruun Kal
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Ec Pand
INTERESTING: Lady Kalena & handmaiden Missa captured by pirates while fleeing from rival house

NAME: Ithori (Ado)
NOTES: Ottega System also sometimes called Ithori System
INTERESTING: Imperial Knight Jao Assam oversaw construction of secondary communications array outpost on an asteroid as part of Empress Marasiah Fel's plans to build galaxy-spanning communication array network

NAME: Jabor
INTERESTING: Jabori were natives to Jabor; Ferus Olin sent double agent Clive Flax undercover into local Seperatist base to destroy Mid Rim spy ring, saving many lives

NAME: Killisu system
INTERESTING: Joined CIS during CW

NAME: Loposi III
INTERESTING: artificial atmosphere of nutrient-rich gases derived from liquid kolto (from medicinal plant); member of CIS during CW

NAME: Tshindral III
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: crater fields, mountains (once tropical, now scant, highly corrosive atmosphere)

NAME: Starlyte Station
INTERESTING: 500m long; station was once Imperial Transfer Post, though never completed

NAME: Hapuntep
INTERESTING: ruled by monarchy; at least one noble held title of "Crown Prince"

NAME: Garcornia
INTERESTING: in 3638 BBY, mass riots here left dozens of manufacturing plants in disarray; Garcornian spice (rare variant, considered contraband mined here)

NAME: Vellas Pavo
NOTES: Add Duros Space Run?

NAME: Ord Hout
INTERESTING: colonized by Republic sometime before Pius Dea Era

NAME: Gevarno Cluster
INTERESTING: loyal to CIS during CW; CIS forces withdrew to the Cluster after inability to defend Haruun Kal; Doolb Snoil began legal apprenticeship here

NAME: Darkknell
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Kerig'En
INTERESTING: homeworld of Alara Fax

NAME: Najan-Rovi
INTERESTING: the dockyards here housed starships for high-ranking Imperial officials; in 3 ABY, the Rebel Alliance's 61st Mobile Infantry attacked the dockyards, setting almost a hundred ships ablaze in an effort to draw security away from Kuat Drive Yards and force CEC to increase ship production

NAME: Callos
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: tropical jungles (historical), icy wastes (After Empire), mountains
INTERESTING: during CW remained neutral; site of black market operation run by Clawfish (oulaw tech); Ahsoka and Kit Fisto traveled here to prevent an advanced starfighter design from falling into the wrong hands; in 3 ABY, Empire destroyed Callos's planetary reactor after discovering the Callosians were developing offensive tech to be used against Empire, leaving it a freezing iceball; traveling Callosians returned home to die; Imperials later found no survivors

NAME: Cmaoli Di
INTERESTING: Hydian Way charted through planet between 3701 and 3699 BBY; known to receive broadcasts from Brema News service; major cities: Ferronel, Mallonore

NAME: Gad
INTERESTING: home to ore traders in years after Galactic Civil War

NAME: Sululluub
NOTES: images show as planetary ring orbiting blue-brown world (check)
INTERESTING: Imperial TIEs sent to search for Rebels here shortly before Yavin

NAME: Sullust
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, volcanoes, rocky deserts, obsidian crags, caves, rivers of lava
INTERESTING: atmosphere barely breathable; hot, thick clouds of toxic gases, blackout ash clouds released in eruptions; only certain portions of the world had actively erupting volcanoes. yet few volcanoes were reliably extinct; Sullustans evolved underground where stable tunnels connected edible lichen gardens to pools of potable water; trade hub; often locked down by Empire

NAME: Sulon
INTERESTING: thriving ag program; homeworld of Kyle Katarn; HQ of Sulon Incorporated (SoroSuub subsidiary) which utilized underground areas of moon for manufacturing, starport facilities, munitions storage, bacteriological testing; active Rebel group here during GCW; Empire waged war against them until Alliance ordered all forces on Sulon to retreat; in order to escape, Rebels captured Akkalo Station, a small Imperial spaceport

NAME: Umnub
INTERESTING: smaller moon of Sullust; incapable of supporting life; mined for ores & minerals, but mines played out c. 1000 BBY and facilities were abandoned

NAME: Mumunubb
INTERESTING: shared fifth orbital position with Munumubb

NAME: Munumubb
INTERESTING: shared fifth orbital position with Mumunubb

NAME: Ord Ibanna
INTERESTING: site of intense naval battle during Great Galactic War during which Rycus Kilran distinguished himself; Tibanna mining colony here abandoned prior to Battle of Naboo; during CW used as secret meeting spot between Quinlan Vos and Tholme, and decrepit mining platforms used as podrace courses; planet disappeared from history when Empire outlawed podracing

NAME: Drilbia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Drilbian wine (beverage)

NAME: Harlequin Station
INTERESTING: XQ1 platform serving as independent trade center that did business with Azzameen Station; Ace delivered his first cargo here shortly after Hoth; K'Armyn VIraxo presumably bought off the system patrol craft that abandoned the station just before several Viraxo ships attacked during the delivery; Ace was awarded the key to the station by the outpost's Mayor Brauken

NAME: Adras
INTERESTING: had dark night skies; Nezan was major city, with a detention center on its outskirts; shortly before Endor, team of Sullustan Alliance Intelligence officers was tasked with meeting other Rebel agents to lead group of combat starships to join main Rebel fleet but were captured by Empire before escaping & completing mission

NAME: Orish
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: lush, pastures, farms (prior to bombing); poisoned wasteland (after devastation)
INTERESTING: original agriworld home of Orishen species; Empire strip-mined Orish, enslaved Orishen, worked them hard for food production; Orishen created, detonated massive chemical weapon that destroyed Imperial occupation but also poisoned their world; a few thousand survivors fled to a network of tubes and stations in orbit, as well as orbiting asteroid archipelago)

NAME: Orish Orbital Station
INTERESTING: network of tubes and stations in orbit; after Orishen drove away the Empire by devastating and poisoning their own homeworld with a massive bomb, a few thousand survivors fled here, as well as to an orbiting asteroid archipelago

NAME: Orish Asteroid Archipelago
INTERESTING: after Orishen drove away the Empire by devastating and poisoning their own homeworld with a massive bomb, a few thousand survivors fled here, as well as to a network of tubes and stations in orbit

NAME: Dzass IV
INTERESTING: site of presitgious Lunis-Medix Medical Academy; Yin Vocta (Anomid businessman) graduated top of his class here

NAME: Tendo system
INTERESTING: system contained several planets frequented by Stalnus (Riorian murderer), who had a network of informants in the system who helped him evade capture

NAME: Coyerti
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Battlefront: Twilight Company/near Malastare?; on edge of Mid Rim (presumably outer, since Alliance was retreating to Outer Rim)
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: hills & valleys covered in humid jungle
INTERESTING: during CW, Republic Senate debated opening a hyperlane between Malastare & Coyerti to transport permacrete; Imperial bioweapon research outpost released toxins into environment, rotting the jungles; native Coyerti entered reproductive cycle in 3 ABY, leaving them defenseless against the Empire; Twilight Company was called to defend them while destroying the facility and covering an Alliance retreat from the Mid Rim

NAME: Cyclor
INTERESTING: relatively small planet that appeared green and brown from space; orbited by vast shipyards

NAME: Cyclor Shipyards
INTERESTING: the Cyclor shipyards were renowned for being extremely advanced due to the engineering capabilities of the Cyclorrian swarms

NAME: Jutrand
INTERESTING: razed by stone mites during Hundred-Year Darkness, but subsequently rebuilt; during the Republic Dark Age, served as capital world of the Bactranate (a Sith state led by the Quermian Sith Lord Ayanos Bactra); following the Battle of Gazzari in 1032 BBY, family matriarch Vilia Calimondra ordered her grandchildren to turn on Bactra, and Odionate forces conquered Jutrand; CIS member

NAME: Heptooine
INTERESTING: considered one of the oldest relics of Galactic Republic colonization in the Grumani sector; for millennia, it existed as a frontier outpost until a sizable population grew into the surrounding regions of the sector; by the time of Sith control, it had reverted to barbarism after several decades of famine and war

NAME: Sanrafsix
INTERESTING: cosmopolitan trade hub during New Sith Wars (doomed the world's populace when it could not maintain quarantine during a Candorian plague outbreak); forced to isolate its groundside population, which eventually all succumbed; site of Jedi victory over the forces of the Sith decades later; part of CIS, Galactic Empire; eventually fell under Eriadu Authority (Imperial splinter faction)

NAME: Tramanos
INTERESTING: Cyanogen-Oxygen atmosphere (colony of Celegians)

NAME: Byllura
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: plateaus, waterfalls, rainforests, rivers, deltas, oceans
NOTES: Shown on M-17 and N-17. Grumani map N-17 supercedes?

NAME: Syned
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: shattered ice sheets, glaciers, frozen plains, ice calderas, under-ice seas, domed urban

NAME: Gazzari Minor system
INTERESTING: Sebolto (Dug crimelord) ran a smuggling operation here at some point prior to Naboo; his dealings were leaked to the Republic Security Force by Bendix Fust, leading Sebolto to lose a huge amount of credits; Sebolto placed a bounty on Fust's head, eventually collected by Jango Fett during The Hunt

NAME: Azzameen Station
INTERESTING: orbited a volcanic planet; HQ of Azzameen family's Twin Suns Transport Services; had holosimulator and a large hangar; shortly after Hoth in 3 ABY, Azzameen family were labeled traitors to the Empire for helping Rebels; station was turned over to Viraxo Industries; renamed Falcon's Nest by occupying mercs and finally liberated by Rebels and femaining Azzameen family

NAME: Roccus
INTERESTING: a blue world with some cloud cover

NAME: Twin Sun Station
INTERESTING: owned and operated by Azzameen family and used by their shipping company, Twin Suns Transport Services, often referred to as the "family repair yard"; 1.85km long; had drydock facilities for two large starships as well as 2 pressurized hangars for smaller craft; seized by VSD II Furious

NAME: Verdanth
INTERESTING: frequently fought over during New Sith Wars; title "Conqueror of Verdanth" passed to a new Sith Lord every few years (Jedi Master Vannar Treece estimated 17 since 1032 BBY); Vader failed to capture Luke here during GCW;

NAME: Crait
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: briny seas, waterways, canyons, mountains, salt flats

NAME: Oetchi system
INTERESTING: remote system where the Resistance fleet rendezvoused after evacuating D'Qar; a First Order fleet attacked them here during the events of The Last Jedi

NAME: Arbran
INTERESTING: a rebel fleet hid within the star to avoid detection by a passing Imperial fleet

NAME: Arbra
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, rainforests, mountains, subterranean ruins, underground caves, ice caps, lakes, small seas, volcanoes
INTERESTING: nicknamed "Salvation"; became Rebel Alliance HQ after evacuation of Golrath Station c. 3 ABY; once inhabited by ancient race who lived in subterranean cities; no visible surface technology, but within a huge cavern there remained a vast array of geothermal power rods that drew energy from planet's core and released it into high atmosphere as lightning, creating stability and feeding Hoojibs

NAME: New Mankoo
none/Old Mankoo is in Mid Rim
INTERESTING: extrapolation: Old Mankoo suggests New Mankoo

NAME: Serphidi
INTERESTING: Doom-Joust (contest) was popular here; Imperial-allied King S'Shah (Serp male) who had a taste for human flesh; Luke toppled the corrupt government and placed Rebel-friendly King Elglih (Serp male) on the throne; Elglih told of how technology had led to constant wars and of how the Serps eventually signed a pact banning technology and united the planet under one ruler

NAME: Baarstal
NOTES: no WP page for Raalo
INTERESTING: Raalo (Toydarian junk dealer) related a story about a trader from Naboo who picked up a distress signal from someone who claimed to be stranded on Baarstal after her M38 droid went haywire and damaged her ship

NAME: Chommell Minor
INTERESTING: homeworld of Janus Greejatus; in 22 BBY Amidala capaigned against Military Creation Act here

NAME: Lofquar system
INTERESTING: home of Lofquarian gooney birds

NAME: Cirtappa
INTERESTING: On one of Ace Azzameen's first missions, a group of Alliance Y-wings attacked an Imperial convoy near Cirtappa

NAME: Tovash Tchii
INTERESTING: when the Millennium Falcon ran low on fuel after the Battle of Crait, Nien Nunb suggested stopping here to refuel; the idea was abandoned due to the likelihood of drawing First Order attention and CHewbacca suggested an old smuggler way station instead

NAME: Draik 4
INTERESTING: Imperial-run Damorian Repair Yard was nearby

NAME: Damorian Repair Yard
INTERESTING: Imperial-run 1350m-wide repair yard where Ace Azzameen destroyed the docked Carrack Cruiser Sodrab; the repair yard was damaged or likely destroyed

NAME: Kaliida N.
INTERESTING: Neebray native to Kaliida N.

NAME: Kaliida Shoals
NOTES: Kaliida Shoals not listed on Ryndellia System page

NAME: Huip
INTERESTING: classified as a sungrazer planetoid

NAME: Brenu
INTERESTING: classified as a sungrazer planetoid; no life existed here

NAME: Hebeth
INTERESTING: no life existed here

NAME: Hebine Ring
INTERESTING: Sith built an ancient observatory in one of larger asteroids

NAME: Beheboth
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, mountains, outpost towns, shallow salt lakes, moisture farms
INTERESTING: Human, Bothan colonists din't realize native Tirrith were sentient; Gideon Longspar enslaved some, forced rest to help him and his brigands steal water from moisture farms; Luke freed them with help from Darial Anglethorn (later represented planet in NR Senate); home of sand lice; homeworld of Thall Joben and the Davani family

NAME: Golrath
INTERESTING: Rebels used abandoned magma smelting plant here as base after Hoth, but abandoned after magma cooled; bedrock had unusual light-absorbing and hologram-replaying properties

NAME: Sanbra
INTERESTING: Callow Batta (pirate) seen in-system in 2 ABY; location of University of Sanbra; location of Shoapy Hostel

NAME: Gash Rugosa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Rugosa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: once had vast oceans that later dried up, leaving coral forests and rocky cavernous areas; considered neutral territory during CW; chosed as secret rendezvous location between Yoda and Toydarian King Katuunko; some corals were large enough to support starships; used as vacation spot by Toydarians; migratory neebray used moon as birthing ground

NAME: Aquilaris
INTERESTING: once a popular resort world, planet's economy revolved around podracing by end of the Golden Age of the Republic; travel between cities mostly accomplished by undersea transparisteel tunnel, which provided a view of aquatic fauna imported from Naboo; Nave Vengaris (governor) encouraged podracing, converting many old floating cities into tracks; old capital was in ruins, sinking beneath waves

NAME: Yuga 2
INTERESTING: hosted popular Yuga Planetary park, which Galaxy Tours visited; Callow Batta raided a Galaxy Tours cruiser prior to Hoth

NAME: D'Qar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: system hosted at least 3 planets

NAME: Loratus system
INTERESTING: Loratus Manufacturing probably named after this system

NAME: Huvveck system
INTERESTING: shared name with University of Huvveck (known for its sentientology department)

NAME: Celsor 3
INTERESTING: uninhabited except for native jakoosks; visited by inhabitants of the Colossus, who hunted a jakoosk for sustenance in 34 ABY

NAME: Metharg system
INTERESTING: shared name with Metharg's University (had an oceanographic institute on Mid Rim world of Trieron)

NAME: Shafr
INTERESTING: Shafr Center (prestigious university of xenoarchaeology) located here; Dr. Follnor Callat was dismissed from the center for dishonorable conduct relating to his field

NAME: Farstine
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Regulgo
INTERESTING: months after Han Solo departed Kamar in ~2 BBY, Kamarians tracked him down on Regolgo, where they captured him, though he eventually escaped

NAME: Gall
INTERESTING: location of naval supply depot and factories that made parts for Rothana, overseen by Jans Coorsa's clan; Council of Elders seceded from Republic during CW but continued to resist Empire; Empire discovered Coorsa's identity and massacred his village; after Fett's capture of Han Solo in 3 ABY, he was spotted in Gall's Imperial spaceport having Slave I repaired; population 57 M (mainly Humans)

NAME: Kile
INTERESTING: Rogue Squadron established a base, from which they launched a mission to rescue Han Solo from Boba Fett

NAME: Taivas
INTERESTING: hidden Jedi Temple built here sometime after YV War (location picked by Nat Skywalker; his brother Kol used YV terraforming to change the atmosphere without updating the planet's official records; bioluminescent creatures were known to float around the temple area

NAME: Outpost 327
INTERESTING: also known as Imperial Colony Outpost 327; apparently functioned as a cargo depot; heavily defended by TIE squadrons; Ace Azzameen stole the shuttle Tydirium from here

NAME: Breeka
INTERESTING: one of this dry desert world's native animals was a distant cousin to Tatooine's dewbacks

NAME: Maill
INTERESTING: well-known for its king having produced one of the rarest coins in the galaxy in honor of his wife; the flaming sunset-color was intended to match her hair color but ended up destroying the minting machines such that only a few hundred were made

NAME: Eos
INTERESTING: mineral-rich; hosted a large Trade Federation droid foundry; Trade Federation defended the world with a deflector shield powered by 8 generator pylons and a large planetary cannon; natives used treaded/wheeled vehicles rather than repulsorlift due to powerful, variable EM fields; Eos produced many of the weapons used in the Naboo invasion in 32 BBY

NAME: Melida/Daan
INTERESTING: engulfed in centuries-long civil war, whose factions couldn't agree on planet's name (Galactic Senate used both names separated by a slash); eventually a group called the Young (led by children of both factions) rose up and ended the war in 44 BBY with Obi-Wan's help; parts of the planet were scarred from the war; took 3 days of travel to Coruscant with a fast starship

NAME: Trigalis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: trading post of New Coronet founded long before CW, but degenerated over decades into a busy center of various illegal activities; Aayla Secura assigned a mission here, met a month later by Obi-Wan, looking for Asajj Ventress; Secura led him to fortress of Xist (Black Sun enforcer with CIS ties) in New Coronet; Celot Ratua Dil here arrested here by Empire on presumption of piracy

NAME: Stend IV
INTERESTING: Gran settlers colonized Stend IV decades before GCW, searching for new sources of energy; also settled by Elomin; targeted by eco-terrorist Army of Life and humanocentrist Knights of the Core in successful plan to smuggle in clodhopper eggs (omnivorous creatures known for devastating other worlds)

NAME: Stend VI
INTERESTING: democratic government; manufacturing site for Empire; plagued by swoop gang violence, including the Skull and Knights gangs; local police forces outmatched

NAME: Vallt
INTERESTING: half-covered in glacial ice; the snowy winds were inhospitable to offworlders; birthplace of Jyn Erso; Galen Erso and his team were working on Vallt for Zerpen Industries when the government was overthrown in a coup by CIS sympathizers, leading to Galen Erso's imprisonment in Tambolor prison on charges of espionage; the world had lacked fair representation in the Republic Senate

NAME: Qeimet system
INTERESTING: served as HQ for Republic's Sarin Oversector during CW; during GCW, shared name with Qeimet fleet (fought Rebel forces in Hook N.); name of Ubiqtorate leaked here; Death Squadron (Vader's Fleet) rendezvoused here in 3 ABY while searching for Hoth base; population 10 - 100 M (25 ABY)

NAME: Vorusku
INTERESTING: waterworld with a volcano city as well as the Hyperdrive Cantina (floating bar); Kina Ha (Kaminoan Jedi) lived here for a time and had a vision of Kaminoan cloners during CW; after 32 BBY, Jalla Spree (crimelord here) began to supply Blue Star Pirates with military-grade weaponry

NAME: Tebru
INTERESTING: by 3 ABY Toria Tell (droid inventor, historian) maintained a large residence with a workshop, extensive droid collection, and massive library here

NAME: Yasilor
INTERESTING: around 10 ABY, served as homeworld for Palkandi Brokerage House (front organization for criminal Tenloss Syndicate)

NAME: Verisin
INTERESTING: c. 10 ABY, served as homeworld of Tenloss Coalition (criminal organization specializing in contract kidnapping)

NAME: Kabaira
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, island-continents, volcanic islands, snowy mountains
INTERESTING: damp, foggy weather; 2 northern island-continents (Belshain, Madieri); 2 M volcanic islands (only a few in southern hemisphere were active during GCW; capital: Eponte Spaceport; Rebel Cell here; birthplace of the Aquatic Terrain Armored Transport (modification of AT-AT by Imperial Army garrison here)

NAME: Rezi-9
INTERESTING: homeworld of Wesau T'orrin, an individual participating in the blaster skill event of the Galactic Games in 27 BBY (helf on Mid Rim planet Euceron)

NAME: Jarvanam
INTERESTING: around 10 ABY, served as home of Baradis School of Technology (overt criminal training organization, Tenloss Syndicate member)

NAME: Y'Dar system
INTERESTING: shared name with Y'Dar Princess (luxury liner)

NAME: Zobbera system
INTERESTING: home to zobberan hounds

NAME: Magravia
INTERESTING: notable spice-production site; origin point of Magravian cat-spice (spice variant) and therefore well-known to smugglers

NAME: Lok
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren dusty badlands, sulfur pools, lifeless rivers, volcanoes, mountains
INTERESTING: home of Kimogila (massive creature); one for first planers in Karthakk system to be colonized; Nym grew up here, later had a base here until Trade Federation captured it, but Nym's Lok Revenants recaptured it in 22 BBY; during GCW, a city named Nym's Stronghold was built around Nym's old base and served as planet's spaceport; Empire ventually claimed planet

NAME: Spine of Lok
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: giant asteroid belt made almost entirely out of obsidian rock, rendering it almost invisible; remained an untapped natural resource as of GCW

NAME: Khons
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Nym staged an assault on Lok while it was occupied by Trade Federation from here, acquiring an Orbital Defense Cannon and directed it at the Trade Federation refueling station below

NAME: Lok Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: owned by Nym; cleared ships for landing at small starport of Nym's stronghold, provided emergency repairs for damaged starships

NAME: Bloodlight Sea Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Nym maintained a space station here that served as a place of business, often visited by an assortment of hagglers and thieves; later, it was a centerpoint for the war between Nym's allies and the Empire; Nym set Y-wing bombers patrolling the Bloodlight Sea region

NAME: Maramere
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: fell under domination of Lord Toat of Trade Federation who used it as a repository of stygium crystals from Aeten II; planet was crime-free from 27 BBY to 24 BBY when Sol Sixxa killed Toat; population: 900 M; home of Relix (massive predatory fish)

NAME: Nod Kartha
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: cold barren rock, some surface water
INTERESTING: site of CIS laboratory producing trihexalon (illegal chemical weapon) prior to CW; heavily defended by orbital defense cannons and powerful deflector shields; Nym compromised the defenses and staged an assault on the factory planetside

NAME: Spacestation 1138
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: prison space station maintained by Trade Federation prior to CW; Nym and his Lok Revenants staged an assault to save Captain Orsai and his men

NAME: Censorious Tempest Nebula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: lay on outermost reaches of system; a nearby asteroid field built up static charges, creating electrical outbursts that gave the nebula its name

NAME: Trade Federation Outpost
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: research center in outer reaches of Karthakk system, where Trade Federation hoped to study the Spine of Lok's obsidian rocks away from prying eyes of Empire during GCW

NAME: Imperial Outpost
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Imperial space station occupied Solar Phoenix 2 (region of Karthakk system) and patrolled the area with TIE Fighters and Bombers

NAME: Ruby Nebula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: considered to be part of the Karthakk system, but this nebula had 3 suns, giving it a ruby-red coloration; free-floating asteroids provided a hiding spot for ships

NAME: Fair Hollis system
INTERESTING: Hali Ke (Kaminoan geneticist) interviewed (from a distance) a Human pirate from here

NAME: Gorgaria system
INTERESTING: home to Gorgarian buzzadder; c. 3637 BBY, scientists here claimed to have synthesized a poison more lethal than Ziroxin-12 (chemical developed by reconstituted Sith Empire; a future commander of the Eternal Alliance tasked a companion with determining their claims' validity

NAME: Tarkenia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Tarkenian Nightflower (beverage)

NAME: Ragmar V
INTERESTING: population center was an outpost of various species' outcasts, including Humans, Klatooinians, Bith, Rodians, Ithorians, Gamorreans, Jawas, and Devaronians; at end of CW, Jed General Sev's force sought to establish a staging area here but was interrupted by Order 66

NAME: Ruhe
INTERESTING: CIS-aligned during CW; Dooku maintained a citadel here, on the edge of a massive volcanic or meteoric crater; half a month after Battle of Boz Pity, Anakin, Obi-Wan and Jenks (Clone trooper) was shot down here while trying to capture Dooku, later revealed as a trap

NAME: Yerbana
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, mountains with vegetation, canyons, oceans
INTERESTING: CW battle fought on a bridge here in 19 BBY; cities were connected by bridges, nestled among cloudtops atop mesas or mountains

NAME: Redcap
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fluid mud lakes, mud plains, barren lands, canyons, mountains
INTERESTING: rainy world that hosted a full-scale mining colony, populated by impoverished descendants of mining colonists, living in settlements at bases of mountain chains; starships would sink in the thick mud, so landings were made in Tyma Canyon (ran for several hundred km) travel conducted on olai (beasts of burden brought from a nearby moon)

NAME: Neelabi
INTERESTING: Neelabi: shy, fish-like, beady eyes, short stature, could only breathe in water, had social hierarchy built on competition

NAME: Jostaar system
INTERESTING: shared name with Jostaar Express (starship used by Raan Calrissian during CW)

NAME: Rim 3
INTERESTING: Boba Fett visited while hunting Abal Karda (rogue Imperial colonel) in 3 BBY

NAME: Korteen
INTERESTING: planetary belt (possibly orbiting a planet called Korteen); belt's denizens (supposedly miners) sctually used sonic jamming devices to disrupt starship drives, sending ships crashing into asteroids, where they could recover their cargoes; governed by Quarg's father during last years of the Republic

NAME: Duunir
INTERESTING: site of refuge for critically endangered bha'lir (created by the Black Bha'lir smuggler's organization) after deforestation of Iyred

NAME: Omman Minor
INTERESTING: featured a wide diversity of cultures; capital: Capital City

NAME: Socorro
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: black sands, desert swells, flatlands, mountains, volcanic areas, badlands
INTERESTING: homeworld of Lando Calrissian; no unifying government; contested by various criminal organizations; unified cultural force integrating nomadic and criminal elements, offered protection from offworld authorities; exported water, nether ice, and high-tech skills; imported metals, high technology (imports and exports both performed illegally); peculiar starship mods were a major source of income

NAME: Neftali
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren glaciers, fjords, frozen oceans, mountains, ice canyons, deep caverns
INTERESTING: name in Old Corellian meant "home" or "safe place"; home of unsavory elements; barren world with long orbit; deep underground chambers warmed by geothermal forces hosted mosses and lichens, providing food for the planet's fauna; population: 15,000

NAME: Thrugii Belt
NOTES: another asteroid belt orbited in the Thrugii system, near the planet Thrugii
INTERESTING: widespread belt with 3 different orbitals; astrogation reports suggested they were the remains of 3 planets destroyed when Sokor blossomed into a red giant; Kanauer Corporation claimed all rights and mined the belt for small quantities of doonium and turminum; Empire had no presence here, so the corporation felt free to turn away outsiders at blasterpoint

NAME: Thrugii
NOTES: another asteroid belt orbited near the planet Thrugii
INTERESTING: located near an asteroid field; home of many failed miners, who were considered claim jumpers by sector authorities, who claimed they owned the rights instead; miners found themselves out of supplies after authorities locked down the planet; Kaine Paulsen (smuggler) was killed while trying to deliver supplies

NAME: Iyred
INTERESTING: home of bha'lir, driven so near to extinction by deforestation that they were declared officially extinct and refuges were created on other worlds such as Duunir

NAME: Fligger system
INTERESTING: home of Fliggerian firebeasts

NAME: Purala IV
INTERESTING: at some point by 27 BBY, Lords of Purala IV requested Kaminoans create human clones who would serve as members of infiltration squads, as noted by Hali Ke (Kaminoan geneticist) in an internal memo

NAME: Julsujod III
INTERESTING: waterworld; at some point 5000 years before GCW, a series of cataclysms occurred here, leaving the native inhabitants helpless until a group of spacefaring benefactors arrived and relocated the Stribers to Iskalon, where they eventually became the rarest of the species comprising the Iskalonian cultural group and faced extinction

NAME: Oshora system
INTERESTING: origin point of Oshora Rainbow Pearl Necklace (sold by Toydarian vendor Nenmo at his curio shop at the Cularin Trade Show aboard the TAV Prosperity during CW)

NAME: Branteez
INTERESTING: at some point by 38:1:15 a Shrine of Kooroo (one of a number of mysterious stone structures found on several Outer Rim Worlds including Gelgelar, Sufezz, and Boztrok) had been uncovered here

NAME: Arkanis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galactic Atlas/Dawn of Rebellion p. 62 (Arkanis Academy)
INTERESTING: orbited at least 2 suns; downpoured 2 - 3 days a week and drizzled the rest; sunshine considered rare; the Exchange attempted to deliver lethal weapons to mercs here during Galactic War; throneworld of Regency Worlds; Imperial officers' adacemy was here; homeworld of Armitage Hux; had a fishing industry; Scaparus Port was hub for fisherfolk; location of Vensenor Flight Academy

NAME: Issor
INTERESTING: most powerful planet in Trulalis system

NAME: Cadezia
INTERESTING: prosperous technology and business world

NAME: Trulalis
