INTERESTING: colonized c. 500 BBY; known for its theater; populace eliminated by the Empire; home of Adalric Brandl, who trained his his son Jaalib as an actor on the depopulated world; he also trained Fable Astin in he Jedi arts, intending to turn her to the dark side and give her to Palpatine on Byss; home to widely regarded university that drew students from surrounding sectors

NAME: Najiba
INTERESTING: backwater with considerable criminal activity; covered in wetlands; surface was lashed with lightning and frequent rainstorms; located only an hour's hyperspace travel from Issor system; during half its elliptical orbit, Najiba passed near a hazardous asteroid belt known as the Children of Najiba at which time all travel to and from was restricted; Byzal Canyon popular with swoop racers

NAME: Children of Najiba
INTERESTING: made Najiba hard to reach or leave during half of the planet's elliptical orbit

NAME: Huldamun
INTERESTING: industrialized planet; one of the Regency Worlds (planets that controlled economic control of trade along Corellian Run near crossroads with Triellus Trade Route as well as Hutt-dominated aconomics spinward of Kemal Station); exported mining gear

NAME: Vor Deo
INTERESTING: trade world; received a lot of smuggler traffic

NAME: Tarnoonga
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, undersea mountain ranges, immense natural caves & grottos
INTERESTING: home to giant sea monsters such as the Miridon, which made its nest in ruins of sunken freighter ships sitting atop undersea mountain ranges; Gir Kybo Ren-Cha (pirate) established a hideaway base in depths of one of these mountains (actually an island since it broke the surface of the waves), where he hid captured treasures from nearby worlds such as Tammuz-an; Luke contronted S'ybll here

NAME: Siskeen system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Siskeen
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Death Wind Corridor not on page?
INTERESTING: CIS built up forces here and several other worlds at the start of the CW's Outer Rim Sieges; the Siskeen theater became one of the main theaters of this campaign; Avik Lore had a routine run planned to Siskeen for a shipment of rock wart eggs c. 0 ABY

NAME: Olanet
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: sided with CIS during CW; said to be the home of the second largest droid factory, after Geonosis; nerf-meat industry was one of the most important sectors of its economy

NAME: Kaer
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Kaer Station was a tibanna gas mining platform built in the atmosphere, but by 137 ABY it had been taken over by Black Sun and was used as a base for Vigo Lun Rask

NAME: Kaer Orbital Platform
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: 2km wide orbital platform; constructed by InterGalactic Banking Clan using materials specially ferried by Banking Clan Cargo Ships; used as refueling, repair base by CIS; shortly after Geonosis, Sev'rance Tann (CIS General) was assigned here to rebuild droid armies; she clared out local population of mynocks and started building droids but fled when a Republic general found the base

NAME: Nishr
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, temperate areas, forests, rough ground, upland (accessible through passes), mountains, plains, seas
INTERESTING: during GCW, native Nish were still in feudal stage, but in southern Feldt (continent), below the mountains, an industrial society was developing, withs everal cities; had untapped mineral resources and some strategic value location-wise; in 2 BBY a small Imperial garrison was deployed here from Mirshilan, and abuses by troops led to a native rebellion and the Nishr Campaign (waged by the Alliance)

NAME: Gerzob
NOTES: EA grid square & sector disagree
INTERESTING: homeworld of Yellow-Bellied Green-Proboscis Marsupial (creature)

NAME: Sirpar
INTERESTING: large planet w high gravity and few natural resources; Imperial high-gravity training center; primary Imperial training facilities in Arkanis sector; stories about Sirpar (usually negative ones) were circulated throughout Empire); scarcely defended; aside from a pleasant starport (Jacelle) and Imperial facilities, native nomadic Eklaad were only things on the planet

NAME: Gorno
NOTES: Corellian Run not listed
INTERESTING: Empire had a secret research facility here used to design the 2nd Death Star superlaser, code-named Hammertong; spaceport here used as an embarkation point from which Hammertong was to depart, shortly before Yavin

NAME: Vasch
INTERESTING: agriworld; source of Vaschean rye (alcoholic drink); possibly the homeworld of Sam Heggs; during Galactic War, government of Vasch sold a large quantity of cheap "rubbish" that was confiscated from criminals

NAME: Mika
NOTES: WP says R-16
INTERESTING: Imperial penal planetoid; Mikans: statues of beautiful near-Human women which came to life at sunset, luring in unwary beings and then dissolving into jellyfish-like creatures to consume their prey

NAME: Heffrin
INTERESTING: small mining colony maintained by Empire; held ruins from a vanished civilization, including the continent-spanning Heffrin Aqueducts (research during the Cold War identified the aqueduct builders as early Ithorian explorers)

NAME: Khubeaie
INTERESTING: misty, nondescript industrial planet, but better-known as a stopover for spice smugglers traveling down the Old Corellian Run from Ryloth to Tatooine

NAME: Cirus II
INTERESTING: mining world for syntonium; Lex (human male) was mining operator here; cargo hauler pilot Tem Chesko visited here to pick up syntonium haul, then subsequently was stranded in deep space after an asteroid collision; at that time he calculated 10 parsecs to the nearest planet, such that he wouldn't arrive in less than 60 years

NAME: Orvax IV
INTERESTING: slave trade world; traders lived in upper city levels; crew of Uhumele attempted to rescue Bomo Greenbark's family here but were too late

NAME: Iscera
INTERESTING: "dry" planet lacking any legal establishments that sold alcohol; Fable Astin saw Jaalib Brandl perform in a play here

NAME: Nysza III
INTERESTING: after Yavin it was the location of an Imperial communications bunker

NAME: Juma 9
INTERESTING: critical Republic base during CW

NAME: Derora
INTERESTING: inhabitable moon

NAME: Isamu
INTERESTING: home of Mu trees (trees that grew in pairs and whose shadows at night looked like lovers kissing

NAME: Shimia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: represented directly in Galactic Senate; following rise of NR, increasing numbers of Pacitthip left homeworld to explore the galaxy and find careers abroad rather than a career determined by caste at home

NAME: Lorn system
INTERESTING: governed by Moff Murquan during GCW

NAME: Arapia
NOTES: "some minions to Arapia to met"...
INTERESTING: adoptive homeworld of Kadri'Ra (population: 100 M+ during Republic era; Empire decided they were not sentients and reduced their numbers to 14,000 via slavery and other measures by 0 BBY; crime here was controlled by Sadoon-Kauldi (Kadri'Ra crimelord, a native who left the system after one assassination attempt)

NAME: Mirshilan
INTERESTING: under armed Imperial occupation in 2 BBY; a unit from here was deployed to garrison Nishr; events of subsequent Nishr Suppression implied the occupation force had been using harsh methods to retain control

NAME: Luudria system
INTERESTING: home of Luudrian lockjaws (tenacious creatures); shared name with freighter Luudrian Star

NAME: Beta Rhama
grid square/sector/on same hyperroute as Nimba Five

NAME: Miv'rah system
INTERESTING: shared name with Miv'rah Firestorm (light freighter)

NAME: Liintaar Station
INTERESTING: Alliance communication base here was attacked by Empire during GCW

NAME: Ryloth
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungles, mountains, snow plains, temperate forests, mesas, valleys, volcanoes, deserts
INTERESTING: hot and humid; affected by pull of its 5 moons; much of its wildlife was lethal, leading Twi'leks to live underground or in defensible locations; exploited by Hutts for centuries as a key spice trade world and for slave labor; Zygerrian Slave Empire also controlled Ryloth until its destruction by Jedi; CIS invaded during CW and Twi'leks fought for freedom under Cham Syndulla, later against Empire

NAME: Ryloth's largest moon *
INTERESTING: housed the command center of Delian Mors (Imperial Moff) in 14 BBY

NAME: Ryloth's nearest moon
INTERESTING: desolate, rocky moon with a breathable atmosphere; shortly after the rise of the New Order, members of the Free Ryloth Movement (including Gobie Glie and a young Hera Syndulla) arranged a rendezvous to pick up illegal weapons here from the Bad Batch

NAME: Ryloth's third moon *
INTERESTING: the Free Ryloth Movement had an underground base here, where Cham Syndulla spent several days planning an assault on the ISD Perilous, which was transporting Palpatine and Vader to Ryloth

NAME: Unidentified moon *
INTERESTING: Leia traveled here in 0 ABY to scout its potential as a new Rebel base, but was ultimately unsuccessful... Empire 20, 21

NAME: Or Tuma
INTERESTING: small colony of 700 or so Twi'leks settled here to get away from the scorching temperatures of Ryloth

NAME: Wxtm
INTERESTING: home to ravenscreechers (six-legged avians)

NAME: Ab Dalis
INTERESTING: home to numerous corporations; Ab Dalis's corrupt government catered to their tower-living oligarch trillionaires; city-sized factories were operated by slum-living workers; during the Great Hyperspace Disaster, Ab Dalis was struck by the first Emergence, killing 20 million; the impact left a massive crater and cracked the crust, which became unstable, leading to the planet's abandonment; the Rebel Alliance situated a base on the edge of the crater hundreds of years later

NAME: Krmar system
INTERESTING: shared name with epithet "Champion of Krmar", one of many titles bestowed upon Sharad Hett (Jedi Master) by 47 BBY

NAME: Lessuris
INTERESTING: homeworld of Luskin Exovar (Human male scout who retired from Republic Scout Service in anticipation of Republic's downfall)

NAME: Rordak
INTERESTING: originally orbited by 4 planets; millions of years BBY, it expanded to form a red giant, destroying the three innermost planets and leaving only Rordak (planet)

NAME: Rordak
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountainous desert, desert plains, huge mountains, deep gorges, rare water
INTERESTING: when its star expanded and destroyed inner 3 planets, Rordak's seas were scorched and great tectonic shifts occurred, destroying most life-forms; Viska and other new forms of life arose; rich in metals, atmosphere hostile; rare rains were highly acidic due to volcanic ash; high CO2 was fatiguing to most visitors; few indigenous fauna; four starports; repulsorlift cities moved to avoid eruptions

NAME: Daslkehnt
INTERESTING: Jrahl Ferrin gang performed criminal activities here before 6 ABY, when Rei'Kas (a Rodian) was a member

NAME: Pelgrin
INTERESTING: 2 M+ years before Yavin, Pelgrin built the Oracle here (a merging of tech and the Force) before going extinct, leaving mysterious ruins, artifacts; legends told that c. 25,000 BBY, Xim the Despot visited the Oracle; c. 3000 BBY, Ermin Phin-Mar and Shannur Darkstar (Jedi) studied the Oracle after the Jedi Council detected a Force tremor from Pelgrin; world was given to the Jedi

NAME: Perilious
INTERESTING: home to a large criminal element, including a large slaving ring that dealt in Twi'leks; continually covered in storms; during CW Vydel Dir'Nul (Jedi) tracked Kardem (serial killer) to the planet

NAME: Zoma V
INTERESTING: Felinians: primitive felinoids; Sithless Leethe (Saurian crimelord) attempted to smuggle Imperial weapons to the Felinians under oversight of Slopper (his associate and fellow Saurian), for which the Felinians wished to trade precious stones; couriers delivered weapons to Rebel Alliance instead

NAME: Alarevi system
INTERESTING: origin point of Alarevi ale

NAME: Aaloth
NOTES: no info (listen to audiobook)

NAME: Gaulus
INTERESTING: Caluan Ematt (Alliance Lieutenant) and Ruescott Melshi (Alliance Sergeant) served together here during the early Rebellion; hosted an Alliance base at one time; an espionage droid infiltrated the base and transmitted its location to the Empire; the base was destroyed shortly after; during Alliance retreat, they deployed U-wings as medevac lifters

NAME: Tellanroaeg
NOTES: EA Appendix lists as Hunnoverrs sector but maps show location in Gaulus on Corellian Run
INTERESTING: site of CW battle between CIS and Republic; lay within Hutt sphere of influence from at least 22 BBY during first CW campaigns until Order 66 reached Tellanroaeg in 19 BBY; by 17 BBY it was situated within Imperial Space

NAME: Wrea
INTERESTING: Wrean: aquatic; hosted a comm tower/ Republic outpost during CW; notoriously difficult to reach because of Smuggler's Run asteroid belt nearby; for this reason, Saw Gerrera established a Partisan base here during reign of Empire; inhabited; Wreans offered medical assistance when Kueller's explosive droids decimated the inhabitants of the Smuggler's Run

NAME: Eufornis Minor
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Servants of the Empire: Rebel in the Ranks/
INTERESTING: sometimes confused with Eufornis Major (prestigious ecumenopolis in Core Worlds) because people sometimes referred to that world simply as Eufornis

NAME: Kich
INTERESTING: hot climate

NAME: Rannon
INTERESTING: settled centuries before reign of NR; inhabited by population of 10 M Humans and Rodians (governed settlements via cooperative council); after Endor c. 4 ABY, Danaan Kerr (Dark Jedi) took up residence in Valley of Ternaax; by 7 ABY, Kerr sensed that Palpatine had returned; the valley began to be corrupted by the dark side as Kerr terrorized and committed atrocities against the populace

NAME: Shinbone
INTERESTING: hardscrabble mining world; hit by Harden plague; homeworld of Beilert Valance (Stormtrooper turned bounty hunter)

NAME: Stoga
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, canyons, craggy rock formations, rock arches
INTERESTING: overlooked by governments due to remoteness; haven for smugglers, outlaws and mercs; home to 6 Rebel cells loyal to Garm Bel Iblis, under leadership of Karn and Lhira; cells were compromised after BoShek befriended Rasha Bex here, believing her an ally (actually an Imperial spy); BoShek was arrested; BoShek said it was "about as far out on the Rim as you can get without falling off the map"

NAME: Nimba Five
grid square/on same hyperroute as Beta Rhama
INTERESTING: had some sort of time warp between a tropical era and a frozen tundra era; homeworld of grumph (8m spiny lizards that laid purple eggs); on same hyperroute as Beta Rhama

NAME: The Quintarad system
INTERESTING: unusual system consisting of five stars orbiting each other; considered an oddity; astrophysicists were convinced that the Quintarad was artificial by nature; widely believed that system was constructed by Celestials; several probes were sent into system, but none survived the journey

NAME: Vengler
INTERESTING: discovered by Imperial scouts a few years before 7 ABY; principal interest of the planet was Varno Market (about 1 square km), sited within its very primitive spaceport; inhabitants were mostly subsistence farmers; also home of Scitrok Warriors; after trading a dozen Holoreels for some food, a scout was given a medallion that turned out to be the Eye of Koda (map to Koda's World)

NAME: NCW-781
INTERESTING: unexplored planet; Kala Kevv (Sullustan male Rebel operative) shot down here and crash-landed with a vital data plaque; Empire and Alliance both dispatched forces to locate him; Rebel SpecForce troopers arrived aboard Bravado (light freighter) , descended to surface through a canyon on combat paragliders for stealth, recovered Kevv and the plaque, and were extracted aboard their ship

NAME: Koda Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: surrounding space mostly populated by planets with poor farming communities; many farmhands visited for excitement; smugglers also kept it busy despite its insignificance; fugitives Mammon Hoole, Tash Arranda, Zak Arranda used it as a temporary hideout 9 mo. after Yavin; station poorly maintained with trash lining hallways at that time; Nagai raiders attacked in 4 ABY

NAME: Samovar
NOTES: actually in Western Reaches?
INTERESTING: legacy planet (protected from exploitation or environmental damage); the Empire hired Ranos Yalli and Has Obitt to transport old Seperatist weapons here so the Empire could "discover" them and thus remove the world's Legacy status, opening it to heavy doonium and dolovite mining -- crucial materials for the development of the Death Star project

NAME: Coveway
INTERESTING: harsh; homeworld of Jak Bremen (constable of his colony-village); hidden Imperial garrison whose commander decided to achieve his assignment by eliminating the locals; Bremen tracked the killers to the garrison and helped a recently arrived Rebel strike team to neutralize the Imperial base; Bremen left the planet with the Rebels

NAME: Kovor
INTERESTING: battle occurred here during Galactic War between reconstituted Sith Empire and Republic (who won) thanks to intervention of Coruscant Aegis squadron

NAME: Hospital
INTERESTING: XQ2 Platform in deep space; short hyperspace jump from Brint-wo colony; many injured Rebels taken here after Hoth for treatment but an Imperial Star Destroyer assaulted the platform with TIE Bombers; Ace and Eamon Azzameen held off the TIEs long enough for at least 66% of the Rebel personnel to escape; Tomaas and Galin Azzameen presumed killed in battle; Hospital seized by Imperials

NAME: Brint-wo
INTERESTING: ringed planet presumably friendly to Rebels (Rebel Pilot Olin Garn stationed there in 3 ABY, when he rendezvoused with Azzameen family); system served as getaway point for Emon and Ace Azzameen after fleeing an Imperial ambush on Hospital

NAME: Brint-wo Colony
INTERESTING: civilian Golan Space Colony 3 in orbit around Brint-wo; Azzameen family rendezvoused with Rebel Pilot Olin Garn here before traveling to Hospital

NAME: Kobal's World
INTERESTING: atrocities committed by Empire here, including slaughter of women, children by stormtroopers, one of whom accompanied Vader to Cheelit where Clat the Shamer used his memories to induce him to commit suicide

NAME: Lipsec system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: explored between 1000 and 25 BBY; Republic's Nineteenth Sector Army charged with defense of system's vicinity against CIS; populaion around 25 ABY about 1 to 10 M

NAME: Lipsec system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: explored between 1000 and 25 BBY; Republic's Nineteenth Sector Army charged with defense of system's vicinity against CIS; populaion around 25 ABY about 1 to 10 M

NAME: Ostor
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren deserts, deep canyons, red soil, wind-sculpted rock formations
INTERESTING: orbited yellow star; in aftermath of CW, Seperatist holdout moved onto planet, hoping to avoid Empire; Empire discovered presence by 17 BBY and sent forces in for SHrouded Offensive (military operation); but Vader made at least 3 mistakes, and operation proved to be one of the most disastrous for the Empire

NAME: Virgillia 7
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: tiny colony world; hotbed of Virgillian Free Alignment resistance against Imperial-aligned Aristocracy since beginning of Virgillian Civil War, led by parents of Tessa Manchisco; Imperial forces raided Manchisco home, killed Tessa's parents; site of a mission early in CW

NAME: Sump
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: humid, impoverished; area was considered well-explored by 1000 BBY; native Nuknogs sold planet to consortium of mining corporations in exchange for food, eployment, modest accomodations; Nuknogs worked without pay in mines, processing factories; eventually, planet's ecosystem was poisoned; two Jedi brought attention to their plight and Senate ordered corps to terminate operations, repay Nuknogs

NAME: Niran
INTERESTING: homeworld of Viran Qol (human male); Qol had just graduated a civil engineering program in 3 ABY when the Empire invaded; Qol took up with the Niran Resistance and eventually joined Rebels

NAME: Usean II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: equatorial valleys with tall, woody grass stalks
INTERESTING: home of lrashtash (herbivores with large bluffing incisors to scare off predators

NAME: Greyman's Planet
INTERESTING: Imperial industrial world; location of Da'Harrin Spaceport; location of Rebel base during GCW

NAME: Remitik
INTERESTING: Republic repair yard near here

NAME: Rebel Repair Yard
INTERESTING: near Remitik; Empire destroyed repair yard here in preparation for Battle of Hoth; afterwards, Empire ambushed Rebel craft retreating from Hoth

NAME: Imperial Munitions Depot
INTERESTING: depot commanded by Colonel Gralm; attacked by NR during GCW; located in grid oh-four-two (unclear if coords are for depot or system)

NAME: Oko E
INTERESTING: known for its "wild-water" rafting on molten sulfur rivers

NAME: Slotern
INTERESTING: battle fought between Empire, resistance group here sometime between 19 BBY - 1 BBY

NAME: Karinda
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: red-brown dust, valleys, small seas, lakes
INTERESTING: site of an Imperial garrison as well as Rebel base called Karinda Outpost; planet was mostly dry

NAME: Cuthbern
INTERESTING: known for factories producing high-quality weapons; annexed by Empire; population enslaved; later abandoned by Empire after Rebel attack

NAME: Wazta
INTERESTING: site of Wazta Emergence (part of Great Hyperspace Disaster) during High Republic era; two Hassarians injured and transported to Starlight Beacon Station for medical care; Imperial Army infantry units defected to Rebels around 0 ABY here

NAME: Lutrillia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Port Jerrell
INTERESTING: during height of Empire, known to be a smuggler's haven

NAME: Tancon
INTERESTING: group of Rebels left an Alliance base here in 0 ABY aboard Arion Star, headed for Greyman's Planet

NAME: Pulassas Minor
INTERESTING: Nozzo Naytaan joined Rebels after his TIE squadron was ordered to bombard civilian targets here

NAME: Varlinaar
INTERESTING: Rorworr (Wookiee Rebel Agent) once smuggled team of Rebels into Imperial base here under pretense of bringing Imperials rare foods

NAME: Tegrat
INTERESTING: many inhabitants fled to Tatooine shortly before an Imperial invasion meant to flush out Rebels

NAME: Keskin
INTERESTING: site of battle between Rebellion and Empire during GCW; population 1 - 10 M c. 25 ABY

NAME: Merokia
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: inhabited during NR era; homeworld of Karr Nuq Sin (force-sensitive human)

NAME: Abridon
INTERESTING: pleasant mountainous world where Luke was captured by the Empire and then freed when Brenn Tantor (Imperial General) defected to Rebellion

NAME: Plavonia system
INTERESTING: home of Plavonian starfish (edible aquatic creature)

NAME: Tureen VI
INTERESTING: home of Soup People (group known for making high-quality soup)

NAME: Tureen VII
INTERESTING: after Yavin, people of Tureen VII started aiding Rebels in secret, but Empire learned of their alliance sympathies and blockaded the planet; [presumed to belong to same system as Tureen VI]

NAME: Banvhar Station
INTERESTING: asteroid HQ of Banvhar Combine asteroid miners; due to proximity to Trade Federation spaceways, Combine's minerals stolen by CIS during CW; some residents used as target practice by Grievous's droid army; remaining miners helped Jedi deserters to locate Grievous, sneak into enemy territory and try to assassinate him

NAME: R'terleD'er
INTERESTING: known as hunter's paradise

NAME: Taul
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: swamps, acidic deserts, rocky hills, toxic atmo
INTERESTING: a Rebel Alliance trading post and severe conditions training base was established here; Empire largely ignored Taul until one of the probe droids seeking the base at Hoth discovered the Taul base; inhabited by dangerous steel-eating spice spiders; during First Order Cold War, the Sterdic Star (Sphyrna-class Hammerhead corvette belonging to Resistance) crashed here; C-3PO and several other droids had to fight off spiders, but only C-3PO survived

NAME: Tellanada system
INTERESTING: home of Tellanadan moonflower plant

NAME: Doaskin
INTERESTING: primary base for TaggeCo operations

NAME: Javin
INTERESTING: capital of Javin sector; once a propserous Mugaari colony, with Mugaari population second only to Mugaar; Mugaari control over trade in Greater Javin threatened Republic traders; several centuries before Yavin, Republic won a decisive conflict over Mugaari, leading to a mass departure of Mugaari from Javin, allowing Republic traders & others to take over; Mugaari still made up a third of population

NAME: Outpost D-34
INTERESTING: XQ1 Platform orbiting Javin; served as Imperial checkpoint; carried both TIEs and stormtrooper transports; nav buoys several kilometers from the station marked hyperspace exit points; later captured and plundered by Rebels before an Imperial frigate returned to recover the base

NAME: Aztubek
INTERESTING: wealthy, little-developed; originally one of 11 member worlds of Mugaari Space prior to Galactic Republic intervention, which reshaped region's power stucture; became home to many corporate complexes; few workers took up permanent residence; most workers commuted from Javin on weekly basis; considered to be in Wild Space when first discovered

NAME: Kumru
INTERESTING: thriving industrial world originally goveredn by Mugaari, who surrendered territorial holdings to Republic after they were decisively defeated by Republic several centuries before Yavin; to the chagrin of their more aggressive kin, the Mugaari who remained onworld coexisted well with the Humans, Lutrillians, and Nothoiins who moved in

NAME: High Chunah
PARENT: Outer Rim/Western Reaches, Mugaari Space//Javin/High Chunah
INTERESTING: once an outlying Mugaari Space colony world; became profitable speeder-manufacturing planet once Republic capitalized on region's economic potential; planet had an unusual green glow from space due to its rocks, which phosphoresced for up to 6 hours after sunset

NAME: Miser
INTERESTING: core of mostly iron and gententhium; most metal used to build Cloud City mined here; Ecclessis Figg sketched a plan for rolling mining center that could stay out of direct sunlight on Miser's dark side, but idea was never followed up; terrain was too rough for wheeled vehicles to move easily; location of secret Imperial base commanded by Admiral Grendreef, protected by ISD Desolator

NAME: Orin
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: black volcanic rock, lava rivers, volcanoes
INTERESTING: elliptical orbit took it through nearby Velser's Ring twice during its year; black surface rocked by frequent groundquakes; unbearably high surface temperature; atmosphere choked with thick soot, raining ash

NAME: Velser's Ring
INTERESTING: separated Miser and Orin from Bespin; named after leader of survey team that discovered the belt; Lando owned a cane with aeroxite (metal) tips mined here; remains of an unstable gas giant; composed of refractice frozen gases and liquids; appeared as a giant rainbow in space from certain angles; Ugnaughts sent to collect the frozen gases, which were used in the production of lasers, carbon-freeze units and tractor beam helix tubes used on Bespin

NAME: Bespin
INTERESTING: had a liquid rethin metal core known as the Rethin Sea; home to several floating cities and platforms, including Cloud City, Tibannopolis, the Ugnaught Surface, and several floating health spas and floating tibanna gas refineries such as BesGas Three

NAME: H'gaard
INTERESTING: 5km diameter moon, known as one of "The Twins"; one of Bespin's 2 largest moons

NAME: Drudonna
INTERESTING: 2.5km diameter moon, known as one of "The Twins"; one of Bespin's 2 largest moons; Shirmar Base, a staging area and processing center for Ugnaught expeditions into Velser's Ring, was located here

NAME: Vinza
INTERESTING: located in CIS space during CW

NAME: Gentes
INTERESTING: one of 3 habitable worlds in system; frequently raided by slavers; Ugnaughts: lived in primitive colonies; Brotherhood of Darkness operated Sith academy here c. 1002 BBY; Grievous captured it during CW, took slaves, herded many Ugnaughts into a building and bombarded it from orbit; sparsely populated after Endor, with most remaining Ugnaughts on Cloud City or elsewhere

NAME: Belsus
INTERESTING: location of Ugnaught Main Rendering Plant 908, where Flynn Kybo died trying to kill Grievous, who had crushed all resistance on Gentes; Grievous had attempted to establish a laboratory for study of the Force; underground cities devastated when moon's thermal core was destroyed by Kybo; rumors of lab's existence persisted through time of Iron Blockade

NAME: Anoat
INTERESTING: sector capital; years before Yavin, Empire gassed entire planet, making atmosphere toxic and poisonous; much of population fled; those who stayed and survived went insane, evolving over time into savage and feral creatures called "lurkers"; remained Anoat sector's largest concentration of Imperial forces; sometime after Crait, Resistance maintained camp here

NAME: Deyer
INTERESTING: one of 3 habitable planets in system; Empire established prisons, outposts here; prior to Iron Blockade, Data Seekers placed undercover agents within Empire's ranks, discovering truths about Deyer's prisons; world of oceans, raft-cities; settled a generation before CW; colonists created peaceful, anarchistic political system; brutally subjugated when they spoke out about Alderaan

NAME: Pujool
NOTES: listed as 6th orbital position; actually 7th

NAME: Zhanox
NOTES: add rocky spires

NAME: Hoth
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: glaciers, ice plains, mountains, oceans, canyons, ice caves, tundras

NAME: Tokmia
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, snow fields, flatlands, tundras, oceans

NAME: Shuxl system
INTERESTING: no planets or asteroids, just giant dust rings

NAME: Shuxl system
INTERESTING: no planets or asteroids, just giant dust rings

NAME: Oovri II
INTERESTING: site of starfigher battle during GCW

NAME: Drekker
INTERESTING: Imperial X7 Factory station owned by Drekker Industries; used for production of valuable crystals; came under attack by Meteor (Rebel Nebulon-B) and Z-95s; Inexorable (Victory-Class Star Destroyer) intervenedand saved station; station carried 2 Lambda-class shuttles (Fubarium and Tymtogo) to evacuate station if needed

NAME: Shusko Station
INTERESTING: mining operation in Gam Tim'nisi belt; Kelko (heir to warring Rodian clans) inherited the station and turned it into one of the most profitable small mining operations in the Outer Rim

NAME: Tallis Outpost
INTERESTING: Galactic Republic listening post in Gam Tim'nisi belt during CW; assaulted by Grievous c. 21 BBY

NAME: Tungra
INTERESTING: primary planet of system; namesake of sector

NAME: Pellastrallas
INTERESTING: populated by wild native arquets (vicious mountain predators), uthori breix, Ixzinian rock rams

NAME: Upell system
INTERESTING: colonized by Ithorians after Yuuzhan Vong devastation of Ithor

NAME: Uthor system
INTERESTING: home to Uthori breix (creature)

NAME: Velga
NOTES: WP says M-18

NAME: Juvex
NOTES: Senex-Juvex Loop not listed

NAME: Usnia
NOTES: One of the routes through the Tangles: "The Tangleway"?

NAME: Yetoom Na Uun
INTERESTING: shadowport

NAME: Dolla
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: WP says Mid Rim and Senex-Juvex under Canon
INTERESTING: part of Republic during CW; later served as major staging area for Imperial Navy during GCW; at some point Imperial Governor Jedselk of Sellasas was promoted to governorship of Dolla; c. 25 ABY population numbered between 1 - 10 M

NAME: Goibniu Platform
INTERESTING: Imperial XQ2 platform serving as a supply depot; carried TIE/LNs for defense; came under Rebel attack by a strike force of Z-95s and Y-wings, which tried to disable the platform defenses before rebel Heavy Lifters arrived to pick up containers of bacta

NAME: Golh
INTERESTING: aquatic planet owned by Hydrospeare Corporation, which used Golh as a test site for aquatic projects such as weapons or military vehicles; a group of Sedrian Rebel operatived managed to reach Golh and ambush a test team. Dr. Sere Lure escaped and recommended any other aquatic world as a site for testing

NAME: Obran Cluster
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance hid cargo containers full of warheads here; Imperials learned of the site and placed a minefield here, intending to ambush the Rebels and capture the warheads; Rebels learned of the ambush and sent A-wings to remove the mines and hold off Imperial forces long enough for Heavy Lifters to pick up the containers

NAME: Sunaj IV
INTERESTING: Relentless (Imperial I-class Star Destroyer) patrolled area around Sunaj IV prior to Hoth; the Juvaini (Nebulon-B) was destroyed here while undergoing servicing near Sunaj IV

NAME: Melasaton
INTERESTING: low-tech planet devastated by a great plague; saved when Arbor Industries developed an antidote (but it was Arbor that had secretly unleashed plague in the first place)

NAME: Hiffis
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance raided a lightly guarded Imperial warehouse and stole a large number of Ultra-Light Assault Vehicles here

NAME: Farfeld II
INTERESTING: site of Imperial System Patrol Squadron abse guarded by Olrac Etnom and Cutlass (CR90s) until it was destroyed by B-wings from Red Squadron

NAME: Sellasas
INTERESTING: after Yavin there was an Imperial and civilian presence; under administration of Governor Jedselk; planet and its Imperial garrison underwent siege by Rebel strike force after Yavin; Tyionsis Cex (Srrors'tik bounty hunter serving Empire) and Amara Jedselk (governor's daughter) fought in the siege

NAME: Karfeddion
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: The Noopiths
INTERESTING: possibly stellar cluster; possibly some Z-axis info in "Children of the Jedi"

NAME: Belsavis
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Canon says Mid Rim
INTERESTING: became prison colony in Rakata Empire; entered ice age c. 5000 BBY; inhabitants dwelt in 3 volcanic jungle rifts; Republic used prison here to house dangerous Sith Lords, war criminals during the Great Galactic War; in 88 BBY community called Plett's Well (shortened to Plawal) settled; Republic colonization followed in 20 BBY; many plants and animals imported from Ithor; Jedi younglings hid here in 19 BBY

NAME: Belsavis Star Fortress
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of many (if not hundreds) deployed by Emperor Arcann of the Eternal Empire to watch for uprisings on subjugated worlds; later destroyed by Theron Shan and Commander of the Anti-Zakuul Alliance

NAME: Ossel II
INTERESTING: main export was syp wood; traders trying to purchase syp wood from Ossans were often required to take Ossans on as part of crew; many Ossans ended up slaves on Karfeddion

NAME: Tibrin
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Sibilaar system
INTERESTING: Sibilaari homeworld formerly located in this system; Sibilaari: ~3m long, black, had resistant flesh, no obvious mouth, three lower limbs and two upper appendages, each of which ended with four fully opposable digits and had a line of 6 independent eyes in a line between them, with ability to metabolize sound, light or the Force; planet was destroyed but Sibilaari were able to hibernate in shielded shelters

NAME: Garnib
INTERESTING: population: 100 M; subjugated by Empire; many Balinaka (ice sculptors considered by some to be galaxy's most artistic beings) exported as slaves to breeding farms on Karfeddion; HQ of Galactic Crystal Creations (exported Garnib crystals); adopted homeworld of Vernol species (emigrated when their homeworld's orbit shifted, became uninhabitable)

NAME: Mastala
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance named a ship after this world

NAME: Greeb-Streebling Cluster
INTERESTING: possibly some Z-axis info in "Children of the Jedi"

NAME: Brodogon Consortium Headquarters
INTERESTING: origin point of Brodogon Consortium (purchased slaves from Krayn)

NAME: Jankok
NOTES: some details from Srrors'tok page could be added to Jankok page
INTERESTING: Srrors'tok: fur-covered, anthropomorphic felinoids with mostly non-technological society of hunters with strong concepts of honor and life debts; rainforest world with few resources of interest; rarely visited; no spaceport; occasionally visited by some scouts and merchants who sometimes tried to deal with natives

NAME: Drong II
INTERESTING: home to Llwelkyn (predator)

NAME: Kelrodo-Ai
INTERESTING: known for its gelatin mines and water sculptures; in 12 ABY its Baron Administrator was Drom Guldi

NAME: Bortras
INTERESTING: homeworld of Jorus C'baoth; capital: Reithcas

NAME: Belloria
INTERESTING: origin point of Bellorian ale

NAME: Agomar
INTERESTING: during CW Battle of Agomar, Republic regained control of world; home to Whaladons during CW

NAME: Pyolli system
INTERESTING: origin point of Pyollian cake (dessert)

NAME: Uvena Prime
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forested continents, oceans, caves, rock formations
INTERESTING: most Shistavanens remained on homeworld, though some left for wider galaxy; warm climate; Empire controlled planet, which outraged native Shistavanens, though it took little interest in planet outside basic maintenance

NAME: Uvena II
INTERESTING: Shistavanens colonized or otherwise laid claim to every planet and object in the system to ensure they remained in control; established outposts on large asteroids, maintained probe droid patrols

NAME: Uvena III
INTERESTING: Shistavanen colony planet; expats included Mal Biron, Caet Shrovl, Riv Shiel

NAME: Delmaas
INTERESTING: origin point of Delmaasi pirates

NAME: Phelarion
INTERESTING: homeworld of wealthy Motti family (wealthy citizens in the megonite moss mining business, established in centuries prior to 60 BBY using slave labor), including Lady Thalassa Tarkin, Wilhuff's wife, who erected a black obelisk in tribute to him, named the main starport Port Tarkin, and ran mining operations for the Empire, but mines were sabotaged by Leia after her ship was shot down here

NAME: Spuma
INTERESTING: at some point before Yavin, 1st Tapani Assault Battlegroup claimed an Imperial victory in the Rout of Spuma, which Cassio Tagge (Imperial High General) later commemmorated in Imperial Handbook; NR Intelligence Service discovered increased trooper recruitment by warlord Harrsk's fleet c. 8 years after Endor

NAME: Hockaleg (Patriim)
INTERESTING: Canon: considered strategically insignificant, yet location of major deployment of Imperial forces, subject to comm blackouts and source of several encrypted communiques referring to Death Star project; Cassian Andor sent to investigate reports of Empire transporting kyber crystals here; Legends: construction site of Tarkin superweapon; residents of spaceport town worshiped Holy Jaf (deity)

NAME: Tarkin
INTERESTING: stripped-down Death Star cannon sabotaged by Luke, Leia, Chewbacca, R2 and C-3PO

NAME: Moshaw Dark Star
INTERESTING: Dark Star Dellions (swoop gang) originated in space neighboring black hole

NAME: Lucrusia
INTERESTING: origin point of Lucrusian fengrills (type of creature that could get extremely drunk)

NAME: Luptoom
INTERESTING: home of Luptoomians (humans), known for unsusual fashion

NAME: Eriadu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Muntiadu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Jaroona
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: had similar surface to that of system's third planet, Erinar

NAME: Erinar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: had similar surface to that of system's second planet, Jaroona

NAME: Eriadu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
NOTES: Eriadu Way / Bypass, not Nothoiin Corridor?
INTERESTING: originally located on Eriadu Bypass until Hydian Way was remapped to run through Eriadu rather than Seswenna to reflect economic realities; important launch point for Moddell sector-bound ships, such as colony ship Free Enterprise in 130 BBY; homeworld of Wilhuff Tarkin; cheif industry revolved around lommite ore

NAME: Tarastra
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Kelliadu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Eczar
INTERESTING: Vacander (Filar-Nitzan infiltrator) maintained a bank account here by 2 ABY

NAME: Boden
INTERESTING: some time before 0 ABY, Leger DeMain once helped Airen Cracken escape capture during an Imperial occupation of the planet

NAME: Dorvalla
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, forests, deserts, dust/mud, thick lommite clouds
INTERESTING: near space stations Rimma 13 and Rimma 18; controlled by Dorvalla Mining; in 33 BBY, site of battle between Nebula Front and Trade Federation, who took the world; originally temperate but mining operations covered it in lommite dust, which turned to thick mud in rainy season

NAME: Dorvalla IV
INTERESTING: controlled by Dorvalla Mining; was the planet beyond their main base (Dorvalla); habitable, unknown if settled; in 34 ABY, Arwen Cohl's crew wanted to land here, but Cohl knew there were ships under way to Dorvalla and knew a single shuttle would attract much attention

NAME: Riome
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ice, seas, occasional patches of grass, small magma-heated creeks
INTERESTING: in 33 BBY, Toom clan set up hideout here after sabotaging Lommite Limited and InterGalactic Ore's freighters; Maul anonymously led Patch Bruit and other Lommite workers here where they gunned down every Toom member, but Maul subsequently took down the remaining combatants; home to thin, ribbon-like sea snakes

NAME: Rimma 13
NOTES: mentioned as space station in Dorvalla system WP page; called a planet in Rimma 13 page
INTERESTING: planet that anchored Rimma Trade Route; During GCW, Imperial Governor was Alyk Krysusten

NAME: Swarquen
INTERESTING: homeworld of Mol Hedron (human Imperial spy)

NAME: Rimma 18
NOTES: mentioned as space station in Dorvalla system WP page; called a planet in Rimma 18 page
INTERESTING: planet that anchored Rimma Trade Route

NAME: Vendrak V
INTERESTING: during GCW Rebel forces were operating on Vendrak V; Imperial intelligence planted false information leading the Alliance to believe a large hangar bay in the starport contained a batch of potentially useful weaponry to draw them into a trap; Rebel "Victor" and "Bravo" squads were ambushed by two squads of stormtroopers, who attempted to prevent their escape

NAME: Averam
INTERESTING: one of few planets to openly sympathize with small groups of Rebel supporters during early GCW;

NAME: Chelleya
INTERESTING: in 4 ABY, Nagai raiders' path of conquest was redirected away from Eriadu by a squadron of Eriadu Authority TIE Interceptors led by Shea Hublin (Imperial pilot)

NAME: Orryxia system
INTERESTING: home to orycats (small pack predators); origin point of Orryxian Catsblood (beverage); at some point before his death in 4 ABY, Wilek Nereus (Bakura's Imperial governor) visited the Orryxia system to collect orycat teeth for his collection, but the conditions of the orycats' native woodlands were too challenging for him to carry out a complete ecological survey of their habitat

NAME: Brintooin
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: plains, deserts, marshes, scrub, scattered woods, other flatlands
INTERESTING: ideal terrain for armored combat; served as baseworld for Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit; after Endor, as Empire splintered, Zel Johans (Colonel in command) withdrew the Hammers and affiliated forces to Brintooin, not wanting to participate in fighting between Imperial warlords, and became increasingly isolated due to lack of transportation for combat vehicles

NAME: Parwa
INTERESTING: Canon: planet's seasons were several centuries long; Parwans: three-eyed, mushroom-shaped head, tentacles instead of legs, could fill themselves with gas to "float", some hibernated along with changing seasons even if they were not on Parwa; homeworld of Parwan bounty hunter Derrown

NAME: Mirnic system
INTERESTING: shared name with with Mirnic University

NAME: Seswenna
INTERESTING: Canon: homeworld of Conan Antonio Motti; Legends: by 3699, planet lay on future Hydian Way; by 1004 BBY the super-hyperroute it had shifted to pass through Eriadu instead; eventually, the sector capital was shifted from Seswenna to Eriadu as well; temporarily housed Death Star project and Imperial Military Shipyards as well

NAME: Virmeude
INTERESTING: HQ of Issham Mining Corporation (actually cover for a Rebel base)

NAME: Anchoron
INTERESTING: human Anchoroni were known for flowery speech and genteel decorum; former Senator Garm Bel Iblis was scheduled to give a talk against New Order at Treitamma Political Center before 2 BBY; Armand Isard had a bomb planted but Bel Iblis survived when he stepped out to rendezvous with an agent about Death Star plans, but his family died in the explosion; Bel Iblis widely presumed dead

NAME: Dorenia
INTERESTING: origin point of Dorenian Beshniquel (musical instrument also known as the Fizzz

NAME: etrago
INTERESTING: known for its flowers; within CIS space during CW; Han visted once; many Ithorian refugees from the YV devastation of Ithor settled here

NAME: Xagobah
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: canyons, fungal forests, swamps, mountains, jungles, deserts
INTERESTING: orbited a blue sun; appeared to be a cloud-covered world shrouded in purple mists due to massive amount of spores, pollen given off by trees, fungi, which offworlders usually needed an antidote for before exposure; relatively peaceful before CIS occupied world; afterward Xamsters used as laborers; Republic hired some to fight droid armies; liberated by Republic in 20 BBY

NAME: H'nemthe
INTERESTING: rapidly fluctuating climate; during trine (season), all three moons gave off light; home of M'iiyoom, a carnivorous flower that bloomed during trine; remained unaligned throughout much of history; H'nemthe: females gutted males with razor-sharp tongues after mating (twenty females for every male), virgin females often not allowed to leave world, and only allowed to eat fruits and vegetables

NAME: Colu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: expanded enough to destroy Clak'dor I in 8000 BBY

NAME: Clak'dor I
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: destroyed by expansion of its star Colu in 8000 BBY

NAME: Clak'dor II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: became system's innermost world after Clak'dor I was consumed by its star Colu in 8000 BBY

NAME: Clak'dor III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Clak'dor IV
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: Bith colony world; most Y'bith ("Ghost Bith") left Clak'dor VII and resettled here in the city of New Nozho

NAME: Clak'dor V
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: former prison colony several decades prior to 3630 BBY, when religious persecution was high in the early days of Bith spaceflight; in 3630 BBY the colony's ruins were rediscovered; the Bith forbade any outsider to study them

NAME: Clak'dor VI
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: possibly the remains of a destroyed planet

NAME: Clak'dor VII (Bith A)
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: domed cities, mountains, poisoned jungles & swamps
INTERESTING: small planet; longtime member of Republic; Bith built great cities in mountains and jungles; around 300 BBY capital city of Weogar and domed Nozho fought over a stardrive patent; chemical, biological warfare wiped out Nozho and destroyed planet's ecosystems; surviving Bith declared themselves pacifists and relocated to domed cities, but burrowed underground to alleviate cramped conditions

NAME: Triton
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Triton
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: small, almost lifeless world; often used to describe a dead thing, due to the ban on stimulants of any kind; also known as checkpoint at the chokepoint of several hyperroutes; native Tritonites were insectoids who developed a faith around the teachings of the mysterious Gactimus; some spacers were forced to join the cult; Tritonite followers often handed out tracts in spaceports everywhere

NAME: Gactimus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: several religious retreats established here by insectoid Tritonites; all spacers stopping here were required to tithe away some possessions to Gactimus (religious figure) before leaving

NAME: Triton Besh
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: inhabited by Tritonite (insectoid) worshipers of Gactimus (religious figure)

NAME: Gactimus' Halo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: situated beyond Triton

NAME: Mynock 7 Station
INTERESTING: Bnugor (male Gamorrean) briefly lost Snowball (pet snuzzleguff) here but recovered it later at the Farrimmer Cafe, which was owned by H'nib Statermast (male Filvian) and his partner Grosteek (Vaathkree)

NAME: Zhotta 3
INTERESTING: Rebels sent Han & Chewie here to invite the planet's leaders to a congress to determine the fate of the galaxy

NAME: Innton II
INTERESTING: sparsely populated world near the Triton system; home to the Defiant Core (unfinished Seperatist base built from parts salvaged from a Recusant-class light Destroyer, Nova Defiant, that crashed here; later Rebels investigated rumors of its existence and repurposed it as Rebel base; under command tof Romar Kek (human General); housed a squadron of Y-wings

NAME: Bofa II
INTERESTING: housed an Imperial Cargo Transfer Area during GCW; distribution site of Imperial surveillance droids; Libom (Imperial BBF-1 bulk freighter) captured here

NAME: Garrthinius
INTERESTING: ruled by Empire by time of Endor; became site of much Rebel activity; Alliance tried to establish a cell network there to overthrow Imperial leaders

NAME: Black Stall Station
INTERESTING: Cad Bane's hideout during CW, a small space station in an asteroid field; after Bane was forced to bring Obi-Wan and Mace Windu here, he escaped and set the station to self-destruct, destroying it; hyperspace coords were 673117-7rb71

NAME: Omwat
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: in 4000 BBY, Omwati established small but successful colony on Coruscant; homeworld forgotten until rediscovery in 25 BBY by Wilhuff Tarkin; Omwati built honeycombed cities, devoted to advancing sciences, arts; natural resources used sparingly; during CW, located in CIS space; site of battle in 20 BBY; between 0 and 4 ABY, Omwati developed hyperdrive, restablishing contact with Coruscant kin

NAME: Cerroban
INTERESTING: following Battle of Yavin, this airless, waterless rocky world was scouted by the Rebel Alliance as a possible base; pounded by asteroids regularly

NAME: Luxiar 7
INTERESTING: R'Ytha Myr (female) dated a person called "Ace", possibly Ace Azzameen

NAME: Sharlissia system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: situated in space first explored 3000 - 1000 BBY, when it fell within Sith Brotherhood of Darkness territory; during CW, located in CIS space but Republic's Fifteenth Army was tasked with defending vicinity; situated within Imperial borders by 17 BBY; population 100 M - 500 M by 25 ABY

NAME: Nellac Kram
NOTES: "Nellac Kram was planet..."
INTERESTING: Nartissteu (NR freighter) based out of here; population 100 M - 500 M by 25 ABY

NAME: Gonda
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/

NAME: Speco
INTERESTING: ruled by unnamed Imperial governor; rumored that Miaxi (Falleen mistress) actually had control by manipulating him with her charms

NAME: Destreg II
INTERESTING: small brown-and-blue planet with some cloud cover; significant civilian traffic; K'Armyn Viraxo set a trap for Ace and Emon Azzameen here, luring them by supposedly being on his yacht, the Highroller (SoroSuub Luxury Yacht 3000); although he wasn't aboard, the brothers managed to evade Imperial patrols and mercenaries to destroy the yacht, and even take the ship's wheel as a trophy

NAME: Destreg Spaceport
INTERESTING: 2,100m; Golan 2 space station that catered to both transport and passenger services, though latter were emphasized due to station's popular resorts; even during GCW, Sea Sprite 1 (passenger liner) was bringing tourists here

NAME: Yarnil
INTERESTING: homeworld to farmers, merchants

NAME: Reyniu
in Mayagil sector on Sanrafsix Corridor between Omwat and Kabal
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: arid plains, canyons, inland seas, oceans
INTERESTING: 8 major continents divided by thin bands of open ocean; canyon systems connected chains of inland seas dotting continents; home to moderately developed alien life and vegetation; breathing mask required after 15 minutes; popular with tourists from Eriadu and Seswenna sector prior to CW; tourism cut off after it became part of CIS; Cliffview resort later became Rebel Intelligence base

NAME: Dunari's Rest
INTERESTING: casino/resort/trading facility; popular with legitimate traders, smugglers, bounty hunters; crew 1,250, could accomodate up to 15,000 guests; had shields and guarded by Bouncer (IPV/1 system patrol craft)

NAME: Narth
INTERESTING: evacuated by Imperials after Endor along with Narth (nearby planet); while this was happening, ISD Grisnal was crippled by internal explosions and had to be scuttled; NR recovered Imperial Order of Battle from the wreckage

NAME: Daxam IV
INTERESTING: in binary star system (at its edge); many pilots from Pamarthe were recruited to work here; despite its self-reliance and limited off-planet commerce, it joined the NR by 28 ABY, and was aligned with the Centrists; it was home to the Amaxines during this time

NAME: Vedis IV
INTERESTING: around 3 ABY, Toob Ancher (smuggler) left Soco-Jarel Spaceport on Socorro in the Glory (YT-1300) to travel here; Lu Esi (smuggler) died here when he crashed his freighter while being chased by sector authorities

NAME: Ihopek
INTERESTING: evacuated by Imperials after Endor along with Narth (nearby planet); while this was happening, ISD Grisnal was crippled by internal explosions and had to be scuttled; NR recovered Imperial Order of Battle from the wreckage

NAME: Kabal
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: suffered food riots after Trade Federation abandoned the Trade Corridor, supposedly in protest of heavy Republic taxation but actually to try to encourage planet to secede; Dooku airdropped food to appear the hero; planet seceded just before CW; neutral during GCW; hosted Conference of Uncommitted Worlds just afer Yavin, which Leia attended, meeting with Silver Fyre

NAME: Nezni system
INTERESTING: incident between the Hurrim (pirate group) and Rebel Alliance happened here after the Hurrim decided to attack the Imperial citizens the two forces were scavenging from; Y-wings from Green Squadron sent by the MC80 Liberty destroyed the Hurrim Preybird frighters and regained control of the situation

NAME: Corvalis
INTERESTING: an incident between the Hurrim (pirate group) and Rebel Alliance forces happened near the Golan Space Colony 1 Corvalis; the combined forces were supposed to capture cargo from a civilian convoy and leave the ships intact, but after the Hurrim began firing on the citizens who had surrendered, the Rebels had to destroy the Hurrim fighters

NAME: Henlon Station
INTERESTING: during an incident between the Hurrim (pirate group) and Rebel Alliance forces, the station sent fighters to try to stop the Rebels from making off with cargo

NAME: Tolig IV
INTERESTING: site of Imperial orbital scrapyard where material owned by the Azzameen family (including the datacore from their home base space station) was scrapped after Azzameen Station was seized

NAME: Junkyard Control
INTERESTING: Ace and Emon Azzameen traveled to this Imperial junkyard station in the Otana and the Andrasta to search for communications log data about who had betrayed their family to the Empire; they retrieved the datacore from their home base space station

NAME: Pamarthe
INTERESTING: Pamarthens known for excellent piloting, courage, and gusto; Pamarthen pilots often recruited by neighboring worlds for racing or military service; in early days of Galactic Civil War many flocked to join the Imperial Navy, but later hundreds defected to the Rebels after Alderaan; many of its islands were connected by stone, wood or rope bridges

NAME: Besn
INTERESTING: Imperial world known for its perfection of artistic participlays

NAME: Chagaria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Chagarian ale

NAME: Engebo V
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: grasslands, scrublands, oceans, nerf ranches, mines
INTERESTING: constant winds; colonized by Outer Rim Oreworks Company, who mined most of planet's mineral resources and later abandoned the world; later the planet was infested with skekfish (burrowing predators which reproduced rapidly), which wiped out Engebo V's population

NAME: Hurrim Base
NOTES: No Hurrim system page
INTERESTING: XQ1 Platform in an asteroid field; served as heavily defended HQ for Hurrim; just prior to Endor, Hurrim were removed from Dunari's trading Empire; Hurrim imprisoned a number of Dunari's staff here; Hurrim also captured Rebel cargo vessels, including 6 Mobquet transports; later located by Rebel and Dunari intelligence, leading to a Rebel strike during which hostages were rescued, Hurrim leaders were captured and the station destroyed

NAME: Syboona
INTERESTING: Syboona: blue-skinned with thin physiques and long curved muzzles, red eyes and upright ears

NAME: Entooine
INTERESTING: system originally named N-2 by explorers; abandoned as unpromising; eventually Entooine (moon of a gas giant) was colonized; tidally locked to gas giant; had extreme electromagnetic field; relatively close to an Imperial shipping lane; home to lichen, shrubs, quohr (carnivores), Askhew: tribal, blue banthas: sapient, force-sensitive

NAME: Rior
INTERESTING: peaceful world; practically crime-free; Riorians: insect-like with large, red eyes and sensitive hearing, preferring calm reasoning to settle disputes; Stalnus was a murderous exception; additionally, at least one Riorian was a member of the Karazak Slavers Cooperative

NAME: Viraxo 54
INTERESTING: busy storage station and cargo transfer port operated by Viraxo Shipping and frequented by many cargo vessels; as payback for a cargo of spice planted to frame the Azzameens, Antan schemed to plant the spice at this VIraxo facility where it would be discovered by the Empire, but the plan mostly failed

NAME: Garis
INTERESTING: ruled by the Regent of Garis, who allied with Grievous during CW, despite supposedly being Republic-allied

NAME: Camen Spaceport
INTERESTING: civilian space station; two members of Dunari's coalition escaped from Hurrim in shuttle Merte under heavy pursuit by Preybird fighters - ?

NAME: Saruwen Station
INTERESTING: XQ2 platform orbiting a ringed yellow gas giant, which in turn orbited a distant purple sun; a distant nebula was visible from the station; Ace, Emon and Aeron Azzameen provided cover for Tomaas and Galin as they piloted the Vasudra twice on their way to and from an ambush involving a shipment of Bacta for the Rebel Alliance; this turned out to be a ruse by the Loose Cannon pirates

NAME: Z'trop
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: tropical; volcanic islands, wide beaches, clear waters, oceans
INTERESTING: popular destination for romantic holidays; trileaf trees grew on volcanic bluffs; home of septapus (vegetarian, seven-tentacled creatures with five glowing eyes which fed on seaweed); Firmus Kett's family had a retreat here; in 5 ABY Han and Chewbacca flew the Falcon here for a vacation along with Leia, Luke, Ken Palpatine and their droids; vacation was cut short upon finding an Imperial CAV

NAME: Alis Point
INTERESTING: site of Rebel base evacuated shortly after Yavin; Zev Senesca singlehandedly held off 3 TIE/LNs while base's unarmed transport fled to hyperspace, earning him a spot in newly-formed Rogue Squadron

NAME: Dravian Station
NOTES: There are notes on the WP page about travel times to nearby systems
INTERESTING: haven for smugglers because it was far from any inhabited systems; due to clientele, filled up with casinos, hotels, restaurants, shipping businesses such as Topatz Shipping, Jontz Freight, and Skypath Industries

NAME: Shadda
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: transitioned from red giant phase to white dwarf phase in 38 BBY, destroying its planets

NAME: Figili
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Shadda-Bi-Boran
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: sun-worshiping civilization; after eons of peace, beautiful world was ruined when its star faded, setting off groundquakes, weather changes; soon the planet froze, venting its atmosphere to space; wealthy galactic citizens wore armbands of handcrafted Shadda silk to raise awareness; Padme attempted to assist in evacuation but its people were unable to adapt to life elsewhere and died out

NAME: Tears of Zylun
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Chunno-ka-Alee
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Shadda-Ul-Haru
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Shadda-Ul-Morn
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Oosti
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Shadda Nebula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: formed by star Shadda sometime before 43 ABY when it transitioned from a red giant into a cooling white dwarf, shedding its outer layers

NAME: Warchigade system
INTERESTING: shared name with Warchigade Trade Route, which presumably passed through the system

NAME: Altikar IV
INTERESTING: during GCW, became home to Jhor-Kai (human Jedi); through the Force, he appeared in the dreams of Sha'lia (Force-sensitive female Twi'lek slave), who escaped with Goort; they traveled together to Altikar IV, where Jhor-Kai trained Sha'lia in the ways of the Force and Goort to pilot starships, but the Jedi was killed buying time for their escape when Stormtroopers attacked

NAME: Quesna Base
INTERESTING: Imperial Cargo Facility 2 where Emon Azzameen was arrested and imprisoned for "crimes against the Empire" before being rescued by Ace Azzameen; it orbited a terrestrial planet

NAME: Aturi Cluster
INTERESTING: hotbed of Rebel Alliance support during GCW until the Scimitar assault wing took out much of Rebel resistance

NAME: Santarine
INTERESTING: High Lord Jaris Affric (local noble, crimelord) was Imperial governor; also hosted base for the Mantis Syndicate

NAME: Lesser Galam
NOTES: "Lesser Galam first and only mention..."
INTERESTING: incapable of supporting life; extremely ore-rich; discovered by Republic c. 1300 BBY; soon after, the Gaminne Group, Inc. (Human mining conglomerate) purchased the system's mining rights from the Qieg; eventually Qieg and Human colonists formed a stable government; became part of Imperial Space, but Empire had no official presence here

NAME: Lan Fellov
NOTES: "Lan Fellov first and only mention..."
INTERESTING: incapable of supporting life; extremely ore-rich; discovered by Republic c. 1300 BBY; soon after, the Gaminne Group, Inc. (Human mining conglomerate) purchased the system's mining rights from the Qieg; eventually Qieg and Human colonists formed a stable government; became part of Imperial Space, but Empire had no official presence here

NAME: Lan Tundi
NOTES: "Lan Tundi first and only mention..."
INTERESTING: incapable of supporting life; extremely ore-rich; discovered by Republic c. 1300 BBY; soon after, the Gaminne Group, Inc. (Human mining conglomerate) purchased the system's mining rights from the Qieg; eventually Qieg and Human colonists formed a stable government; became part of Imperial Space, but Empire had no official presence here

NAME: Lan Barell
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, mountains, plateaus, polar ice caps, cacti forests
NOTES: "stripped mined"
INTERESTING: most inhabitable areas were on large plateaus that served as continents; uninhabitable lowlands separated the plateaus like oceans; by time of GCW, Lan Barell only had two moons (third moon had been strip mined, broken down and refined); Qieg: mechanically minded insectoids who lived in colony nests throughout cacti forests; Human-Qieg Guild (planetary gov't) based in Shulell City

NAME: Greater Galam
INTERESTING: not ore-rich

NAME: U'Dray
NOTES: WP page conflicts about Rebel/Imperial victory
INTERESTING: during GCW, it was the location of the Assault of U'Dray (relatively extensive operation during which Scimitar assault wing was sent against Rebel positions on U'Dray); repeated missions took their toll on the pilots of the wing's TIE Bomber squadrons, who were replaced with trainee pilots new to TIE Bombers, fresh from Victorious; the Alliance eventually won the campaign

NAME: Nulan VI
INTERESTING: prior to Yavin, rebelled against Empire and its capital came under siege by TIE bombers of the Scimitar assault wing, forcing the rebellious population to surrender

NAME: Empartheca
NOTES: coords not listed in E. system WP page

NAME: Idaflor
INTERESTING: known to be uninhabited; Clone Force 99 considered laying low here but since they didn't have enough fuel to reach the system, they decided to replenish supplies on Pantora instead

NAME: Parein II
INTERESTING: Churhee's Riflemen often trained on Parein II's savannas

NAME: Parein II 4
INTERESTING: Human-inhabited; native sweetgreen fruit, terrberries, and spicy nuts used to make daranu (alcohol); site of first real test of MagnaGuards; site of Battle of Parein II 4 in which Grievous defeated the Republic army of Colonel Tyneir Renz and General Sannen

NAME: Turak IV
INTERESTING: seismically-active; Empire inflicted great damage on Rebels here at the cost of many S-1 FireHawke Heavy Repulsortanks (General Maltaz allowed the 2 tank battalions to be cut off from their supply lines by counterattacking Rebel forces in the mountains, allowing many of the tanks to be destroyed before air support TIEs arrived to rout the Rebels

NAME: Shumari
INTERESTING: the Tusken Raider KkH'Oar'Rrhr was rumored to have traveled here to confront the Demon Outlander (Vader) who wiped out his village

NAME: Parmel system
INTERESTING: Harkov (Imperial Admiral) took refuge here to escape Imperial authorities upon discovery of his defection to the Rebels but eventually he was captured and brought before Vader

NAME: DS 5
INTERESTING: Rebel XQ1 platform and military outpost where Harkov (Imperial Admiral) fled after his defection to the Rebellion

NAME: Research
INTERESTING: Imperial XQ6 platform that conducted (among other types) TIE starfighter research; TIE Defender prototypes began their journey to the Emperor from here; defended by Thunderer (Imperial frigate)

NAME: Gosho IV
INTERESTING: during GCW, Gunman and his squad from Churhee's Riflemen (mercenary group) engaged Imperial soldiers here; although pinned down, Gunman's squad managed to set up Ubrikkian Man Traps to capture grenades, allowing them time to rally against the Imperials

NAME: Vohai
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: industrial, urban towers, gardens, parklands, mountain ranges
INTERESTING: Vohai Unirail encircled entire planet from pole to pole, 2km above surface; Arkanian Microtechnologies (Arkanian company) HQ here; Churhee's Riflemen (mercenary company) often trained in Vohai's mountains

NAME: Kallistas
INTERESTING: low mountains rich in radioactive elements, rare gemstones; numerous pirate beases here; Osvald Teshik (Imperial Grand Admiral) spent part of his childhood, especially summers here; at night he stargazed from the roof of a threshing-house

NAME: Revkinn V
INTERESTING: known for its megalopolises; during GCW, Churhee's Riflemen (mercenary company) carried out an assignment to seek out Rebel cells in the cities of Revkinn V

NAME: Aris V
INTERESTING: a planet chosen as possible base of operations for Laramus Base Irregulars (mercenaries) after leaving Laramus Base; Rebels struck an Imperial military target on Aris V before Battle of Turak IV, leading to an increase in Imperial operations in the sector

NAME: Turcan III
INTERESTING: HQ of Churhee's Riflemen (mercenary company)

NAME: T-1583 (Imperial R&D Station)
INTERESTING: Imperial Research & Development Station invaded by forces of Sard Nightbringer (crimelord) sometime after Endor; they cleaned out the base and stole an experimental personal energy shield

NAME: Kheedar
INTERESTING: ruled by King Gordan (supported New Order); local underworld controlled by Horch (crimelord); Gordan denounced New Order when Imperial forces led by the Pestage subjugated the planet and instituted martial law; during invasion, Noval Garaint (bounty hunter) took over Horch's empire; planet hosted hydrocarbon processing facilities

NAME: Courkrus (Khuiumin IV)
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: semi arid terrestrial, ag fields, oceans
INTERESTING: modest population of human & other settlers; support its own agricultural needs via modern farming methods; largest city: Vlarnya (only spaceport facilities, main trade and economic base); Eyttyrmin Batiiv Pirates were based here until mostly destroyed by Empire, remnants became Khuiumin Survivors; later main base for Leonia Tavira's Invid pirates

NAME: Ord Grovner
INTERESTING: served as staging area for Imperial task force led by Freeda (Admiral) which wiped out Eyttyrmin Batiiv Pirates

NAME: Tedonia system
INTERESTING: origin point of Tedonian wine

NAME: Yityl
INTERESTING: Imperial planet inhabited by Humans; Hewat (Imperial Customs agent) and her daughter Kora Hewat lived here

NAME: Eva-T system
INTERESTING: Thrawn promoted to Grand Admiral in this system; Empire negotiated a TIE Defender scientist's release from pirates here

NAME: Elshandruu Pica
INTERESTING: known as a health resort; within an asteroid belt used as staging area for pirates, the planet had a red moon and two white moons; capital: Picavil (site of a spaceport and a conglomerate of bars, casinos, restaurants owned by Kina Margath); Elshandruu City was site of hotel/resort Margrath's, which made galactic news when it was robbed twice in 2 days by Tombat (infamous master thief)

NAME: Godo
INTERESTING: source of flame gems; Godo was an Alliance member, saved by Lando & Han yet the Godoans refused to save Lando from a deadly disease in return until Han threatened to attack with an Alliance fleet; Jabba had two statuettes (the Dancing Goddess and he Minstrel) stolen from the Godoans, who paid to get it back after Jabba's death

NAME: Shogun
INTERESTING: surreal, crystalline terrain formed vistas described as "dreamscapes"; conquered by and aligned with Taung Mandalorians years before Great Sith War; several Mandalores had visions leading to important changes in Mandalorian theology, including admittance of non-Taungs; Fenn Shysa died here in 21 BBY while saving Boba Fett's life

NAME: Baes Logia
INTERESTING: during GCW, Empire and Rebels were engaged in a campaign here; Alliance tried to capture an Imperial general alive, but he was killed by the insane Graf Yonna; Tamo Lan (male Carosite Rebel) served the Alliance here before serving at Massassi Station

NAME: Seylott
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rainforests, dense jungles, vast canal systems, ancient white stone temples
INTERESTING: site of one of Maz Kanata's treasure troves; Cikatro VIzago, Azmorigan and Lando traveled there to look for treasure but were stopped by Black Sun thugs who controlled the world; Andris spice mined here; during High Republic Era, Vecari trees exported to Coruscant; home to Disciples of Shaa; vast canals dug during time of Infinite Empire

NAME: Ebiwaan
INTERESTING: endpoint of Leisure Corridor, opposite Coruscant

NAME: Vergesso I
INTERESTING: valueless asteroid belt; possibly the remains of a planet destroyed by an unknown force (possibly an encounter with a rogue star); contained 1 major planetoid

NAME: Vergesso II
INTERESTING: valueless asteroid belt; possibly the remains of a planet destroyed by an unknown force (possibly an encounter with a rogue star); contained 1 major planetoid

NAME: Vergesso III
INTERESTING: valueless asteroid belt; possibly the remains of a planet destroyed by an unknown force (possibly an encounter with a rogue star); contained 3 major planetoids

NAME: Vergesso Prime
INTERESTING: marked as shadowport by Maz Kanata on Smuggler's Guide map; Rebels considered alliance with Mining Guild while investigating their operations here; site of Vergesso Base (joint Ororo Transportation / Rebel Alliance asteroid hangar wiped out by the Executor; patrolled by TIEs due to pirate activity; Rebels hired Han to plant an EMP in a shipment heading to Corulag to disable fleet there

NAME: Vergesso IV
INTERESTING: valueless asteroid belt; possibly the remains of a planet destroyed by an unknown force (possibly an encounter with a rogue star); contained 2 major planetoids

NAME: Vergesso V
INTERESTING: valueless asteroid belt; possibly the remains of a planet destroyed by an unknown force (possibly an encounter with a rogue star); contained no charted major planetoids

NAME: Talofan
INTERESTING: HQ of Grand Moff Kintaro during Imperial Era

NAME: Bajic system
INTERESTING: flashpoint during GCW (at some point between 2 BBY & 4 ABY) with several battles fought here; Empire and Alliance victorious at various times

NAME: Bahalian Shipyards
NOTES: Llanic Spice "Route" listed vs "Run" - broken link?
INTERESTING: small, well-respected shipwright company that was a front for the Tenloss Syndicate; Onyx Star (prototype for Z-95 Headhunter) produced here

NAME: Qiaxx
INTERESTING: HQ of Black Nebula (Dequc's Black Sun splinter group); site of famous Bubble Cliffs of Nezmi and an elaborate casino (owned by Dequc through intermediaries); Mara Jade traveled here after Endor to eliminate Dequc

NAME: Andasala
INTERESTING: discovered after Ruusan Reformation; remained outside Republic borders; settled as mining colony for Gesenix Mining; after word of its lush natural resources spread, many colonists emigrated from nearby Svivren; avoided CW; many Imperial battles fought along shipping lanes around the world; haven for criminals, pirates until rise of crime lord Valis Lorn; notable spice transshipment point

NAME: Tresidiss
INTERESTING: owned by Herglic criminals who ran massive gambling establishments and usurious banking operations here; dues to its deliberately lax tariff laws, it attracted intelligence agents of every stripe; population: 2.1 M

NAME: Eirrauus
INTERESTING: planet apparently had two suns; Eirraucs: peaceful, omnivorous, had six limbs, long four-eyed faces and moved with a leaping run, using their rear and middle limbs for locomotion, though the middle limbs could also be used as arms; native Eirraucs were subjugated and enslaved by Empire

NAME: Xiunsrus
INTERESTING: site of first known criminal act committed by Bloodsniffers (swoop gang), who demanded 10,000 credits from a village of farmers and destroyed the village when they failed to comply

NAME: Suhuurmin system
INTERESTING: during GCW, a group of slavers not authorized by the Empire operated here, but was exterminated by the Mantis Syndicate (bounty hunter organization) at some point between 0 ABY and 4 ABY

NAME: Vinzen Neela 5
INTERESTING: site of major Rebel defeat during GCW; after Hoth, Rebels tried to thwart a transfer of prototype TIE Defenders to the Hininbirg (Ton-Falk-class escort carrier) but were repelled by Maarek Stele (Imperial pilot)

NAME: Spice Terminus
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: major hub in the spice trade, near the end of the Llanic Spice Run and its intersection with the Five Veils Route

NAME: Laramus
INTERESTING: location of Laramus Base (HQ of Laramus Base Irregulars); rapidly growing Rebel cell here; Visseon II led a Rebel ambush of an Imperial convoy over Laramus; Imperials later destroyed much of the planet's surface, forcing the Irregulars to move elsewhere

NAME: Shownar
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: vertag crystal landmasses, vertag crystal spires
INTERESTING: paradise planet with a view of the Torch Nebula, which illuminated the planet with red and blue light at night; three large landmasses were composed entirely of a rare form of vertag crystal; crystal spires several km tall dotted the landscape; wind blowing at high altitudes through the spires created ghostly harmonic audio waves referred to as Shownar Lullaby

NAME: Nixus
INTERESTING: low-gravity; hosted Nixus Hub 218 (black market outpost visited by numerous individuals); site of deal between Vizago and Azmorigan, but Hondo imprisoned VIzago on his own ship and attempted to do the deal himself, leading to skirmish between the two and Ezra Bridger; later, the Spectres arrived to liberate two Lasat from the Empire and help them find Lira San (original Lasat homeworld)

NAME: Reuss
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Reuss VI
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Reuss VIII
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: Llanic Spice Run not listed?
INTERESTING: agriworld that became a polluted industrial world under Empire; Torel Vorne was the most powerful crime lord here; atmosphere was full of toxin, acid rain, and caused lung damage with prolonged exposure without a breath mask; Medical Supervisor Sena Pakkalo served here briefly, providing hygiene instruction to locals

NAME: Jermac
INTERESTING: notable spice producer

NAME: Bridin Anchorage (Gallienis IV)
INTERESTING: renamed after Quarlo Bridin (con artist) took over world shortly after THrawn's death; once a lush world with beaches, but covered in slums under Bridin's rule; capital: Bridis City

NAME: Hyrol Preen Beta
INTERESTING: populace wiped out by Imperial Storm commandos and ZQ infantry droids due to suspected Rebel activity; Johin (spaer) brought word of the devastation

NAME: Friijillis
INTERESTING: Friij News Services (Hutt-sponsored news network, a clearing house of illegal information and data replication, Tenloss Syndicate member) based here

NAME: Midani
INTERESTING: favored destination of hunters; notable transshipment point in spice trade

NAME: Vorlag
INTERESTING: the native Vorlaggn had three eyes and spoke in the third person, often confusing members of other species; a Vorlaggn crimelord named Slussen Urla-fir Kal Kethin-Wa Canker owned a fortress here

NAME: Ifron
INTERESTING: location of Bovris Tapcafe (seedy establishment Mara Jade visited during her search for Dequc)

NAME: Silexa
