INTERESTING: system contained at least three planets, the third of which was orbited by a barren moon once occupied by a sentient species millenia before 1 ABY; rogue Imperial Commander Rezi Soresh destroyed the system with a prototype superweapon, which caused Silexa to go nova but he failed to destroy Luke, a Rebel fleet and an Imperial fleet led by Vader

NAME: Skann
INTERESTING: farmers here grew crops such as Dust-Corn and Dry Gene Wheat and also made Skannbult Likker (unique beverage, possibly galaxy's most volatile fire-water) from surplus crops, distilled in rock basins; quality varied greatly, with smaller farmers from major towns making the best; owner of Margath's entertainment complex on Elshandruu Pica scored a small supply of highest quality Likker

NAME: Ennth
INTERESTING: planet's moon orbited such that every 8 years, the two bodies passed close enough that their atmospheres connected and Ennth was wracked by enormous groundquakes and massive natural disasters; colonists usually evacuated to crowded orbital refugee stations until they could return, but many were invariably killed as they took too long to gather possessions or left too late

NAME: Danchian Prime
INTERESTING: Milko (droid bounty hunter) claimed to have "family" here

NAME: Danadine
INTERESTING: served as homeworld of Relekin Confidential (collection agency, Tenloss Syndicate member) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Lesu
INTERESTING: homeworld of Malakin Enterprises (criminal organization, Tenloss Syndicate member) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Calline I
INTERESTING: hazardously hot, uninhabitable; had a dense metal core; theoretically suitable for mining; surveyed by Rebel scouts searching for possible alternate bases c. 2 ABY

NAME: Calline II
INTERESTING: tide-locked planet lacking atmosphere; sun-facing side uninhabitably hot, side facing away was as cold as vacuum, thin habitable zone between; once very seismically active; caves riddled its crust; when Rebels scouted it for an alternate base c. 2 ABY, they found smugglers already using the caves, but smugglers might have been willing to join forces with Rebels due to their antipathy for Empire

NAME: Calline III
INTERESTING: no moons; trace industial grade gases in atmosphere

NAME: Lol system
INTERESTING: Sumrias: their thought-caste had four-fingered hands and developed a base-eight measuring system that produced Df (parameter characterizing the combat performance of military artillery); mentioned by Rebel historian Major Arhul Hextrophon in a compilation of Imperial documents prepared for Mon Mothma and other Rebel officers

NAME: Dom-Bradden
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: in 18 BBY, Empire stationed several Stormtroopers here to be picked up by the Eye of Palpatine, (didn't arrive until 12 ABY); failing to find troopers, it instead took a number of Affytechans and attempted to brainwash them into being Imperial Navy troopers; Affytechans: tall, bipedal sentient plants with unique growths of leaves, petals, tassels and tendrils, and were beautiful, but smelly to humans

NAME: Drexel
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: home of Drexelian shell-diggers, who wore ragged clothing; while infiltrating Palpatine Archive (space station) in 4 ABY after Endor, rebel operative Jaxxon claimed to be beinging artifacts from here; sole planet in system; waterworld; home to sentient Sea-dragons; Jedi exiled corrupt governor Quarg and his pirates here on a mobile floating city; rebels against his rule became Dragon Lords

NAME: Majilop
INTERESTING: homeworld of Lucin Syndicate (major producer and distributor of illegal holoporn) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Kendamar
NOTES: WP says Dail sector in article? EA says Lol
INTERESTING: homeworld of Kendamari Casinos (chain of casinos, Tenloss Syndicate member) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Tamra system
INTERESTING: Tamrans: cherubic-faced sentients

NAME: Goshyn system
INTERESTING: location of Goshyn Detention Center (asteroid used by Empire as a prison); years before 9 ABY, Billey (Human smuggler) was imprisoned here; upon release, he continued his smuggling operations using a transport ship he named the Goshyn Queen

NAME: Changa system
INTERESTING: origin point of Changa bushfighting (martial arts discipline); may also be source of a disease called "Changa Bloodrot" from unreleased novel Alien Exodus

NAME: Ragnar VIII
INTERESTING: remote astronomical object that served as HQ of the Ragnar Syndicate (chapter house of the Bounty Hunters' Guild

NAME: Sakuub
INTERESTING: tourist spot for its sector; in 44 ABY Jaina Solo and Jagged Fel honeymooned here after defeat of Abeloth; location of Sky Temple of Karsol (ancient temple which Jaina Solo discovered to be a Jedi temple upon visiting)

NAME: Kinun Depot system
INTERESTING: location of Kinun Depot; Malak (Rodian slaver) stopped here to refuel; Myo (Abyssin previously captured by Malak) escaped and booked passage to Tatooine

NAME: Kasiol 3
INTERESTING: home to herlixx (amphibian omnivores that hunted fish and smaller amphibians; colonized by time of Empire

NAME: Draay 2
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, hills, valleys, plains, tall grasses
INTERESTING: moon was purchased by Lucien Draay in case he had need to reconstitute a True Covenant from his mother Krynda Draay's Jedi Covenant; many Jedi lived here by 3963 BBY; during CW, B'ink Utrila (Jedi Master) and Rennax Omani (her Padawan) were sent here with a squad of Clone troopers to find the Gauntlet of Kressh the Younger hidden in an abandoned temple built by the True Covenant

NAME: Tyaonon system
INTERESTING: system shared it sname with the Tyaonon Ranger (freighter)

NAME: Smuggler's Run
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ice, snow, volcanic cave systems, mountains, ice-covered rivers
NOTES: Corellian Run not mentioned
INTERESTING: treacherous asteroid field with a shadowport harboring a plethora of smugglers who couldn't afford the relative luxury of havens like Nar Shaddaa; despite its location along the Corellian Run, only certain people (mostly smugglers) knew how to find the Run; under Hutt control until deaths of Jabba and Palpatine; Skips (asteroid bases) were numbered in order in which they were inhabited

NAME: Skip 1
INTERESTING: numerous asteroids were inhabited, but the largest and most important was Skip 1; home to a spaceport and massive smuggling facility with cantinas, casinos; almost exploded once due to a mysterious slime; Boba Fett and some of his bounty hunter associates had quarters there; by 17 ABY these were abandoned and turned into an eating area; damaged by Kueller's explosive droids

NAME: Skip 2
INTERESTING: Han speculated that Skip 2 likely sustained damage when Kueller's droids bombed the Smuggler's Run, since it had droids on it

NAME: Skip 3
INTERESTING: Han speculated that Skip 3 likely sustained damage when Kueller's droids bombed the Smuggler's Run, since it had droids on it

NAME: Skip 5
INTERESTING: home of Jedi Knight Traavis; abandoned during time Han was a regular because it was unbearably hot to most species; a decade previously, a number of smugglers who lived there for months ended up killing each other in a fight, supposedly started by the heat; Jawas were brought in c. 17 ABY to repair damaged Imperial equipment and was presumably damaged by Kueller's explosive droids

NAME: Skip 6
INTERESTING: HQ for Nandreeson (Glottalphib crime boss), who chose to fill its caves with pools of algae-filled water to make them more comfortable to his fellow Glottalphibs

NAME: Skip 8
INTERESTING: Han and Chewie once visited here during their smuggling years

NAME: Skip 52
INTERESTING: known for constant swirling rock storms around it, making landings difficult; served as location of large ryll shipment, stolen on the way to an Alliance medical facility; Rebels and ISB dispatched agents to find it; Blackhole watched the operation through a hologram; most of the shipment ended up in ISB hands, though Rebel agents escaped with a few crates in the Millennium Falcon

NAME: Skip 72
INTERESTING: Han speculated that Skip 3 likely sustained damage when Kueller's droids bombed the Smuggler's Run, since it had droids on it

NAME: Naos III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: urban, ice, snow, volcanic cave systems, ice-covered rivers, mountains
NOTES: Naos Belt may be located here?
INTERESTING: frigid moon; locals exported Naos sharptooth (delicacy fish from Mon Cala to Corellia); Naos III Mercantile controlled most businesses; streets were mucky, dangerous, damaged, with little sanitation and low-slung, prefab buildings draped with icicles; local climate control machinery not in good repair; colonists from Rodia and Ryloth lured here in hopes of finding ryll spice in caves

NAME: Indoumodo
INTERESTING: northern hempisphere held forests known for hanava trees, large populations of greddleback termites; home to kouhuns (poisonous arthropods that lived in damp caves and vast hollow trees, hunted dog-size creatures in crevices); destination for assassins trying to capture them for use as untraceable killers; in 22 BBY Jango hired Zam Wesell to assassinate Padme using kouhuns

NAME: Gertafuu
INTERESTING: frigid astronomical object occupying 6th orbital position within Gertafuu system; site of Fort Balarad (well-protected smuggler outpost / shadowport); at some point, its Aqualish and Whiphid inhabitants traded in furs and exotic meat

NAME: Lamaro
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Lamarebb
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: orbited very close to Lamaro (star) and Lamarecc (second planet); every 14 years, Lamarebb and Lamarecc approached each other until almost rubbing, causing natural light phenomena on Lamaredd and scrambling communications; probably owed its name to a notation in an old star map

NAME: Lamarecc
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: orbited very close to Lamaro (star) and Lamarecc (second planet); every 14 years, Lamarebb and Lamarecc approached each other until almost rubbing, causing natural light phenomena on Lamaredd and scrambling communications; probably owed its name to a notation in an old star map

NAME: Lamaredd
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: 85% water cover; rich in minerals and seafood; in 500 BBY Hugo Bartyn (agent of Outer Rim Oreworks Company claimed planet for industrial use; he removed Menahuunand created Bartyn's Landing (fishing community) populated by indentured fisherfolk belonging to amphibious species; eventually they were released but most stayed onworld; believed-dead, now-aggressive Menahuun reappeared after Naboo; Empire later sent troops here; untouched during VW war

NAME: Lamaremm
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: small icy world that developed native life made of microbes and lichen; arounf 500 years before Naboo, Outer Rim Oreworks Company analyzed the world and deemed it commercially worthless

NAME: The Reef asteroid cloud
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: asteroid, dust belt; result of collision of 2 outermost planets; astrogators had to choose between entering/exiting hyperspace outside Lamaro system and coming in on sublight, or using very precise coordinates; ships crossing at hyperspeed suffered from anomalies that destroyed hyperdrive components; pilots were then forced to land at Bartyn's landing, only repair starport

NAME: Unnipar system
INTERESTING: between 0 BBY and 3 ABY, Archduke Monio from the Dentamma Nebula bet the ownership of this system in a high-stakes sabacc game and lost it to Ceezva (Teltior con artist), who had bluffed her way into the game

NAME: Skye
INTERESTING: attempted to gain admittance to Council of Neutral Systems during CW but interrupted by invasion led by Zeta Magnus; S'kytri divided into Highland, Lowland and outcast Outland clans

NAME: Eiram
INTERESTING: competed with E'ronoh over control of the system; during High Republic Era, ruled by queen regnan Dima and her consort Thandeka, who was kidnapped by the Directorate; after this crisis, the two planets' relationship improved and they allowed the Republic to build Starlight Beacon to be built in the system

NAME: E'ronoh
INTERESTING: competed with Eiram over control of the system; during High Republic Era, ruled by Monarch Cassel (Pantoran); after this crisis, the two planets' relationship improved and they allowed the Republic to build Starlight Beacon to be built in the system

NAME: Lost Moon
INTERESTING: breathable atmosphere; moon broke from its orbit and drifted between sister worlds of Eiram and E'ronoh; neither planet's inhabitants knew which world it originally belonged to, but devoid of value; during High Republic era, members of the Directorate kidnapped rulers from both worlds and held them here in caves; home of carnivorous cave-dwelling white serpents

NAME: Starlight Beacon
INTERESTING: large station constructed in 232 BBY on Galactic Frontier during High Republic Era; situated in center of region's unexplored dark zones; acted as beacon, sending out a signal that guided travelers; had hospital, observatories, research stations, markets, cultural center with exhibits of countless world in Republic; station was 19 percent triazurite, rare mineral which helped boost transmissions

NAME: Thakwaa
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/Alphabet Squadron p. 319
INTERESTING: temperate, isolated world that attracted little Imperial attention until end of Galactic Civil War, but Empire gave up trying to conquer it due to Thaakwaese strength, size and unpredictability; Tensent spent a night in the Red Isles of Thakwaa, infested with biting flies

NAME: Veccacopia
INTERESTING: discovered at some point before 44 BBY; designated Republic protectorate; over time, judicial offices grew corrupt, with judges not doing their best, and convicted Cacops hiring stand-ins to serve their sentences; Finis Valorum served as a judge here not long after its discovery under frontier conditions; eventually he broke the corrupt sentence-trading scam via a retinal scan system

NAME: Absit
INTERESTING: Yatir: sympathetic to Rebellion; Empire finally subjugated at some point before Hoth in 3 ABY (Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit was instrumental in operation); Empire used population for slave labor

NAME: Dalna
PARENT: Outer Rim/unknown//Dalnan (appears to be in Tunka)/Dalnan
INTERESTING: small world orbiting two suns; inhabited by settlers known as Dalnans, who distrusted outsiders and rarely travelled; planet suffered a war about a century before the Great Hyperspace Disaster that led Dalnans to adopt a culture focused on battle training; not part of the Republic, though the Jedi had a small presence there, having fought the Ro family during the war; following the Disaster, Dalna considered joining the Republic, but the ship with the delegation aboard was sabotaged by the Nihil

NAME: Varada Five
INTERESTING: location to HQ of Varada sector branch of SoroSuub, run by Tyanna Tymb

NAME: Delantine
INTERESTING: 3-star system; openly joined Rebel Alliance; conquered by Empire

NAME: Benon
INTERESTING: Imperials were supposed to think Trux Zissu fled o Benon after abandoning the Timespan (Alliance transport)

NAME: Delantine
INTERESTING: 16 languages spoken here; Alliance sent Granit here to bolster Rebel sympathy; Trux Zissu chosen as governor after Yavin; Trux and son Stuart traveled here from Yavin 4 in Timespan but ship was disabled by Imperial warship but Stuart, R2 and C-3PO escaped to Sa'nor in an escape pod; Imperials conquered planet but Granit was able to evacuate Rebels

NAME: Da'nor (Planet X)
INTERESTING: went through four seasonal changes each day due to trinary orbit; Stuart Zissu rescued here by Granit and orderd to Romm; N'or language spoken here; home to predatory birds and large flying lizards

NAME: Romm
INTERESTING: Stuart Zissu, R2 and C-3PO ordered here by Granit after escaping to Da'nor in an escape pod

NAME: Bestal III
INTERESTING: close to Kadal asteroid field; vortal trees produced seeds from which efficient stimulants could be harvested; Alara Fax (head of Fax Ventures) used mining the nearby asteroids as a cover for a lucrative medpac manufacturing operation as vengeance against her old rival, SoroSuub's Tyanna Tymb

NAME: Kadal Asteroid Field
INTERESTING: close to Bestal III; asteroids contained significant deposits of aluminite and corax ores; during GCW Alara Fax (head of Fax Ventures) secured rights to mine the field, which also served as a cover for the more profitable venture of manufacturing efficient medpacs including stimulants derived from vortal tree seeds on Bestal III

NAME: Dentamma Nebula
INTERESTING: Archduke Monio was from here and lost the enire Unnipar system to a Teltior con artist named Ceezva in a sabacc game

NAME: Rhamalai
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, mountains, valleys, plains, ag fields
INTERESTING: population: 11 M; Cherishites (quasi-religious sect) fled Republic persecution, discovered and settled c. 400 years before GCW; 100 years later, corporate scouts discovered and tried to take the world, but were stopped by a native Jedi (an original settler) who continued to protect Rhamalai during his long lifespan and died during the rise of the Empire, which then conquered the planet after Yavin

NAME: Borlov
INTERESTING: Borlovians: feathered, timid species who communicated with multi-layered whistles and trills, and valued stability rather than mobility or change; most never left city or village of their birth; space travel was all but unthinkable until Llollulion (a misfit) departed with Booster Terrik

NAME: Rivoria system
INTERESTING: home to Rivorian grain-bandits (rodents)

NAME: Quintas
INTERESTING: known to be far removed from Denarii Nova

NAME: Solem
INTERESTING: brutally subjugated as demonstration of power after Yavin; Yolan and Malvander Bren (Imperial governors) ruled from Imperial stronghold in city of G'ai Solem during GCW; Yolan realized evils of the Empire and left to join resistance; native species green-skinned, pointy-eared

NAME: Pako Ramoon
INTERESTING: TransGalMeg Industries, Inc. corporate HQ located here; site of Diskio and K'lial Khzrry's rescue of Basal Moor (Rebel Agent)

NAME: Dahvil
INTERESTING: starting point of Dahvil-Fodro Hyperpsace Promenade (illegal starship race)

NAME: Abrihom
INTERESTING: supply station platform used by the Alliance, destroyed by the Empire during the GCW

NAME: Karra
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungle canyons, grassy plateaus, mines (under Empire)
INTERESTING: briefly colonized by Mineral Assets Partnership in 500 BBY; varmigio mines established by Empire; both settlements were destroyed by swarms of insects controlled by Karran hive mind

NAME: Seven Flames
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance established support base here, which Rebels used to launch diplomatic operation to Karra; alliance with native primitive Karrans, which failed; Rebels were able to capture and imprison Darryn Edalm (Karra's Imperial governor) and send him to the prison camp on Shimmer

NAME: Shimmer
INTERESTING: site of Rebel Alliance medium-security work camp; Darryn Edalm (former Imperial governor of Karra) was imprisoned here

NAME: Laim Subspace Relay Station
INTERESTING: 4 hours' travel from Najarka system, 6 hours from Narg system; devoid of planets; had a subspace relay station which was part of Rayer Sector Subspace Broadcast Network

NAME: Lurr
INTERESTING: a stormtrooper who accompanied Vader to Cheelit killed a young woman while on this planet; Clat the Shamer used his memories to induce him to commit suicide

NAME: Najarka
INTERESTING: 4 hours from Laim system; orbited relatively far from system's star; 3/4 of planet's surface was covered in glaciers; remaining 1/4 was equatorial subtropical rain forest, which should not have been able to thrive on the meager light from the star alone; Imperial Survey Corps assumed the difference was made up by geothermal energy; considered too isolated to be of use for industrial development or settlement

NAME: Narg
INTERESTING: controlled by TransGalMeg Industries, Inc. during GCW; hunam inhabitants known to be xenophobic

NAME: Nevarro
INTERESTING: controlled by the Empire; after the Empire's fall it became a lawless haven for bounty hunters working for Greef Karga, an agent of the Bounty Hunters' Guild; it was captured by Imperial Remnant forces led by Moff Gideon, though they were expelled after Din Djarin helped destroy an Imperial base on the planet; as High Magistrate, Karga later led the planet to become an independent trade port of the Hydian Way (despite not being located on that hyperlane)

NAME: Gastrula
INTERESTING: Gastrulans: four-armed gastropods with spotted, bulbous heads with eyestalks on either side; terminus of short-lived Great Bantha Breakfast Biscuit Run, established by Bungo Bung (Sullustan freighter captain)

NAME: Tamboon
INTERESTING: ruled by benevolent monarchy

NAME: Sontor system
INTERESTING: shared name with Sontor Skipper (freighter)

NAME: Chateuse VII
INTERESTING: population divided into warring factions, which Leia attempted to reconcile so they could join the NR

NAME: Pendaxa
INTERESTING: site of battle of Western Reaches Operation during Imperial Reconquest of the Rim in 17 BBY

NAME: Rentean
INTERESTING: inhabited by humans who aided the Rebel alliance by manufacturing starfighters; this aid was discovered by the Empire following interrogation of a Bothan spy; Empire subsequently dispatched a team to infiltrate the facility, destroy it, and punish the local inhabitants

NAME: Feenicks VI
INTERESTING: Imperial System patrol squadron base and its Assassin-class corvettes were destroyed by Red Squadron B-wings

NAME: Cathis
INTERESTING: site of Rebel starfigher base during GCW

NAME: Actlyon
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Galaxy's Edge: Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
INTERESTING: located on hyperspace route leading to Batuu; Actlyon City: lower district was crowded; according to Izal Garsea, hundreds of smugglers and pirates operated here; c. 34 ABY, Ana Tolla's (smuggler) crew operated here for some time but abandoned their associate Izal Garsea here in a cantina when they moved on to their next job

NAME: Yunkor IX
NOTES: coords missing in WP article
INTERESTING: site of early B-wing testing; single B-wing destroyed a TIE/LN staging area near planet

NAME: Berrol's Donn
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Rebel base commanded by Zeke Rondel here after Yavin; Sangorn's Net (bar popular with ciminals) located here; attacked by Nagai invaders in 4 ABY

NAME: Trenchenovu
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Alphabet Squadron p. 77 () p. 80 after Trenchenovu, Tensent limped to Entropian Hive for repairs) p. 470 (7 months before Pandem Nai, Shakara Nuress loaned a 204th squadron to ISD Sanction to repel anticipated Rebel attack here and killed Tensent's squadron)/
INTERESTING: world orbited by Trenchenovu Shipyards

NAME: Trenchenovu Shipyards
INTERESTING: Nath Tensent's squadron was sent here to attack the Imperial-held shipyards but when the operation went wrong, they all were killed except Tensent

NAME: Celestial Wake
INTERESTING: there were spectacular cystalline asteroids nearby; pink blobs had six claws, metal devices on their backs, and could join together to form large objects

NAME: Brink of the Celestial Wake
INTERESTING: apparently abandoned during CW; Republic task force stationed here, but Jedi in charge and all clone troopers were slaughtered by strange pink blobs; Serra Keto survived and was discovered by and escaped with Anakin, who rigged the station to detonate as soon as they exited the hangar bay

NAME: Sil'Lume Belt
NOTES: Corellian Trade Spine not listed
INTERESTING: over 800,000 asteroids catalogued and claimed for mining or other operations; during Yavin blockade, Luke scouted the belt for potential as a new Rebel base

NAME: Tredway
INTERESTING: owned by Axton Tredway (male human Jedi Knight), who was slain by Vader during Great Jedi Purge; Sebastian parnell (Imperial governor) later destroyed the asteroid

NAME: 400,324 Henryson
INTERESTING: small, crater-ridden planetoid about 1km in length, about 1/2 km in width and thickness; 400,324th planetoid to be catalogued as property of a sentient; site of a hospice during GCW

NAME: Gal Milnor
INTERESTING: main supply base used by Rebels to store food, munitions, fuel; base and sizeable freighter fleet were both destroyed by the Empire shortly before Endor, forcing the Alliance to seek supplies from Dunari (owner of Dunari's Rest Casino) and the Hurrim (Outer Rim-based pirate group)

NAME: Tallek
INTERESTING: during outbreak of thorn fever, Empire rounded up anyone who caught the plague and let them die in isolation camps

NAME: Vryssa
INTERESTING: home of Buldobeasts; Imperial garrison base here, which was entirely wiped out by Boba Fett at some point in 1 ABY while he eas pursuing bounty on Rivo Xarran; orbited by "twin moons"

NAME: Bryndar
INTERESTING: remote planet in middle of an ice age; Flynn Kybo, B'dard Tone and Codi Ty (smugglers) hid here during hunt for Grievous; site of battle of Western Reaches Operation during Imperial Reconquest of the Rim in 17 BBY

NAME: Dalicron-4
INTERESTING: remote, little-noticed world with diverse and vibrant ecosystems and fierce, unpredictable weather patterns; population of no more than 1 K (descendants of Republic colonists, suspicious of outsiders); agrarian society based on barter, trade; nearly a millennium before Yavin, a Jedi named Duumas uncovered a prophecy about a "Child of Light" who could serve as a conduit to the Force

NAME: Barkhesh
INTERESTING: lush agriworld; homeworld of Antidar Williams (Judicial Forces pilot); population resisted New Order, supported Rebel Alliance during GCW; Cassio Tagge (Imperial Army High General) claimed 1st Tapani Assault Battlegroup claimed victory in Humiliation of Barkhesh sometime before Yavin; however, Carlist Rieekanrefuted Tagge, claiming 1st Tapani withdrew after losing 1/5 of trroopers in acidic hailstorm

NAME: Doxxen system
INTERESTING: origin point of Doxxen tea

NAME: Seitia Prime
INTERESTING: Bellorin Medical Academy located here

NAME: Fanha
INTERESTING: site of battle of Western Reaches Operation during Imperial Reconquest of the Rim in 17 BBY; Screed (Imperial Admiral) and Shea Hublin smashed Iska pirates her, forcing pirate lord Guun Cutlax to flee to Atravis Sector

NAME: Bendii
INTERESTING: appeared as blue orb; about 6 months after Yavin, Han, Leia and Chewie fled Imperial and bounty hunter pursuit above the world while ferrying supplies for Rebel Alliance aboard the Falcon

NAME: Tol Ado
INTERESTING: orbited in 3rd position; Imperial prison planet with poisonous atmosphere containing hydrogen fluoride with 10x average atmospheric pressure, and temp of 477 Celsius; had 124 orbital sensor stations; prison contained more than 1.4 M cell blocks, each with 4,000 cells

NAME: Seezar's Planet
INTERESTING: Shirley ("Chanteuse of the Stars") once performed here c. 3.5 ABY

NAME: Rycep Asteroid Belt
INTERESTING: located just one hyperjump away from the Anoat system; during his efforts to capture the Trandoshan Doshanalawook (also known as "Chainbreaker"), Bossk traced the outlaw here, where a dungeon ship of Wookiee prisoners was scheduled to pass by

NAME: Asteroid X342
INTERESTING: Bossk parked the Hound's Tooth here while waiting to get the drop on the outlaw Trandoshan Doshanalawook (also known as "Chainbreaker")

NAME: Jjannex II
INTERESTING: Stormclaw (Imperial Star Destroyer) defeated a pirate attack near Jjannex II

NAME: Tarawa
INTERESTING: site of a battle during GCW

NAME: Prexiar
INTERESTING: Pirates of Prexiar operated an outpost here; planet had lots of jungle growth

NAME: Letaki
INTERESTING: Letaki: egg-shaped head, eight tentacles, four eyes, sharp beak, two sets of gills (could breathe air or water), carnivorous; homeworld of Evar Orbus (leader of Evar Orbus and His Galactic Jizz-Wailers)

NAME: Dorlo
INTERESTING: controlled by Empire; Professor Nij Por Ral, working for SoroSuub Corporation, helped excavate a 3-mile wall; Sorosuub hoped to use the runes on the wall to find Dorlo's resources; Qu Rahn led Rebel forces on Dorlo, but was defeated by Jerec's forces

NAME: Shumavar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: site of a CW battle in which famous Shockball player and Seperatist hero Kob Mondray fought; located in CIS space; attacked by Nagai raiders in 4 ABY; hosted a trade conference in 24 ABY where Bornan Thul (trader) had planned to meet with Nolaa Tarkona (head of Diversity Alliance) to deliver a parcel, but skipped meeting after he realized that the parcel contained the coords for a storehouse containing a Human-specific plague

NAME: Vale
INTERESTING: Shea Hublin (Imperial Ace) lost his leg and half his right arm when his squadron was ambushed by Rebels here in 13 BBY

NAME: Ogoth Tiir
INTERESTING: site of final battle of Western Reaches Operation in 17 BBY, in which Jona Grumby was crippled and Imperial forces killed Seperatist General Kendu Ultho, capturing his remaining forces

NAME: Gon Tiek
INTERESTING: 501st Legion fought on Gon Tiek at some point after formation og Empire in 19 BBY

NAME: Gorbah
INTERESTING: site of 4 secret fighter bases under control of a rogue group attempting to take out Imperial forces, who immediately fled their bases when they realized there was no hope of beating the Empire

NAME: Siluria III
INTERESTING: capital: Koved City

NAME: Atterol
INTERESTING: Battle of Atterol (Rebel Y-wing and Z-95s attempted to raid a small Imperial convoy) took place here during GCW

NAME: Atravis system
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: scouted by Freia Kallea and Banu Hydia in 3694 BBY; surrounding area explored between 5000 and 3000 BBY; fell within CIS borders in 22 BBY; 18th Sector Army of Republic charged with engaging CIS forces here; civilians suffered extensive casualties during reign of Empire; population 1 - 10 B c. 25 ABY

NAME: Pursin
INTERESTING: Pursians constantly at war with Yugami

NAME: Yugami
INTERESTING: Yugami constantly at war with Pursin

NAME: ZXK-100346.6a
INTERESTING: sixth planet in system; hiding place of Soulsaber (deadly dark side artifact concealed by ancient Jedi); map showing location of this system was installed inside Temples of Vormijj on Pamorjal; in 3 ABY, dark Jedi discovered the location and traveled there in search of the weapon

NAME: Uru
INTERESTING: Oni: militant species often known to work off-planet as mercenaries, and female Oni could store static electricity in a unique gland in their bodies

NAME: Heriston Depot
INTERESTING: key space station in Outer Rim, which boasted a drydock (rarity in the Outer Rim at the time), standard refueling and repair facilities; prior to its establishment, Imperial vessels had to travel coreward to find a drydock; Eriadu had comparable facilities, but was often fully engaged maintaining Seswenna sector's defense fleet; protected by a number of platforms, starfighter wings, system patrol craft

NAME: Carreras Major
INTERESTING: backwater; Shifala: simians with furry humanoid features; developed government that spanned the entire star system

NAME: Carreras Minor
INTERESTING: ringed planet; an ice mining platform was operational on the ring

NAME: Carreras Minor's moon
INTERESTING: Ania Solo ran a junkyard here; home of gesaw rats (blue-skinned rodents that fed on power)

NAME: Carreras G51 Communications Array
INTERESTING: part of Marasiah Fel's galaxy-spanning G51 communications array; Darth Wredd took control of the array and flew it to his hiding place on the rogue planet of Mala, his homeworld; it was destroyed in a collision with the planet

NAME: Mala
INTERESTING: remote world home to near-Human species (extinct); with sedentary and nomadic iron age communities; the One Sith used Mala as a testing ground for new bioweapon, which exterminated all life on planet and also knocked it out of orbit, turning it into a rogue planet; Darth Wredd was sole survivor

NAME: Surd Nebula
INTERESTING: Mala and the Carreras system were just beyond the nebula's veil; Mustafar system was the closest system to Surd Nebula

NAME: Mustafar
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, glens, lava oceans, lava rivers, molten rock plains, lava pits, obsidian mountain ranges, obsidian shorelines, volcanoes
INTERESTING: once a lush green world, until an intense Force battle pulled the planets into their current arrangement; Black Sun drawn here as a place to dispose of evidence; last capital of CIS; Vader and Kenobi dueled here; planet constantly flexed and torn by competing pulls of Jestefad and Lefrani, which each prefented Mustafar from becoming a moon of the other

NAME: Nur
INTERESTING: water moon in Mustafar system (presumably a gas giant's moon); home of heavily secured underwater Fortress Inquisitorius; used to contain captured Jedi; infiltrated by Cal Kestis and Cere Junda

NAME: unidentified planetoid
INTERESTING: uninhabited; destroyed during test of (Star Destroyer) Conqueror's superlaser

NAME: Buruunin
INTERESTING: site of an Imperial assault resulting in heavy civilian casualties, commanded by General Cascaan

NAME: Tosste
INTERESTING: Tosste once home to billions of lifeforms, but lost its ocean and other water at some point; young Maul introduced to the Force here by Sidious, who flung rocks and crushed boulders together; under CIS control at end of CW; site of a Western Reaches Operation battle during Imperial Reconquest of the Rim in 17 BBY; Imperial starfighters defeated Guun Cutlax and Iska Pirates here

NAME: Tortali Platform
INTERESTING: Imperial XQ3 Platform presumably used as customs checkpoint; heavily armed, carried squadron of TIE Interceptors & Bombers; Rebels sent a strike force of X-wings and Y-wings (with A-wing escorts) to destroy the platform)

NAME: Orto
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: frozen wastelands, massive ice caps, mines, farms
INTERESTING: small, cold planet in highly elliptical orbit (possibly caused by ancient cometary impact) around red dwarf star; all life forms over 200 kg were driven to extinction and lack of food; growing season was short and only at equatorial latitudes; neutral in CW until Financial Minister declared CIS allegiance, but world was liberated by Ortolan Jedi Knight; Empire established several processing centers here but Ortolans also traded with Rebels

NAME: Canoliss IV
INTERESTING: Cannolite: culture based on three-dimensional mathmatics, causing problems for visiting offworlders (exemplified in locking mechanisms for doors, which few non-Cannolites could operate

NAME: Praesitlyn
INTERESTING: within 60 LY of Bpfassh; location of Intergalactic Communications Center (key HoloNet relay for Republic, Empire, and NR, located 150m km from center of a major continent); strategic asset during CW; planet buffeted by sudden dust storms; fierce Battle of Praesitlyn fought here

NAME: Sluis Van
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Sluis Van Shipyards
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: series of orbital shipbuilding complexes considered to be the best of its kind in Outer Rim, but also one of the slowest due to bureaucracy and because Sluissi regarded shipbuilding akin to a form of art; at one point built up to encircle entire world

NAME: Sluis Van Central Station
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: shipyard catering to pilots seeking maintenance; overwhelmed by repair orders in 9 ABY after Thrawn's raid of the shipyards (repelled by NR forces); Luke needed new hyperdrive motivators for his X-wing so he could fly to Coruscant and prefent Ackbar's political expulsion, but Sluissi defense craft were given top priority

NAME: Sluis Van Orbit Dock V-475
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: site of beginning of Battle of Sluis Van; Nartissteu (freighter) explored close to this station; 4,846m long

NAME: Sluis Van Outer Starfighter Base
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: NR military installation primarily used as starfighter base; flight instruction also carried out here; Noell Ciro (trainee from Dolomar) underwent pilot training here and qualified for active military service in NR Starfighter Corps in 4 ABY

NAME: Bpfassh
INTERESTING: arid double planet orbited by a complicated system of moons; site of a Jedi Praxeum; near start of CW, Nejaa Halcyon and his crew were stranded for months after Zozridor Slayke disabled his Scarlet Thranta and stole Halcyon's Plooriod Bodkin; Praxeum joined CIS-aligned Jensaarai and was site of Dark Jedi uprising later in CW, quelled by Yoda; Thrawn feinted here; Noghri attacked Rebel heroes here

NAME: Lonjair Prime system
INTERESTING: Lonjair: shy, half-meter tall (average) self-centered species that primarily occupied a cluster of 3 systems in the galaxy's South Arm and had four turquoise eyes, indigo skin, and a tuft of blue hair on top of their heads; had a representative in Imperial Center during GCW

NAME: Queyta
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: CIS base that operated as a chemical plant here, which was on an island that was floating down a river of lava; three Jedi Masters visited the base and were killed by Asajj Ventress and Durge; Obi-Wan survived and was able to obtain the antidote to Jenna Zan Arbor's swamp gas

NAME: Polordio system
INTERESTING: origin point of Polordion smootdust (drug)

NAME: Eedoq
INTERESTING: ruled by Camblian Order

NAME: Denab
INTERESTING: prior to Yavin, Alliance starfighters led by Grisserno (Commander) defeated Imperial Fourth Attack Squadron (VSDs) here

NAME: Malo VI
INTERESTING: warrant issued here for arrest of Tegist Byrg (governor of neutral planet Glova but secretly working with Empire)

NAME: Kalab
INTERESTING: known to be frequented by smugglers

NAME: Agora
INTERESTING: population 10 - 100 M; Sluis sector remained loyal to Republic for centuries but quickly seceded during CW; Freedom's Sons attempted to hold planet but fell to Seperatists around time of Battle of Cerea

NAME: Kerest's star
INTERESTING: this red giant underwent a radical reduction in energy output, sending Kerest into a perpetual ice age

NAME: Kerest
INTERESTING: Kerestians: established sophisticated society in antiquity, developed repulsorlifts and sublight drives, colonized nearby moons and dispatched sleeper colony ships; planet entered a vast ice age throughout history of Republic and Empire due to dimming of its star; once technologically sophisticated, those Kerestians who had not moved offworld devolved into savages in the frozen wastes

NAME: Pharna
INTERESTING: colonized by Kerestians in antiquity, but later abandoned after Kerest's star dimmed

NAME: Karoliston
INTERESTING: colonized by Kerestians in antiquity, but later abandoned after Kerest's star dimmed

NAME: Darlo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: 50,250 LY from Core

NAME: Ness
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Dagobah
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: swamps, forests, vast mud fields, caves
INTERESTING: hundreds of years BBY, Minch (Jedi) killed a powerful Bpfasshi Dark Jedi here, whose energies tainted the cave where he diedl served as Yoda's refuge after Order 66; reachable only by obscure hyperlanes, appeared on few charts; discovered and forgotten several times; few truly open bodies of water; home to many creatures; Tash: 8m forest giants, reclusive, worm-like, skilled craftsbeings

NAME: Undar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Bubbok
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Sty
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Hysalria system
INTERESTING: Hysalrians: four-armed, four-eyed semi-serpentine sentients

NAME: Farboon
INTERESTING: Maarek Stele (TIE pilot) rescued Imperial Admiral Mordon's shuttle from an X-wing and Y-wing attack here

NAME: Metharian Nebula
PARENT: Outer Rim/Metharian Nebula Territories//Tantra, Elrood, Danjar/unknown
INTERESTING: contained Metharian Nebula Territories (elrood, Tantra, and Danjar sectors

NAME: Hyder
INTERESTING: homeworld of Trask Lucan (NR agent)

NAME: Utozz Prime system
INTERESTING: shared name with Utozz Prime Brewery (corporation that manufactured Utozz (a brand of the Utoz beverage)

NAME: Arkonne III
INTERESTING: home of (human) business rivals Divina Quri Adner and Phean Tic'Karcta; Phean sabotaged Divina's vehicle, killing her; Divina's beau Wilek Nereus personally killed Phean and removed her teeth

NAME: Tarabba system
INTERESTING: center of communication, commerce in sector

NAME: Glova
INTERESTING: semi-tropical world colonized c. 195 BBY; mines abandoned when precious metals ran dry; inhabitants turned to farming; became leading food supplier in region; declared neutral in 4 ABY; population 100,000; following Endor, NR kept an embassy here; NR First Fleet drove Delvardus's forces from Glova, which prevented him from joining with Imperial forces in Elrood/Minos sectors

NAME: Camaria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Camarian crystal (mineral)

NAME: Tantra
INTERESTING: 2 continents; locked deep in an ice age by time of GCW; landmasses covered in km-deep ice, oceans frozen over; atmosphere poisonous; Tantrans lived in sealed-off settlements, some buried deep under ice, others built on top of frozen ocean; surface structures linked by enclosed tunnels or elevated monorail tracks; spaceports built atop the ice had landing pads built on special substructures to protect the glacier ice from engine heat

NAME: Rhamsis Callo
INTERESTING: during GCW, Schenor gov't signed a treaty to allow Imperials to construct a base on the surface, but treaty was nullified after nest-guildmaster B'karitz learned of an Imperial-backed massacre of Schenor colonists at a research station

NAME: Qexis
INTERESTING: high-security research planet with single spaceport; few knew it existed

NAME: Yrrna system
INTERESTING: Imperial cargo transfer area located here until attacked in 3 ABY by the Nami, led by Ali Tarrak who sent a full force of their TIE Defenders (built from a prototype captured from the Empire) to destroy facility in a demonstration in hopes of selling the fighters to the Alliance; facility's personnel were saved by freighter Ulzepdi during a reactionary strike by Maarek Stele

NAME: DeGerrillion
INTERESTING: Marg Sonat and Pari' Notgoth (criminals) almost killed here

NAME: Lumea
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Sevarcos II
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: canyons, mountains, plains, deserts, subterranean tunnels & water networks
INTERESTING: only inhabitable planet in system; only source for carsunum, andris (spice variants); Dooku negotiated Sevarcos Dispute in 52 BBY (had consequences for galactic history, rise of Empire; southern hemisphere covered in deserts; northern hemisphere mountainous; vast equatorial plains; harsh winds caused gale-force sandstorms: "The World of Endless Wind"; underground networks of water

NAME: Fujar Prime *
INTERESTING: Tertiary Fujar suggests Fujar Prime and Secondary Fujar

NAME: Secondary Fujar *
INTERESTING: Tertiary Fujar suggests Fujar Prime and Secondary Fujar

NAME: Bengely
INTERESTING: seedy world with dangerous reputation

NAME: Kirdo III
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, hills, arid mud plains, quicksand, caves, temporary lakes & rivers after rainfall
INTERESTING: winds often blew at speeds of 400kph or more; rainfall once a decade; herds of migrating chooba grazed on sulfaro plants and hunted by Kitonaks; discovered by scouts a few decades before rise of Empire; Luke forged a new hyperroute between Kirdo and Orto Plutonia on way back from Rodia; Eye of Palpatine stopped here, took Kitonaks onboard when it couldn't find stormtroopers

NAME: Tertiary Fujar
INTERESTING: Fujari pirates were particularly active in amarin and Rseik sectors about 2 centuries before fall of Old Republic, until they were defeated by the Trade Defense Force (military arm of Trade Federation)

NAME: Rantine Space Station
NOTES: WP article lacks coords
INTERESTING: located on edge of Tamarin sector, about 6 days' hyperspace travel from Kwenn Station

NAME: Skustell
INTERESTING: Ongree: amphibious; became part of Republic, although its people were not often seen offworld; planet was mostly covered in water; rumored that a golden waterfall hid the entrance of a cave which hid treasures; homeworld of Jedi Master Coleman Kcaj

NAME: Utapau
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, plains, rocky areas, scrublands, giant sinkholes
INTERESTING: 51,000 LY from core; had small, molten metallic core, rocky mantle, and rocky, calcareous crust; only 0.9% of the planet's surface was covered by water, though a vast subterranean ocean encircled the planet below the crust (planet once had surface oceans that leaked away through the readily eroded crust; vast mineral deposits below underground ocean were great source of mineral wealth

NAME: Deretta
INTERESTING: staging point of Deretta Destroyers (Rebel Alliance mixed starfighter squadron) until destruction prior to Hoth

NAME: Laria
INTERESTING: during Cold War between Republic and reconstituted Sith Empire, archaeologists were trying to restore a dozen star-charts discovered in the databases of old ruins; sometime after the Bordal Contagion, the Trade Federation upgraded its spaceport here

NAME: Valo
INTERESTING: during the High Republic era, the Republic hosted the Republic Fair on Valo, which dignitaries and visitors attended from across the galaxy; a Nihil attack left much of the planet destroyed and hundreds of thousands dead; Elzar Mann was the marshal of Valo's Jedi Temple; in the Imperial era, the world was famed for its barbeques

NAME: Rindoon system
INTERESTING: shared name with Rindoon Dart (spaceship)

NAME: Sloogaria system
INTERESTING: Sloogarians: slimy, slug-like, known to enjoy eating bantha droppings and other waste most species usually found disgusting; known for stretching the truth for profit

NAME: Lanjer
INTERESTING: remote; defied Emperor Palpatine shortly after Empire's formation; suffered an unspecified devastation as a result

NAME: Baffop
INTERESTING: Empire ravaged Baffop before Yavin, leading to many civilian casualties; Anselm (human male) born here in 32 BBY and joined Rebellion after devastation; by 9 ABY, Baffop was situated in space either conquered by or allied with Thrawn's confederation

NAME: Breshkall
INTERESTING: hidden space station base used by Prengahl Kreen (Twi'lek arms dealer) as refuge for family, friends, servants, trusted associates; rumored to be heavily armed; Kreen did no business here (operating instead in the Hook Nebula's Empartheca system)

NAME: Drexel II
INTERESTING: lacked proper name; also known as the "Waterworld of Drexel"; ocean-covered with no dry land; catastrophe around 5000 BBY caused considerable disaster here; benevolent but unidentified species evacuated the Inleshat and relocated them to Iskalon; during YV War, a group of Gluss'sa'Niko established a colony here

NAME: Susevfi (Suarbi 7/5)
INTERESTING: settled by Corporate Sector expats in 400 BBY; history unknown until arrival of Nikkos Tyris (Anzat Dark Jedi, minion of Dooku, established Jensaarai cult, died at hands of Nejaa Halcyon); came under control of Empire; shortly before 11 ABY, Susevfi's Imperial governor was killed by Leonia Tavira after refusing her advances and her Invid pirates took up base here; Caamasi Remnant moved here

NAME: Kiilimaar
INTERESTING: site of a battle between Empire and Rneekii pirates shortly before Endor, which began with a dispute over an abducted TIE Defender R&D scientist held for ransom; the Imperials paid the ransom, then attacked the Rneekii pirate forces and took the ransom back

NAME: Sulloria system
INTERESTING: origin point of Sullorians

NAME: Svivren
INTERESTING: despite harsh climate and severe seasonal variation, native Svivreni thrived; important regional trading port; population 8+ B including large colonies of humans, Sullustans, Ewoks; had Festival of Great Trade; planetary law expressly forbid weapons; violent acts immediately resulted in public execution, carried out by well-armed security forces; low crime rate; avoided by smugglers

NAME: Buula's Rocky Home
INTERESTING: asteroid base of Buula Nen (Chevin crimelord) and his raiders; hideout, smuggling hub, base of operations and primary slave pens; base full of pirates and fringers hoping to cash in on Nen's enterprises but once recruited, they found themselves deep in a game of lies and deceit, in which Nen held all the cards; main docking bay had room for three light freighters

NAME: Bront
INTERESTING: around 0 ABY, the Empire committed atrocities on Bront that led to the destruction of the planet and the deaths of Graf Yonna's family, driving him insane and leading him to assume the personality of Parsol d'Ahndole, an ancient adventurer and hero

NAME: Maryx Minor
INTERESTING: Spectres (Rebel cell) looked to establish a base here at some point between 5 and 4 BBY, but quickly left after an eruption caused a lot of damage to the Ghost; hermitage of Ancient Order of Pessimists

NAME: Ab'Bshingh
INTERESTING: Farang and Waroot fought continuously for centuries; Crat Dakerno (Imperial military strategist) traveled here to study them and drew on their tribal rituals and centuries-old tactics to create B'shingh (holo boardgame)

NAME: Parmic system
INTERESTING: during GCW, contained a research facility operated by Demetrius Zaarin (Imperial Grand Admiral), in which he equipped his TIE squadrons with a new beam weapon after Hoth, setting off a short arms race with the Rebel Alliance

NAME: Torch Nebula
NOTES: unplaced planet Guat'a nearby

NAME: Piluvia system
INTERESTING: shared name with Piluvian salamander-storm (phenomenon characterized by constant motion and noise)

NAME: Fallowan
INTERESTING: agriworld; site of Imperial base infiltrated by Han and Leia

NAME: Orto Plutonia
INTERESTING: home to Talz and narglatches; considered a protectorate of Pantora (its moon) until Pantorans discovered the Talz and them political self-determination after a brief conflict during CW (resolved by Anakin and Obi-Wan)

NAME: Pantora
INTERESTING: member of Galactic Republic with full senatorial representation; had feudal system of government which eventually developed into democratic system presided over by the Pantoran Assembly; received Republic outpost as protection against CIS; later blockaded by Lott Dod and Trade Federation; cut off from galaxy when Republic collapsed; Pantoran assembly was divided over response to rise of Empire

NAME: Alzoc III
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: frozen wastelands, arctic tundra, mountains, mines
INTERESTING: part of Infinite Empire c. 30,000 BBY - 25,000 BBY; sporadically visited throughout Republic era; major introduction to galactic society was through Imperial scouts; roch with natural resources; Empire secretly enslaved Talz natives as miners, using them to extract ore and valuable Alzoc Pearls; Imperials withdrew after Endor; NR later discovered records, established contact

NAME: Skynara
INTERESTING: surrounding space explored between 1000 BBY and 25 BBY; shared name with luxury yacht Veil of Skynara (carried famous and valuable Balved Sculpture); population 1 - 10 M

NAME: Karazak
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: one of Outer Rim's slavery capitals (along with Zygerria and Thalassian system); Karazak Slavers Cooperative used tunnels and caves here as HQ; in 4 ABY, Lormar-class space station Whitedrift Exchange (mobile trading post, residential station) arrived in orbit

NAME: Askkto-Fen
INTERESTING: Lexo Sooger was raised in the slave pits here before becoming a masseuse at Zord's Spa and Bathhouse in Canto Bight on Cantonica

NAME: Syni IV
INTERESTING: Sotorus Ramda (commander of Syni IV's Imperial garrison) once crushed a local insurrection when Rebel forces attempted to besiege the garrison and cut the system off by jamming subspace communications; the Rebels bombarded the facility using over-the-horizon artillery from outside the garrison's weapons range; loss of comm contact led Imperial sector command to send an ISD

NAME: Wodenstam
INTERESTING: served as homeworld of Lucross Collections (loan sharking, credit laundering operation, Tenloss Syndicate member) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Skine
INTERESTING: capital city bombarded by xenophobic Advozse Hegemony using Hammer Station during the Cold War when the city refused to surrender; location of Skine Bounty Hunter College by GCW era

NAME: Lucrenn
INTERESTING: served as homeworld of Galindas Exports (fencing operation, Tenloss Syndicate member) c. 10 ABY

NAME: Nedij
INTERESTING: Nediji: avians who evolved in the thin air, rarely left homeworld, worshiped the Cosmic Egg, preferred snowy mountains over lowlands; a species of humanoids served as prey for Nediji; homeworld of Kaird (Nediji Black Sun operative)

NAME: Bentora system
INTERESTING: shared name with region known as Bentora Space (home to a group called the Chyakk clan, not to be confused with the Wookiee Chyakk clan)

NAME: Sabrix
INTERESTING: mining operation led by Denedin extracted radioactive elements here to fund Sabrin Ring (criminal organization whose operations were limited to the worlds of the Sabrixin system)

NAME: Helisk
INTERESTING: Sabrin Ring operated here

NAME: Elokas
INTERESTING: Sabrin Ring operated here

NAME: Yanibar
INTERESTING: barely habitable; known for blistering, dry summers and wet, frigid winters; colonized by a group of Jedi and their relatives seeking refuge from Sith predations; forgotten by the Jedi in the rest of the galaxy and remained isolated for years; many colonists didn't survive harsh conditions, but survivors developed Zeison Sha (Force tradition); later became a stopping point for fringe traders

NAME: Guudria system
INTERESTING: Guudrians: short stature, warty, wrinkled faces, short snouts, wild manes of hair, blunt teeth, clawed fingers, eyes had pattern of black checks; Guudrians relatively unknown away from their homeworld

NAME: Havoc Outpost
INTERESTING: Havoc Outpost was a rebel rendezvous point in Wild Space used by the fledging rebellion, located on the edge of a cliff overlooking a river. In 4 BBY, Sabine Wren of the rebel crew of the Ghost brought GNK-series power droid EG-86, who carried information for the rebellion, to Havoc Outpost. It was delivered to the astromech droid R2-D2, acting on behalf of Senator Bail Organa of Alderaan

NAME: Baralou
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungle islands, barren rock islands, oceans
INTERESTING: four moons caused violent storms and tremendous 50 m tidal shifts; many gemstones found here; most plants had deep root systems and at least trace poisons that affected non-natives; Krikthasi (undersea) and Multopos (amphibious) were stone age cultures and enemies; Aqualis (Rebel) Base provided many foodstuffs to Alliance; Aqualis Food Conglomerate also operated here

NAME: Crytal Nest
INTERESTING: Shashay: sentient avians renowned as singers, astrogators; kept planet location a secret to prevent plunder by Empire;

NAME: Dosuun
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forests, hilly grasslands, lakes, mountains, seas
INTERESTING: saved by an ancient group called The Architects through the construction of Breeze, Rain, and Solstice Globes. Together, the globes powered a machine which regulated the planet's environment within a partially underground chamber called the Chamber of the Sun

NAME: Seoul 5
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: home to ancient Pre-Republic era Human civilization later wiped out; initially conquered by the Rakata during the height of their Empire; they may have brought Human slaves here; archaeologists studied ruins here, finding legends that all Human life originated on a mysterious planet known as Notron (now Coruscant); Han destroyed an Imperial base here and most of the planet with it

NAME: Mephout
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: capital of Mephout Dominion; discovered by the Empire during GCW; home to the Plintep Cybernetics Corporation

NAME: Dyspeth
INTERESTING: shadowy moon settled by Human colonists c. 900 BBY when they broke away from Republic; Twilight (mysterious woman) united some of the Force-sensitive colonists to form the Disciples of Twilight (Force-based organization that defended the population but held no political or military power and spread to nearby systems once Dyspeth rediscovered by Republic survey team c. 500 BBY)

NAME: The Clar
INTERESTING: Barosa Warren (Morellian scout) and Casti Tholon (his human student at the Galactic Oudoor Survival School visited here by 2 ABY and explored and charted VIvab deserts

NAME: Needan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, jungles (before), freezing wastes, domed cities (after)
INTERESTING: formerly a jungle world, it was struck by a passing comet just as its civilization was entering the information age; climate cooled suddenly, but Geelans survived ensuing mass extinction by sheltering inside dome-like habitats; eventually an Arcona-crewed medical starship picked up distress signals and facilitated a mass emigration of the Geelan from their doomed homeworld

NAME: Olabria
INTERESTING: home to Olabrian trichoid parasite, which could easily be fatal to its hosts

NAME: Woern's Asteroid
INTERESTING: one of largest asteroids in field; mineral composition interfered with ships' sensors, which Laerron Woern (Elomin pirate) made use of to hide a pirate base; in 7 ABY a group of individuals discovered base, leading to a NR assault on asteroid; population: 200

NAME: Cantros 7
INTERESTING: Cantrosians: felinoids, many of whom joined the Rebel Alliance

NAME: Lust system
INTERESTING: origin point of Lost Sultans of Lust (group who dined with Human scholar Ebenn Q3 Baobab at some point prior to 6 ABY)

NAME: Anoth
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Manpha
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: attacked by Nagai invaders in 4 ABY; homeworld of Rappertunie (Shawda Ubb musician); city of Shanpan was home to world's only spaceport (the only area of the city that saw regular traffic from the rest of the galaxy)

NAME: Renforra
INTERESTING: site of Alliance base during height of GCW; Jon "Dutch" Vander led Specter Squadron's Y-wings from his HQ

NAME: Mydasos
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: marshlands, shallow seas, continent-spanning forests interspersed with craggy mountains
INTERESTING: nearly undiscovered backwater; Phylodons: spiritual Force-aware symbiotes consisting of mammalian humanoid Agarans, fungal rhizome Orucytes (both had consciousnesses, but Phylodons were both a pair of individuals and a blanded whole with intra-species gestalt consciousness); lived in close-kni groups across the planet; rarely left planet because symbiotes would feel isolated if distanced from rhizome

NAME: Faldos
INTERESTING: dirty backwater world used by smugglers to sell stolen weapons, armor, tech; attacked by Nagai invaders in 4 ABY

NAME: Spee
INTERESTING: visited by Roark Garnet (smuggler)

NAME: Anto's Star system
INTERESTING: shared name with Anto's Star (CR90 corvette used by pirate Drek Drednar and crew)

NAME: Relkass
INTERESTING: home of Relkass sentinel plant (type of cactus-like plant which contained powerful narcotic compound in its juice); during dry season, draagax (nocturnal pack creatures) fed on sentinel plants, inducing a state of frenzy that caused them to attack other creatures on sight; local ranchers posted bounties on draagax pelts;

NAME: Saijo
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: part of Alliance of Free Planets until conquered by the Nagai; later taken by Tofs and became location of Nagai-Tof War; by 130 ABY, was a colony and fortress world of Nagai; became a heavily-defended planet of Krayt's Empire by 130 ABY

NAME: Fwatna
INTERESTING: Lando found Spicy Lady (abandoned freighter belonging to his smuggling associate Jarril) here; population less than 1 M

NAME: Polis Massa
INTERESTING: once a barren, arid, habitable planetoid and homeworld of Eellayin civilization, which dwelt in underground cities such as Wiyentaah, but it was struck by mysterious cataclysm, which shattered planetoid into an asteroid belt; Eellayin disappeared; around 519 BBY Kallidahin abandoned Kallidah and established Polis Massa Research Base here, trying to prove the Eellayin were their ancestors

NAME: Zi'Dek system
INTERESTING: a system in the logs of a starship located at Dathomir Imperial Prison; Han used to make smuggling runs through this system

NAME: Katchan
grid square/sector/on Corellian TS near border with Saijo sector
INTERESTING: Katchani: olive-skinned, elfish humanoids ruled by monarchy; planet had two large continents separated only by narrow sea; royal family owned an A9G-series Data Storage Unit (humanoid droid) until it was stolen by pirates

NAME: Grava
INTERESTING: the Empire operated an asylum here, but it was later inhabited by the Brotherhood of Wire and Bone

NAME: Terminus
INTERESTING: infested with pirates, such as Ohnaka Gang; Spirit of Jedha's hyperdrive motivator was sabotaged, leading it to drop out of hyperspace and drift here in 3 ABY; highly trafficked port despite remote location; proximity to Wild Space and Unknown Regions meant strange and unfamiliar ships were a common sight; under influence of Gorensla Hutt clan by GCW; Alliance of Free Planets battled Nagai here

NAME: Duhma system
INTERESTING: located on major space lane yet receives little traffic

NAME: Rutan
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: traditional hunts, meat feasts most days of the week; Rutanians and offshoot Senali warred throughout history; Senali won, but conflict was so devastating that both species' rulers exchanged firstborn children from ages 7 to 16; Jedi mediated when Rutan leader's son refused to return; pirate raids stopped by Empire in 18 BBY; attacked by Nagai in in 4 ABY

NAME: Senali
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Senali colonists were offshoot of Rutanians; subsisted mostly on fish and fruit

NAME: Esyvam
INTERESTING: possibly also known as Esyram system

NAME: Ather
INTERESTING: manufacturing world; travel from Ather to Dravian Starport took 2 days with a Class 1 hyperdrive; during GCW, Dravian Starport-based company Nar Shaddaa Shipping offered free-traders a job transporting 50 tons of datapad circuit boards to Ather for 3,500 credits

NAME: Phosphura Belt Nebula
INTERESTING: Phosphura Belt Pirates took their name from the nebula; contained Zirtran's Anchor after it vanished from the Besberra system

NAME: Zirtran's Anchor
INTERESTING: shadowport; originally located in Besberra system; mysteriously disappeared and later reappeared in Phosphura Belt Nebula; consisted of a number of starships joined by accessways and pressure tunnels, changing shape frequently as ships arrive and depart; free-trader's paradise

NAME: Trosh
INTERESTING: one of many planets whose natives were enslaved by the Empire, while it claimed it was protecting the rights of the inhabitants

NAME: The Pangarees
INTERESTING: region of agriworlds whose farming firms were dominated by Eriaduan interests; traveling from Eriadu, spacers were advised to stop over at Triton

NAME: Ochotl
INTERESTING: Ochotl Ag (company) harvested chak-root plant here; homeworld of Kob Mondray (galaxy-renowned shockball player); by 22 BBY, Ochotl Ag was ruined by its competitors, and its orbital depots were destroyed in a pirae attack; during CW Ochotl and Airam sector joined CIS

NAME: Ochotl Ag Orbital Depots
INTERESTING: destroyed during pirate attack

NAME: Nodgra system
INTERESTING: located between Coyn and Socorro (cannot be correct due to sector placements)

NAME: Repair Yard KDY-77
INTERESTING: Telgorn Corporation repair facility; Interdictor Compellor scheduled for repairs and maintenance here, but was hijacked by Rebel strike team during Battle of Swellen

NAME: Aiquin
INTERESTING: during GCW, Rebels staged attack in Aiquin 4 system to capture clan leader Ilay who was attempting peace settlement with Empire (succeeded, repelled Imperial forces at Nocto and fortified sector)

NAME: Elliirad Platform
INTERESTING: Imperial XQ6 Platform serving as a cargo transfer station under Commander Klavisor; targeted by Rebels in an assault featuring the Katarn Commandos in which at least 2,400 metric tons of cargo, 5 exterior fuel modeules, a Class-H Hypermatter Reactor Core, and 2 Strike-class Cruisers were stolen or destroyed, despite the ISD Striker running defense

NAME: Mylok IV
INTERESTING: Demetrius Zaarin (Imperial Grand Admiral) became interested in this planet when its two native species developed a new hyperdrive technology, though by 3 ABY they were embroiled in civil war; Habeen appealed for Imperial support; Nharwaak turned to Rebels; As Habeen were turning over hyperdrive tech to Imperials, Rebels and Nharwaak tried to ambush the summit but were routed

NAME: Goff Platform
INTERESTING: XQ5 Supply Platform used by the Airam, and supplied Rebels as well; defended by 2 IPV-1 Patrol Craft, 2 Squadrons of R-41 Starchasers, and shuttles; ISD Rage and Interdictor Compellor captured the station and were then attacked by a Rebel Nebulon-B Frigate, which was subsequently destroyed; later, Imperial Battlegroup Orion was ambushed and destroyed here by the Alliance

NAME: Blair Cluster
INTERESTING: vast asteroid field; first region targeted by Wooyou Senn (Imperial Admiral) in Task Force Vengeance pacification campaign; Imperials blockaded cluster with Interdictor Compellor to pull any transport vessels out of hyperspace and detain them, while ISD Rage launched Avenger Squadron's modified TIE Interceptors to induce the trapped ships to surrender

NAME: Nocto system
INTERESTING: site of Battle of Nocto, during which SSD Vengeance and Rebel shipyard Calenz were destroyed in 3 ABY

NAME: Nocto
INTERESTING: prior to CW, pirates from Nocto attacked Ochotl's orbital depots

NAME: Calenz
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance Telgorn shipyard destroyed during Battle of Nocto in 3 ABY

NAME: Chundu
INTERESTING: shared name with Chundu Shunt (realspace location, interpreted to be hyperlane)

NAME: Dravin system
INTERESTING: shared name with Dravin Cut (realspace location, interpreted to be hyperlane)

NAME: Kallidah
INTERESTING: planet abandoned by Kallidahin after Archaeological Research Council established a Research Base on Polis Massa asteroid colony to try to uncover evidence of evolutionary link between Kallidahin and extinct Eellayin natives

NAME: Besberra
INTERESTING: original location of Zirtran's Anchor space station before it mysteriously disappeared and reappeared later in the Phosphura Belt Nebula

NAME: Makthierse
INTERESTING: home of lacas (herd animals massing about 300 kilos, raised on ranches by locals, and preyed on by...) makthiers (blind, sonar-equipped flying predators that looked like insect larvae with leathery, bat-like wings, long, thin mandibles and a tail with a stinger); Quantrax Creek located here

NAME: Orax
INTERESTING: discovered in 119 BBY; known for wondrous mineral formations; many Shard ambassadors operating offworld were murdered with rise of Empire; Orax became mining center using slave labor; many Shard colonies were destroyed; Shard allied with Alliance to free their homeworld

NAME: Subterrel
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: widely known for extensive mining operations, worked by many Kaminoan-created clones known as shovel-handed miners; Dexter Jettster spent some time prospecting here

NAME: Vizcarra
INTERESTING: Imperial prison planet; Tait Ransom (smuggler) scheduled to be sent here after smuggling weapons on Omman

NAME: Dega
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: rocky wastelands, barren hills, abandoned mines

NAME: Kur Nebula
INTERESTING: bright green nebula; site of Battle of Kur, in which the Nihil force of Kassav Milliko's Tempest were sent to their deaths against a combined Republic/Jedi fleet by the Eye of he Nihil, Marchion Ro

NAME: Delfii system
INTERESTING: site of "deep space" Rebel Alliance summit prior to Endor

NAME: Gesaril
INTERESTING: dense jungle appeared to float above a noxious swamp; Gesaril: furry, hyperactive creatures classified as barely sentient by Imperials; 9 Imperial ships crashed in exactly the same coastal area (reason unknown); planet was put under strict quarantine; tribal governments; population: 16 M

NAME: Gesaril Prison Colony
INTERESTING: Imperial prison colony on a large asteroid in far orbit around star; cells for 1,300 prisoners were hollowed out of the rock, spaced widely along kms of corridor; large tube in asteroid's center led to ships' dock; Intrepid (light cruiser) stationed here to enforce planetary quarantine, guard prison; held Minos Cluster's long-term prisoners; held 1,000 inmates, roughly half criminals, half political

NAME: Travnin
INTERESTING: orbited a gas giant (sole planet in the double-star system); sector capital; swept by intense winds; main settlement Travnin Spaceport; The Grand Design (cantina), a Sector Interdiction office, and HQ of Delgad (smuggler) located here; local underworld was controlled by Tecknel Shnick; economy plummeted when Empire withdrew; most coreward inhabited world in Minos Cluster; population: 140 M

NAME: Eliad
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, plains, valleys, plateaus, deserts, variousv
INTERESTING: planet contained all types of biomes; population: 6 M; palaces, villas, replica castles dotted the world; planet had some mineral exports; rich nobles with nothing to spend credits on developed increasingly demented forms of entertainment; Battle of Eliad was significant in Minos Cluster Campaign; Palpatine exiled 300,000 nobles here; Leia debated nobles to convince them to aid Rebels

NAME: Wadi Raffa
NOTES: actually in Western Reaches?
INTERESTING: legacy planet (protected from exploitation or environmental damage); the Empire hired Ranos Yalli and Has Obitt to transport old Seperatist weapons here so the Empire could "discover" them and thus remove the world's Legacy status, opening it to heavy doonium and dolovite mining -- crucial materials for the development of the Death Star project

NAME: Yoberra
INTERESTING: home to Jomo's species (eight-legged)

NAME: Paradise system
INTERESTING: once contained the Ugor homeworld, which had vast natural resources but was overpopulated and polluted by Ugors, who evolved to survive in such conditions; after developing spaceflight and moving offworld, the Ugors sliced up every planet in the system over the course of a century to make way for a system-spanning junkyard of asteroid belts

NAME: The Holy of Holies
INTERESTING: this 40,000 ton unrecognizable piece of one of the Death Stars contains a gravity well generator the Ugors have managed to reactivate and use to construct orbiting rings of debris, asteroids and planetoids; they revere this generator as a religious icon; at some point Rebel operatives tried to steal the gravity well generator

NAME: Ugor junk ring
INTERESTING: the Ugors have carefully arranged the asteroid remains of their system's planets as well as the junk they continually collect (or that is dumped by others in their star system) into concentric rings

NAME: Ytha'ac Cluster
INTERESTING: Rebel operatives were scheduled to meet Airam smugglers who had stolen Imperial munitions, but the Empire sent a strike force of Assault Gunboats and Gamma-class ATR-6 assault transports to recover the weapons

NAME: Rocrin system
INTERESTING: Task Force Vengeance set up an ambush to destroy a Rebel convoy with the ISD Rage and the Interdictor Compellor here; Avenger Squadron IDed the convoy contents and destroyed every ship with the help of TIE Bombers

NAME: Mobetta system
INTERESTING: was apparently one of the more industrialized systems in the Airam sector

NAME: Soren
INTERESTING: Rebel Alliance X7 Deep Space Manufacturing Facility; following unsuccessful attempt to destroy Compellor (Imperial Interdictor) at the Goff Platform, Soren was discovered by the Empire and Task Force Vengeance sent the ISD Rage to disable and destroy the factory and uncover additional rebel activity; Rebel evacuation attempts failed

NAME: Gallofree
INTERESTING: AIram-owned X7 Deep Space Manufacturing Facility; in 3 ABY, used by Rebel Alliance to transfer the Compellor's gravity well generators to the modified Strike Cruiser Peregrine; during the process, the factory came under attack twice by Imperial forces; a third attack by two ISDs and 3 Corvettes forced the Airam to abandon the factory with cover from their Rebel allies

NAME: Bes system
INTERESTING: shortly before Battle of Nocto in 3 ABY, a resupply operation for the ISD Rage came under attack from Rebel forces during first Battle of Bes; shortly afterward, a combined Rebel / Airam force failed to destroy the Rage in the Second Battle of Bes

NAME: Squab
NOTES: info about Squab being a small red star could be added to WP article

NAME: Skor II
INTERESTING: small world with vast natural resources; system of government called the polyanarchy, headed by a king; Metrobig City (major city) was site of Metrobig Interplanetary Blastport; Squibs evolved an innate bargaining instinct, which later allowed them to trade for hyperspace tech and rise to galactic prominence; Republic loyalists, invaded by CIS in 21 BBY

NAME: Onadax
INTERESTING: small world thick with dust drifts; in early days, small planet was an agglomeration of asteroids and had rampant mynock population; Han played sabacc against a Givin and was accused of cheating after a very unlikely hand; location of Onadax Droid Technologies (specialized in Human Replica Droids) compound infiltrated by Jaina Solo

NAME: Jillsaria system
INTERESTING: Jillsarians: muscular, 2+ m tall, four-armed humanoids, some with orange skin, some with brown fur

NAME: Dorcin
INTERESTING: a Dorcin trader traded starship technology to the Squibs in exchange for mineral rights to a frozen waste on Skor II

NAME: Mestra
INTERESTING: no planets; had one of most expansive asteroid fields in galaxy, including Javis-12; at least some asteroids hosted mining operations (rich deposits of durelium ore, valuable in hyperdrive construction); no accurate count was made, but estimated 100 trillion sizable chunks of rock in system, hundreds the size of small moons;

NAME: Javis-12
INTERESTING: roughly egg-shaped, 400km wide; only asteroid in Mestra system with any sort of landing beacon or starport, ship repair and refual services (charge was 200% of list price); spaceport consisted of series of domes, caves, located on edge of asteroid belt; all spin was removed, and spaceport faced away from the belt, making it fairly safe from asteroid strikes

NAME: Talcim Cluster
INTERESTING: had abandoned, forgotten mining facility that was used by the Empire as a staging point for 16 stolen Rebel Delta-class JV-7 escort shuttles, in a plan to attack Rebel-friendly sites in the Airam Sector with biological weapons to frame them

NAME: Askaj
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: no central government, but rather tribal societies; technology not very advanced; Tomuon (long-horned, woolly herd animals) were central to the lives of the Askajians, who used them for food, shelter, fabric, other items; under administration of Grand Moff Wilkadon, whose oppression drove many Askajians offworld to Tatooine; liberated by NR sometime after Endor

NAME: Moon Lady
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: primary moon of Askaj; revered as a deity by the Askajians

NAME: Vo Tunbren
INTERESTING: location of Imperial communications research facility; Jeres Moridon (later assigned to oversee construction of backup HoloNet system on forest moon of Endor) stationed here

NAME: Rystan
INTERESTING: freezing world with a habitable band that could sustain some life, like the slarga; Marchion Ro of the Nihil met his cousin Kufa here, requesting that she take him and the Talortai Udi Dis to a location known as the Shrine in the Golamaran Ice Flats

NAME: Shesharile
INTERESTING: a number of moons orbited Shesharile, two of which supported life (known as "the Twin Planets"; both societies collapsed after drug trafficker Shlith-dan introduced an addictive fungus

NAME: Shesharile 5
INTERESTING: gov't employed the legally Authorized Law Authorities (private law enforcement agency based in Gallisport); capital: Gallisport (crowded, run-down); Dutan Mining Supply Exports also based in Gallisport; society collapsed due to introduction of addictive fungus

NAME: Shesharile 6
INTERESTING: entire moon was almost unbrearable due to smell produced when first spring heat activated the bacteria in underground waste-sinks; Callista Ming (Jedi Knight) stopped here at some point in her travels; society collapsed due to introduction of addictive fungus

NAME: Yelsain
INTERESTING: homeworld of many Jedi; some trees as tall as 400m; atmosphere high in oxygen (offworlders got dizzy at first); famed for spectacular near-nightly thunderstorms; large animals 2x size of human on average, some dangerous carnivores; home of trogliths and garaths (two most dangerous creatures); systematic denial of basic rights by Empire; capital: Tradetown; population 4.5 B

NAME: Adarlon
INTERESTING: colonized 250 BBY by Republic altruists (many from Alderaan) for beauty rather than resources; became tourism hotspot; known for music, holographic entertainment; home to one of the most famous opera companies in the galaxy and Neile Janna (famous opera singer); warm climate was well-suited to various resorts and parks; population: 20 M

NAME: Pernam Minor
INTERESTING: Kassar Kosciusko (male Tarro, owner of Royal K Hotel & Casino on Kwenn Station, secret Rebel operative) saved life of Meysen Kayson (owned greel wood logging company, owned a percentage of holdings of Kwenn Station) here

NAME: Karideph
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
NOTES: not a true ecumenopolis as WP tags it
INTERESTING: discovered 3956 - 3681 BBY; invaded by Sith Empire during Great Galactic War but Republic counterattack drove them back; surface covered in carefully tiled ag fields (even mountains, coastlines) that supported population of 88 B; by GCW no original flora/fauna remained; fields dotted by several massive cities (upper levels had to be pressurized due to height); most Kari lived in deep tunnel systems

NAME: Quockra-4
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: flat, featureless deserts, vast salt flats
INTERESTING: never rained here; no oceans; dangerously hot during midday hours, dangerously cold at night; one city, located near spaceport, built largely underground to escape temperature extremes; larger galaxy assumed the world to be populated by droids of a thousand varieties, many of Imperial manufacture, some of unknown design; population: at least 10 M droids

NAME: Regellia
INTERESTING: homeworld of Nozzo Naytaan (Rebel Pilot); origin point of Regellian draught (alcoholic beverage, exported)

NAME: Tyrellia
INTERESTING: origin point of Tyrellian ale (alcoholic beverage)

NAME: Pergitor
NOTES: Listed as Rimma TR
