INTERESTING: excessive mining set off volcanic eruptions that poisoned atmosphere, destroyed ecosystems; inhabitants retreated to sealed cities; despot ruled planet for years before being overthrown by a group of young liberals in 37 BBY, resulting in disorganized democracy; just before CW, Church of Infinite Perception launched a counter-coup and installed a theocracy; Republic had tenuous association and could do nothing to stop the bloody revolt

NAME: Teh'Jar II
INTERESTING: Empire introduced a high technology ban here; Xenobiologists Dr. Angrail Rhyl and Nardo Sau searched for legendary Um'Tal ("Sky Stone") here

NAME: Haven
NOTES: above galactic plane
INTERESTING: small planetoid that served as rendezvous point for Rebel Alliance and primary resistance center in Minos Cluster; Alliance fleet regrouped here after Hoth in 3 ABY; Luke received prosthetic hand in orbit here

NAME: Taroon system
INTERESTING: in Imperial Space

NAME: Bordal
INTERESTING: humans were primary inhabitants; in 214 BBY Bordal Contagion broke out; 6 M doses of Republic-developed antidote were ruined when transports carrying them were attacked by Fujari pirates; millions of Bordali died until Rseikharhl began manufacturing the antidote; by 20 BBY, was still fighting a decades-old war with Kuan; no one remembered original cause; economy in ruins; Empire declared martial law

NAME: Kuan
INTERESTING: by 20 BBY, had warred for decades with neighboring Kuan, though no one remembered original cause; Empire had to intervene by sending an Imperial Navy fleet under Admiral Mordon; homeworld of Maarek Stele

NAME: Rseik
INTERESTING: at some point after 214 BBY, Kett family maintained investments on Rseik; Rseikharhl: technologically advanced, provided antidotes to Bordal Contagion in 214 BBY, and developed droids such as the LE-VO law enforcement droid, which they used across the sector; by the time of the Empire, Rseikharhl under Imperial jurisdiction and their droids had spread throughout galaxy

NAME: Frong
INTERESTING: located in fringe system orbiting dim star; no navy or defense fleet; looked to NR, Black Sun or Red Key Raiders for protection shortly before Jakku; Frong: face-tubules, big, glossy black eyes, long blue forearms lined with contracting suckers, insular, clannish, remained tightly-knit through borderline incestuous bloodlines; little to offer the galaxy but fruit, spice and clean water

NAME: Nalrith system
INTERESTING: Nalrithians: muscular four-eyed sentient insectoids; Nalrithians born from same clutch of eggs were known to share memories in a sort of hive mind;

NAME: Nalrith
INTERESTING: Nalrithians: muscular four-eyed sentient insectoids; Nalrithians born from same clutch of eggs were known to share memories in a sort of hive mind;

NAME: Delemede
INTERESTING: in 3643 BBY when Delemede was struck by plague, its Republic governor initially refused to provide medical aid to Sith Empire refugees; homeworld of Bosbit Matarcher (human male), whose starship suffered a hyperdrive malfunction in 212 BBY and was thrown 190 years forward to 22 BBY; he expressed delight because Delemede had been shoddy and run down when he left, but was now thriving

NAME: Ma'ar Shaddam
INTERESTING: Firmus Kett's family had investments here; home to Boba Fett's armorers; settled by Republic Master Weaponsmiths not only for quality of ore, but because remoteness made it difficult for authorities to police sale of illegal weaponry

NAME: Spindrift
INTERESTING: had Imperial base during GCW; Imperial troops here were previously stationed at Aduba-4, where one of them had a girlfriend; base was destroyed in an attack by Rebel Alliance's Flying Bantha Squadron, consisting of 4 modified TIE Fighters

NAME: Chortose
INTERESTING: during High Republic Era, a factory called Agricultural Hub 42 was attacked by Nihil marauders in the time leading up to the Republic Fair; Keeve Trennis (Jedi Knight) sent to defend Chortose, while Orla Jareni (Jedi Wayseeker) followed a distress signal there; homeworld of Porgo Goo (Chortose engineer and starship mechanic)

NAME: Corva Yag
INTERESTING: by 214 BBY, Hajara (pirate gang) established a presence here, raiding Kett Shipping convoys traveling across the Little Minos Run hyperlane; during time of Empire, about 300 colonists were supposedly clawed to death here by a malfunctioning scout collector droid (by 0 ABY it was theorized to be a cover-up for secret Imperial activities)

NAME: Cotellier
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: dry, hot desert world with deep red color, very little standing water, frequent dust storms; orbited by emerald-green moon encircled by 3 rings of ice and rock; nova crystal production was primary industry; Firmus Kett's family carried ore, nova crystals from Cotellier up the Sanrafsix Corridor for centuries; population: less than 1 M by 25 ABY

NAME: Tyne Albamon
INTERESTING: Trade Federation extended its operations to the Rseik sector following Bordal Contagion in 214 BBY; within a decade they established a depot for storing various goods here

NAME: Vanaria
INTERESTING: home to Vanarian Tree Eaters (used its tail, which resembled a small, inoffensive-looking creature, as a lure for prey)

NAME: Vestar
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: invaded by Empire in 3 BBY in campaign to subdue the Icarii, which ended in the extermination of the species via biological warfare

NAME: Carz
INTERESTING: orbited a blue-and-white gas giant in the unimportant Carz system, which was most often referred to by its galactic coordinates; Yosger (Yorseg) maintained a smuggler's base here, hidden deep within the rocky crust of the moon. Natural ores helped hide the nase from sensors

NAME: Gottlegoob
INTERESTING: planet in NR; during Leia's presidency, its people suffered from famine

NAME: Silken Asteroids
INTERESTING: system governed by Moff Derliff; asteroids were rocky, waterless; site of battle during early days of the Rebellion; mynocks found here; Jan Dodonna established a minor asteroid base here c. 2 BBY, but it was discovered by Derliff's ISDs; the base's Z-95 squadrons held off the initial attack, and Dodonna was able to rally the base's forces to drive off the Imperials

NAME: Neoli
INTERESTING: origin point of Neolians (group, probably a species)

NAME: Starstation 12
NOTES: "Stastation 12"
INTERESTING: full of thriving trade and crime; after Killing General Nim, Abal Karda deserted from the Empire and bribed the crew of the freighter Port-Esta Queen to secretly drop him here; he then fled to Maryx Minor aboard a passenger liner; Boba Fett pursued him to the station while on assignment for Vader; he killed a member of Nevo's team here and left his body in a photo booth to be discovered

NAME: Xirl
INTERESTING: home to Stinkers (long-lived creatures); Gozetta (Human female) built a hunting lodge on Xirl; planet was a source of messages piggy-backing on official channels, calling on people to resist the Empire

NAME: Kalidorn
INTERESTING: Muttani: had sickly appearance, peculiar body odor; generally hairless; mouths filled with sharp teeth; Meeko Ghintee (Muttani male sent to Desolation Alley)

NAME: Corg system
INTERESTING: system contained at least 2 perilous asteroid fields which were explored and charted by 2 ABY by Barosa Warren (Morellian Scout) and Casti Tholon (his human student at the Galactic Outdoor Survival School

NAME: Lira San Nebula
INTERESTING: treacherous nebula formed from an imploded star cluster; blocked the way to Lira San; Garazeb Orrelios used his bo staff in the ancient method to navigate a safe path between the gravitational anomalies in the nebula to reach his people's original homeworld

NAME: Lira San
INTERESTING: hidden behind a treacherous nebula; original Lasat homeworld; colony on Lasan had lost contact so long ago that Lira San faded into legend; an ancient prophecy led Garazeb Orrelios, Chava, and Gron to rediscover Lira San after their Lasan colony was wiped out by Empire; later, Zeb took Kallus to Lira San, to heal Kallus' guilt at destroying the colony and welcome him into their society

NAME: Lasan
INTERESTING: arid and warm; inhabited by herbivorous banthas; Lasat: mostly nomadic, rarely found offworld, tribe-based trappers, at relatively low tech level; a few regions had developed city-states with social sstratification and feudal-level tech, including advanced applied chemistry; isolated world rarely visited by interstellar traders; Empire's Lasan Suppression happened by 0 BBY

NAME: Culroon III
INTERESTING: long history of violence, civil war; largely ignored by Old Republic; never developed space travel but traded for tech devices; Empire constructed garrison, and the Culroon agreed to formally surrender but it was an ambush; Veers rescued the Imperial staff in an AT-AT

NAME: Red N.
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: extra-galactic nebula that had drifted away from main body of galaxy; contained a planet, a multitude of stars, and a meteor field;

NAME: Planet of the Red Nebula
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: inhabited world whose pointed-eared natives protected their homeworld from asteroid bombardment using mystical red jewels; group of exiles led by Klysk tried to steal the jewels but were thwarted by Han; the jewels were eventually stolen; planet's cities were destroyed by Domina Tagge and group of bounty hunters; Leia and Lando thwarted Tagge's plan to use jewels against Rebels

NAME: Yalara
INTERESTING: originally inhabited by Yalarans (primitive species not ready to join galactic society); Jedi Master Broden Kel Verdox installed a cloaking device that masked the entire planet; later, Noghri were sent there (presumably by Vader), wiped out Yalarans and began guarding the device; Jedi Knight Jaden Korr destroyed the device rather than let the Imperial Remnant take posession

NAME: Kinooine
INTERESTING: Lumiya & Nagai set up combined HQ here; Luke sent Alliance scouting party here, which disappeared (captured by Lumiya); Luke, Dani and Kiro went to investigate; Luke fought Lumiya but was defeated and captured by Nagai, then rescued and escaped as Imperial/Nagai invasion fleet amassed in orbit; after Empire Reborn fell, a Firrerreo remnant settled here and survived YV war

NAME: Imynusoph
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
INTERESTING: Freia Kallea charted final segment of Hydian Way to Imynusoph around 3694 BBY; considered part of Kallea sector by 0 ABY; in famous opera The Kallea Cycle, the world was home to a native species who betrayed Kallea as she tried to capture her Neimoidian rivals Thoax and Farge Osaax in the Temple of Imynusoph; population less than 1 M by 25 ABY

NAME: Zonju V
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: deserts, scrublands, dusty, sparsely-foliated canyons and gorges, mountains, valleys, sandstone-carved ruins
INTERESTING: in 3640 BBY, a powerful chieftain was searching for his family's lost crown so he could secure his bid for the planet's throne; in 14 ABY, the canyons were a lawless area plagued by swoop gangs; Jaden Korr sent on a mission here to make contact with a spaceport worker to gain information about the Disciples of Ragnos, but the worker was shot dead and Korr had to flee mercenaries

NAME: Delrakkin
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: jungles, mountains, constant stormy cloud cover
INTERESTING: 3 planets in system, but only Delrakkin supported life; located at end of hyperlane leading to Outer Rim; most natives lived underground; Delrakkin City (on high mountain) only civilized location on-planet, from which Imperials expelled native Delrakkin, populating it with own citizens; Tarkin ordered populace eliminated to maintain secrecy of experimental interdictor technology, but Rebellion evacuated them instead

NAME: Daimla
INTERESTING: Daimlos: short, stocky humanoids who underwent year-long rite of passage during which they rammed each other until unconscious with newly-grown skullplates and horns; homeworld of Zanales (popular winner of ramming rite, who later became podracer)

NAME: Koltine
INTERESTING: more than a decade after the establishment of the Empire, Bentilais san Sk'ar (Kaleesh Imperial General) led a strike force in conquering Koltine and other worlds along the Jahilid Drift; his victories led to a boost in his reputation even amongst the most speciesist Imperial admirals

NAME: Pral
INTERESTING: more than a decade after the establishment of the Empire, Bentilais san Sk'ar (Kaleesh Imperial General) led a strike force in conquering Pral and other worlds along the Jahilid Drift; his victories led to a boost in his reputation even amongst the most speciesist Imperial admirals

NAME: Jahilid
INTERESTING: likely in the Jahilid Drift

NAME: Shiva IV
INTERESTING: noted for extremely remote location, far from the Empire; generations of warfare between Calian Confederacy (Human) and the Twelve Tribes of T'Syril, which forged both peoples into formidable fighters; conflict finally ended via Concordat of Peace signed by Aron Peacebringer (Calian Warlord) and Kral Longknife (T'Syril Demarch), who later worked together with Rebels to repel Empire

NAME: Pembric II
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, beaches, urban, volcanic fields, wetlands

NAME: Kal'Shebbol
PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

NAME: Corjain
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: caves, warrens, underground mines, poisonous atmo

NAME: Bresan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren, underground cave cities capped with sealed domes

NAME: Dolstan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fertile plains, savannas, deserts, land-locked salt lakes

NAME: Swedlan
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: barren, underground cave cities capped with sealed domes

NAME: Sapella
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: cool hilly coastlands, massive ice caps

NAME: Jangelle
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: sandy lowlands, many streams, rivers, deltas, few large bodies of water

NAME: Ehjenla
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: fertile plains, fjords, large deep oceans

NAME: Uukaablis
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: forested mountains, skyway cities on stone columns

NAME: Exocron
INTERESTING: hidden inside protostar

NAME: Q'Maere
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: ammonia oceans, volcanic salt-caked islands, chlorine atmo

NAME: Yvara
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountain-ringed continents, fungal plains, oceans, river networks, ice caps, desert plains, underground warrens

NAME: Kathol
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, archipelagoes of volcanic islands, organic skyscraper ruins, wastelands, polar ice caps

NAME: Vatta Four
INTERESTING: Airen Cracken was able to fight off Imperial forces here by using a Baed Sharpshooter and some modified explosive slugs during GCW

NAME: Kesh
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: mountains, jungles, plains, rivers, oceans, frozen polar wastelands
INTERESTING: homeworld of Lost Tribe of the Sith; had at least 3 southern continents: Keshtah (dominion of Sith Tribe), Alanciar, and Eshkrene (at South Pole); isolated from rest of galaxy due to strange magnatic field that limited hyperspace travel and offworld signals communications; two rival Force-wielding factions eventually made peace and relocated to Eshkrene as The Doomed

NAME: Ertrax
INTERESTING: Ertraxi: peaceful multiple-eyed humanoids who repaired a crashed vessel with no survivors at some point during the Republic and flew it off-world in search for other species; group of explorers charting far reaches of Minos Cluster found a trail of Cronau radiation left by the ship and backtracked it to find Ertrax; discovery of the world led slavers, traders and conquerors to the planet

NAME: DNX-N1
INTERESTING: charted but largely unexplored; homeworld of Filar-Nitzan (sentient, gaseous shape-changers)

NAME: Kligson's Moon (Droid World)
INTERESTING: massive mobile platform; 800 m long; constructed out of spare starship parts, including significant weaponry, shielding, tractor beams; served as home for cyborg Kligson and large, bustling society of ~1000 droids in years after CW; organics not permitted; occasionally visited by beings interested in Kligson's famed mechanical skill; visit by Luke kicked off a civil war aboard in 3 ABY

NAME: Bekkra Star Cluster
NOTES: Near Tragan system

NAME: Scarif
KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, rocky archipelagoes, sandy beaches, jungles, volcanic island chains
INTERESTING: relatively small, remote tropical world; played central role in top-secret Imperial research beyond inspection distance of the Imperial Senate; protected by impenetrable deflector shield only passable at its Shield Gate; home to areca nut palm trees and giant peetalex sea grapes; had dangerous predators; Citadel Tower was surrounded by Imperial security complex
